(175, 1392879488, '英文内容经理 English Content Manager', 'Ping West', 'Technology', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '旧金山', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>We currently have an exciting opportunity for a native English speaker serve as English Content Manager for PingWest English site. As the content manager, you will be responsible for the overall quality of the English content to deliver a great user experience to our global audience. The ideal candidate will be familiar with tech industry. This is a full-time, on-site position located in either our Beijing office or San Francisco office. You will be translating and editing the articles and infographics from PingWest Chinese site into English;working closely with the in-country team to deliver market appropriate translation, including Slides presentations, newsletter, brochures, and more. Further, you will also beauthorized to develop, own and manage the content strategy and content collection that drives brand awareness, thought leadership and demand creation, and frequently create content, campaigns or other rich media for our social media profiles.</p>\n<h4>What might make you to be competitive：</h4>\n<ul class="lietou_ul">\n<li>1. You must be a 100% native English speaker.</li>\n<li>2. You will be proficiency in Chinese;translation experience is a plus.</li>\n<li>3. A mixed mindset of journalistic, editorial with an understanding an dappreciation for marketing.</li>\n<li>4. Excellent understanding of social media channels and the unique content needed for each.</li>\n<li>5. Ability to work in a fast-paced and diversity environment.</li>\n</ul>', '', 'recruiting@pingwest.com', 5, 90, 2),
(176, 1393049401, 'Office Assistant', 'Sangfor USA', 'Service', 'Santa Clara, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Santa Clara', 37.354107, -121.955238, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '圣克拉拉', 'None', 'Part Time', '<section id="postingbody">Sangfor USA (<a href="http://www.sangfor.com/" rel="nofollow">http://www.sangfor.com</a>) is seeking an energetic and outgoing office assistant. A positive attitude is essential as you will be working closely with other office staff to get things done. Full-time possible for the right person.&nbsp;<br /><br />RESPONSIBILITIES:&nbsp;<br />&bull; Manage office, including office supplies and vendors agreements.<br />&bull; Manage calendars, schedules, conference calls, schedule meetings, travel arrangements.<br />&bull; Perform general administrative duties such as archiving documents.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Handle office payables and expense reports.<br />&bull; Managing inventory and shipment.<br />&bull; Closely communicate and collaborate with other staff in China Headquarter.<br />&bull; Additional project as assigned<br /><br />QUALIFICATIONS:&nbsp;<br />&bull; MUST be proficient in both English as well as Mandarin<br />&bull; Positive attitude, outgoing, amiable and detail oriented.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Excellent written and verbal communication skills<br />&bull; Experience in a fast-paced work environment and like the challenge of many moving parts&nbsp;<br />&bull; Excellent planning, organizational, and analytical skills&nbsp;<br />&bull; Familiar with Google Doc and MS Office.<br />&bull; Ability to manage multiple demands, work independently and meet deadlines<br />&bull; Ability to accommodate Asian time zones if needed.<br /><br />Thanks for applying.</section>\n<section class="cltags">\n<ul class="blurbs">\n<li>Compensation: $12+ per hour depending on experiences</li>\n<li>This is a part-time job.</li>\n<li>This is an internship job</li>\n<li>Principals only. Recruiters, please don''t contact this job poster.</li>\n<li>do NOT