(246, 1394866848, 'Operations Management Trainees.', 'East West Bank', 'Finance', 'Pasadena, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Pasadena', 34.147785, -118.144516, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '帕萨迪纳', 'H1B', 'Full Time', '<div class="WB_text">East West Bank 招聘Operations Management Trainees. 要求:MBA or Master;<strong>流利中英文</strong>;</div>\n<div class="WB_text">&nbsp;</div>\n<div class="WB_text">2014 Spring graduates are welcome and FY2016 H-1B Sponsorship is available.</div>\n<div class="WB_text"><br />Operations Management Trainees<br /><br />Location: Pasadena, CA<br /><br />Program:<br /><br />- First 6 months will be the same training as the RM Trainees.<br /><br />- The latter 6 months will split into more focus on operations/ commercial lending<br /><br />- Upon 1 year training, trainees will become operations specialists or loan operations specialists, then eventually becoming officers / supervisors<br /><br />Qualifications:<br /><br />- MBA or Masters Degree.<br /><br />- <strong>Bilingual in Chinese</strong>, with excellent communication skills in English<br /><br />- Must have strong analytical and customer service skills with a positive and mature attitude<br /><br />- Must have prior solid work experience. Experience can be in operations, sales, customer service, non-profit, back office, etc. Banking experience not a must have.<br /><br />- <strong>Eligible for H1B sponsorship</strong>.<br /><br />Contact: Sisi Hwang<br /><br /></div>', '', 'sisi.huang@eastwestbank.com', 5, 330, 2),
(247, 1394905857, '律所财务助理', 'Clifford Chance LLP', 'Finance', 'Shanghai, China', 'China', 'Shanghai', 'Shanghai', 31.230415, 121.473701, '中国', '上海市', '上海', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Clifford Chance LLP，一家英国很有名的律师事务所，招一名女生，主要做整理发票的事情，年薪26万人民币，不会升职，不会加薪，9:00-16:30，中英两国假期，福利待遇不错，工作地点上海。要求英语非常流利，海归，硕士。不错的闲职。</p>\n<p>比较适合打算拿份薪水同时做副业的朋友们或者是把生活重心放在家庭的年轻妈妈们。白天可以看看儿童心理学啦，做做设计，写写小说什么的(因为貌似在公司上外网有限制)</p>', '', '328320258@qq.com', 5, 101, 2),
(248, 1394988289, '科研助理', '旧金山科学馆 Exploratorium', 'Service', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '旧金山', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><span class="summary">旧金山科学馆 Exploratorium招科研助理了。会说中文的优先,(最好是广东话)。这个职位主要是研究怎么提高科学馆访客的体验。</span></p>\n<p><span class="summary">Research Assistant Visitor Research &amp; Evaluation <br /> Fixed-Term, Part-Time Position <br /> <br /> This position is responsible for assisting with a research study for the Exhibit Engagement project. Responsibilities include recruiting, observing, and interviewing Exploratorium visitors using open-ended questions, generating non-leading but clarifying follow-up questions during the interview, entering and coding data, and actively suggesting improvements to instruments and methods being developed. As appropriate, the research assistant may assist with other research and exhibit development projects. This position reports to the Director of Visitor Research and Evaluation, and will work closely with more senior evaluation staff on exhibit projects as assigned <br /> <br /> <strong>Essential Functions: </strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Conduct open-ended interviews with visitors about their expectations and responses to different versions of exhibits or programs, using questions provided by senior research staff.</li>\n<li>Generate appropriate non-leading questions to further clarify visitors&rsquo; responses.</li>\n<li>Observe visitors and make rigorous written records of their behaviors, as identified by the senior research staff.</li>\n<li>Input visitor interview data into spreadsheets and other electronic documents, and score data using coding schemes developed by senior research staff.</li>\n<li>Other duties as assigned.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class="summary"><strong>Minimum Qualifications: </strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree or equivalent experience</li>\n<li>Excellent listening, communication, and interpersonal skills</li>\n<li>Ability to take comprehensive and legible notes while interviewing visitors</li>\n<li>Ability to take and follow direction from more senior evaluation staff</li>\n<li>Interest in and/or experience with evaluation process</li>\n<li>Accurate, rigorous, and detail-oriented</li>\n<li>Ability to use Microsoft Excel and Word; familiarity with FileMaker Pro a plus</li>\n<li>Available on weekends (at least one weekend day required) and flexibility in weekday schedu</li>\n<li><strong>Ability to speak, read and write in either Spanish or Chinese (Cantonese preferable) is highly desirable.</strong></li>\n<li>Ability to perform general office tasks including using a computer terminal and office equipment, move from place to place, lift and carry up to 25 pounds.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class="summary"><strong>Scheduled to Start: </strong>April 4, 2014 <br /> <br /> <strong>How to Apply </strong>This position is up to full-time (22.5 to 37.5 hours/week). It is a fixed term, non-exempt, union position. The fixed term is scheduled to end on or before October 31, 2014. There are on-call positions also available. <br /><br /></span></p>', '', 'resume@exploratorium.edu', 5, 192, 2),
(249, 1394988833, '经理助理领袖发展计划 Assistant Manager Leadership Development Program', '美国银行 Bank of America', 'Finance', 'West Norriton, PA, United States', 'United States', 'Pennsylvania', 'West Norriton', 40.129551, -75.378517, '美国', '宾夕法尼亚州', '伊格尔维尔', 'H1B', 'Full Time', '<div id="job-detail">\n<div><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Our Business:</span></strong></div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Consumer &amp; Small Business Banking (CSBB) serves more than 51 million consumer, client and small business households through a distribution network of 5,200 retail banking offices, 16,200 ATMs, and award-winning online banking with 30 million active users and more than 14 million mobile users.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Overview:</span></strong></div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Bank of America is seeking outstanding college graduates interested in a rewarding career in sales and management to enter our selective Banking Center Channel Assistant Manager Leadership Development Program.&nbsp;&nbsp; Assistant Manager Associates are responsible for learning to execute and coach against each of the roles within the Banking Center.&nbsp; During this rotational program, you will learn the necessary skills and behavior to effectively lead a team of sales and service professionals to meet and exceed aggressive sales goals and service targets.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<ul>\n<li>18&nbsp; months will be spent learning the fundamentals of the Banking Center in the following key roles:&nbsp; Personal Banker, Sales and Service Specialist, Assistant Manager, Teller, Teller Operations Specialist, and&nbsp; Banking Center Manager</li>\n</ul>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Targeted participants will:</div>\n<ul>\n<li>Be responsible for assisting and supporting the Banking Center Manager in managing the day-to-day aspect of running a banking center and leading a team to create a quality banking experience for our customers.</li>\n<li>Assist with managing all aspects of a successful business including resource management, identifying and minimizing risk, operational excellence, managing partnerships, associate development and proficiency, building and retaining customer relationships and giving customers more reasons to increase their level of engagement with us, in an effort to meet and exceed performance targets.</li>\n<li>Supervise and coach teammates on the proper execution of banking center key plays while role-modeling the desired behaviors and skills to ensure a consistent positive customer experience through the eyes of the customer.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Training:</span></strong></div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<ul>\n<li>Participants will complete fundamentals training programs for each role within the banking center</li>\n<li>Regular coaching and feedback will be provided by the market team and program managers</li>\n<li>Participants will be provided with additional leadership development through the Campus Enterprise Learning Plan</li>\n</ul>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Locations:&nbsp; </span></strong></div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Various &ndash; USA</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Enterprise Job Description:</span></p>\n<p>Bank of America is seeking outstanding college graduates interested in a rewarding career in sales and management to enter our selective Assistant Banking Center Manager Leadership Development program. Assistant Banking Center Managers are responsible for leading a team of sales and service professionals to meet and exceed aggressive sales goals and service targets. They are also responsible for service, operations, and managing a team of Tellers. ABCMs work with customers to uncover and satisfy their financial needs and they play a critical role in helping the banking center achieve competitive product sales goals to maintain our status as one of most profitable companies in the world. Over the 12 -18 months you are in the program your rotations will be spent learning the fundamentals of the Banking Center in several key areas:Teller Training &amp; Development, Teller Operations, Personal Banker Training &amp; Development, Sales and Service, Banking Center Control &amp; Review. Once you consistently meet performance goals, you will enroll in Leadership Fundamentals. This part of the program focuses on developing leadership and coaching ability, driving customer delight and sales excellence, and building associate satisfaction and retention.</p>\n</div>\n<div id="job-qualitifation">\n<h3>Qualifications</h3>\n<div><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Required Qualifications:</span></strong></div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<ul>\n<li>Must have a Bachelor&rsquo;s degree from an accredited college or university with a <strong><em>graduation date between May 2013 and June 2014</em></strong></li>\n<li>Minimum GPA of 3.0</li>\n<li>The ability to develop and maintain customer relationships through superior customer service</li>\n<li>The ability to pass the company sponsored assessment</li>\n<li>A minimum of 6 months experience working directly with Customers in a sales or service role</li>\n<li>The ability to be flexible with scheduling</li>\n<li>Availability to work a 40 hour week Monday through Saturday</li>\n<li>Preference given to candidates who speak Spanish or <strong>Chinese</strong> fluently in addition to the above qualifications</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Preferred Qualifications:</span></strong></div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<ul>\n<li>Demonstrated ability to motivate and train sales and service teammates to grow the business and drive execution</li>\n<li>Proven record of sound decision making, balancing risk with customer/client needs and business goals</li>\n<li>Proven customer service skills and the ability to resolve problems and prevent customer dissatisfaction</li>\n<li>Previous banking/financial services, mortgage, retail or hospitality experience</li>\n<li>Ability to communicate effectively with all levels of management</li>\n<li>Ability to effectively manage multiple responsibilities and priorities</li>\n<li>Demonstrated experience leading, managing, motivating, or developing a team, to meet and exceed assigned goals</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class="sub-section">\n<p><strong>Posting Date</strong>: 03/05/2014</p>\n<p><strong>Location</strong>: US-PA-West Norriton, US-PA-Philadelphia</p>\n<p><strong>Travel</strong>: No</p>\n</div>\n<div class="sub-section">\n<p><strong>Full / Part-time</strong>: Fulltime</p>\n<p><strong>Hours Per Week</strong>: 40.00</p>\n<p><strong>Shift</strong>: 1st Shift</p>\n<p><strong>Weekly Schedule</strong>: Hours between 7:30am and 8:00pm, Monday through Saturday.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>', 'http://careers.bankofamerica.com/job.aspx?n=16580&c=United%20States&r=us&src=JB-11684', '', 5, 139, 2),
(250, 1394989003, '高级国际商业分析师', 'QVC', 'Finance', 'West Chester, PA, United States', 'United States', 'Pennsylvania', 'West Chester', 39.960663, -75.605492, '美国', '宾夕法尼亚州', '西切斯特', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Senior International Business Analyst</p>\n<div class="job2">International Finance Team</div>\n<div class="space10">&nbsp;</div>\n<div class="job2">Full Time</div>\n<div class="job2">West Chester-Studio Park, PA 19380</div>\n<div class="job2">&nbsp;</div>\n<div class="job2">QVC, the world&rsquo;s leading video and eCommerce retailer, is currently looking for a Senior International Business Analyst to join our International Finance team at corporate headquarters in West Chester, PA. This analyst will work with multiple countries in Europe or Asia. English and a second language (ex: Japanese, <strong>Chinese</strong>, Spanish, French, German, Portuguese) is highly preferred.<br /> <br /> QVC is an entrepreneurial company that is reinventing the digital shopping experience in markets around the world. Our dramatically expanding and unique product mix showcases the most desired, progressive and fashionable brands. We provide award-winning service to satisfy millions of the most savvy and engaged customers who make up our global shopping community.<br /> <br /> Partnering<br />\n<ul>\n<li>Partners with the international countries, U.S. corporate accounting and FP &amp; A for accurate delivery of information needs for reporting purposes.</li>\n<li>Supports the implementation and continued evolution of BPC (SAP Budgeting and Reporting tool) in the market in the role of Change Advocate.</li>\n<li>Addresses questions from CFO, European CEO and President related to the quarterly performance and annual budget review meetings.</li>\n<li>Identifies areas of concern, takes action to understand the cause of the issue, and analyzes the strategy to address, offering solutions using the knowledge of another market''s approach, if applicable.</li>\n<li>Manages country communications in a timely manner to the appropriate level, escalating issues within a country initially, and, if without resolution, then involving the Vice President, International Finance.</li>\n<li>Communicates and advocates best practices across markets.</li>\n</ul>\n<br /> Analytics<br />\n<ul>\n<li>Evaluates and questions accounting practices and financial assumptions used in compiling financial statements.</li>\n<li>Identifies opportunities to improve the business (such as reducing cost or increasing efficiency) via benchmarking country&rsquo;s performance to other markets.</li>\n<li>Drills into all levels of the P&amp;L and Balance Sheet and is able to understand standards and key metrics/assumptions used.</li>\n<li>Provides financial analysis, modeling and advisory services to the assigned country.</li>\n<li>Reviews the business and financial assumptions in the capital requests from the countries, where appropriate challenging assumptions for costs and benefits and ensuring that these are reflected in forecasts/budgets. Provides input following review and follow-up to International VP.</li>\n</ul>\n<br /> Reporting<br />\n<ul>\n<li>Manages timelines to ensure key deliverables meet requirements of Senior Management and corporate reporting.</li>\n<li>Develops new processes and models to analyze data and improve financial analysis. Provides new models to assist country in financial planning.</li>\n<li>Partners with country&rsquo;s functional managers to resolve questions relating to performance or strategy.</li>\n<li>Prepares the plan and forecasts for the Non-Operating companies in the countries for P&amp;L, Balance Sheet and Cash Flow.</li>\n</ul>\n<br /> Forecasting/Budgeting<br />\n<ul>\n<li>Evaluates assumptions used in compiling the estimate, forecast and budget financial information by leveraging historical trend information and business knowledge of the country and global practices.</li>\n<li>Provides insights to risk and opportunities of the information.</li>\n<li>Drives improvement in the rigor of assumptions by challenging questionable assumptions within the plan.</li>\n<li>Prepares the plan and forecasts for the Non-Operating companies in the countries for P&amp;L, Balance Sheet and Cash Flow.</li>\n</ul>\n<br /> Required Qualifications:<br />\n<ul>\n<li>Thorough understanding of all financial statements (P&amp;L, Balance Sheet and Cash Flow).</li>\n<li>Able to deliver while managing multiple issues and deadlines.</li>\n<li>Advanced verbal and written communication skills required. Need to be able to communicate with all levels within the global organization.</li>\n<li>Able to foster a positive work environment whilst influencing and promoting change and challenging current approaches.</li>\n<li>Ability to operate in a self-directed environment.</li>\n<li>Strong facilitation skills and ability to collaborate effectively with all levels of the country''s business units.</li>\n<li>Excellent analytical, negotiation, diagnostic, interpersonal and problem-solving skills.</li>\n<li>Strong attention to detail to ensure accuracy of reporting.</li>\n<li>Knowledge of SAP.</li>\n<li>Ability to travel internationally required; 10% to 15% annually.</li>\n<li>Advanced Excel skills.</li>\n</ul>\n<br /> Preferred Requirements:<br />\n<ul>\n<li>Minimum seven years experience.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>', 'http://www.qvc.jobs/jobs/Senior_International_Business_Analyst/International_Finance_Team/West_Chester-Studio_Park_Pennsylvania/116/64157/?sponsored=0', '', 5, 50, 2),
(251, 1394989189, '理财顾问', '美国银行 Bank of America', 'Finance', 'Philadelphia, PA, United States', 'United States', 'Pennsylvania', 'Philadelphia', 39.952335, -75.163788, '美国', '宾夕法尼亚州', '费城', 'H1B', 'Full Time', '<div id="job-detail">&nbsp;</div>\n<div>美国银行招理财顾问，会讲中文的优先。</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><strong>Job Posting Description</strong><br />The primary role of the Field Financial Solutions Advisor (FSA) is to deepen banking and investment relationships with Bank of America''s Mass Affluent (MA) customers. Located in Banking Centers with a concentration of mass affluent customers, the FSA will act as the primary point of contact for MA customers, although will not have a "book of business." Walk-in MA customers will be directed to the FSA who will provide end to end comprehensive advice and customized solutions to help customers achieve their financial goals. Customer reviews/presentations will include a review of investment goals and prepare presentations that recommend products such as stocks, bonds, mutual funds, insurance, annuities and banking solutions. Also, the FSA will transact point of fulfillment investment and banking business for clients with less than $250k in investable assets. In addition, the FSA will engage in daily outbound calling to pre-selected Bank of America or Merrill Edge customers inviting them into the Banking Center for a customer review. <br /><br />The Banking Center FSA will provide a single company and agnostic product view for our mass affluent clients. The FSA should therefore have experience in investment, banking and lending products to bridge banking and brokerage solutions. The FSA will build and maintain effective partnerships with internal business partners including other Banking Center teammates, Mortgage Loan Officers, Financial Advisors, banking and investment contact center teammates in Customer Services &amp; Solutions (CS&amp;S) and Merrill Edge Advisory Center (MEAC). The FSA will directly report to a Regional Sales Manager on the Mass Affluent Sales team and partner closely with the Banking Center staff to drive cross-segment referrals.<br /> <br /><strong>Key Job Responsibilities</strong><br /><ol>\n<li>Assess customer goals by conducting financial opportunity sessions with new or existing banking clients. Leverage business knowledge to determine prudent and appropriate strategy to meet client''s needs by recommending financial solutions for Mass Affluent clients.</li>\n<li>Build strategic partnership with Banking Center as a valued team member. Refer business back to appropriate Banking Associate/Personal Banker. Refer clients with an investment need and more than $250K in investable assets to a local Merrill Lynch Wealth Advisory Complex. Refer to other appropriate business channel(s) (i.e. Small Business, HL&amp;I) as needed</li>\n<li>Demonstrates strong awareness of enterprise-wide opportunities to serve our customers.</li>\n<li>Pro-actively build relationships with potential and existing clients to meet business objectives.</li>\n<li>Comply with all applicable banking and investment laws, regulations, company polices, and procedures, in order to serve the clients'' best interests and enhance client satisfaction.</li>\n<li>This position may be subject to SAFE Act Registration Requirements. Pursuant to the SAFE Act requirements, all applicants for employment who will be engaged in residential loan mortgage originations (as defined by the SAFE Act) must register with the federal registry system and maintain a status in good standing under the SAFE Act requirements. If at any time the Bank determines that your position requires SAFE Act registration, you will be required to register and to submit to the required SAFE Act background check and registration process. Failure to register successfully or to maintain a status in good standing under the SAFE Act will affect your eligibility for continued employment and may result in your immediate termination.</li>\n</ol><br /><strong>Qualifications</strong><br /><br />Required Skills- "Must" have these skills to be minimally qualified<br />1. 3+ years of proven investment business development experience, including investment training. In-depth knowledge of investment products and services<br />2. 4 year degree, preferably in business related field, CFP desired<br />3. Series 7 &amp; 66 (63 &amp; 65 in lieu of 66) and Insurance licenses required<br />4. Experience creating a comprehensive financial strategy, assessing needs, identifying, and recommending financial solutions<br />5. Knowledge of banking (credit and deposit) products and services desired<br />6. Demonstrated ability to cultivate effective revenue generating partnerships with other Lines of Business<br />7. Proven track record of ability to influence: present oneself assertively, convincingly and with confidence to establish credibility and respect with others<br />8. Must be able to provide evidence of consultative communication and relationship building skills leading to client fulfillment and delight in previous roles<br />9. Must possess sound business ethics; acts in the best interest of the client<br />10. Highly motivated self-starter, proactive, with intense focus on results. Conveys a sense of urgency to achieve business goals and exceed expectations<br />11. Excellent time management and organizational skills<br /><strong>12. Bilingual Chinese preferred</strong><br /><br />Location: US-PA-Philadelphia<br /><br />Travel: Yes, 25 % of the Time<br /><br />Full / Part-time: Fulltime<br /><br />Hours Per Week: 40.00<br /><br />Shift: 1st Shift<br /><br />Weekly Schedule: Monday-Friday open to close of banking center + some Saturdays</div>', 'http://careers.bankofamerica.com/job.aspx?n=9680&c=United%20States&r=us&src=JB-11684', '', 5, 202, 2),
(252, 1394993488, '北美娱乐新闻记者', '腾讯(美国)', 'Media', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', 'Carson', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Entertainment Reporter</p>\n<p>Tencent&rsquo;s QQ.com is China&rsquo;s largest portal in Chinese integrating news, interactive communities, entertainment products and widely-used basic services. The website serves Chinese users around the world and is dedicated to becoming a trend-setting and mainstream Internet media platform with a powerful communication capacity and interactivity. We are&nbsp;is looking for a motivated, self-starting, detail-oriented individual who thrives in a creative environment to be the Entertainment Journalist for the North America region.&nbsp;This indivdiaul will be responsible for:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Interviewing, writing and photographing entertainment news events in the United States and North America, including the news coverage of big events such as Oscar and Grammy Awards</li>\n<li>Writing in-depth articles and feature stories covering US entertainment celebrities and events</li>\n<li>Building relationships and recruiting influential entertainment industry individuals to cooperate with Tencent Weibo as well as promoting QQ.COM</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"> <strong>Requirements:</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor''s degree or higher preferred in Journalistm, Communciaitons or a related field</li>\n<li>More than 5 years of editorial and reporting experience, preferrably in the field of entertainment and online media. <strong>Fluent in Chinese Mandarin</strong> and English (read and write).&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Strong connection with the media, self-starting, flexible, and comfortable working in a fast-paced, dynamic environment</li>\n<li>Excellent oral and written communication skills</li>\n<li>Professional, responsible and a team player, can work under pressure</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Combining the results-oriented nature of a startup with the resources of a profitable and leading internet company, Tencent America offers a unique opportunity for aspiring individuals to thrive.&nbsp; We embrace a culture of teamwork &amp; creativity and are driven by our values - Integrity, Passion, Collaboration, and Innovation.&nbsp; We seek like-minded individuals who prosper and thrive in this culture, and also know how to have fun.&nbsp;</p>', 'http://hire.jobvite.com/CompanyJobs/Careers.aspx?k=Job&c=q7c9Vfw7&j=owq1XfwE', '', 5, 197, 2),
(253, 1394994790, '基金管理助理', 'Yang''s Pension Consulting', 'Consulting', 'Fullerton, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Fullerton', 33.870293, -117.925339, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '富勒顿', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><span class="summary"><span class="summary"><strong>* Chinese Speaking A MUST *</strong></span></span></p>\n<p><span class="summary">Assist a Pension Administrator in the annual administration of retirement plans for other small businesses. This position will include data entry, help with pension calculations and help with tax return filings. Assistant will communicate via email and phone with other professionals. Being well organized and detailed oriented is a MUST. Bachelor degree required &amp; 2 years office work experience preferred. Room to grow!</span></p>', '', 'info@yangspension.com', 5, 142, 2),
