(262, 1395206447, 'Residential Manager', 'Gphomestay', 'Service', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '旧金山', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p >Gphomestay is a Boston-based educational service provider that specializes in bringing quality international student homestay, boarding components and English as a second language support to private high schools around the U.S. Our worldwide network has brought hundreds of young people from around the world to experience American education and build worldwide connections.</p>\n <p >We are seeking a Residential Manager for a position in San Francisco, CA who displays a high level of professionalism, ability to multi-task and attention to detail that will communicate with our international students, host families and with our oversea offices to support the coordination of residential student programs at schools around the US.</p>\n <p >REQUIREMENTS:</p>\n <p >- Manage comprehensive administrative tasks as assigned<br />- Supervise residential programs<br />- Ensure host recruitment targets are met<br />- Provide cultural competency support to host families and students<br />- Manage remote local coordinators<br />- Be committed to customer service</p>\n <p >QUALIFICATIONS:</p>\n <p >- BA or MA graduate required/MA/PhD preferred<br />- Interest or experience in global business or education<br />- Previous Residential life or residential management experience<br />- Sales and recruitment experience<br />- Committed to diversity in education<br />- Previous experience working with teenagers<br />- Strong communication skills, including telephone and email skills<br />- Flexibility and willingness to work and communicate outside normal business hours<br />- Strong organizational skills and ability to multi-task<br />- Ability to work closely with managers and colleagues around the globe<br />- Professionalism and punctuality, with the ability to work independently<br />- US Citizen or Permanent Resident</p>\n <p >PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS (Optional):</p>\n <p >- Remote employee management experience<br />- ESL experience<br />- <strong>Fluency in Mandarin Chinese</strong><br />- International travel experience<br />- Previous experience with boarding style accommodations<br />- Background in social work, mentoring, personal counseling and/or childcare<br />- 1-3 years of experience preferred</p>', '', 'humanresources@gphomestay.com', 5, 66, 2),
(263, 1395206686, 'Director of Communications ', '中美国际学校 Chinese American International School', 'Service', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '旧金山', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><span >Chinese American International School<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><br  /><br  /><span >seeks a<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><br  /><br  /><strong >Director of Communications<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></strong><br  /><br  /><em >(full-time  exempt position)<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></em><br  /><br  /><span >www cais.org<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><br  /><br  /><strong >The School<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></strong><br  /><br  /><span >The Chinese American International School (CAIS) is an independent, PreK-8 th grade school in San Francisco, CA. CAIS was founded in 1981 with an enrollment of just ten students; CAIS now enrolls nearly 500 students from PreK through 8 th grade. CAIS&rsquo;s commitment to dual language and dual culture education, international mindedness and diversity of every sort has remained at the core of our vision and educational program. We are proud of our leading role in preparing culturally sensitive, globally literate young people with a high level of proficiency in Chinese for the world that awaits them.<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><em >Please see the Learn More section for our full school profile.<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></em><br  /><br  /><strong >The Position<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></strong><br  /><br  /><span >The Director of Communications is responsible for spearheading the creation and implementation of a strategic, multi-faceted communications program designed to build and strengthen the Chinese American International School&rsquo;s reputation as a leader in dual language immersion education. To that end, the Director of Communications will devise program guidelines and policies, oversee the implementation process, and provide quality control for the communications program, simultaneously ensuring an integrated approach to the school&rsquo;s communications efforts. The Director of Communications will be joining a devoted Advancement team. We are looking for a strategic and visionary thinker, an experienced and creative communicator, and a hands-on doer, who is also capable of leading and collaborating with a multi-disciplinary team of colleagues, staff, and volunteers.<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><br  /><br  /><strong >Main areas of focus and responsibility<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></strong><span >:<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><br  /><br  /><em >Strategic:<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></em></p>\n <ul >\n<li>Develop and implement a strategic communications plan to support CAIS&rsquo;s mission, goals and objectives.</li>\n<li>Build and foster collaborative relationships with other departments within the organization to stay informed and abreast of new initiatives.</li>\n<li>Identify opportunities to support organizational initiatives and develop communications materials and programs to promote and publicize these activities.</li>\n<li>Partner with key leaders to design and produce collateral materials to support admissions, auxiliary programs and development initiatives.</li>\n</ul>\n <p><em >Tactical:<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></em></p>\n <ul >\n<li>Oversee day-to-day operations of specific year-round communications programs.</li>\n<li>Serve as editor for communications materials including print materials, online content, program announcements and the annual report.</li>\n<li>Ensure communications (print, media, internal, external) are aligned with the school&rsquo;s brand look and feel, mission and strategies.</li>\n<li>Manage and implement the school&rsquo;s brand and editorial guidelines in all written and visual communications.</li>\n</ul>\n <p><br  /><strong >Job Requirements<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></strong><strong >Required Qualifications<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\n <ul >\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree</li>\n<li>Minimum of 8-10 years of related work experience</li>\n<li>Familiarity with current software, technologies, and practices including use of web and social media platforms.</li>\n<li>Technical/Computer skills as required for job performance</li>\n<li>Initial and continued tuberculosis clearance</li>\n<li>Initial and continued criminal background clearance by DOJ and FBI</li>\n<li>CPR and First Aid Certification</li>\n</ul>\n <p><strong >Desired Qualifications<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\n <ul >\n<li><strong>Bilingual: Mandarin/English</strong></li>\n<li>Master&rsquo;s Degree is a plus</li>\n</ul>\n <p><strong >Success Factors/Core Competencies<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\n <ul >\n<li>Proven strategic and creative marketing and communications thinker who can support the needs of CAIS&rsquo;s day-to-day operations as well as its numerous local, national, and international initiatives.</li>\n<li>Understanding of independent school, college, or nonprofit culture.</li>\n<li>Excellent interpersonal and communication skills</li>\n<li>Experience working in and with diverse communities</li>\n<li>Ability to work with colleagues from different backgrounds</li>\n<li>Exceptional writing and editing skills</li>\n<li>Commitment to school mission, policies and initiatives</li>\n</ul>\n <p><strong >To Apply<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></strong><br  /><br  /><span >Please follow the below for submission requirements:<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n <ul >\n<li>In subject line of email, indicate &ldquo;Director of Communications&rdquo;.</li>\n<li>Please combine the following items into one PDF before submitting: resume, desired salary, two writing samples, and list of references.</li>\n<li>The PDF must be titled: &ldquo;[Candidate&rsquo;s name]&ndash; Director of Communications&rdquo;</li>\n</ul>', '', 'advancement_jobs@cais.org', 5, 150, 2),
(264, 1395206797, 'D.P./ Operator ', 'China Blog Weekly Magazine', 'Media', 'Pacifica, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Pacifica', 37.613827, -122.486916, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '帕西菲卡', 'None', 'Part Time', '<p>A Chinese magazine is looking for a videographer in San Francisco area (Pacifica). This is a temp position. You will be working with our reporters on Mar. 20. <br /><br />We are going to have a 2-hour interview with Kevin Kelly, editor of &ldquo;Wired&rdquo; magazine and author of &ldquo;Out of Control&rdquo;, in his studio in Pacifica. So if you are a fan, this is a great chance to meet with KK. <br /><br />We would like to hire a person to shoot a short video during the interview (we will deal with the production and after-effects part, so you just need to take care of the shooting). The video will be used as a part of our promotion campaign through popular Chinese video websites such as youku.com (Chinese version of Youtube). Thus there will be a lot of exposure. <br /><br />Job description: <br /><br />Time of work: <br />Afternoon of Mar. 19th, Mar. 20th <br /><br />Location: <br />Pacifica, CA <br /><br />Schedule: <br />Afternoon of Mar. 19th <br />Pre-meet with the producer and reporters, get camera equipment ready in San Francisco <br />Mar. 20th <br />2-hour interview video shooting in Pacifica, CA. <br /><br />Job responsibilities: <br />Meet with producer on Mar. 19, do preparation <br />Arrange indoor lighting, placing the camera, shooting interview content, b-roll, etc. on Mar. 20 <br /><br />Requirements: <br />Able to bring a personal Canon 5D mark ii or other DSLR, which can take videos on site, is a plus. <br /><br />Payment: <br />Paid as our correspondent of this interview (details shall be discussed). <br /><br />Other benefit: <br />Your name will be cited in the video, and you can put it in your portfolio/CV if you want to. <br /><br />Please feel free to contact me if you&rsquo;re interested. <br /><br />Contact: <br />Producer Shelly Yang <br />Tel: 1(573)489-3969 <br /><br /><br />p.s. A brief introduction to the magazine: Blog Weekly Magazine is a Chinese news magazine of current affairs, business and popular culture. Founded in 2008, the magazine has been growing rapidly among the top three most popular news magazines in China, with a circulation of 650,000 copies per issue. Blog Weekly aims at producing news of high quality and taste, as well as providing unique, stylish articles to our readers. <br /><br /></p>', '', 'ydhshelly@gmail.com', 5, 89, 2),
(265, 1395207066, 'Receiptionist', 'Dental Front Office', 'Service', 'West Covina, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'West Covina', 34.068623, -117.938950, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '西柯汶纳', 'None', 'Part Time', '<div class="viewhtml" >\n <div >Part Time Bilingual Receptionist</div>\n <div ><br />Responsibility:<br />-customer service: acknowledge, greet patients upon arrival/dismissal.<br />-making, canceling and confirming appointments, taking payments, and writing up receipts.<br />-chart filing.<br />-maintaining a clean and friendly waiting area for patients.</div>\n <div ><br />Main Qualification:<br />-fluent Bilingual English and <strong>Mandarin Chinese</strong><br />-dental experience preferred</div>\n</div>', '', 'smilebuilder91792@gmail.com', 5, 85, 2);
