(277, 1395555465, '速记人员', '联合国', 'Language', '', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 0.000000, 0.000000, 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 'H1B', 'Full Time', '<p>Special Notice<br /> <br />&nbsp;<br /> <br />Staff Members are subject to the authority of the Secretary-General and to assignment by him or her. In this context, all Staff are expected to move periodically to new functions In their careers In accordance with established rules and procedures.</p>\n<p><br />&nbsp;<br /> <br />Org. Setting and Reporting<br /> <br />&nbsp;<br /> <br />This position is located in the Chinese Verbatim Section, Verbatim Reporting Service, MPD/DGACM and the incumbent is under the general supervision of the Chief of the Verbatim Reporting Service, and directly under the Chief of the Chinese Verbatim Reporting Section.</p>\n<p><br />&nbsp;<br /> <br />Responsibilities<br /> <br />&nbsp;<br /> <br />Within the delegated authority, the Reviser-Verbatim Reporter will be responsible for the following duties: Revises in extenso verbatim records of meetings. Ensures consistency and checks for uniformity and continuity of records. Provides Verbatim Reporters with advice and guidance. Consults relevant reference sources and carries out additional research as required.&nbsp;<br />Ensures conformity of the revised record with the original and/or other language versions and with the United Nations established practice. Reports to Chief of Section on the quality of the work of verbatim reporters. Performs the duties of a Verbatim Reporter, as required. May serve as officer-in-charge of the Section in the absence of the Chief. Performs other related duties as required.</p>\n<p><br />&nbsp;<br /> <br />Competencies<br /> <br />&nbsp;<br /> <br />PROFESSIONALISM: Ability to demonstrate good writing skills, high standard of accuracy, consistency and faithfulness to the spirit, style and nuances of the original text with a good grasp of the subject matter. Ability to demonstrate a high level of concentration and good judgment and discretion. Ability to work under continuous stress in dealing with a broad range of subjects. Ability to exercise flexibility and adaptability; firm grasp of research techniques. Knowledge of a broad range of subjects dealt with by the United Nation, i.e. political, social, legal, economic, financial, administrative, scientific and technical. Shows&nbsp;<br />pride in work and in achievements; demonstrates professional competence and mastery of subject matter; is conscientious and efficient in meeting commitments, observing deadlines and achieving results; is motivated by professional rather that personal concerns; shows persistence when faced with difficult problems or challenges; remains calm in stressful situations. Takes responsibility for incorporating gender perspectives and ensuring the equal participation of women and men in all areas of work. Good skills in word processing technology are required. Readiness to adapt to non-standard equipment and peripherals.&nbsp;<br />Readiness to respond punctually on short notice, on weekends and after hours.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>PLANNING AND ORGANIZING: Develops clear goals that are consistent with agreed strategies; identifies priority activities and assignments; adjusts priorities as required; allocates appropriate amount of time and resources for completing work; foresees risks and allows for contingencies when planning; monitors and adjusts plans and actions as necessary; uses time efficiently.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>TECHNOLOGICAL AWARENESS: keeps abreast of available technology; understands applicability and limitations of technology to the work of the office; actively seeks to apply technology to appropriate tasks; shows willingness to learn new technology.<br /> <br />&nbsp;<br /> <br />Education<br /> <br />&nbsp;<br /> <br />A first-level degree from a university or institution of equivalent status is required. Candidates&nbsp;<br />for this position must have passed the United Nations Competitive Examination for Chinese Verbatim Reporters.<br /> <br />&nbsp;<br /> <br />Work Experience<br /> <br />&nbsp;<br /> <br />At least five years of progressively responsible work in verbatim record writing, out of which at least three years should have been in the United Nations System.<br /> <br />&nbsp;<br /> <br />Languages<br /> <br />&nbsp;<br /> <br />A perfect command of Chinese, which must be the candidate''s main language, and an&nbsp;<br />excellent knowledge of English. Knowledge of another offical United Nations language is desirable.<br /> <br />&nbsp;<br /> <br />Assessment Method<br /> <br />&nbsp;<br /> <br />Evaluation of qualified candidates may include an assessment exercise which may be followed by competency-based interview.<br /> <br />&nbsp;<br /> <br />United Nations Considerations<br /> <br />&nbsp;<br /> <br />The United Nations shall place no restrictions on the eligibility of men and women to&nbsp;<br />participate in any capacity and under conditions of equality in its principal and subsidiary&nbsp;<br />organs. (Charter of the United Nations - Chapter 3, article 8. The United Nations Secretariat is a non-smoking environment.</p>', 'https://inspira.un.org/psc/UNCAREERS/EMPLOYEE/HRMS/c/UN_CUSTOMIZATIONS.UN_JOB_DETAIL.GBL?Page=UN_JOB_DETAIL&Acti;', '', 5, 197, 2),
(278, 1395626438, '中国研究分析员', 'Matthews International Capital Management', 'Finance', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '旧金山', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="bd">\n<div class="content">\n<div class="joqReqDescription">\n<p><strong>THE COMPANY:&nbsp;</strong><br /><br />Founded by G. Paul Matthews in 1991, Matthews, believes in the long-term growth of Asia. We concentrate our efforts and investment expertise exclusively within the Asia Pacific region. An independent, privately owned firm, Matthews is the largest dedicated Asia-only investment specialist in the United States. Our investment offerings provide a broad range of strategies for building a global portfolio that includes exposure to Asia- Pacific. Matthews is the investment advisor to Matthews Asia Funds, an open-end U.S. mutual fund family; and the investment advisor and global distributor of Matthews Asia Funds, SICAV, a Luxembourg-based fund group. Through offices in San Francisco and</p>\n<p>Hong Kong, Matthews distributes products in the United States, Europe, Asia and Latin</p>\n<p>America.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Additional information on Matthews and our funds can be found at&nbsp;<a href="http://www.matthewsasia.com/">www.matthewsasia.com</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="http://www.micmllc.com/">www.micmllc.com</a>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>REPORTING RELATIONSHIPS:</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This position will report to a lead Portfolio Manager of one of the company&rsquo;s investment strategies.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>ROLE AND RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>We are seeking an individual to join the Matthews&rsquo; China fund to perform fundamental research and investment analysis in support of the Portfolio Managers.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Specially, this individual will be responsible for conducting both qualitative and quantitative analyses, focusing on industrial analysis, business models, products and services, management quality and competitive advantages for China companies.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This role will be responsible for supporting and coordinating investment decisions for a series of SEC-registered mutual funds that specialize in international markets.&nbsp; The duties are as follows:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Research and analysis of individual companies, as well as sector, regional and economic factors affecting issuers based in, or with significant exposure to Asia Pacific;</li>\n<li>Stock selection;</li>\n<li>Work within a team to conduct research and generate ideas for better returns of the portfolio; develop investment strategy;</li>\n<li>Asset allocation of the portfolio based on the changing environments of risks in macro economy, different sectors and individual equities and rebalance stock position;</li>\n<li>Monitor the latest news/developments on the underlining stocks in the portfolio and evaluate the impacts on the stocks using qualitative and quantitative method. Also monitor macroeconomic news;</li>\n<li>Meet with company managements on a frequent basis through on-site company visits, conference calls and meetings in our own office;</li>\n<li>Communicate with existing/potential investors/advisers on the fund&rsquo;s investment philosophy and methodology ;</li>\n<li>Collaborate with lead or co-portfolio manager;</li>\n<li>Market fund, appear in media and conferences</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>QUALIFICATIONS:</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelors degree is required, Masters degree and/or CFA preferred</li>\n<li>At least 4 years of work experience in the investment management industry (buy-side preferred)&nbsp;</li>\n<li>1-3 years on the ground experience in China region OR experience with researching companies/industries in the China region, preferably in the investment management industry</li>\n<li>Keen interest in investing and a demonstrable conviction in Asia-oriented investment</li>\n<li>Strong background in Asia required</li>\n<li>Excellent qualitative and quantitative analytical skills</li>\n<li>Strong understanding of financial statements</li>\n<li>High level of integrity</li>\n<li>Team-oriented</li>\n<li>Ability to articulate clearly an investment case in writing and speech</li>\n<li>Willingness to travel to Asia is required</li>\n<li>Cantonese/Mandarin speaking, reading and writing fluency strongly preferred</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Working knowledge of tools such as&nbsp; Bloomberg, FactSet and strong excel skills</li>\n<li>Must be a U.S citizen or authorized to work in the U.S on a permanent basis</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'https://career4.successfactors.com/career?_s.crb=4EkazDqzqeHQMBwAuacgnP//B18=', '', 5, 162, 2),
(279, 1395628063, '项目经理助理(门店内部设计)', 'Forever 21', 'Design', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', 'Carson', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div id="tms_job_row_jobdescription" class="tms_job_row tdcolor2 wordwrap_breakword">\n<p><strong>Department Summary:&nbsp;</strong><br />Forever 21 is seeking innovative, energetic, and passionate Retail Design member to add to our dynamic team<br /><br /><strong>Job Purpose:&nbsp;<br /></strong>The Assistant Manager will assist in the design; development, scheduling, and coordination of Forever 21&rsquo;s global store design projects and ensure that all projects meet company standards and timelines.<br /><br /><strong>Deliverables:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Work closely with the Project Manager to oversee multiple store design projects across multiple teams of Associates</li>\n<li>Assist in development of project schedules/deadlines and ensure that all deliverables meet timeline goals</li>\n<li>Review and interpret existing conditions from as-built drawings and other existing documentation; identify constraints and opportunities to develop a store layout in accordance with company standards and criteria</li>\n<li>Create architectural floor plans, reflected ceiling plans, specialty lighting plans, floor finish plans and interior wall elevations</li>\n<li>Operate computer-aided drafting (CAD) equipment for interior store planning and storefront design of Forever 21 stores</li>\n<li>Generate design development and construction documents in a timely and effective manner using CAD software</li>\n<li>Maintain and prepare project files for use by Store Planning group; ensure the layout of a retail store using company format and standards</li>\n<li>Collaborate with the Architecture, Visuals, Construction and Purchasing departments to assure feasibility of layout</li>\n<li>Develop 3D drawings of existing and conceptual spaces for presentations as wells as concept development&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<br /><strong>Knowledge, Skills, and Qualifications:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Must have a degree in Architecture or Interior Design</li>\n<li>Must have 3-5 years of experience in Store Planning/Layout</li>\n<li>Proficient CAD experience required</li>\n<li>Working knowledge of Sketchup, Microsoft Word, Excel and Microsoft Outlook</li>\n<li>Must be detail-oriented, meet deadlines consistently and communicate effectively (written and verbal)</li>\n<li>Spanish speaking a plus (Japanese, <strong>Chinese</strong>, Russian etc. 2nd language is plus)</li>\n<li>Must be a team player and willing to contribute to a fast-paced, dynamic, creative environment</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br />At Forever 21, style isn&rsquo;t dictated&hellip;It&rsquo;s inspired. Forever 21 is the leading fashion retailer of the latest trends and the season&rsquo;s hottest styles at can&rsquo;t-resist-prices. U.S. and international locations stay true to the fast-fashion destination&rsquo;s iconic store aesthetic giving fashion fans all over the globe the unforgettable shopping experience that is the one and only Forever 21.&nbsp;<br /><br />Joining the Forever 21 family means joining an incredible team of talented, passionate and innovative people who work together to bring fashion to everyone, everywhere.&nbsp; We&rsquo;re always on the lookout for talented individuals eager to thrive in our fast-paced, dynamic environment filled with vast opportunities for career growth and development. This is a place where your ideas become actualized, creativity is encouraged and the possibilities are endless. Be part of something epic. Be part of Forever 21. Apply today!</p>\n</div>', 'https://forever21.tms.hrdepartment.com/cgi-bin/a/highlightjob.cgi?jobid=11357', '', 5, 42, 2),
(280, 1395628292, 'NBA中国暑期实习 ', 'NBA', 'Sports', 'Beijing, China', 'China', 'Beijing', 'Beijing', 39.904030, 116.407524, '中国', '北京市', '北京', 'None', 'Internship', '<p>　<strong>关于NBA</strong></p>\n<p>　　NBA于1946年成立，是在美国及加拿大境内拥有30支球队的职业体育联盟，同时也是享誉全球的国际品牌。在2011-12赛季，NBA通过 47种语言在215个国家及地区进行赛事转播，而2011-12赛季中来自36个国家和地区的77名国际球员的加盟亦充分体现了联盟的国际影响力。NBA 的授权产品目前在6大洲100个多个国家和地区的超过12万5千家零售点有售。NBA.com每天点击量超过3500万次，其中有50%以上的点击量是来 自于北美以外的地区。NBA是Facebook、Twitter以及Youtube上是最受欢迎的体育联盟，拥有最多的球迷、粉丝以及最高的视频点击量。</p>\n<p>　　此外，NBA一直致力于社会公益事业。通过&ldquo;NBA关怀行动&rdquo;，NBA联盟、NBA球队及球员已为慈善机构筹募善款超过1亿7千5百万美元，贡献了超过180万小时的社区服务，并在世界各地建立了675个供儿童与家庭居住、学习与游戏的场所。</p>\n<p>　　<strong>关于NBA中国</strong></p>\n<p>　　NBA中国公司成立于2008年1月，主要管理NBA在大中华区的联赛相关业务。此前，&nbsp;NBA于1992年在香港设立了大中华区的首个办事 处。NBA与中国篮球界的合作及交流源于数十年前，包括1985年首次邀请中国国家队前往美国比赛。目前NBA与中国众多全国及地方电视台和数字媒体结 盟，其中包括与NBA合作逾20年，向全国转播NBA赛事的中央电视台。联盟每年为球迷举办数百场基层篮球活动、社区活动，&nbsp;并与多家本地及国际企业建立 了市场合作伙伴关系。</p>\n<p>　　NBA中国总部位于北京，&nbsp;目前在北京、上海、香港与台北有超过100名员工。在中国，有3亿人喜欢篮球运动，超过500种NBA特许商品可实 体店及NBAStore.cn上购得。2004年，NBA成为第一家在中国举办赛事的美国职业体育联盟，此后，2007至2013年七年内，NBA又多次 将季前赛带到中国，掀起了新一轮的NBA狂潮。</p>\n<p>　　<strong>NBA中国暑期实习</strong></p>\n<p>　　暑期实习计划为在校大学生提供了能更好更全面地认识NBA的机会。实习生将不仅仅了解到篮球场上的NBA，还将广泛地接触到球场之外NBA发展。比如，NBA的各项业务与活动。暑期实习计划将培养提高大学生各方面能力，特别是社会实践能力与相应工作能力。</p>\n<p>　　本次暑期实习时间固定为<strong>2014年7月7日至8月29日</strong>，为期8周，招收15名实习生，报名截止日期为<strong>2014年3月31日</strong>。NBA中国会根据实习生所学专业和公司业务需求，相应分配学生到各个部门。暑期实习生将可能被安排到下列某一部门中进行实习：</p>\n<p>　　&middot;全球市场合作部</p>\n<p>　　&middot;媒体传播部</p>\n<p>　　&middot;数字媒体部</p>\n<p>　　&middot;现场活动及媒体内容开发部</p>\n<p>　　&middot;商品授权部</p>\n<p>　　&middot;传播及公共事务部</p>\n<p>　　&middot;商务事务部</p>\n<p>　　&middot;财务部</p>\n<p>　　&middot;人力资源部</p>\n<p>　　&middot;法务部</p>\n<p>　　<strong>对于实习生选择的基本要求：</strong></p>\n<p>　　1、仅限于中国籍本科2015年应届毕业生或在读研究生。</p>\n<p>　　2、 学习成绩优秀，有相应的实习工作经验者优先。</p>\n<p>　　3、有较强的英语听、说、读、写能力。</p>\n<p>　　4、工作积极主动，有良好的团队合作精神和人际沟通能力。</p>\n<p>　　5、热爱体育活动，特别是篮球。</p>\n<p>　　<strong>工作地点</strong>：北京/上海</p>', '', 'nbachinarecruiting@nba.com', 5, 153, 2),
(281, 1395628991, '项目分析员', 'A&J Capital Investment', 'Finance', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', 'Carson', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>The Analyst will be a member of our deal sourcing/execution team and will provide support to senior managers by performing due diligence, preparing analysis on potential investment opportunities, and providing support on all related matters as assigned</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Essential Duties and Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Perform investment due diligence (including creating and managing due diligence reports and checklists, building and analyzing financial models, and conducting independent research on the investment target)</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Review and analyze offering documents and loan documents for accuracy and completeness</li>\n<li>Support deal sourcing process by helping to categorize and track new projects.</li>\n<li>Coordinate internally and externally (lawyers and consultants, etc.) to ensure the projects are on schedule.</li>\n<li>Support senior management team with necessary data entry and general administration, e.g. independent research and memo drafting.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Education, Training, Skills and Experience Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Bachelor degree in Economic, Finance, Accounting, or related field. Masters/MBA preferred.</li>\n<li>1-3 years of financial investment, real estate or transactional experience is a plus.</li>\n<li>Outstanding oral and written skills in English. Mandarin preferred, but not required.</li>\n<li>Highly motivated with the ability to work on a team as well as independently and drive results</li>\n<li>Extreme attention to detail, high levels of professionalism , excellent communication skills (oral and written) and can maintain confidentiality</li>\n<li>Exercises judgment within broadly defined practices and policies in selecting methods and techniques for obtaining solutions</li>\n<li>Highly analytical and able to efficiently problem-solve in dynamic&nbsp; work environment</li>\n<li>Ability to work well with internal and external parties</li>\n<li></li>\n</ol>', '', 'careers@ajcap.com', 5, 169, 2);
