(285, 1395771228, '销售工程师 / 区域销售经理', '海康威视 北美分公司', 'Marketing', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '旧金山', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>海康威视是全球最大的CCTV视频安防制造商，深交所上市，<wbr />业务遍布全球，现有员工1万人。公司将继续高速增长，<wbr />特别是北美业务爆炸增长，诚邀有志之士加盟北美业务。</p>\n<div>\n<p>要求：电子工程、计算机或其他工科背景，有视频工作经验优先。<wbr />有工作资格、英文流利、会中文优先</p>\n<p>职位：<br />1. 西雅图及附近地区：销售工程师 覆盖华盛顿、爱德华、蒙大拿、俄勒冈州 - 技术服务、培训、项目跟踪<br />2. 温哥华及附近地区：销售工程师 覆盖安省（不含）以西的西部加拿大地区 - 技术服务、培训、项目跟踪<br />3. 旧金山及附近地区：区域销售经理，覆盖北加州以及北内华达州、<wbr />拓展和服务客户</p>\n<p>待遇：北美中高标准</p>\n<p>工作模式：总部在洛杉矶，各地员工在自己家里工作，出差60%<wbr />以上。</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>', '', 'katherine.chang@hikvisionusa.com', 5, 303, 2),
(286, 1395782349, 'Graphic designer Intern', '北美华人精品生活杂志 "The Asian Magazine"', 'Media', 'Dallas, TX, United States', 'United States', 'Texas', 'Dallas', 32.780140, -96.800453, '美国', '德克萨斯州', '达拉斯', 'None', 'Internship', '<p>职责：</p>\n<p>有良好的审美能力，擅长于色彩搭配，有一定的设计理念和技巧，能够运用图像设计来完成富有艺术感的工作，全面把控画面设计质量。</p>\n<p>学习能力强，理解沟通能力好，热爱设计工作，有创意和执行力，有手绘基础者优先。</p>\n<p>能够独立完成设计，排版，数码打样，菲林，负责印前检查，修改，保证印前以及输出工作的正常无误，熟练掌握印刷常识以及特殊工艺，对纸张和印刷机有一定了解</p>', '', 'Career@theasianmagazine.com', 5, 142, 2),
(287, 1395782927, 'Gallery Associate', '纽约前波画廊 Chambers Fine Art', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.714352, -74.005974, '美国', '纽约州', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="txtChinese">\n<p>前波画廊是一家致力于推广中国当代艺术的国际性画廊，在纽约和北京均设有分点。画廊由茅为清先生（Christophe W. Mao）于2000年在纽约成立。他相信在西方建立一家具有权威性的画廊，提供中国当代艺术发展的信息和展示空间的重要性，并以十八世纪后期英国著名建筑师威廉.钱伯斯勋爵 (Sir William Chambers) 的名字为画廊命名，借喻钱伯斯勋爵不仅在建筑设计上独有建树，同时还是首位中国建筑和园林设计观念在西方的重要阐释和推广者。在最初的七年里，前波画廊与吕胜中、洪浩、宋冬和尹秀珍等艺术家合作，举办了他们在美国的首次个展。之后，邱志杰、谭盾、冯梦波等艺术家风格各异的专题展览更为画廊添光增彩。画廊于2009年搬迁至西19街522号，该地区云集众多由世界著名建筑师设计的新建筑，比如弗兰克∙盖里 (Frank Gehry)、坂茂 (Shigeru Ban)及让∙努维尔(Jean Nouvel)等，同时也毗邻由废弃的铁路轨道改建而成的空中花园 (High Line)。十多年已经过去，前波画廊如今已经成为了那些关注中国发展的人们的一个必访之地。</p>\n</div>\n<p>Established Chelsea gallery specializing in contemporary Chinese art seeks a full-time Gallery Associate to work closely with Directors and gallery staff to support a dynamic exhibition program between our NY and Beijing locations. We are a closely-knit hard-working team and are looking for a highly motivated individual who will contribute to all aspects of the gallery&rsquo;s operations including exhibition-planning, sales, artist-relations, registrarial duties and PR. This is an excellent opportunity to gain experience working closely with the gallery&rsquo;s senior staff and there is significant room for growth based on ability.&nbsp;<br /><br />Candidate must have at least 2 years prior experience working full-time in a gallery, museum, or related art institution.&nbsp;<br /><br />The position&rsquo;s responsibilities include, but are not limited, to the following:&nbsp;<br />&bull; Work closely with senior staff to plan exhibitions including organizing opening-receptions and artist-related events; coordinating shipping and installation; preparing related PR materials.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Manage gallery&rsquo;s PR outreach including maintaining relationships with journalists and developing new contacts, assembling press-materials and maintaining gallery&rsquo;s web presence.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Assist Directors with sales-outreach including creating and assembling sales-material&nbsp;<br />&bull; Support Directors during art-fairs including working at the fair as necessary.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Assist Registrar with managing gallery inventory including organizing incoming and outgoing shipments of artwork, as well as registering and maintaining inventory database.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Co-ordinate events organized by gallery, both on-site and off-site.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Maintain gallery&rsquo;s contact database.&nbsp;<br />REQUIREMENTS:&nbsp;<br />&bull; Bachelor&rsquo;s degree with at least 2 years experience working in a gallery, museum, or related art institution..&nbsp;<br />&bull; Fluent in PC based applications including MS Office/Word/Outlook/Excel, as well as gallery data-base software such as ArtSystems or ArtBase.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Experienced with photoshop and manipulating digital images&nbsp;<br />&bull; Strong organizational and time management skills.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class="summary">If interested, please send resume, cover-letter and at least two references.</span></p>', '', 'cfa@chambersfineart.com', 5, 167, 2),
(288, 1395783057, 'Summer 2014 Intellectual Property Intern', 'Tory Burch', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.714352, -74.005974, '美国', '纽约州', '纽约', 'None', 'Internship', '<p>Overview:&nbsp;<br />The Tory Burch legal team seeks qualified law student interns for summer 2014 with an interest in intellectual property.&nbsp;<br /><br />Responsibilities:&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Assist Senior Counsel on all aspects of brand protection and anti-counterfeiting, specifically online enforcement</li>\n<li>Monitor online platforms based in the US, Asia, and South America for counterfeit Tory Burch products and conduct take-downs on said platforms;</li>\n<li>Assist in civil enforcement as necessary (drafting cease and desist letters, preparing evidence for litigation);</li>\n<li>Maintain IP Enforcement Database for all global anti-counterfeiting matters, includes entering information into system, scanning, saving, and preparing updates and summaries as needed;</li>\n<li>Draft memoranda on relevant legal issues related to IP or other areas of law.</li>\n<li>Assist on any other tasks as assigned by members of the legal department.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br />Qualifications:&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Minimum of full-time commitment June 2nd through August 8th</li>\n<li>Ability to assist with legal and non-legal issues as they arise in a fast-paced corporate environment.</li>\n<li>Must be motivated, eager, and excited to join a growing fashion company.</li>\n<li>Organized, hard-working, and an attention to detail.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\n<li>Experience in trademark and copyright law.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\n<li>Ability to read and <strong>speak Chinese</strong> and/or Korean is a plus.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\n<li>This is a paid position ($10/hr)</li>\n</ul>', 'https://careers-toryburch.icims.com/jobs/2221/summer-2014-intellectual-property-intern/job', '', 5, 194, 2),
(290, 1395784867, '中国运行总监 Director of Operations', 'American Senior Communities', 'Service', 'Chicago, IL, United States', 'United States', 'Illinois', 'Chicago', 41.878113, -87.629799, '美国', '伊利诺伊州', '芝加哥', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><span class="summary">We are currently seeking a Director of Operations tooversee and act as a consultant to ensure the success of foreign developmentswithin China. This position will travel to China and be responsible forconsulting and managing the operations of these new long term care communities.&nbsp;<br /><br />Essential Job Functions:&nbsp;<br /><br />&bull; Consults toensure the planning, developing, implementing, evaluating and directing of theNursing&nbsp;<br /><br />Homes facility programs are in accordance with established policies,goals, and procedures within China.&nbsp;<br /><br />&bull; Ensuresexcellent patient care and customer service is maintained&nbsp;<br /><br />&bull; Reviewsrevenue opportunities; monitors expenses; and assists with developing annualbudget&nbsp;<br /><br />For more information please contact:&nbsp;<br /><br />American Senior Communities&nbsp;<br /><br />Laurel Lingle&nbsp;<br /><br />Recruiting Manager&nbsp;<br /><br />6900 South Gray Road&nbsp;<br /><br />Indianapolis, IN 46256&nbsp;<br /><br />317-788-2500&nbsp;<br /><br />Job Qualifications:&nbsp;<br /><br />&bull; Bachelors Degree in Healthcare Management&nbsp;<br /><br />&bull; 5-10 years experience in Healthcare operations&nbsp;<br /><br />&bull; Bilingual (<strong>Fluent in Mandarin</strong>)&nbsp;<br /><br />&bull; Must be able to travel abroad as needed&nbsp;</span></p>', 'http://www.careerbuilder.com/csh/details.aspx?csh=CSH_AmericanSenior&pubjobs=true&privjobs=false&int=true&did=JB76VQ61RMZK1LXNDLL', '', 5, 149, 2),
(291, 1395785502, '社会化媒体编辑-中国', 'REVOLVEclothing', 'Media', '', 'United States', 'California', 'Cerritos', 0.000000, 0.000000, 'United States', 'California', 'Cerritos', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>企业背景&nbsp;<br /><br />REVOLVE 是美国著名的时尚潮流购物网站,为顾客带来源自洛杉矶的一线潮流设计师品牌。提供将近500种中高端男女装设计师品牌,包括服饰、配件和鞋履等。顾客之上是我们一贯的宗旨。&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>职位介绍:</strong><br />社会化媒体编辑将会管理REVOLVE在中国的社会化媒体账号,中国市场是我们其中一个发展迅速的市场。理想的候选人需要在远程办公的环境下保持高度的工作自主性,能独立完成目标的工作。和中国区经理和中文客服团队保持紧密的联系,汇报并反映顾客的意见和诉求。除此之外,候选人需要对了解时尚,熟悉中国的潮流趋势和关注REVOLVE在中国的竞争对手。&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>主要职责:</strong><br /><strong>主要职责包括但不限制于以下:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>负责每日官方微博和微信的内容发布及运营,和粉丝进行交流互动</li>\n<li>和粉丝的交流互动包括回答微博上的基本咨询,引导顾客至中文客服渠道。</li>\n<li>创建基本微博配图</li>\n<li>挑选REVOLVE其他社会化媒体频道的内容,转化成适合中国市场的微博和微信内容</li>\n<li>分析和根据粉丝的特点和兴趣,撰写有趣和创意的微博内容,有效提高与粉丝的互动和增加粉丝人数</li>\n<li>与时尚博主,网络红人沟通,确保相关的活动能有效进行</li>\n<li>定期向中国区经理反映和汇报顾客或粉丝对REVOLVE的意见</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>能力要求:</strong><br /><strong>求职者需具备以下条件:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>对中国社会化媒体平台有深入的了解和有相关运营经验</li>\n<li>熟悉中国和亚洲的时尚趋势</li>\n<li>对美国潮流品牌有基本了解</li>\n<li>能在快速发展的行业前景下保持积极的工作态度</li>\n<li>热爱并能随时掌握最新最热的时尚,媒体和潮流趋势</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>教育程度/经验要求:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>本科文凭</li>\n<li>必须有微博运营的相关经验</li>\n<li>有淘宝,天猫和微信的经验最佳</li>\n<li>精通Microsoft Excel和数据分析</li>\n<li>熟悉PhotoShop或其他图片编软件最佳</li>\n<li>必须说流利普通话</li>\n<li>能说广东话最佳</li>\n</ul>', 'http://ch.tbe.taleo.net/CH03/ats/careers/requisition.jsp?org=REVOLVECLOTHING&cws=1&rid=110', '', 5, 176, 2),
(292, 1395785923, 'Communication/Marketing Coordinator/Business Development', 'MAD Architects', 'Design', '', 'United States', 'California', 'Santa Monica', 0.000000, 0.000000, 'United States', 'California', 'Santa Monica', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>MAD由马岩松、党群和早野洋介领导。这是一个充满活力的国际事务所，有来自世界各地的60余名建筑师在这里工作。2011年MAD建筑事务所被FASTCOMPANY评为中国10个最具创造力的公司之一。</p>\n<p>MAD Los Angeles office is currently seeking Communication/Marketing Coordinator/ Business Development&nbsp;<br /><br />Applicants must demonstrate the following qualities:&nbsp;<br />&bull; a strong educational background in Marketing /PR/Communications or a relevant major.&nbsp;<br />&bull; A minimum of four years&rsquo; experience in marketing /Press/Communication in major international architecture firms or a relevant profession with professional experience in art promotion.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Fluent English in spoken and written, great writing skill especially, with experience working/studying internationally (Chinese and English speaker is preferred. Tri-lingual is preferred)&nbsp;<br />&bull; understanding the core function of architect firm, and major communication and marketing functions, how to operate them.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Solid written and verbal communication skills as well as grammatical proofing and editing abilities (familiarity with publication production or graphic design would be preferred)&nbsp;<br />&bull; a solid track record communication and marketing skills in traditional and new media&nbsp;<br />&bull; good with establish new connections and also maintain the exist connections.&nbsp;<br />&bull; experience working with Word, Excel, PowerPoint and Mail/Outlook (knowledge of the Adobe Suite and database management is desirable)&nbsp;<br />&bull; a positive attitude towards obstacles and tight deadlines, out-going, strong communicator and able to take priorities and handle multi-tasks when he/she is required to do so.&nbsp;<br /><br />Main job tasks and responsibilities:&nbsp;<br />&bull; Draft or Edit press releases/project descriptions, responding to journalist requests, arranging interviews, maintaining the media/press coverage archive and contact database, together with the Director and Partners to make and operate the Company marketing strategy.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Communicate and make contact and connections with target client and market&nbsp;<br />&bull; strengthening the company&rsquo;s use of social media and managing website and newsletter updates&nbsp;<br />&bull; pro-actively building the company&rsquo;s profile and network, eg. through the production of publications, and submissions for awards and competitions&nbsp;<br />&bull; coordinating participation in international lectures, exhibitions and events, including managing the agenda and travel arrangements.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Coordinating with exhibition request, publication and models.&nbsp;</p>', '', 'Dixon@i-mad.com', 5, 171, 2),
(293, 1395786275, '酒吧招待', '鼎泰丰', 'Resturant', '', 'United States', 'California', 'Glendale', 0.000000, 0.000000, 'United States', 'California', 'Glendale', 'None', 'Full Time', '<section id="job-description" class="row-fluid">\n<p>Din Tai Fung was ranked No. 1 in the inaugural "101 Best Restaurants in Asia (2013)" by&nbsp;<em>The Daily Meal</em>. We are the world leader in contemporary Chinese food and have received Michelin Stars in our locations in Hong Kong. With over 80 locations in Asia, Din Tai Fung is just beginning to grow in the United States.</p>\n<p>We are looking for bartenders that can deliver great customer service with a smile. Our bars have full food service, so applicants should have restaurant experience.</p>\n</section>', '', 'm93gfb9ehw@jobs.shiftgig.com', 5, 128, 2),
(294, 1395871729, 'Chinese Speaking Scheduling Specialist', 'ComplexCare Solutions', 'Service', '', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 0.000000, 0.000000, 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>We are looking for a Chinese speaking individual to work with our Chinese speaking Medicare Members. Prefer someone with customer service and working in a high volume call center environment.&nbsp;<br /><br />Scope:&nbsp;<br /><br />The Scheduling Specialist works with the MLTC RN''s and Nurse Practitioners scheduling the Managed Long Term Care Assessments for CCS members and managing multiple clinician calendars. Also responsible for explaining the program to our members and speaking with the primary care physician. The Specialist must enjoy speaking with people on the phone, and possess the in-depth understanding and the diverse skills to overcome member issues, hesitation or objections. The Specialist will coordinate calendaring for clinical field staff managing member needs and field staff availability and geography. The Specialist is accountable for making a high volume of calls with exceptional member service.&nbsp;<br /><br />RESPONSIBILITIES&nbsp;<br /><br />&bull; Conduct outbound calls to Medicare Advantage members to schedule in-home visits by nurse practitioners or other clinical staff&nbsp;<br /><br />&bull; Provide a member orientation when consent is obtained for the in-home appointment ensuring the member comprehends all the features and benefits of the program&nbsp;<br /><br />&bull; Coordinate schedules of field staff to accommodate member needs, geography and program priorities&nbsp;<br /><br />&bull; Field inbound calls with a positive attitude, building rapport and trust with members&nbsp;<br /><br />&bull; Interact with other departments such as Care Coordination, Social Work, and Care Managers, to resolve member issues&nbsp;<br /><br />&bull; Organize time/tasks and work without direct and daily supervision&nbsp;<br /><br />&bull; Work in a fast paced environment and prioritize tasks to meet deadlines and goals&nbsp;<br /><br />&bull; Perform additional duties as directed by management&nbsp;<br /><br />QUALIFICATIONS:&nbsp;<br /><br />&bull; Associates Degree or equivalent experience.&nbsp;<br /><br />&bull; Possesses computer literacy, including, but not limited to, data entry and retrieval and Microsoft</p>', '', 'lchamberlain@complexcaresolutions.com', 5, 138, 2),
(295, 1395871846, 'Sales Associate', 'The Finish Line Inc', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.714352, -74.005974, '美国', '纽约州', '纽约', 'None', 'Part Time', '<p><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Finish Line and Macy''s have partnered to create a one of a kind retail experience inside of the Macy''s footwear departments all over the country, and we are&nbsp;currently hiring for part-time&nbsp;<strong>Sales Associates</strong>&nbsp;to join our team at three new Finish Line''s in Flushing<strong>.&nbsp;</strong>It would be ideal if this Sales Associate is&nbsp;<strong>bilingual in English and Chinese/Mandarin.</strong></font></p>\n<p><font face="Verdana, sans-serif">&nbsp;</font></p>\n<p><font face="Arial, sans-serif">As a Sales Associate for Finish Line, you are a living, breathing billboard,&nbsp;a human Google search working to find the best products&nbsp;for our customers, and an ambassador of some of the world''s greatest athletic retail brands. &nbsp;</font></p>\n<p><font face="Verdana, sans-serif">&nbsp;</font></p>\n<p><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Sales Associates with Finish Line Receive:</font></p>\n<ul type="disc">\n<li><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Competitive compensation plans</font></li>\n<li><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Opportunities for additional&nbsp;incentive pay</font></li>\n<li><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Employee discounts</font></li>\n<li><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Opportunities for advancement and career growth!</font></li>\n</ul>', '', '2459@finishline.com', 5, 125, 2),
(296, 1395872903, 'Designer (mid-level)', 'Fuhu', 'Design', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', 'Carson', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="jobPostings view">\n<div class="posting description">\n<p>Fuhu Inc., is the leading designer, seller and innovator of &ldquo;thoughtful&rdquo; consumer products and services for children.&nbsp; Creator of the nabi&trade; tablet, the world&rsquo;s first tablet made just for kids, Fuhu provides an ecosystem of hardware, software services, and accessories to immerse kids in rich and engaging experiences.&nbsp; nabi &trade; is available in all major U.S. retailers including Walmart, Best Buy, GameStop, and Target.<br /><br />We are currently looking for a Designer to join our growing team. If you are looking for a fast paced environment at a fast growing company, please apply!<br /><br />Duties:<br />Uses knowledge of current graphic design software to produce graphic art and visual materials for promotions, advertisements, packaging, and informative and instructional material through a variety of media outlets.<br />Must remain abreast of technological advances in the field and be able to identify areas of use in the organization.<br />Familiar with standard concepts, practices, and procedures within a particular field.<br />Relies on limited experience and judgment to plan and accomplish goals.<br />Performs a variety of tasks related to graphic design.<br />Works under general supervision; typically reports to a supervisor or manager.<br />A great deal of creativity and latitude is expected.<br />&nbsp;<br /><br />Requirements:<br />At least 3 years experience working as a Designer.<br />Advanced knowledge of Adobe Illustrator, Photoshop, and a strong grasp of design principles.<br />Deadline oriented.<br />Strong in conceptual and problem solving skills; critical thinking.<br />A portfolio or sample work that clearly communicates successful design solutions that drive business success.<br /><strong>Bilingual English/Chinese is required, both spoken and written</strong></p>\n</div>\n</div>', 'http://fuhu.mytribehr.com/careers/view/19', '', 5, 106, 2),
(297, 1395874013, 'Marketing Graphic Designer ', 'Keyways Vineyard & Winery', 'Design', 'Pasadena, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Pasadena', 34.147785, -118.144516, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '帕萨迪纳', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Keyways Vineyard &amp; Winery, founded in 1989, is one of the most popular wineries in Temecula Valley. We offer the most extensive and competitive priced fine wine to our customers. We are well known for our excellent customer service and knowledgeable wine staffs.<br />We are currently looking to fill a marketing/designer position in the management office in the city of South Pasadena.</p>\n<p>Duties include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Work with director on promotional projects</li>\n<li>Developing realistic marketing strategies, objectives, and targets.</li>\n<li>Produce promotion materials such as digital ads, invitation cards, etc.</li>\n<li>Manage online marketing campaigns and social networking websites</li>\n<li>Analyze the results of marketing campaigns and advertisements.</li>\n<li>Represent the company in events and trade shows.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Qualifications:<br />-Must know Adobe Illustrator and Photoshop<br />-Working design experience preferred<br />-Marketing experience preferred<br />-Good writing skills<br />-Strong communication skills<br />-Good team work mentality<br />-Ability to follow management directions<br />-Ability to complete assignment within guidelines.<br /><strong>-Speak and write Chinese - Mandarin Preferred</strong></p>\n<p>Position is full time.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=1b6a4601c128be2a&q=chinese&l=Los+Angeles,+CA&tk=18juq3st606b06a3&from=ja&alid=9f2e1477827c67ac&utm_source=jobseeker_emails&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=job_alerts', '', 5, 93, 2),
(298, 1395874193, 'A/R Supervisor', 'American Chung Nam', 'Finance', '', 'United States', 'California', 'City of Industry', 0.000000, 0.000000, 'United States', 'California', 'City of Industry', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="jvdescriptionbody">\n<p>This is a unique opportunity to join a high performing team and enhance your professional profile. You will work with and manage a team to determine and verify the correct calculations, postings, verifying and/or reporting data. You will be required to communicate the results of your work to direct and senior management.</p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Major Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Responsible for A/R and resolution of discrepancies with vendors</li>\n<li>Monitor accounts receivables. Participate in monthly aging reviews and present to Accounting management team.</li>\n<li>Review posted payments and prepare monthly statements of accounts.</li>\n<li>Data entry into accounting system.</li>\n<li>Monitor internal controls to assure compliance with established procedures related to accounts receivable</li>\n<li>Enhance the company&rsquo;s policies and procedures surrounding the accounts receivable cycle</li>\n<li>Communicates and coordinates accounting policies, practices and procedures with the department and company managers</li>\n<li>Performs other job related duties and projects as assigned</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong><br />Required qualifications and competencies:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>BS in Accounting or Finance.</li>\n<li>4-6 years of combined accounting and A/R experience in logistics, ocean freight, trucking.</li>\n<li>Experience in the banking industry and/or with foreign exchange rates highly preferred.</li>\n<li>LC experience highly desired.</li>\n<li>Management and/or supervisory experience required.</li>\n<li>Experience with A/R duties, including with credit and collections.</li>\n<li>Team-player with excellent interpersonal and influencing skills.</li>\n<li>Integrity, commitment/dedication, respect for others, pursuer of excellence and innovation.</li>\n<li>Enthusiastic self-starter with an ability to work effectively under pressure.</li>\n<li>Ability to respond and adapt quickly to changing work situations and environments.</li>\n<li>Strong time management, organization, project management, and report writing skills.</li>\n<li>ERP, SAP, and audit experience preferred.</li>\n<li>Strong communication skills &ndash; <strong>written and spoken English and Chinese preferred</strong>.</li>\n<li>Permanent residents and US Citizens only - this position is not eligible for visa sponsorship.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>', 'http://hire.jobvite.com/CompanyJobs/Careers.aspx?k=Job&c=qnz9VfwK&j=ohPEYfws', '', 5, 85, 2),
(299, 1396034233, '中文摄影师', 'mom365 Newborn Photographer', 'Media', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.714352, -74.005974, '美国', '纽约州', '纽约', 'None', 'Part Time', '<p >Love Babies? Love Photography? Mom365 provides a unique opportunity to earn extra income taking baby photos at your local hospital.</p>\n <p >As a Photographer-Sales Rep, you''ll work in the maternity ward of a hospital near you taking baby photos and selling packages to mom and dad. No photography experience? Don''t worry! You''ll use our equipment and we''ll provide you with photography training.</p>\n <p >We are currently seeking Photographers/Sales Reps at:<br />THE NEW YORK HOSPITAL MEDICAL CENTER QUEENS<br />Schedule: 4-5 days a week and weekends; 9am to approximate 5pm</p>\n <p >Qualifications:<br />MUST SPEAK MANDARIN/CANTONESE TO BE CONSIDERED FOR THIS POSITION<br />Strong communication and time management skills.<br />Mature, dependable, and energetic.<br />2 years of sales or customer service experience<br />Comfortable in a commission-based sales environment.<br />A passion for photography.<br />You will be expected to comply with hospital regulations regarding patient privacy, HIPPA, security, sanitation and infection control.</p>\n <p >Mom365 is the nation''s leader in hospital newborn photography. At Mom365 we strive to give every new parent the very best first portrait of his or her newborn baby and provide the level of customer service that makes our hospitals proud to be our partner. Explore an exciting part-time career opportunity with Mom365!</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'https://jobs-mom365.icims.com/jobs/17218/bilingual-mom365-newborn-photographer---queens,-ny/job', '', 5, 140, 2),
(300, 1396034531, '中国艺术品专栏编辑实习生', 'Artnet Worldwide Corporation', 'Marketing', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.714352, -74.005974, '美国', '纽约州', '纽约', 'None', 'Internship', '<p><span class="summary">artnet&rsquo;s marketing department is seeking an intern to provide editorial support to maintain and develop Chinese Art columns on leading media platforms and social media platforms.<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br /><br />Note: This is a full-time internship with a small daily stipend, and may also qualify for academic credit.<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br /><br />Tasks<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br /><br />&bull; Translation and editorial support to maintain and develop content for Chinese Art columns on leading media platforms<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br /><br />&bull; Assist in daily postings and maintenance of artnet&rsquo;s Chinese social media platforms, including Weibo and WeChat<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br /><br />&bull; Assist in implementing online promotional programs aimed at building brand awareness and driving traffic to artnet<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br /><br />&bull; Assist with the creation of Chinese marketing materials, including e-newsletters, email blasts, targeted mailings, advertising, and sales collateral<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br /><br />&bull; Provide support to the artnet marketing department as needed<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br /><br />Qualifications<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br /><br />&bull; Bilingual fluency in Mandarin and English, as well as reading and writing fluency in Simplified Chinese and English is a must<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br />&bull; Strong writing and editing skills<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br />&bull; Experience with social media<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br />&bull; Skilled in Microsoft Word, Excel, Photoshop, PowerPoint, and HTML proficient<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br />&bull; Strong organizational skills, and a high level of attention to detail<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br />&bull; Ability to express written and verbal ideas clearly and concisely<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br />&bull; Technically savvy with a good knowledge of the PC platform<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br />&bull; A background in Asian Art or art history is a plus<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br /><br />Application Instructions<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br />To Apply:<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br />Please send a cover letter and your resume to careers-marketing@artnet.com.<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br /><br />No phone calls.<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br />No recruiters or job placement agencies.<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br />Applicants must have legal permission to work in the United States.</span></p>', '', 'careers-marketing@artnet.com', 5, 152, 2),
(301, 1396035105, '中文兼职银行柜台', 'Bank of America', 'Finance', 'Temple City, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Temple City', 34.107231, -118.057846, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '坦普尔市', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>Job description</strong><br />Tellers primary responsibilities include, processing transactions accurately and efficiently in accordance with established policies and procedures and engaging our customers . Connecting customers through referrals to teammates and specialists making the financial lives of our customers better. Tellers are the face of Bank of America and therefore demonstrate core values in all actions and provide an excellent experience for the customer. May be required to work weekends and/or extended hours and regular, reliable attendance is critical.</p>\n<p><strong>Qualifications</strong><br />Required Skills:</p>\n<p>Minimum of six months customer service experience<br />Ability to work effectively as a team member<br />Strong oral and written communication skills<br />Ability to respond and assist customers with inquiries and/or problem resolution<br />Careful attention to detail and time management<br />Pass teller pre-employment assessment<br />Mandarin Fluency Required </p>\n<p>Desired Skills:</p>\n<p>Minimum of six months cash handling experience<br />Previous experience with cross-selling, upselling, and/or referring products<br />Ability to identify customer financial needs, goals and objectives<br />Proficiency in basic computer skills<br />Previous banking/financial services/teller experience<br /><br />Location: US-CA-Temple City<br /><strong>Language: Chinese (Mandarin)</strong><br />Travel: No<br />Full / Part-time: Parttime<br />Hours Per Week: 20.00<br />Shift: 1st Shift<br />Weekly Schedule: M-F 8:30am-1:30pm and all day sat</p>', 'http://careers.bankofamerica.com/job.aspx?n=26352&src=JB-11684', '', 5, 192, 2),
(302, 1396244835, '中文程序测试员', 'adaQuest', 'Technology', 'Kirkland, WA, United States', 'United States', 'Washington', 'Kirkland', 47.681488, -122.208733, '美国', '华盛顿', '柯克兰', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p >adaQuest is a premier provider of project management solutions. We have been providing industry - leading customer&rsquo;s dynamic solutions to meet their technology and human resources needs since 2001. We are currently hiring a Localization Engineer to work with one of our clients in Kirkland - WA</p>\n <p >The qualified candidate will work with one of our clients that is rapidly expanding their Business in USA!!!</p>\n <p >&nbsp;</p>\n <p ><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>\n <ul >\n<li>Experiences in Globalization &amp; Localization testing and solid knowledge about Web</li>\n<li>Familiar with product localization cycle</li>\n<li>Experience in Web Testing&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Experiences in managing remote vendors as test lead</li>\n<li>Mobile testing (iPhone, iPad and Android) is a plus</li>\n<li>Agile experiences is a plus</li>\n <li><span >3 + years localization testing experiences</span></li>\n <li><span >2 year project management or team management experiences</span></li>\n <li><strong><span >Chinese Native Speaker</span></strong></li>\n</ul>\n <p ><strong>Technology</strong>: C#, HTML</p>\n <p >&nbsp;</p>\n <p >More details regarding the job responsibilities will be provided during the interview&nbsp;</p>', 'https://jobs-adaquest.icims.com/jobs/1409/qa---localization/job', '', 5, 106, 2),
(303, 1396245374, '亚太地区技术支持工程师', 'Tableau Software', 'Technology', '', 'United States', 'Washington', 'Seattle', 0.000000, 0.000000, 'United States', 'Washington', 'Seattle', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>What you&rsquo;ll be doing &hellip;</strong></p>\n<p>Tableau Software customers love working with our products, and we love helping them achieve amazing results. Technical Support Engineers are natural problem solvers, passionate about customers, curious about technology, and driven to succeed.</p>\n<p>In the Technical Support Engineer role, you will work primarily with enterprise customers of Tableau&rsquo;s server and core server products, proactively assisting them with post-sales installation, configuration and set up tasks, or customers of Tableau&rsquo;s Desktop products, proactively assisting them with post-sales installation, data connectivity, performance and analysis of data. Responsibilities include triaging and resolving highly complex, technical, and application-related issues which impact product performance in customer-specific environments, or issues that directly hamper a broader customer adoption of Tableau products.</p>\n<p>Apply in-depth engaged diagnostic technical troubleshooting skills to identify customer issue and perform root cause analysis. Apply mixture of system, database, and application knowledge towards troubleshooting and resolving critical and complex issues. Use skills in debugging to identify steps to reproduce the issue, determine likely cause, and prepare detailed, actionable bug reports for Engineering. Throughout the case resolution process, maintain superb relationship with the customer by keeping them informed throughout and ensure continued collaboration with Engineering and Product Management teams. As customer advocate, provide detailed feedback to Engineering and Product Management on feature enhancements to improve supportability and product quality.</p>\n<p>This role must ramp up quickly in knowledge of Tableau&rsquo;s Desktop and Server Products, including licensing, activation-related installation specifications/settings, and configuration requirements for optimal product performance. In addition to working with customers, the Technical Support Engineer will routinely collaborate with Technical Support, Sustaining Engineering and Sales Consultants to resolve issues.</p>\n<p>Candidates will have the ability and desire to work the Asia Pacific (APAC) shift from 4:00 p.m. to 1:00 a.m., Sundays through Thursdays from our Fremont, WA location.</p>\n<p><strong>Some of the things you&rsquo;ll be doing include &hellip;</strong></p>\n<p>Effectively communicate with customers via email, phone and other electronic methods to ensure client&rsquo;s effective use of Tableau products. Maintain excellent relationships with Tableau customers by applying superb customer service and technical skills. Perform in-depth troubleshooting to identify root cause while understanding the customer&rsquo;s skill level and communicating with them in the manner most appropriate. Use excellent judgment in when and how to communicate with customer for maximum effectiveness and customer satisfaction.<br />Collaborate and consult with select server and core server clients to implement successful server launches, and to resolve highly complex technical issues associated with deployment.<br />Collaborate and consult with Tableau Desktop clients to successfully integrate (installation, data connectivity, analysis and performance) the application into their business, and to resolve highly complex technical issues associated with integration.<br />Apply in-depth troubleshooting and debugging skills along with knowledge of systems, databases, and applications to get to root cause of the customer&rsquo;s issue. Set up test environments to mirror customer set-up, write test scripts, and perform tests using customer&rsquo;s data or representative data. Apply solid test methodology and debugging skills to narrow down the problem as needed. Communicate effectively to Sustaining Engineering step-by-step instructions to reproduce the issue and findings to identify root cause.<br />Partner with clients and help them optimize the use of Tableau software by using skill in listening and understanding the customer&rsquo;s request thoroughly combined with in-depth technical knowledge to assist them in the manner most appropriate. Lead support case resolution efforts for customer cases by using skill in troubleshooting and debugging, identifying root cause, communicating bugs to Sustaining Engineering in a manner that requires little to no additional research on the part of the Engineer. Build strong cross-functional working relationships with Engineering and Product Management.<br />Extensively research and document customer software and technical issues as Knowledge Base articles as appropriate. Using a mixture of system, application and database knowledge, research and reproduce issues. Use excellent written communication skills to produce useful Knowledge Base articles to be applied to the external Knowledge Base used by Tableau customers. Contribute substantially to the ongoing development of the Knowledge Base.<br />Utilize Knowledge Base articles as a resource to solve customer issues, researching the Knowledge Base as a step in the troubleshooting process.<br />Collaborate with Technical Support, Product Management, Sustaining Engineering and Sales Consultants to resolve issues by applying excellent technical, customer service, and interpersonal skills in building solid cross-functional relationships.<br />Mentor Technical Support Specialists in researching, resolving and documenting customer server issues, including bug reports, etc.<br />Escalate support cases and priority issues to management as appropriate using good judgment in when and how to escalate.<br />Maintain appropriate case- and customer-related files and records.<br />Prioritize customer cases and company projects effectively, communicating priorities and plans to management.<br />Other duties as assigned.</p>\n<p><strong>Who you are &hellip;</strong></p>\n<p>Problem Solver. You are a natural problem solver with a curiosity about technology. Others describe you as a highly creative, curious technologist, and you have excellent research skills.<br />Communicator. Your verbal and written skills are top notch. You have an outstanding ability to empathize with customers and convey confidence, and are skilled with conflict resolution, presentation and small group facilitation skills. Ability to fluently communicate verbally and in writing in English as well as one of the following: <strong>Mandarin Chinese</strong>, Japanese, Korean. Ability to fluently communicate verbally and in writing in Spanish, French, German or Portuguese a plus.<br />Organized. You have an uncanny ability to juggle and prioritize a high volume workload and handle details accurately and in a timely manner under pressure.<br />Educated. BSCS is preferred; Bachelor&rsquo;s degrees in a technical or quantitative major will also be considered.<br />Experienced. You have 3+ years&rsquo; experience supporting and troubleshooting commercial end user software applications. You understand networking, server setup and administration.<br />Domain. You have a strong understanding of relational databases; experience with Essbase and MSAS Cubes is a plus. 2+ years experience with SQL scripting, HTML, and JavaScript are preferred.<br /> <br />Tableau Software is an equal opportunity employer.</p>', 'http://ch.tbe.taleo.net/CH11/ats/careers/requisition.jsp?org=TABLEAU&cws=1&rid=2161', '', 5, 63, 2),
(304, 1396245872, '中学中文老师', 'San Mateo-Foster City Elementary', 'Language', 'Foster City, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Foster City', 37.558544, -122.271080, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '福斯特城', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><span >Single Subject Mandarin Credential required San Mateo-Foster City School District is looking for a Middle School Mandarin Teacher to work at a year round school for the 2014-2015 school year.<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><br  /><br  /><span >Applicants must be fluent in listening, speaking, reading, and writing Mandarin Chinese, both traditional and simplified.<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><br  /><br  /><span >Wonderful benefits:<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><br  /><span >fully paid medical/dental for employee, sick leave, paid holiday &amp; STRS retirement!<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><br  /><br  /><span >Please apply on-line through Ed-join.<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><br  /><br  /><span >A complete application will include:<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><br  /><span >* resume<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><br  /><span >*  letters of reference<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><br  /><span >*transcripts</span></p>', 'http://www.edjoin.org/viewPosting.aspx?postingID=556355', '', 5, 204, 2);
