(307, 1396381708, '销售', 'Leopard Inc', 'Marketing', 'Hillside, NJ, United States', 'United States', 'New Jersey', 'Hillside', 40.695503, -74.228729, '美国', '新泽西州', '希尔赛德', 'H1B', 'Full Time', '<p>Leopard Inc. is seeking entry-level sales people to promote wholesale truck tires and tire handling.</p>\n<p>Please attach resume. We do anticipate providing sponsorship for h-1b visa for this employment position.</p>', '', 'kevin@truck-tire.com', 5, 114, 2),
(308, 1396383992, 'Branch Operation Manager', 'Chinatrust Bank USA', 'Finance', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', 'Carson', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>Job Duties</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Manage and supervise the branch&rsquo;s operations activities ensuring compliance with the bank&rsquo;s policies and procedures and government regulations.​</li>\n<li>Ensure branch receives a satisfactory rating on internal audits.​</li>\n<li>Supervise branch daily activities and staff to ensure operating losses are minimized.​</li>\n<li>Attend required monthly/​quarterly operations meeting with Retail Support Department and inform branch manager and branch employees of the up-to-date policies, procedures, and system applications.​&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Assist branch manager in allocating manpower and other resources, and to analyze activities of the branch to develop optimum efficiency and productivity in the operation processes and customer service.​</li>\n<li>Support branch manager to maintain operating, personnel, and other expense within budget.​</li>\n<li>Provide recommendations for improvement of branch operations.​</li>\n<li>Ensure that the branch premises are secure and branch assets are protected.​</li>\n<li>Ensure branch appearance is maintained in accordance with Bank standards.​</li>\n<li>Ensure all branch staff successfully complete all mandatory training assigned in a timely manner.​</li>\n<li>Coach the branch staff on operating procedures, customer service, technical and product knowledge.​</li>\n<li>Supervise branch staff to ensure the branch exceeds customer expectations in terms of accuracy, efficiency, courtesy and professionalism.​</li>\n<li>Ensure that customer problems and complaints are managed professionally and effectively, responded to in a timely manner and maintained at a minimum level.​</li>\n<li>Meet with current and potential customers, to discuss their financial requirements; sell appropriate consumer and commercial financial services products to meet their needs while developing and expanding account relationships.​</li>\n<li>Identify cross-sell opportunities, including opportunities to refer customers to other sales representatives (CRE, C&amp;I, PCM, MLO, Primevest) through proper customer profiling and needs-based selling.​</li>\n<li>Open deposit accounts on bank&rsquo;s system ensuring all documentation requirements, policies and procedures are adhered to.​</li>\n<li>Actively participate in all bank&rsquo;s sales campaigns and promotions and exceed targets set.​</li>\n<li>Maintain superior and courteous service to promote products and expand customer relationships.​</li>\n<li>Exceed customer expectations in terms of speed, efficiency, certainty and professionalism.​</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Identify and understand basic customer needs in order to complete transactions with accuracy speed, efficiency and certainty.​</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Qualification &amp; Pre-requisites</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>5+ ​ years of customer services experience in the branch banking industry or related environment, which including 3+​ years of branch operations experience is preferable.​</li>\n<li>Thorough knowledge of Branch Banking-related information technology.​</li>\n<li>Thorough knowledge of banking regulations and procedures.​</li>\n<li>Knowledge of financial reports, branch banking operations, branch efficiency and productivity, audit procedures, and Bank&rsquo;s laws and regulations in operation areas.​</li>\n<li>Strong communication and inter-personal skills.​</li>\n<li>Basic PC skills and Microsoft Word and Excel competency.​</li>\n<li>Fluent in English and <strong>Chinese</strong> (mandarin preferred) a major plus.​</li>\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in business or related field is required.​</li>\n</ul>', 'http://jobview.monster.com/Branch-Operation-Manager-Job-Los-Angeles-CA-US-132224070.aspx', '', 5, 59, 2),
(309, 1396386327, 'Market Development Chinese Bilingual', 'Pasona', 'Marketing', 'Montvale, NJ, United States', 'United States', 'New Jersey', 'Montvale', 41.046764, -74.022919, '美国', '新泽西州', 'Montvale', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>SUMMARY</strong></p>\n<p>To ensure that the company achieves established sales and sponsoring goals each month through accomplishing the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>&nbsp;The primary contact person between the company and independent sales consultants and leaders.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Responsible for meeting assigned company targets for sales and sponsoring on a monthly basis.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Daily &amp; weekly contact with independent sales consultants and assigned field leaders.</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Responsible for tracking, motivating and supporting assigned field leaders in order for them to meet their monthly sales &amp; sponsoring goals.</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Must be resourceful and support the field with product and business knowledge. Establish a professional relationship with the field to provide full support for each leader to expand/grow their business.</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Responsible for providing feedback, comments and any issues from the field to the company management for better understanding of the market.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>REQUIREMENTS/QUALIFICATIONS:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>&nbsp;Have an interest in cosmetics and beauty products.</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Confident in making presentations to large groups</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Ability to make sound decisions in a manner consistent with the essential job functions and company policy.</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Computer software: Microsoft Word, Excel, Power Point, Lotus Notes, Internet</li>\n<li>&nbsp;High-level people skills, professionalism, and management skills in order to be an efficient business manager for consultants and leaders.</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Constant self-education including reading books, materials, articles on beauty, MLM and the direct selling industry publications.</l