(312, 1396388963, 'Program Coordinator', 'Sheng-Yen Lu Foundation 卢胜彦佈施基金会', 'Service', 'Bellevue, WA, United States', 'United States', 'Washington', 'Bellevue', 47.610378, -122.200676, '美国', '华盛顿', '贝尔维尤', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>Scope of Work</strong></p>\n<p>SYL Foundation is looking for an energetic self-starter with the ability to adapt to the needs of a young organization. The program coordinator will create and operate a new scholarship program and will work closely with the President to monitor existing grants. The program coordinator will also assist with communications activities to promote Foundation program objectives and increase awareness of the organization''s work.</p>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Identify specific areas of scholarship need, then create, launch, and operate a scholarship program that is consistent with the Foundation''s mission.</li>\n<li>Provide scholarship program updates to SYL Foundation board of directors.</li>\n<li>Attend site visits to observe and report on funded grant programs.</li>\n<li>Attend grant recipient events, which may occur during the evening or weekend.</li>\n<li>Assist with creation and update of communications materials such as newsletters, annual reports, brochures, website, and occasional items in connection with events.</li>\n<li>Maintain and update the Foundation''s social media.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>NOTE: The duties listed above are intended only as illustrations of the various types of work that may be performed. The omission of a specific statement of duties does not exclude them from the position if the work is similar, related, or a logical assignment to the position.</p>\n<p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor''s degree in a related field or equivalent.</li>\n<li>Two years of relevant professional experience or equivalent.</li>\n<li>Scholarship management experience is preferred.</li>\n<li>Fluency (speaking and writing) in Mandarin Chinese is preferred.</