(332, 1397107710, '人力资源经理', 'Panda Express', 'Management', 'Rosemead, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Rosemead', 34.080566, -118.072845, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '柔似蜜', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><strong>Descriptions:<br /></strong>&bull;&nbsp;Develops and implements positive workforce practices and strategies in collaboration with Operations leaders and HR.&nbsp; Aligns practices and strategies with the company&rsquo;s Mission, Values, Culture as well as desired work environment and business goals.<br />&bull;&nbsp;Responds to and Investigates associate or guest complaints related to associate relations issues, such as discrimination, harassment, wage and hour laws, or unfair treatment.&nbsp; Maintains accurate records in compliance with company procedures and recommends actions to be taken. <br />&bull;&nbsp;Resolves associate relations concerns following federal and state laws and company policies through effective interaction with associates and Operations leaders.&nbsp; Ensures consistency with company policies.<br />&bull;&nbsp;Prepares formal written responses and supporting documentation related to any associate relations charges (e.g., discrimination, harassment, etc.) as required from within the company and from external agencies.&nbsp; Prepares for EEO hearings and mediations and assists in negotiating settlements.<br />&bull;&nbsp;Reviews and investigates all requests for suspension, corrective action, and termination to ensure requested action complies with company policy.</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-family: Arial;"><br /></span>&nbsp;</p>\n<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.d872917e337.row1" class="contentlinepanel" title="">\n<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.d872917e339.row1" class="inlinepanel" style="display: inline;" title=""><span class="subtitle">Qualifications</span></div>\n<span class="blockpanel"><span>&nbsp;</span></span>\n<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><strong><span style="font-family: Arial;">JOB REQUIREMENTS:</span></strong></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-family: Arial;">&bull;&nbsp;Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in HR or related field required; recruiting experience preferred <br />&bull;&nbsp;Minimum five years of experience in HR handling associate relations issues, preferably in a retail/hospitality operations environment<br />&bull;&nbsp;Must be available for alternative work week schedules, including weekends and non-business hours<br />&bull;&nbsp;Successful completion of annual store training.</span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><strong><span style="font-family: Arial;">KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS, AND ABILITIES:</span></strong></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-family: Arial;">&bull;&nbsp;Ability to demonstrate and teach Panda&rsquo;s Mission, Values, and Culture<br />&bull;&nbsp;Comprehensive knowledge of local, state, and federal laws and regulations pertaining to employment (i.e., discrimination and harassment, wage and hour, etc.)<br />&bull;&nbsp;Strong analytical and research skills <br />&bull;&nbsp;Computer proficiency, including Microsoft Office Suite<br />&bull;&nbsp;Ability to prepare investigation reports and related written documentation<br />&bull;&nbsp;Ability to effectively communicate the values of the organization and to exemplify the highest level of interpersonal skills<br />&bull;&nbsp;Strong communication, listening, presentation, writing, and assessment skills<br />&bull;&nbsp;Ability to work effectively with Operations leadership, providing guidance on company policies and practices related to associate relations <br />&bull;&nbsp;Ability to embrace change and continuous learning</span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-family: Arial;">&bull;&nbsp;Office conditions; flexible work schedule, including weekends and non-business hours; occasional travel to stores</span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-family: Arial;">Panda Restaurant Group&rsquo;s culture is strongly guided by our Mission and Values, highlighted on the Panda websites.&nbsp; We recommend all interested candidates become familiar with our Mission and Values, as well as the principles of The Seven Habits of Highly Effective People, by Stephen Covey.</span></p>\n</div>', 'https://pandarg.taleo.net/careersection/panda+corporate/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=13000226', '', 5, 96, 2),
(333, 1397108151, 'Contract Music Content Editor (Mainland China Specialist) ', 'Gracenote', 'Entertainment', 'Emeryville, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Emeryville', 37.831318, -122.285248, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '爱莫利维尔', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>At Gracenote, we live and breathe music. Gracenote&rsquo;s products and services power products from Apple, Amazon, BMW, Sony, and others. We''re the company behind many innovative music and video products.&nbsp;<br /><br />Our Music Content team is made of up real music experts with a deep knowledge of regional music trends and genres. As part of this team, the content editor will ensure that album and artist metadata are of highest quality. Daily responsibilities include applying independent judgment to target, prioritize, create, review and correct music-related data elements according to established standards and practices. The editor will also be responsible for analyzing internal reports, and tracking various internal and external popularity measures to ensure and improve data quality, content coverage and product performance.&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>JOB REQUIREMENTS&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Comprehensive knowledge of music that is relevant in mainland China with demonstrated expertise in one or more major genres, including detailed subgenres;</li>\n<li>Excellent English writing, editing and verbal communication skills</li>\n<li>Fluency in Mandarin Chinese, literacy in Simplified Chinese</li>\n<li>Excellent basic computer skills (Microsoft Word, Excel, etc.), especially experience working with large amounts of data</li>\n<li>In-depth research skills</li>\n<li>Knowledgeable about database operations and data access methods, including MS Access, MySQL, etc</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Must be detail-oriented, and show familiarity with data-standardization policies and techniques, styles guides, and/or normalization routines</li>\n<li>Able to work independently, with little or no direct supervision, surfacing problems or issues for approval as necessary</li>\n<li>Able to establish, communicate, and follow agreed upon project priorities</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>QUALIFICATIONS&nbsp;</strong><br /><br />B.A. or B.S. in relevant field, or equivalent related experience&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>PLUSES&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Literacy in Traditional Chinese</li>\n<li>Familiarity with other Chinese dialects (esp. any dialects of Wu, Min, Hakka, or Yue)</li>\n<li>Familiarity with schemes for Romanization of Chinese, especially pinyin</li>\n<li>Strong understanding of Chinese internet structure and culture with an eye to research</li>\n<li>Any practical knowledge of SQL and relational databases</li>\n<li>Previous experience in a music technology, music retail, music industry or related media industry job</li>\n</ul>', 'http://ch.tbe.taleo.net/CH01/ats/careers/requisition.jsp?org=GRACENOTE&cws=1&rid=399&source=Indeed.com', '', 373, 85, 2),
(334, 1397108230, 'China Energy Analyst', 'Eurasia Group', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.714352, -74.005974, '美国', '纽约州', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Eurasia Group is seeking an experienced and motivated analyst of Chinese politics and energy policy.<br /> <br /> Candidates are expected to have:<br /> <br /> &bull;A strong understanding of China''s political system and economy, along with geopolitics-- with particular expertise regarding China''s role in global energy markets.<br /> <br /> &bull;The ability to analyze specific sectors of the Chinese economy.<br /> <br /> &bull;The ability to produce in-depth research and forward-looking policy analysis.<br /> <br /> &bull;Excellent analytical and presentation (oral and written) skills in a succinct style at native English standard.<br /> <br /> &bull;Commitment and ability to deliver on tight deadlines.<br /> <br /> &bull;<strong>Reading, writing, and speaking fluency in both English and Chinese</strong>.<br /> <br /> &bull;Familiarity and experience with managing and coordinating complex research projects.<br /> <br /> Requirements include:<br /> <br /> &bull;A minimum of 3-5 years of professional experience in a relevant field connected to producing policy analysis and/or consulting work for the private sector.<br /> <br /> &bull;An advanced degree in political science, regional studies, economics, or another relevant discipline.<br /> <br /> &bull;Extensive knowledge of China''s energy sector and dynamics in the global energy markets.<br /> <br /> &bull;Significant in-country experience.<br /> <br /> Applications from more experienced candidates are welcome.<br /> <br /> Applicants will be considered for the firm''s Washington, London, or New York offices. All applicants must be eligible to work in either the United States or the United Kingdom.<br /> <br /> To apply for the position, please submit resume, cover letter and salary requirements (MS Word, Plain Text or PDF only) in a single document by following the instructions below. This position is available immediately. The resume evaluation process will take place on an on-going basis until the position has been filled.</p>', 'http://www.eurasiagroup.net/careers/view/analyst_china_energy_washington', '', 5, 126, 2),
(335, 1397108995, '中文技术建筑师', 'Skidmore, Owings & Merrill LLP', 'Engineering', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '旧金山', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div id="job_details_ats_requisition_description" class="cell_input   dhtml_editor_render ">\n<p><span style="font-size: small;"><strong>Primary Responsibilities: <br /></strong>&bull; Contribute to the detailed preparation of design and construction documents on assigned projects <br /> &bull; Assist with finding solutions to general architectural problems <br /> &bull; Perform work on project segments, <strong>incl. technical specification and drawing document translation from Mandarin into English and from English into Mandarin</strong> <br /> &bull; Communicate with Design Institutes and Consultants to resolve code compliance, technical and coordination issues <br /> &bull; Check and coordinate details and dimensions <br /> &bull; Review selective shop drawings and samples <br /> &bull; Coordinates work with the project team <br /> &bull; Assist in the preparation of punchlists and field observation reports <br /></span></p>\n</div>\n<div class="cell_label">&nbsp;</div>\n<p><strong><span style="font-size: small;">Background and skillset:</span></strong></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">&bull; Completion of five or six-year architectural degree program or graduate of four-year program <br /> &bull; Minimum of 3 years experience in preparation of construction documents and design development <br /> &bull; Ability to speak, read, write and type fluently in Mandarin Chinese and English. <br /> &bull; Demonstrated general knowledge of building materials, detailing, construction techniques related engineering principles and building codes <br /> &bull; Demonstrated proficiency in AutoCAD (including AutoCAD 2008) <br /> &bull; Previous experience working for an American firm doing business with companies in the People''s Republic of China strongly preferred <br /> &bull; Willingness to take initiatives and responsibility in team projects <br /> &bull; Strong command of Microsoft Office programs <br /> &bull; Excellent communication skills </span></p>', 'https://som.hua.hrsmart.com/hr/ats/Posting/view/449', '', 5, 70, 2),
(336, 1397109624, ' Dealer’s Assistant', 'Pace Gallery', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.714352, -74.005974, '美国', '纽约州', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Pace Gallery is seeking a Dealer&rsquo;s Assistant to directly support a Director by managing all communication, administrative tasks, handling all pre- and post-sales and exhibition-related activities.<br /><br />Responsibilities <br /><br />&bull; Provide all administrative and personal support to Dealer.<br />&bull; Manage all incoming calls and correspondance<br />&bull; Maintain and organize daily schedule<br />&bull; Serve as a liaison to artists and clients <br />&bull; Work closely with Registrar for all sales, consignments, loans and exhibition-related activities including arranging client viewings handling pre- and post-sales activities. <br /><br />Qualifications<br /><br />&bull; BA Degree required, Art History or related degree. <br />&bull; 2-3 years&rsquo; experience within the art world.<br />&bull; <strong>Fluent in MANDARIN</strong><br />&bull; Must have strong knowledge of the gallery world and of modern and contemporary art.<br />&bull; Must be extremely well presented, polished, professional and articulate. <br />&bull; Must have ability to effectively interact with and gain the confidence of clients, artists and internal staff.<br />&bull; Strong computer skills including Microsoft Word, Excel, Outlook.</p>', '', 'jobs@pacegallery.com', 5, 141, 2),
(337, 1397179501, 'Project Manager Assistance', 'Erco Interior Systems', 'Management', 'Glassboro, NJ, United States', 'United States', 'New Jersey', 'Glassboro', 39.702892, -75.111839, '美国', '新泽西州', '葛拉斯堡罗', 'H1B', 'Full Time', '<div class="WB_text">【工作机会/Galssboro, NJ】&nbsp; Erco Interior Systems招聘Inside Office Estimator/Project Manager Assistance. E-verify. 现有内推机会，感兴趣的同学请发送简历(并注明现住址和薪金要求)</div>', '', 'kobe.p@ercoonline.com', 5, 219, 2),
(338, 1397328192, 'Global Customer Service Wizard', 'Omaze', 'Service', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', 'Carson', 'None', 'Part Time', '<div class="WB_text">【洛杉矶】Omaze招聘Global Customer Service Wizard（Part Time）。需要会说中文（还能同时说日文和韩文的最好），主要负责邮件沟通，网络社区互动等。有客服经验，熟悉Zen Desk 是plus。每小时$10-$20。申请邮件主题请写Omaze Global Customer Service Wizard</div>', '', 'careers@omaze.com', 5, 92, 2),
(339, 1398720851, 'China Overnight Reporter', 'Bloomberg News', 'Media', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.714352, -74.005974, '美国', '纽约州', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>The Role:<br />Bloomberg News is seeking a reporter to cover late breaking news from China. This position will be based in New York, working standard hours in New York, and focus on monitoring for and reporting on developments involving Chinese companies, government agencies and financial institutions during the U.S. day.<br /><br />Candidates must be fluent in Chinese, have experience in quickly assessing the importance of breaking news and be able to stay abreast of developments across various industries and markets in China. The reporter should be flexible, calm under pressure, a quick learner and excel in a team environment. Knowledge of China''s economy, its companies and markets is preferred.<br /><br /><strong>Qualifications:</strong><br />- Bachelor''s degree or equivalent experience<br />- Minimum of 3 years of experience in financial journalism<br />- Strong news judgment; the ability to recognize news that is significant to markets and investors<br />- Fluency in English, Mandarin Chinese and <strong>Simplified Chinese</strong> script are mandatory; <strong>other Chinese language skills are a plus</strong><br />- Experience working in a real-time news environment is highly desirable</p>', 'http://jobs.bloomberg.com/job/New-York-China-Overnight-Reporter-Job-NY/55226900/', '', 5, 497, 2),
(340, 1397366108, '画廊暑期实习', 'Crossing Art Gallery', 'Art', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.714352, -74.005974, '美国', '纽约州', '纽约', 'None', 'Internship', '<p>Crossing Art Gallery, a dynamic international contemporary art gallery located in Queens, NY is currently seeking highly motivated, organized, and enthusiastic interns to assist with all aspects of gallery operations. <br /> <br /> RESPONSIBILITIES: <br /> &bull; Assist with general administrative tasks and gallery operations<br /> &bull; Work on research projects <br /> &bull; Assist gallery staff in preparing for new exhibitions <br /> &bull; Update inventory and client database <br /> &bull; Maintain artist press, archives and mailings<br /> &bull; Assist with social media <br /> &bull; Light art handling <br /> <br /> REQUIREMENTS:<br /> Although previous gallery experience is not required, candidates should have a demonstrated interest in and commitment to contemporary art. A background in art history is highly recommended. Proficiency with Adobe Creative Suite and Microsoft Office is required. Knowledge of gallery database systems such as Filemaker Pro is a plus. Candidate must possess strong interpersonal skills, and be comfortable interacting with clients, press, and gallery visitors. Must be highly organized, detail-oriented, professional, and have the ability to multitask.<br /> <br /> Candidates with a strong art history background and excellent writing skills will have additional opportunities to work on specific projects. <br /> <br /> Knowledge of Korean or <strong>Mandarin is preferred</strong> but not required <br /> <br /> Candidates should be able to commit 2-3 days per week for 3 months and be able to attend openings. <br /> <br /> Position to start in early June and run through August. <br /> <br /> A small stipend is provided and school credit can be arranged.</p>', 'http://www.barefootstudent.com/new_york/jobs/internship/summer_gallery_internship_168576', '', 5, 164, 2),
(341, 1397366327, 'District Sales Manager', '熙可集团', 'Marketing', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.714352, -74.005974, '美国', '纽约州', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>Job overview</strong><br /><br />The District Sales Manager is responsible to achieve business targets (both strategic and fiscal) selling Company products through appropriate distributors and distribution channels; developing and managing the channel programs associated with these types of channel partners and developing and/or executing marketing actions to support targeted sales.<br /><br /><strong>Core responsibilities:</strong><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Run channel programs &ndash; develop, understand,support and deliver program goals and objectives. Report, track and execute programs.&nbsp; Execute segment programs supported by customer and consumer feedback on evolution of the category.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform distributor/channel partner volume target reviews on a quarterly basis and jointly manage in-store sampling and other point of sale promotional programs to effectively drive sales volume and optimize profitability.&nbsp; Achieve or exceed goals through setting up best practice standards for all channel partners which are aligned with corporate objectives<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work with channel partner &ldquo;Inside Sales Executives&rdquo; to deliver shared objectives and perform target and objective setting for the entire team across all channels.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work with Company R&amp;D and technical group and local training resources to ensure adequate product and program knowledge within the channel partners.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform regular review of partner plans with Account Executives to ensure that named partners fully understand and are bought into Company technology and solutions.<br /><br /><strong>Desired Skills and Experience</strong><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Minimum 5 years sales and account management experience within the FMCG food industry.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A career which demonstrates ability and a thorough understanding of the drivers of a growing dynamic business in an ever changing market.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A good understanding of operating and financial budgeting and reporting and the ability to complete financial evaluations and feasibility studies.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Previous sales and business development experience in North America in the FMCG industry<br /><br /></p>', '', 'Vivian.faria@hudson.com', 5, 96, 2),
(342, 1397369284, 'Bilingual Product Engineer', 'Media Vision', 'Engineering', 'Oakland, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Oakland', 37.804363, -122.271111, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '奥克兰', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Media Vision is a seeking reliable BilingualProduct Engineer&nbsp;with a strong technical background and a familiarity with the AV industry. The&nbsp;Product Engineer&nbsp;will be responsible for communication with the technical teams of current and potential clients as well as internal team members and the factory on specific technical issues. The successful candidate will speak/write <strong>Mandarin Chinese</strong> and will be able to communicate effectively with the team.</p>', '', 'alissa@media-vision.com', 5, 88, 2),
(343, 1397369620, '中文Educational Consultant', '啄木鸟国际教育咨询', 'Consulting', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', 'Carson', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><span class="summary"><strong>Essential duties and Responsibilities:</strong><br /> Provide an overall application plan; mentor students on a one-on-one basis in the application process, and ensure the applications quality and completion <br />Brainstorm essay topics, and design individual plans for students based on their interests and background. <br />Provide college application and interview strategy, as well as information concerning the visa application <br />Be familiar with top universities and their departments <br /><br /> <strong>Salary :</strong> 20 0000 - 30 0000 RMB per year <br /><br /> <strong>Location :</strong> Beijing, Shanghai, Xiamen, Guangzhou, Shenzhen, Wuhan, Nanjing, Guiyang, Kunming, Chengdu, Dalian, Shenyang, Xi''an, Taiyuan, Changchun, Zhengzhou <br />In addition to educational consultants, we offer the following positions: SAT and TOEFL instructor, marketing specialist, national and international activity planner </span></p>', '', 'overseahr@zmnedu.com', 5, 270, 2),
(344, 1397456713, 'International Store Operations Associate', 'Forever 21', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', 'Carson', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>Department Summary:&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /> Forever 21 is seeking an innovative, energetic, and passionate team player to add to our dynamic&nbsp;Operations team.<br /> <br /> <strong>Job Purpose</strong>: <br /> The International Operations Associate will assist Regional/District Managers in monitoring sales generation, operational, and personnel functions for Forever 21 international stores in the assigned region to ensure customer satisfaction, profitability, business growth, and compliance with company procedures. <br /> <br /> <strong>Deliverables:</strong><br /> &bull;&nbsp;Partner with International Regional/District Store Managers and field Operations personnel to communicate all business performance/sales goals, customer satisfaction expectations and to understand the needs of each region<br /> &bull;&nbsp;Communicate with Store, District and Regional Mangers, as well as internal stakeholders such as IT and Accounting, to gather necessary data to produce performance reports from<br /> &bull;&nbsp;Collaborate with the Regional Manager to understand business best-practices in the region and suggest any business changes/adjustments that could be made to better position Forever 21 in the market <br /> &bull;&nbsp;Partner with the International Regional Manager is assessing the motivational needs of the region&rsquo;s store employees, assisting with employee engagement initiatives <br /> &bull;&nbsp;Serve as a resource for International Regional, District and Store Managers for any questions or issues related to company or industry best-practices<br /> &bull;&nbsp;Communicate with store employees within the region to identify and resolve employee concerns; gather feedback and ensure that any customer-related issues in the region are addressed <br /> &bull;&nbsp;Work with in-country Human Resources personnel to resolve any employment or labor related issues <br /> &bull;&nbsp;Act as a point-of-contact for regional communication, information requests, management conferences/meetings and community events<br /> <br /> <strong>Knowledge, Skills, and Qualifications:</strong> <br /> &bull;&nbsp;Must have a High School diploma or equivalent; Associate or Bachelor&rsquo;s degree is a plus<br /> &bull;&nbsp;Must speak, read and write <strong>Mandarin and Cantonese</strong> <br /> &bull;&nbsp;Must have 1-2 years of previous experience in an administrative/support role, preferably in a corporate retail environment<br /> &bull;&nbsp;Previous retail experience is required<br /> &bull;&nbsp;Must have advanced skills in Microsoft Office Word, Excel, PowerPoint and Outlook <br /> &bull;&nbsp;Excellent organizational and time-management skills<br /> &bull;&nbsp;Ability to prioritize workloads and manage time effectively<br /> &bull;&nbsp;Excellent written and verbal communication skills<br /> &bull;&nbsp;Attention to detail and ability to handle multiple tasks in a fast-paced environment <br /> &bull;&nbsp;Ability to develop effective business relationships with all levels; strong customer service skills</p>\n<p>At Forever 21, style isn&rsquo;t dictated&hellip;It&rsquo;s inspired. Forever 21 is the leading fashion retailer of the latest trends and the season&rsquo;s hottest styles at can&rsquo;t-resist-prices. U.S. and international locations stay true to the fast-fashion destination&rsquo;s iconic store aesthetic giving fashion fans all over the globe the unforgettable shopping experience that is the one and only Forever 21.<br /> <br /> Joining the Forever 21 family means joining an incredible team of talented, passionate and innovative people who work together to bring fashion to everyone, everywhere.&nbsp; We&rsquo;re always on the lookout for talented individuals eager to thrive in our fast-paced, dynamic environment filled with vast opportunities for career growth and development. This is a place where your ideas become actualized, creativity is encouraged and the possibilities are endless. Be part of something epic. Be part of Forever 21. Apply today!</p>', 'https://forever21.tms.hrdepartment.com/cgi-bin/a/highlightjob.cgi?jobid=12856', '', 5, 143, 2),
(345, 1397457034, '兰蔻中文美容顾问', '欧莱雅', 'Marketing', 'City of Industry, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'City of Industry', 34.019733, -117.958672, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '因达斯特里', 'None', 'Part Time', '<div>\n<p>Lancome Beauty Advisor Part Time- City of Industry</p>\n<p><strong>Fluency in Chinese (Mandarin or Cantonese) is highly desirable.</strong></p>\n<p>Lancome is the #1 luxury global beauty brand that delivers luxurious service and innovative products to women all over the world. Beauty Advisors are the ambassadors of the brand. As a Beauty Advisor, in a retail store environment, you will advise, coach, and help women fulfill their expressed beauty image.</p>\n<p><strong>Specific Responsibilities</strong>:&bull; Greet customers in a welcoming and timely manner&bull; Communicate effectively with clients by asking questions and listening attentively&bull; Recommend and inspire others to try our products through product demonstrations&bull; Take initiative to ensure client satisfaction&bull; Strengthen relationships with clients by following-up, recommending new products and inviting them to promotional events&bull; Work independently and as a team to achieve sales goals&bull; Become a Brand advocate and product expert&bull; Stay current on the latest beauty products and trends&bull; Maintain a clean and professional counter by stocking inventory, creating displays, merchandising, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Job Qualifications:</strong>&bull; Customer service-oriented&bull; Outstanding communication and interpersonal skills&bull; Sales experience&bull; Ability to build and maintain relationships with clients and peers&bull; Motivated by challenge and thrives working in a goal-oriented, fast-paced environment.</p>\n</div>', 'http://talentdesk.com/job/44845/loreal/lancme-beauty-advisor-part-time-fluency-in-chinese-mandarin-or-cantonese', '', 5, 164, 2),
(346, 1397534170, '人力资源', '网易', 'Management', 'Guangzhou, Guangdong, China', 'China', 'Guangdong', 'Guangzhou', 23.129164, 113.264435, '中国', '广东省', '广州', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>#国内机会#好机会，绝对不可多得！网易游戏这种油水满满的地方招聘Hr了！要求英文优秀，有长期留学背景，或者有专八资格。有意者请联系： 学传媒的小伙伴们不妨试试！</p>', '', 'gzliusiqi@corp.netease.com', 5, 126, 2),
