(371, 1398097528, 'Chemist - R&I, Global Talent Program, China', '欧莱雅', 'Engineering', 'Clark, NJ, United States', 'United States', 'New Jersey', 'Clark', 40.627804, -74.312759, '美国', '新泽西州', '克拉克', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>L&rsquo;Or&eacute;al was established in 1909 by visionary scientist, Eugene Schueller, and is committed to progressive research and development, state-of-the-art manufacturing, quality products, and making beauty accessible to everyone around the world. L&rsquo;Oreal is the #1 beauty company in the world investing approximately 3.3% of its consolidated sales into its world-wide research facilities while filing 600+ patents and launching over 500 new products each year. Our Research and Innovation team pushes the boundaries of science to invent and perfect innovative, high performance cosmetic products to meet the diverse needs of men and women all over the world. <br /><br />Through our L&rsquo;Oreal R&amp;I Global Talent Program we are committed to recruit outstanding scientific talent to help us reach even greater heights in our Research &amp; Innovation center in China. If you are currently a Chinese student completing graduate research studies in the USA with at least two years of relevant research experience you could be eligible. The components of the program are: <br /><br /><strong>Option 1</strong>: You will be required to commit to: &middot; Start in the US for an assignment from 6 and up to 12 months maximum during your OPT period. &middot; During the time in the US, you are placed in a Formulation Lab or Applied Research Lab (Skin Care, Hair Care, Hair Color, Color Cosmetics or Fragrance) to learn procedures, raw materials, systems, &amp; processes. &middot; At the end of the US assignment, you will be assigned back to China for a local full-time opportunity. <br /><br /><strong>Option 2</strong>: &middot; You will be assigned directly in China to an open position. <br /><br /><strong>REQUIREMENTS</strong>: <br />&middot; Masters or PhD degree in Chemistry (Physical, Polymer, Organic, Analytical), BioChemistry, Materials Science completed between December 2013 or June 2014 &middot; Previous internship experience a must <br />&middot; Post-doc experience or two years relevant research experience a plus <br />&middot; Demonstrated leadership and project management skills <br />&middot; Must be creative, analytical and have excellent communication/interpersonal skills <br />&middot; Must have a desire to work in a fast-paced, dynamic and challenging work environment and possess strong computer skills <br />&middot; <strong>Must be fully bilingual (English/Mandarin) written and spoken</strong> <br />&middot; An eye for color and a passion for art and science <br />&middot; Geographical flexibility and openness to international assignments are a must <br />&middot; Interested candidates must agree to relocation to China post-graduation or within end of employment assignment in the USA <br />&middot; <strong>Must be an F1 Visa holder</strong><br /><br /></p>', 'https://careers.peopleclick.com/careerscp/client_thebodyshop/loreal_ext/jobDetails.do?functionName=getJobDetail&jobPostId=70270&localeCode=en-us', '', 5, 160, 2),
(373, 1398143680, '中英文客服', '去旅游网', 'Service', 'Monterey Park, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Monterey Park', 34.062511, -118.122849, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '蒙特利公园', 'None', 'Part Time', '<p><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman''; font-size: 16px; color: #222222;">We have an immediate opening for Customer Service Representative part-time position in our fast-paced&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman''; font-size: 16px; color: #222222;">office. The ideal candidate will have excellent customer service, effective communication skills, and the ability to multitask in a fast paced environment.</span><br style="color: #222222; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; font-size: 16px;" /><br style="color: #222222; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; font-size: 16px;" /><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman''; font-size: 16px; color: #222222;">Job Description:</span><br style="color: #222222; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; font-size: 16px;" /><br style="color: #222222; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; font-size: 16px;" /><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman''; font-size: 16px; color: #222222;">- This position is responsible to assist customers with all phases of their travel arrangements. The individual will be required to respond to customer''s inquiries over the phone, email and live-chat in a courteous manner.&nbsp;</span><br style="color: #222222; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; font-size: 16px;" /><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman''; font-size: 16px; color: #222222;">- Confirm bookings with the tour operators and notify travelers any updates with their itinerary in a timely fashion.</span><br style="color: #222222; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; font-size: 16px;" /><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman''; font-size: 16px; color: #222222;">- Maintain a close relationship with the service providers and solve any issues related to the booking process.</span><br style="color: #222222; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; font-size: 16px;" /><br style="color: #222222; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; font-size: 16px;" /><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman''; font-size: 16px; color: #222222;">Job Requirements:</span><br style="color: #222222; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; font-size: 16px;" /><br style="color: #222222; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; font-size: 16px;" /><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman''; font-size: 16px; color: #222222;">- Associate Degree or higher education;</span><br style="color: #222222; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; font-size: 16px;" /><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman''; font-size: 16px; color: #222222;">- Must be able to speak, read and write fluently in both English and <strong>Chinese</strong>;</span><br style="color: #222222; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; font-size: 16px;" /><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman''; font-size: 16px; color: #222222;">- Must be able to commit to a work shift from 9:00am to 6:00pm (PST) 1:00pm to 6:00pm (PST), and work on one day on weekends/holidays occasionally;</span><br style="color: #222222; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; font-size: 16px;" /><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman''; font-size: 16px; color: #222222;">- Experience in the travel industry is a plus.</span></p>', '', 'jobs@gotobus.com', 5, 186, 2),
(374, 1398144657, '学术辅导部门经理', '加州留学网', 'Management', 'El Monte, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'El Monte', 34.068623, -118.027565, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '艾尔蒙地', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><span class="postbody">加州留学网是一家立足于加州，年轻，富有朝气的创业型公司。在此行业已有五年的稳定发展，加州留学网一直秉持着以客户为本，尽力维持客户的最高满意度为原则；以引领新的留学风潮，打造全新留学体验为宗旨。现由于业务扩张，聘请 学术部项目经理／留学顾问<br /></span></p>\n<p><span class="postbody">Responsibilities:<br />1. 负责与客户沟通，了解客户需求。<br />2. 负责学术部学业部项目发展计划制定及管理<br />3. 负责审核，包装并递交客户材料。<br />4.按时认真完成上级交代的任务。<br />5.工作时间周一至周五，按时完成份内工作。<br /></span></p>\n<p><span class="postbody">Benefits:<br />1. 试用期短，底薪优，具体面议。<br />2. 公司推行年轻态管理环境，可以自由发挥您的特长。<br /></span></p>\n<p><span class="postbody">Requirements:<br />1. 专业不限，硕士以上学历。<br />2.熟悉了解美国大学教育体系环境，了解课业辅导，utor教学等，相关从业者优先考虑。<br />3.熟练操作PPT，Word, Excel等办公软件。<br />4.有良好的沟通技巧，客户服务经验，中英文流利 ，有责任心，耐心。<br />5. 吃苦耐劳，工作效率高，并且细心谨慎。<br />6. 良好的团队合作<br /><br /></span></p>', '', 'info@liuxuetime.com', 5, 139, 2),
(375, 1398145653, '网站开发', '长岛商学院', 'Technology', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.714352, -74.005974, '美国', '纽约州', '纽约', 'H1B', 'Full Time', '<div class="WB_text">【招聘公告】长岛商学院创校于1968年，通过美国独立院校ACICS认证，是美国纽约州教育部门核准颁发副学士学位的两年制独立大学。现招一名全职Web Developer，要求有相关工作经验，会流利中英文。学校待遇优渥，符合要求者，帮助申请免名额的H1B工作签证，有意者请发简历至 HR@libi.edu。</div>', '', 'HR@libi.edu', 5, 200, 2),
