(418, 1401713242, '高科技专业销售', 'Shanghai Optics', 'Marketing', 'Clark, NJ, United States', 'United States', 'New Jersey', 'Clark', 40.627804, -74.312759, '美国', '新泽西州', '克拉克', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>一生难得的机会</strong>，新州中部Clark 高科技光学公司销售部, 有前途和发展机会，公司业务持续增长，诚聘专业销售加入团队。办公室环境佳，薪优（底薪+佣金+奖金），年假，年底分红。无技术背景或专业要求，公司提供训练，需要1-2年的工作经验，好学肯做，熟电脑，英文好（口语和书面，日常工作是通过电话和邮件和客人沟通），有销售经验优先考虑。新州本地应聘者优先考虑，也欢迎有意定居新泽西的申请人</p>\n<p>中国公司总部53年历史，北美销售总部13年历史，专为全世界高科技公司定制高端紫外，可见，红外各个波段镜头和显微目镜。公司提供各种成像产品，以满足不同工业，药业，军事，科技研究的需求。提供广泛系列的工业相机，投影，远心、变焦、定焦以及微型视等成像镜头，并提供专业光学设计，用于修改、测试及校准成像系统的产品，包括测试目标板及成像滤光片和各类光学零件，同时也提供成像配件以及提高功能性的适配器。</p>\n<p><strong>有兴趣的人士请email</strong><strong>简历 <a href="mailto:hr@shanghai-optics.com">hr@shanghai-optics.com</a></strong></p>', 'http://www.shanghai-optics.com', 'hr@shanghai-optics.com', 618, 264, 2),
(419, 1401713234, '销售助理', 'Shanghai Optics', 'Marketing', 'Clark, NJ, United States', 'United States', 'New Jersey', 'Clark', 40.627804, -74.312759, '美国', '新泽西州', '克拉克', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>高科技光学公司，中国总部已经有53年历史，北美销售总部已有13年历史。有前途和发展机会，业务稳定，薪优，有年假，年底分红。<br /> <br /> 无经验要求！好学肯做，熟电脑，英文好。<br /> <br /> 新州本地应聘者优先考虑，也欢迎有意定居新泽西的申请人。</p>', 'http://www.Shanghai-optics.com', 'hr@shanghai-optics.com', 618, 261, 2),
(420, 1398702465, '会计', 'Michael Chen, CPA', 'Finance', 'Alhambra, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Alhambra', 34.095287, -118.127014, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '阿罕布拉', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div id="jobwrapper">\n<div id="jobcopy">\n<div id="jobBodyContent"><span id="TrackingJobBody">ACCOUNTANT: Review personal and business financial records and prepare periodic financial statements, income tax returns, payroll tax returns &amp; summaries for client''s financial position; interpret US and State Tax Law and regulations to clients in Mandarin or Cantonese; provide bookkeeping training. </span></div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><span id="TrackingJobBody">Req: Bachelor focus on Accounting + exp. w / "Quickbook," "Taxact," "Lacerte," &amp; "Laserfiche;" bilingual in English, <strong>Mandarin and Cantonese</strong>. $5,093/mo. </span></div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><span id="TrackingJobBody">Job &amp; Interview: Alhambra, CA. </span></div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><span id="TrackingJobBody">Contact: Michael Chen, Michael Chen, CPA, A Professional Accountancy Corporation, 33 E. Valley Blvd., Ste. 217, Alhambra, CA 91801</span></div>\n</div>\n</div>', '', 'michaelchencpa@hotmail.com', 44, 159, 2),
(422, 1398703421, 'Component Engineer', 'GoPro', 'Engineering', 'San Mateo, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Mateo', 37.562992, -122.325523, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '圣马特奥', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div>GoPro is seeking a top tier candidate for the Component Engineer role. As Component Engineer you will have responsibility for identifying, qualifying, documenting and releasing components from a variety of commodities for our line of products. This position will provide support to engineering and operations by providing specification review and ensuring the accuracy of our PLM system. You will be responsible for finding alternate sourcing and tracking component qualification. In addition you will be responsible for coordinating, evaluating and tracking all component PCNs and FA reports, implementing corrective actions and assessing the risk to projects.</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div>In this fast paced and dynamic organization it will be necessary for you to drive the component selection process and perform your work in a consultative manner as the subject matter expert. The position requires strong communication skills in an individual that is self-directed and capable of meeting aggressive schedules. Must possess exceptional organizational skills and be capable of managing several projects in parallel.&nbsp;</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div><strong>Responsibilities</strong></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Identifying, qualifying, documenting and releasing components from a variety of commodities for our line of products</li>\n<li>Support engineering and operations by providing specification review and assisting in the qualification of second sources</li>\n<li>Coordinate component failure analysis with component manufacturers</li>\n<li>Responsible for coordinating, evaluating and tracking all component PCNs and FA reports, implementing corrective actions and assessing the risk to projects</li>\n<li>Reviewing all components released to our PLM system for accuracy and working with our manufacturing partners to ensure accurate synchronization with GoPro&rsquo;s PLM system&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Recommend up-screening, if required, to qualify device to a more rigorous environment than original device specification.</li>\n<li>Recommend alternative part if specified part is unavailable or if it cannot be made to meet requirement</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div><strong>Requirements</strong></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>BSEE, MSEE</li>\n<li>5+ years relevant experience as a Component Engineer</li>\n<li>Must be capable of coordinating cross-functionally with internal teams and ODMs/CMs to resolve issues pertaining to component selection and use</li>\n<li>Must have understanding of the fundamentals of electrical testing and the use of tools and test equipment (e.g. supplies/generators, meters, signal analyzers, logic analyzers, oscilloscopes, etc.)</li>\n<li>Should be knowledgeable on a wide range of semiconductor components including analog ICs, digital ICs, memory, timing devices, and microprocessors</li>\n<li>Complete understanding and working knowledge of engineering documentation (e.g. schematics, component data sheets, footprints, RoHS, etc.) and standard document control practices (e.g. ECRs, ECOs, MCOs, Deviations, etc.)</li>\n<li>Strong problem solving skills</li>\n<li>Ability to interface effectively across organizational and geographic boundaries</li>\n<li>Excellent communication skills, both written and oral</li>\n<li>Strong interpersonal and planning skills</li>\n<li>Highly proficient with Excel and related Microsoft Products</li>\n<li>Experience working with Arena or Agile PLM</li>\n<li>Fluent in English</li>\n<li>(Desired) <strong>Fluent in Mandarin</strong></li>\n</ul>', 'http://gopro.com/careers/?gnk=job&gni=8acda1104096878a0140c600d8ee77ec', '', 5, 95, 2),
(423, 1398720159, 'Associate (人民币业务)', '汇丰银行', 'Finance', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.705631, -73.978004, '美国', '纽约州', NULL, 'None', 'Full Time', '<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1598.row1" class="contentlinepanel" title="">\n<p><span style="font-family: Verdana;"><strong>Overview</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">The RMB Initiative has been established as a group-wide strategic priority for HSBC.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">With the goal of becoming the leading international bank for RMB services in the Americas, Senior Management has recently given ultimate responsibility to the CF COO and Business Development team to lead this front for both Banking &amp; Capital Financing, across the continent.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">As the RMB Initiative in the Americas continues to grow in importance and scope, there is a need for a dedicated junior support to help lead the day-to-day articulation, coordination and execution of the China-related business development strategy in the region. This position is key to help avoid the risk of losing a front-runner position to win RMB business, as well as ensuring we establish the necessary management framework and equip RMs with the tools necessary to succeed in an increasingly competitive environment.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<div><span style="font-family: Verdana;"><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></span></div>\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Development of China-related business</span>\n<ul>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Support new RMB-specific business opportunities &ndash;particularly those connected to new trial zones, regulations and product solutions</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Conduct a comprehensive market-sizing study, with the ultimate goal of identifying both existing and new clients with the largest overall RMB opportunities and specific scenarios with each</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Pursue opening of relevant regional desks with Banking Multis team in Shanghai, and determine appropriate set up (i.e., one Americas desk, NAM/LAM desks, US or Brazil desks, etc.)</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Develop a comprehensive strategy to extract synergies and expand the US$460M of existing revenue being generated from Americas clients in China and Chinese satellites (especially Hong Kong) and US$30M of exiting Chinese inbound revenues</span></li>\n<li>\n<p>Help ensure Americas&rsquo; participation in broader RMB Internationalization Strategy, interacting on a daily basis with colleagues in London and HBCN</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Potentially participate in client-facing interactions &ndash;once competency is fully establishes- that RMs can leverage&nbsp; Take a client-facing role in select meetings where appropriate</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Management and execution of the RMB Initiative</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>&nbsp;Create an Americas RMB committee of appropriate stakeholders that meets at appropriate intervals and act as secretary to drive agenda towards productive sessions and meaningful output</li>\n<li>Establish strong relationships with RMB teams in mainland China and other offshore centres, chiefly Hong Kong</li>\n<li>Produce MI that adequately tracks overall progress on growing RMB revenues, as well as specific opportunities that have been identified and signed-up to</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Education, Communication and Marketing</span></li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Keep abreast of relevant China related news for the Americas client base, leveraging such information to drive specific incremental revenue opportunities and disseminating to bankers as appropriate</li>\n<li>Coordinate external and internal RMB related events, ensuring high engagement and high impact through careful planning and preparation</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Leverage and modify existing training materials, as well as supplement with new materials as necessary, to empower RMs to pitch RMB business to clients with knowledge and credibility</span></li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1656.row1" class="contentlinepanel" title="">\n<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1672.row1" class="inlinepanel" title=""><span class="subtitle">Qualifications</span></div>\n<span class="blockpanel">&nbsp;</span>\n<p><span style="font-family: Verdana;"><strong>Essential Experience</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Post-graduate or experienced hire career opportunity</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Demonstrable 3-5 years of relevant work experience necessary</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Post-graduate degree in general management / business / finance from a top international program &nbsp;highly desirable</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Previous work experience in a client-facing or strategy role in the financial services industry or a top-consulting firm also highly desirable</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Familiarity of working in a client-facing role or product team facing Chinese customers strongly preferable</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">An understanding of the Chinese economy, its financial sector and related regulatory change also preferable&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Previous experience working with HSBC -particularly in GBM- considered a plus</span></li>\n<li><strong><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Proficiency in Mandarin essential</span></strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span style="font-family: Verdana;"><strong>Essential Skills/Competencies</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Strategic mind-set</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Superior interpersonal ability, and ability to influence outcomes without formal authority&nbsp;</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Strong verbal/presentation and written communication skills</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Ability to win support and interact diplomatically with a diverse group of senior stakeholders and business partners</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Analytical ability and attention to detail</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Track record of &nbsp;working independently and proven ability to prioritise work under pressure</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Flexibility and pragmatism to cope with abrupt changes to plans</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Willingness and interest to travel occasionally outside of their main work location</span></li>\n</ul>\n</div>', 'https://hsbc.taleo.net/careersection/external/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en_GB&job=263226', '', 5, 267, 2),
(424, 1398721096, 'Contract Chinese Editor', 'CORESTAFF Services', 'Language', 'Seattle, WA, United States', 'United States', 'Washington', 'Seattle', 47.606209, -122.332069, '美国', '华盛顿', '西雅图', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>CORESTAFF&nbsp;Services&nbsp;is&nbsp;seeking&nbsp;a&nbsp;contract&nbsp;Editor&nbsp;for&nbsp;a&nbsp;long&nbsp;term&nbsp;contract&nbsp;positions<br />for&nbsp;a&nbsp;large&nbsp;internet&nbsp;client&nbsp;located&nbsp;in&nbsp;downtown&nbsp;Seattle.&nbsp;You&nbsp;must&nbsp;be&nbsp;proficient&nbsp;in<br />applying&nbsp;DITA&nbsp;structure&nbsp;to&nbsp;documentation&nbsp;and&nbsp;have&nbsp;a&nbsp;background&nbsp;in&nbsp;technical&nbsp;writing,<br />editing,&nbsp;and&nbsp;information&nbsp;design.&nbsp;You&nbsp;will&nbsp;be&nbsp;working&nbsp;with&nbsp;complex&nbsp;content&nbsp;sets<br />involving&nbsp;conditions&nbsp;and&nbsp;multiple&nbsp;output&nbsp;destinations,&nbsp;reviewing/editing&nbsp;content<br />produced&nbsp;by&nbsp;others,&nbsp;and&nbsp;providing&nbsp;education&nbsp;and&nbsp;mentoring&nbsp;on&nbsp;our&nbsp;new&nbsp;XML/CMS<br />authoring&nbsp;environment.&nbsp;This&nbsp;is&nbsp;a&nbsp;3&nbsp;month&nbsp;contract&nbsp;paying&nbsp;up&nbsp;to&nbsp;$27/hr.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>&shy;Fluent&nbsp;Chinese&nbsp;language&nbsp;skills&nbsp;required</li>\n<li>DITA</li>\n<li>XML</li>\n<li>Strong&nbsp;time&nbsp;management&nbsp;skills</li>\n<li>Strong&nbsp;communication&nbsp;skills&shy;</li>\n</ul>', 'https://ess.impellam.com/job/JO000007926', '', 5, 205, 2),
(425, 1398721690, 'Entry Level IT/Marketing Position', 'iGavel Auctions', 'Marketing', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.705631, -73.978004, '美国', '纽约州', NULL, 'None', 'Full Time', '<div id="Content" class="centered Content">\n<div class="Classifieds">\n<div id="ClassifiedsContent">\n<div class="ListingPage">\n<div class="Description">Seeking an entry-level college graduate for a position working with the IT and marketing departments for a premier fine art and antiques auction house.</div>\n<div class="Description">&nbsp;</div>\n<div class="Description">Duties include:<br /><br />&bull; Updating and maintaining various web presences, including auction content<br />&bull; Client relations and technical support for buyers and sellers<br />&bull; Graphic design for advertising and marketing purposes<br />&bull; IT/Systems support for a Mac-based office and Filemaker database system<br /><br />A high degree of knowledge of HTML/CSS, Photoshop and InDesign a must. PHP/Javascript, Applescript, and Filemaker a plus. This position will report to the Director of Media and Technology. Computer Science, Marketing, Graphic Design, or Art History degree preferred. Must be a hard and versatile worker. Experience with auction houses, art galleries, or direct client relations a plus. <strong>Chinese speaking (Mandarin or Cantonese) a plus</strong>.</div>\n<div class="DescriptionLabel">&nbsp;</div>\n<div class="DescriptionLabel">Application Instructions</div>\n<div class="Description">Please email with a cover letter, a copy of your resume, and two references</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', '', 'customerrelations@igavelauctions.com', 5, 199, 2),
(426, 1398721983, '寻纽约地区影评人作专访', 'MatCH独立电影协会', 'Entertainment', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.705631, -73.978004, '美国', '纽约州', NULL, 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="WB_text">[寻纽约地区影评人作专访]&nbsp;</div>\n<div class="WB_text">最好是有評過英雄片，对此类题材熟悉. 例如鋼鐵俠，變形金剛之類的. 请高大上的影评人联系我们</div>', 'http://t.cn/8sTxlHi', 'filmsociety@chinus.org', 5, 132, 2);
INSERT INTO `post` (`id`, `timestamp`, `jobtitle`, `company`, `industry`, `user_entered_location`, `country`, `state`, `city`, `latitude`, `longitude`, `country_cn`, `state_cn`, `city_cn`, `sponsor`, `employment_type`, `description`, `link`, `email`, `owner`, `clicks`, `status`) VALUES
(427, 1398788734, 'LAX Premium Services Concierge Representative（必须会中文）', 'American Airline', 'Service', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', 'Carson', 'None', 'Part Time', '<div align="center"><strong><span style="color: #ff0000;"><em>American Airlines is seeking candidates for part-time<br />Premium Services Concierge Representative (Mandarin Speaker Required) to work at Los Angeles International Airport.<br />Comprehensive Benefit Package provided and airline travel privileges at an hourly rate of $15.67 USD for the first thirty (30) days and $10.91 USD thereafter.<br /></em></span></strong></div>\n<p><strong><span style="color: #ff0000;"><em>&nbsp;</em></span></strong></p>\n<div class="large-12 columns nopadding description-body">\n<div>The Premium Services Concierge Representative provides superior hospitality, excellent customer service, extensive ticketing and problem resolution for our premium guests in all areas covered by the Premium Services department including Admirals Club, Flagship/Premium Lounges, ConciergeKey, Five Star and Executive Center locations. &nbsp;Will also be responsible for in-house Concierge Services. &nbsp;Acts as the "Face" of American Airlines and&nbsp;<strong>one</strong>world products.&nbsp; While working in all areas of Premium Services which includes, but is not limited to Admirals Clubs, Premiums Lounges and ConciergeKey/Five Star, provides enhanced, extraordinary services in a positive, enthusiastic, courteous and friendly manner to any visiting member or guest. &nbsp;Will perform comprehensive domestic and international ticketing functions, day of and future date ticketing. &nbsp;Manage guest needs during off-schedule operations, including reroute travel itineraries.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Concierge Services will assist guests/customers with destination features, special events, restaurant recommendations, cars, hotels and sightseeing. &nbsp;Proactively assists guests/customers utilizing mobile technology on concourse and within lounges. &nbsp;Provide assistance with operational functions in all areas of Premium Services and work closely with Customer Services, Sales and Marketing. &nbsp;Utilize successful customer service techniques by listening and showing interest with guest''s concerns and/or needs and taking the initiative to proactively prevent customer service failures and be observant for service deficiencies. &nbsp;Promote Admirals Club/American services and products to members and guests. &nbsp;Remain current on all departmental and applicable AA products, services, features and marketing promotions with ability to speak to value of benefits while identifying potential new business involving corporate and leisure guests and refer leads to sales and/or marketing. &nbsp;Be well-versed in entire suite of Small Medium Enterprise (SME) products to demonstrate knowledge and identify leads for follow-up.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Expertise in JointBusiness and&nbsp;<strong>one</strong>world airline policies, procedures with ability to assist customers with policies and benefits in order to proactively develop local relationships to provide assistance to customers of JointBusiness partner airlines and&nbsp;<strong>one</strong>world airline.&nbsp; Participates regularly with various internal departments helping to support and deliver their goals and initiatives. &nbsp;Engages in required and rigorous hospitality and service training. &nbsp;At Executive Center locations may make conference room bookings and performs all Executive Center duties, including assistance with airline transactions.</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n<div class="large-12 columns nopadding qualifications-header">\n<h2 class="large-title">Qualifications</h2>\n</div>\n<div class="large-12 columns nopadding qualifications-body">\n<ul>\n<li>Mandarin Speaker Required (will be tested)</li>\n<li>High School diploma or GED</li>\n<li>Must be able to read, write, fluently speak and understand the English language</li>\n<li>Bilingual language skills required in some locations</li>\n<li>Sabre proficiency preferred</li>\n<li>Prior field experience preferred</li>\n<li>Prior customer hospitality experience required</li>\n<li>Must be well-groomed with a professional appearance</li>\n<li>Strong organizational and administrative skills required</li>\n<li>Excellent salesmanship skills/interpersonal skills with ability to interact effectively with all levels of management and public contact</li>\n<li>Ability to work under pressure, handle a multitude of projects concurrently while paying close attention to detail and customer service</li>\n<li>Actively demonstrate extraordinary customer service and customer engagement in an environment of hospitality</li>\n<li>Ability to assume various passenger services duties and functions within the realm of Premium Services Rep tour of duty - including but not limited to ATO, ticket lift, baggage services, Customer Services Manager</li>\n<li>Bar service preferred</li>\n<li>PC experience preferred</li>\n<li>Required to complete a variety of administrative reports detailing club sales, liquor controls, budget tracking</li>\n<li>Ability to work irregular and/or extended hours, including weekends and holidays</li>\n<li>Must fulfill FAA criminal background checks to qualify for unescorted access privileges to airport security identification display areas (SIDA)</li>\n<li>Must be able to secure appropriate airport authority and/or US Customs security badges</li>\n<li>Must report to work on a regular and timely basis</li>\n</ul>\n</div>', 'http://careers.aa.com/en/ac/jobpost/4671', '', 5, 292, 2),
(428, 1398788840, '客服代表', 'East West Bank', 'Finance', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', 'Carson', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="7">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="bodytext">\n<p>East West Bank is seeking a Full Time Customer Service Representative (CSR). The Customer Service Representative must be able to perform in a fast-paced, high volume capacity with face-to-face interaction with customers in a banking center. The CSR is the frontline representative who processes transactions and introduces bank&rsquo;s products/services at the teller line.</p>\n<p><br /><strong>Duties include, but are not limited to:</strong></p>\n<span class="bodytext"><span class="bodytext"><br /></span></span><br />\n<ul>\n<li>Cashing checks, processing deposits, withdrawals, transfers and loan payments&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Documenting larger deposits using Currency Transaction Reports&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Identifying and selling East West Bank products and services beneficial to customer needs&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Addressing customer questions/concerns referring to appropriate internal resources for resolution&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Identifying fraudulent activity to prevent potential losses to the Bank&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Developing new customer relationships and opening new accounts for customers</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="7">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="largeheaders">Job Requirements</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Qualifications/Requirements:</strong></p>\n<span class="bodytext"><span class="bodytext"><br /></span></span><br />\n<ul>\n<li>At least 6 months of recent customer service experience &lsquo;&nbsp;</li>\n<li>At least 6 months of recent cash handling experience&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Bilingual Mandarin and Cantonese preferred&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Previous teller and new accounts experience in a banking institution a plus&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Excellent customer service skills&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Proficiency in Word and Excel&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Must have reliable transportation&nbsp;</li>\n<li>High School Diploma required or equivalent, Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree preferred</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'http://www.careerbuilder.com/jobseeker/jobs/jobdetails.aspx?Job_DID=J3H5FX74ZPGYQJVR7H5', '', 5, 146, 2),
(429, 1398788955, 'Project Architect', 'amphibianArc', 'Engineering', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', 'Carson', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>amphibianArc, founded in 1992, represents a philosophy of design and architecture that is informed by the idea of evolution in the formation of human spirit and habitation. amphibianArc has been designed a wide range of projects in both the U.S. and China.</p>\n<p>Our Los Angeles office is seeking a Project Architect with 10+ years experience primarily in commercial, retail, and/or institutional work.&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Prior working experience in China and proficiency in Mandarin is preferred</strong>, but not required.&nbsp; Candidates should have:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>An MArch or BArch from an accredited architectural program</li>\n<li>Excellent design skills, and the ability to convey ideas well in various media</li>\n<li>Strong communication, organizational and collaborative skills</li>\n<li>Excellent Autocad knowledge, BIM proficiency desired</li>\n<li>Managed relevant projects through all phases of design and construction administration</li>\n<li>Ability to work in a fast-paced and rigorous environment&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Qualified candidates should submit a cover letter, resume, portfolio samples, and salary requirements, stating the applicant&rsquo;s role in each project to&nbsp;<a href="mailto:jobs@amphibianarc.com" target="_blank">jobs@amphibianarc.com</a>. Please reference "Project Architect &ndash; Los Angeles" in the subject line of your e-mail. Submission to be in A SINGLE PDF DOCUMENT, NO MORE THAN 10MB. Only applicants that meet the qualifications will be contacted.&nbsp;</p>', 'http://archinect.com/jobs/entry/98855841/project-architect', 'jobs@amphibianarc.com', 5, 115, 2),
(430, 1398789789, 'Event Sales Associate', 'UBMAsia', 'Marketing', 'Manhasset, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'Manhasset', 40.797878, -73.699577, '美国', '纽约州', '曼哈西特', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div>\n<p>UBMAsia serves the needs of US companies to gain access to the Asia Market, as either a supplier to these markets or as a buyer of Asian goods. Apart from serving the jewelry trade, including the largest Int&rsquo;l jewelry fairs in Asia (twice a year in HK, three times a year in China), once in Japan, twice in Macau, three fashion jewelry fairs in Hong Kong, Asia&rsquo;s Fashion Jewelry Review. UBM Asia&rsquo;s New York office also serves the vast health industry, including the leading Japan health &amp; beauty fairs, Sign China &amp; Cashmere World.</p>\n<p>This position works with the Sales Manager to generate new sales revenue for the trade shows (mainly Jewelry industry) organized by UBM Asia while maintaining follow up on the existing customers.</p>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p><strong>UBM, LLC, is a subsidiary of UBM, PLC,&nbsp;</strong>a global events-led marketing and communications services business. We help organizations make connections, communicate their proposition and do business effectively. We help professional people in more than 30 countries around the world succeed by enabling them to connect with each other and with the markets they serve. And we do this by whatever means works best &ndash; at live events, through digital media or in publications.</p>\n<p><strong>Our 5,500 expert staff</strong>&nbsp;are deeply embedded in the many specialist communities we serve, bringing both an unusual depth of understanding and real know-how. We organize hundreds of live events each year and provide a range of related market-leading digital and print marketing and media products, and we support professional marketers and communicators through our targeting, distribution and monitoring services.</p>\n<p><strong>Our culture of innovation and collaboration</strong>&nbsp;brings our people together around common interests to create value, enhancing our ability to do exactly the same for UBM customers and the communities UBM serves. So, whatever their business and wherever they operate, our customers do better business through us.</p>\n</div>\n<div>\n<ul>\n<li>Prospecting and identifying new customers (exhibitors, advertisers &amp; visitors) by cold-calling and going out on sales trips, and customer visits at trade shows and clients&rsquo; offices</li>\n<li>Responsible for booking space for the trade shows and Advertisement spaces in all show publications and Websites</li>\n<li>Assisting the Sales Manager as well as working independently on finalizing sales contracts/agreements and providing service to visitors</li>\n<li>Following up with existing clients and maintaining recurring business in order to build up the business by &lsquo;up sale&rsquo; from existing revenue.</li>\n<li>Organizing sales leads and providing close follow ups. Also must be able to close sales and collect payment within the given deadlines</li>\n<li>Attending trade shows for prospecting new customers &amp; promoting the fair name by distribution of show information booth by booth. Also helping to set up/tear down our own booth on the set up day and at closing of the show.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Business Acumen &ndash; Ability to learn and understand the trade show business and develop key relationships with customers.</li>\n<li>Customer focus &ndash; Very customer oriented so that business relationships are developed as a win/win situation for customers and UBM Asia. Must be professional &amp; proactive to the customer&rsquo;s needs while keeping in mind the company&rsquo;s business objectives.</li>\n<li>Excellent written and verbal communication skills &ndash; Ability to maintain good record keeping and organization.</li>\n<li>Initiative - Ability to provide business-value suggestions that can improve efficiency or revenue for the business. Willingness to contribute creative ideas.</li>\n<li>Leadership &ndash; Ability to learn the business and work independently on work assigned on a timely basis. Should be able to handle multiple assignments, be deadline oriented and able to work under pressure.</li>\n<li>People Development &ndash; A true team player that is willing to help colleagues to be successful through collaborative efforts, creative thinking, and completing a project or helping a visitor on little things.</li>\n<li>Sales Abilities &ndash; Ability to develop good relationships with existing clients for recurring business, cold calling for new business development, and sales forecasting (periodic projections of business objectives versus goal). Able to expand business by prospecting new clients and opportunities and Closing sales.</li>\n<li>B.A. or B.S. and proven sales experience a must</li>\n<li><strong>Fluency in Mandarin or Cantonese preferred**</strong></li>\n<li>Good computer skills using Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint). Also some knowledge of Customer contact system (i.e. ACT or Access)</li>\n<li>Proven sales abilities working with customers</li>\n</ul>\n</div>', 'https://hiring.accolo.com/jobs/Manhasset/New_York/Event_Sales_Associate/330133222/job.htm', '', 5, 166, 2),
