(466, 1402511601, 'Branch Manager', 'Union Bank', 'Finance', 'San Marino, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Marino', 34.121395, -118.106461, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '圣玛利诺', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1661.row1" class="contentlinepanel" title="">\n<p><strong>Position Summary</strong></p>\n<p>Responsible for all management of activities in a branch office.&nbsp; Manage staff to achieve the mission, vision, and values of the Bank, along with Bank strategic objectives and Branch specific sales and profitability goals.&nbsp; Ensures adherence to Bank policy and procedures by all Branch personnel.</p>\n<p>Depending on office/market location, the Branch Manager may be assigned specialty customer segments such as Priority, Cash and Save etc.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;<br />5+ years in retail bank management.<br />Excellent communications skills, both verbal and written.<br />High energy level, and proven track record in managed sales process.<br />Demonstrated business development success.<br /><strong>Candidates fluent in Cantonese or Mandarin are highly preferred.</strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />This position may be subject to SAFE Act Registration Requirements.&nbsp; Pursuant to the SAFE Act requirements, all applicants for employment who will be engaged in residential loan mortgage originations (as defined by the SAFE Act) must register with the federal registry system and maintain a status in good standing under the SAFE Act requirements.&nbsp; If at any time the Bank determines that your position requires SAFE Act registration, you will be required to register and submit to the required SAFE Act background check and registration process.&nbsp; Failure to register successfully or to maintain a status in good standing under the SAFE Act will affect your eligibility for continued employment and may result in your immediate termination.<br />&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;<br />We are committed to leveraging the diverse backgrounds, perspectives and experiences of our workforce to create opportunities for our people and our business. Equal Opportunity Employer Minority/Female/Disability/Veterans.<br />&nbsp;</p>\n</div>', 'https://uboc.taleo.net/careersection/10000/jobdetail.ftl?job=455074', '', 5, 127, 2),
(468, 1402591233, 'Patient Assistant', 'New York Methodist Hospital', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.705631, -73.978004, '美国', '纽约州', NULL, 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>In this role, the Medical Assistant will Assist Physicians, Physician Assistants &amp; RN''s in all aspects of patient flow while maintaining a high quality of patient care in a compassionate and humane manner. This includes, but is not limited to greeting patients, retrieving and filing charts, completing forms, preparing and recording laboratory specimens; ordering clinical, pharmaceutical and laboratory supplies. Taking vital signs (height, weight temperature, pulse, and blood pressure.&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>REQUIREMENTS:&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>High School Diploma or Equivalency required.</li>\n<li><strong>Must be Bi-lingual Chinese- Cantonese / English&nbsp;</strong><br /><br />Medical Assistant certificate.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Excellent communication, customer service and computer skills.</li>\n<li>Excellent attendance and punctuality record. Flexibility, highly developed interpersonal skills, and a comfort level in a fast-paced area of the hospital is key for the position.</li>\n</ul>', 'https://www.healthcaresource.com/nyp/index.cfm?fuseaction=search.jobDetails&template=dsp_job_details.cfm&cJobId=893049', '', 5, 86, 2),
(469, 1402591413, 'Sales Representative - MarketPoint', 'Humana', 'Marketing', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.705631, -73.978004, '美国', '纽约州', NULL, 'None', 'Full Time', '<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.d101687e326.row1" class="contentlinepanel" title="">\n<div>We&rsquo;re looking for associates who are dedicated to service and believe in following the Golden Rule of treating others the way you want to be treated. Humana was founded on this premise, and this value is reflected in our expectations for providing perfect service to our consumers, providers, employers, agents and others we work with.&nbsp;&nbsp; At Humana, Perfect Service&reg; means getting the basics done right, delivering value and quality, and providing everyone with personalized attention and guidance. We want to engage with our members through every step of their journey to lifelong well-being.&nbsp; This includes meaningful direct consumer interaction and developing positive relationships with healthcare providers. Humana associates provide Perfect Service every day to our members, employers, providers, and colleagues. We&rsquo;re looking for people who improve their own well-being by looking out for the best interests of others.</div>\n<div><strong>&nbsp;</strong></div>\n<div><strong>Assignment Capsule</strong></div>\n<div>Be a part of the Humana Sales Team -- build relationships and deliver customer-focused solutions that meet the needs of the customer.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Humana is seeking a Sales Representative to sell MarketPoint and Medicare services and products, and build relationships with Humana&rsquo;s customers and external business partners.</div>\n<ul type="disc">\n<li>Prospect and enroll eligible individuals in the Medicare Advantage Private Fee for Service (PFFS), Medicare PPO and HMO plans</li>\n<li>Market long-term care, life insurance, and other specialty products for the 50+ population</li>\n<li>Conduct one-on-one and group presentations for potential customers</li>\n<li>Generate sales leads from various sources</li>\n</ul>\n<div><strong>Key Competencies</strong></div>\n<ul type="disc">\n<li><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Accountability:</span></strong><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>Meets established expectations and takes responsibility for achieving results; encourages others to do the same.</li>\n<li><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Builds Trust:&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></strong>Consistently models and inspires high levels of integrity, lives up to commitments, and&nbsp; takes responsibility for the impact of one''s actions.</li>\n<li><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Customer Focus:</span></strong><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>Connects meaningfully with customers to build emotional engagement and customer advocacy.&nbsp; Simplifies complexity and integrates internal efforts to deliver an optimal customer experience.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Pursues Excellence:</span></strong><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>Seeks out learning, strives to develop and expand personally, and continuously helps others upgrade their capability to contribute to Humana.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class="staticcontentlinepanel"><span class="inline">&nbsp;</span></div>\n<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.d101687e336.row1" class="contentlinepanel" title="">\n<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.d101687e338.row1" class="inlinepanel" title=""><span class="subtitle">Qualifications</span></div>\n<span class="blockpanel"><span>&nbsp;</span></span>\n<div><strong>Role Essentials</strong></div>\n<ul type="disc">\n<li>High School Diploma</li>\n<li>Health &amp; Life Insurance Licenses</li>\n<li>AHIP Certification (or the ability to pass prior to hire date)&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Valid Driver&rsquo;s License</li>\n</ul>\n<div><strong>Role Desirables</strong></div>\n<ul type="disc">\n<li>Associate&rsquo;s or Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree</li>\n<li>Previous experience with health and life insurance, long-term care and/or annuity products</li>\n<li>Valid securities license</li>\n<li>Bi-lingual in English and Mandarin</li>\n</ul>\n<div><strong>Reporting Relationships</strong></div>\n<ul type="disc">\n<li>You will report to a Sales Manager. This area is under the leadership of the SVP &amp; Chief Operating Officer.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>', 'https://humana.taleo.net/careersection/externalus/jobdetail.ftl?job=686941', '', 5, 90, 2),
(467, 1402591113, 'English/Chinese Project/Account manager', 'Multilingual Group, Inc', 'Language', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.705631, -73.978004, '美国', '纽约州', NULL, 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>The project/account manager will work in a team environment where the main responsibility will be to follow projects from beginning to end. This includes receiving jobs, assigning the project accordingly, providing quotes and invoicing. Additionally, the project manager will maintain communication with linguists and proofreaders to ensure the projects meet specifications and requirements. This is an entry level position.</p>\n<p>Job Duties include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Developing strong client relationships through excellent communication skills</li>\n<li>Ability to create timelines and create project specifications</li>\n<li>Editing documents by using desktop publishing tools</li>\n<li>Prepare purchase orders, quotes and invoices</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Must read and write English/Chinese (Traditional)</li>\n<li>Ability to multi-task, meet tight deadlines and attention to detail</li>\n<li>Strong organizational skills</li>\n<li>Excellent writing and oral communication skills</li>\n<li>0-2+ years Project management experience</li>\n<li>Knowledge of Microsoft Office, Adobe Acrobat and Trados a plus</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If interested in this position, kindly email your resume and cover letter with salary requirements</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=e15c8c5b3b24256e&q=chinese&l=New+York,+NY&tk=18q7o6hdd069g5ln&from=ja&alid=0ac784b61d4fb51b&utm_source=jobseeker_emails&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=job_alerts', '', 5, 139, 2),
(470, 1402591607, 'Business Process Analyst', 'Collabera', 'Management', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.705631, -73.978004, '美国', '纽约州', NULL, 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="insidebox-row">\n<h3 class="col-sm-12"><span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblDescription">Description</span></h3>\n<div class="col-sm-12"><span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblDescription"><strong>Bilingual - Mandarin</strong> or Arabic&nbsp;<br />Strong document management skills; experience with documenting process maps/workflows<br /><br />The ideal candidate will be able to:&nbsp;<br />&bull; Identify requirements using interviews, analysis, workshops, surveys, business process descriptions, use cases, task and workflow analysis.<br />&bull; Critically analyze and evaluate data/information gathered from multiple sources, and reconcile/address conflicts.<br />&bull; Conduct independent analysis, and reviews requirements utilizing knowledge of alternatives, business systems, and functional requirements.<br />&bull; Drive creation, definition, and documentation of business requirements and functional specifications.<br />&bull; Analyze high-level information requirements and information flows.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Manage and create &lsquo;bottom up&rsquo; Work Breakdown Structure for Business Analysis tasks, and provide tasks and schedule in project plans.<br /><br />The ideal candidate should possess:&nbsp;<br />&bull; An understanding of project administration activities&nbsp;<br />&bull; Strong document management skills; experience with documenting process maps/workflows<br /><br />Responsibilities include but are not limited to:&nbsp;<br />&bull; Track Change Control impact assessments&nbsp;<br />&bull; Maintain project terms of reference, charters, definitions etc.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Current State Assessment&nbsp;<br />&bull; Process Mapping&nbsp;<br />&bull; Maintain various project &amp; program documents&nbsp;<br />&bull; Document management&nbsp;<br />&bull; Assist in the development and maintenance of project plans and project communications</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class="insidebox-row">\n<div class="col-sm-12">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n<div class="insidebox-row">\n<h3 class="col-sm-12">REQUIREMENTS</h3>\n</div>\n<div class="insidebox-row">\n<div class="col-sm-12">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n<div class="insidebox-row">\n<div class="col-sm-2"><strong>Experience</strong></div>\n<div class="col-sm-10"><span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblExp">5 - 7 years</span></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n<div id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_trContactDetails">&nbsp;</div>', '', 'samuel.suryawanshi@collabera.com', 5, 181, 2),
(471, 1402594188, '手机销售', 'Diamond Wireless (法拉盛)', 'Marketing', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.705631, -73.978004, '美国', '纽约州', NULL, 'None', 'Full Time', '<div><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></div>\n<div>As a Wireless Sales Consultant for Diamond, you will sell and service both new and existing Verizon customers &ndash;&nbsp;</div>\n<div>ensuring that their needs are met and that our standards of operation are consistently upheld. This role is truly that of&nbsp;</div>\n<div>a consultant, as you will be offering service support as well as technical assistance, as needed.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;Additional responsibilities for the Wireless Sales Consultant include:</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Keeping the store clean and organized&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Ensuring that merchandise is fully stocked&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Assisting with returns, exchanges, etc.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Performing inventory counts&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Managing the cash drawer&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Preparing bank deposits&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div><strong>Requirements&nbsp;</strong></div>\n<div>As a Wireless Sales Consultant for Diamond Wireless, you must stay abreast of new technological developments in</div>\n<div>the industry. You must also be computer literate, understanding how to run Windows applications, navigate the&nbsp;</div>\n<div>internet and efficiently use Microsoft Office programs. POS System experience is a plus.</div>\n<div>Additional requirements of the Wireless Sales Consultant include:</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>High School diploma; some college experience, a plus&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Ability to stand for extended periods of time&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>Bilingual Mandarin</strong></li>\n</ul>', 'http://newton.newtonsoftware.com/career/JobIntroduction.action?id=8a5814f644f21364014500704a6e339a', '', 5, 131, 2),
(472, 1402595375, 'Administrative Puchasing Assistant', 'Seville Classics', 'Management', 'Torrance, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Torrance', 33.835850, -118.340630, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '托伦斯', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p>-&nbsp;Bachelor''s degree required</p>\n<p>- Bilingual (English &amp; Chinese) required (ability to speak Chinese a definite must)<br />- A successful candidate will have a strong knowledge of or interest in purchasing<br />-&nbsp;Strong computer skills&nbsp;and proficient in MS Word and Excel</p>\n<p>- Ability to influence others through excellent written/verbal communications, negotiation skills and strong multitasking capability<br />-Strong time management skills<br />- Ability to work effectively independently and in a team environment<br />- Import&nbsp;experience a definite&nbsp;plus, but not required<br />- Wholesale/Retail industry experience a plus, but not required<br />- Experience in a manufacturing environment a plus, but not required<br />- Proven to be number and detail orientated, and&nbsp;candidate must be improvement driven.<br />- Strong people management and interpersonal skills&nbsp;<br />- Smart, organized, attention to detail, and great attitude a MUST!<br /><br /><br /></p>\n<p><strong>Job Description</strong>:<br />Seeking full-time Administrative Purchasing&nbsp;Assistant<strong>.</strong>&nbsp;Working out of our International Headquarters in Torrance, California. Responsibilities include:<br /><br />- Assisting with the management of the planning, purchasing,<br />- Assisting in the development of a comprehensive item/product database (currently lacking within the company)<br />- Obtaining quotes and negotiating pricing, delivery, and other terms with our key Asian suppliers/factories and recommending specific suppliers that meet or exceed cost, quality, and delivery requirements.<br />- Interacting with all departments within the company and improving the department, with a focus on cost savings and minimizing total procurement costs.<br />- Highly credible and professional interface with company&rsquo;s key suppliers/factories and capitalizing on their internal design expertise in pursuit of most cost effective design solutions.<br />- Placing orders and maintaining and monitoring appropriate inventory levels.<br />- This position highly supports sourcing, product development, and sales.<br /><br /><br /><a name="OLE_LINK1"></a><strong>Compensation</strong><strong>:</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />- Salary (negotiable)<br />- Annual Bonus (depends on performance)<br />- Health Insurance</p>\n<p>- 401(k)<br />- Sick leave</p>\n<p>- Vacation days</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Company Profile</strong>:<br />Seville Classics, Inc. is a well-established International Manufacturing &amp; Import Company of Consumer Products that has been in business for over 25 years. Our annual sales are in excess of $100 million, and we sell our products to the world&rsquo;s major retailers both in the U.S. and abroad. Our focus has been to bring innovative products to homes and businesses while providing the best design, quality and pricing. We specialize in house wares, hardware, and in the innovation of everyday products. Our&nbsp;global offices&nbsp;are in the US, Canada, China, Hong Kong, and Taiwan.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our products are sold in the US, Canada, Mexico, Puerto Rico, United Kingdom, Japan, Korea, Taiwan, Spain, South Africa, Italy, Ireland, Australia, Israel, France, Holland, New Zealand, and Chile.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Company Website and e-Commerce Store</strong>:<a href="http://www.sevilleclassics.com/">www.sevilleclassics.com</a></p>', 'http://jobview.monster.com/Administrative-Puchasing-Assistant-Job-Torrance-CA-US-135327378.aspx', '', 5, 89, 2),
(473, 1402595982, 'Billing Assistant - Voice Department', '中国电信(美国)', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', 'Carson', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>Summary:</strong></p>\n<p>The Billing Assistant in the Voice department of the Los Angeles office will be responsible for processing billing to Voice clients, customer care, providing assistance to the Finance department in the Herndon, VA headquarters office with Voice-related invoices, and financial reporting including the preparation of financial statistics, financial statements, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Tasks &amp; Responsibilities:&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Assist Finance department with Voice invoices, A/R analysis and customer payment and collection.</li>\n<li>Assist Sales to generate selling price notices</li>\n<li>Assist purchasers to&nbsp;prepare&nbsp;buyer target list daily</li>\n<li>Assist NOC to test new routes and keep appropriate records</li>\n<li>Reporting and communications to the parent company in China.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n<p><strong>JOB REQUIREMENTS</strong></p>\n<div class="section-body">\n<p>Essential Skills and Qualifications needed:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>A bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Accounting or other business-related&nbsp;field.</li>\n<li>Minimum of one year hands-on experience in an accounting position, including credit and collections.</li>\n<li>Knowledge with GAAP and IAS.</li>\n<li><strong>Excellent verbal and written communications skills in English and Chinese.</strong></li>\n<li>Ability to identify, research and solve problems with an eagerness to learn.</li>\n<li>An energetic and positive, can-do approach.</li>\n<li>Ability to work independently as well as within a team.</li>\n<li>Diligence, responsibility, attention to detail and the ability to multi-task.</li>\n<li>Competent in Microsoft applications including Word, Excel and Outlook,&nbsp;and experienced with common accounting software.</li>\n<li>Experience with the telecommunications industry is a plus.</li>\n</ol></div>', 'http://www.careerbuilder.com/jobseeker/applyonline/aoreviewreq.aspx?Job_DID=JHQ6MY6H3R2RRVMJ5K7', '', 5, 193, 2),
(474, 1402596712, 'Relationship Banker', 'JPMorgan Chase', 'Finance', 'Hacienda Heights, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Hacienda Heights', 33.993069, -117.968674, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '哈仙达岗', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div><strong>Qualifications</strong>:</div>\n<ul>\n<li>College degree preferred or High school degree/GED or foreign equivalent</li>\n<li>Minimum of one year Branch Sales Experience or equivalent Financial Services Sales experience with proven success in establishing new clients, revenue generation, and the ability to deliver results.</li>\n<li>Series 6/7, state registration (including 63 if required), and life licenses REQUIRED.&nbsp; If unlicensed, must be obtained within 90 days of joining Chase</li>\n<li>Ability to establish credibility and rapport, be friendly and personable and look for ways to benefit the customer''s financial relationship both over the phone as well as in person.</li>\n<li>Excellent customer contact skills; comfortable asking questions/interviewing customers about their financial situation; strong listening skills comfortable making outbound calls</li>\n<li>Understands how to present features, and benefits of products and services to customers with differing needs</li>\n<li>Self motivated, assertive, performs well in a competitive sales environment</li>\n<li>Professional, thorough and organized; able to follow standard operating policies and procedures</li>\n<li>Ability to learn products, services and procedures quickly and accurately; explain concepts clearly to customers</li>\n<li>Understand how to interpret numbers, trends and data to make effective decisions</li>\n<li>Ability to work branch hours, including weekends and some evenings</li>\n</ul>', 'https://jpmchase.taleo.net/careersection/2/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=1447538', '', 5, 186, 2),
(475, 1402598386, 'Automotive Product Manager', 'Young Technology', 'Management', 'Addison, IL, United States', 'United States', 'Illinois', 'Addison', 41.931698, -87.988953, '美国', '伊利诺伊州', '艾迪生', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>JOB DESCRIPTION</strong></p>\n<p>This Entry level Product Manager position is responsible for&nbsp;ensuring the accurate, timely&nbsp;development and maintenance of products for Young Technology Inc.&nbsp; Under the direction of&nbsp;immediate supervisorcoordinate the procurement, development, and implementation of equipment and achieving companygoals for quality, cost, and delivery.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>DUTIES and RESPONSIBILITIES</strong></p>\n<ul type="disc">\n<li>Communicate daily with the overseas factories to ensure all aspects of manufacturing and product specifications are met</li>\n<li>Directs the procurement of products, control the movement of materials, monitor the levels and accuracy of inventory, and oversee production schedules and follow-up on the above items.</li>\n<li>Oversee production schedules, including material procurement and manufacturing schedules.</li>\n<li>Develop supplier relationships to assure a continuing source.</li>\n<li>Responsible as main contact point for their assigned project to customers.</li>\n<li>Takes necessary actions to eliminate delays or quality issues so as to insure adherence to production and shipping schedules.</li>\n<li>Oversee prompt shipment schedules to ensure customer requirements are met.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>POSITION REQUIREMENTS</p>\n<p><strong>EDUCATION</strong></p>\n<p>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in engineering, management, or equivalent is required.</p>\n<p><strong>SKILLS:</strong></p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ability to speak, read, and write English and Chinese Mandarin is required.</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Excellent oral, written communication and presentation skills are required.</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Strong project management and time management skills are required.</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Previous supplier management experience preferred.</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Business plan development experience preferred.</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Product development and sourcing experience preferred.</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Inventory Management and purchasing experience preferred.</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Computer literacy and proficiency in word processing and spreadsheet software is required.</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Knowledge and understanding of the procurement and inventory process and associated costs including inventory, logistics, acquisition costs, purchasing, and related accounting functions are preferred.<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p><strong>TRAVEL</strong></p>\n<ul type="disc">\n<li>Travel schedule must be flexible</li>\n<li>Estimated domestic travel 1-2 times a month.</li>\n<li>Estimated international travel 1-2 times a year.</li>\n<li>Must be open to potentially travel to China for training for a period up to 3 to 6 months.</li>\n</ul>', 'http://jobview.monster.com/Automotive-Product-Manager-Job-Addison-IL-US-135325393.aspx', '', 5, 97, 2),
(476, 1402599233, 'Sr. Marketing Manager', 'NewEgg', 'Marketing', 'Industry, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'City of Industry', 34.019733, -117.958672, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '因达斯特里', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Purpose Of The Job:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<p>To develop and implement plans to assist the company in taking advantage of the global marketing and sales opportunities available through the Internet and supporting the Company&rsquo;s business objectives.</p>\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Responsibilities/Duties:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<ul>\n<li>Design, implement, and facilitate annual marketing plan.</li>\n<li>Plan and manage promotions on a regular basis.</li>\n<li>Be alert with the Rosewill.com website performance, including but not limited to traffic, page views, ads Campaign performance.</li>\n<li>Keep close relationship with 3rd party product reviewers and collaborate with PM teams to help schedule product reviews to ensure positive reviews and increase brand awareness.</li>\n<li>Work closely with cross-functional PM team, Marketing team, and Merchandising team to develop and ensure successful marketing campaign on e-commerce websites.</li>\n<li>Work on other projects as assigned on a routine basis in other marketing areas such as research, reporting, and new idea development and execution.</li>\n<li>Plan and administer the marketing budget, maximize the Return on investment of any money spent on marketing.</li>\n<li>Organize and implement customer relations including: Customer satisfaction surveys, Acquire development activities, special events, and tradeshow.</li>\n<li>Responsible for the employment and development function of employees including hiring, terminating, coaching, developing, and leading.</li>\n<li>Other duties as assigned.</li>\n</ul>\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Minimum Requirements &amp; Special Attributes:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<p> Bachelor Degree preferably in Marketing or Merchandising or 8 years of relevant work experience.<br /> Valid state driver&rsquo;s license and automotive insurance.<br /> Ability to acquire work/travel documents (i.e., passport and visa) as required by various countries.<br /> 7 years of progressive marketing or merchandising experience.<br /> 5 years of employee management experience.<br /> Prior leadership experience in merchandising/marketing management.<br /> Excellent written/verbal, time management and quantitative/analytical skills required.<br /> Proven analytical and conceptual skill.<br /> Proven ability to drive change and results through influential leadership skills.<br /> Highly effective communicator to all levels, able to clearly articulate the company''s values.<br /> Proven ability to effectively manage multiple projects in a dynamic environment.<br /> Demonstrated strong facilitation skills and ability to identify common ground amongst individuals with divergent opinions and perspectives.<br /> Strong abilities in the areas of analysis, budgeting, problem solving and decision making.</p>\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Essential Mental and Physical Functions:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">Mental Functions:<br /><br />Decisions have significant, broad implications for the management and operations of a division. Job contributes to decisions on the overall strategy and direction of the Company. This position establishes procedures for attaining specific goals and objectives in a broad area of work. Only the final results of work done are typically reviewed.&nbsp;<br /><br />Physical Functions:<br /><br />Sitting required 90% of the time. Walking and standing required 5% of the time respectively. No heavy lifting required. Constant working on a computer.<br />\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Equipment Used:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">Standard office and computer equipment including MSOffice software.\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Work Environment:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">Office cubicle environment with minimal exposure to the environment or health hazards.\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Supervisory Responsibilities:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">Manage up to 5 employees.\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Language Skills:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">Must be able to speak, read, write and comprehend English. Bilingual preferably in Mandarin a plus.\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Travel Requirements:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">Must be able to travel 20% of the time both domestically and internationally.\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'https://careers-newegg.icims.com/jobs/1958/sr.-marketing-manager/job', '', 5, 72, 2),
(477, 1402676775, 'OPT助理', '乐学乐游美国', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', 'Carson', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><br />乐学乐游美国是美国洛杉矶一所专业留学和旅游公司，公司长久以来用专业和耐心的服务帮助了无数在美留学生解决各类难题。 公司为了提高更好的服务质量，和业务扩展的需要，现补招另外一名OPT助理。有意者请尽快联系，会统一安排面试时间。</p>\n<p>主要岗位职责：<br />1负责公司的业务推广和咨询服务。<br />2.管理开发好自己的客户，拓展与老客户的业务。<br />3.各类书面写作,口语交流。<br />4,.保持良好的渠道联系，维护与合作伙伴的关系。</p>\n<p>岗位要求：</p>\n<p>工作认真丶积极丶有高度的责任心<br />善于沟通，具备很强执行能力<br />本科毕业，有工作经验者优先<br />中英文流利，有较强的英文写作能力<br />合法的工作身份，OPT Fulltime</p>\n<p>薪水面谈<br />联系方式：<br />909-918-9002 Martin Wang<br />909-918-9003 Alison Fang<br />请在工作时间联系我们 Mon-Fir 9am-6pm</p>', '', 'llestudy20133@gmail.com', 5, 178, 2),
(499, 1403117278, '市场销售', 'The Asian Magazine', 'Media', 'Dallas, TX, United States', 'United States', 'Texas', 'Dallas', 32.780140, -96.800453, '美国', '德克萨斯州', '达拉斯', 'H1B', 'Full Time', '<p>创造The Asian Magazine这样一个多媒体平台的初衷是分享与融合。把华人的声音和态度分享出去，把中西方的美学生活融合在一起。这个平台和所有华人在美国新兴的力量一样，渴望交流与成长，渴望展示与创造。未来很广，而大梦想照进现实的执行正等待着我们一起能量爆发。这将是一件多么让人兴奋不已又成就感十足的事情，期待新的伙伴们一同来加入我们充满活力热情四溢的团队！<br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> 1. 市场销售：<br /> 1）性格开朗，形象良好，思维敏捷，具备较强的学习能力和优秀的沟通能力（中英文）<br /> 2）做事条理性强，具有良好的组织能力，拥有出色的应变能力和承压能力，<br /> 3）有敏锐的市场洞察力，有强烈的事业心、责任心和积极的工作态度，吃苦耐劳<br /> 4）有车，有美国驾照<br /> 5）有相关销售工作经验者优先<br /> <br /> <br /> 薪酬：<br /> 3个月实习期提供提成；实习期结束后提供底薪+提成模式<br /> <!-- [if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br /> <!--[endif]--></p>\n<p>申请流程：<br /> 请将你的简历、cover letter和其他相关材料发至<a href="mailto:career@theasianmagazine.com">career@theasianmagazine.com</a>。<br /> 其他：<br /> 1) 可以提供OPT、CPT支持<br /> 2) 工作表现优异者，公司可以提供H1－B VISA支持</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>公司所在地：Dallas,TX</p>\n<p>新浪微博：TheAsianMagazine</p>\n<p>微信公众平台：TheAsianMagazine</p>\n<p>官方网站： www.theasianmagazine.com</p>', '', 'career@theasianmagazine.com', 805, 189, 2),
(479, 1402762335, '市场咨询部实习生', '美国厚仁教育', 'Marketing', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', 'Carson', 'None', 'Internship', '<p>美国厚仁教育招聘洛杉矶地区市场咨询部实习生。需中英文流利，对教育行业感兴趣，适应能力强。工作时间灵活，提供实习补贴和奖金。有校联工作经验或转学经验的申请人优先考虑。</p>', '', 'job@wholeren.com', 5, 138, 2);
