(480, 1402763653, '中英双语 Jr. Foreign Exchange (FX) Dealer', 'The FXCM, Inc', 'Finance', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美国', '纽约州', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>The FXCM, Inc. Dealing Department is seeking entry level and enthusiastic individuals for full time positions, on all shifts. If you are a driven individual with a passion for the FX market, the Jr. FX Dealer is a great opportunity to join the leading foreign exchange firm, with tremendous advancement opportunities in the trading field.</p>\n<p><strong>Key Duties &amp; Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Liaise with clients wishing to place phone orders for FX trades</li>\n<li>Run multiple reports for senior dealers for the monitoring of positions</li>\n<li>Focus and compute all incoming and outgoing trade traffic</li>\n<li>Multi-task by monitoring multiple servers</li>\n<li>Ensure currency rates are being updated and our clients are being provided competitive market prices</li>\n<li>Continuously take an active interest in learning FX and the financial markets</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Be computer literate, possess excellent communication skills and professional demeanor</li>\n<li>Candidate must have a genuine interest to learn and succeed in the FX markets</li>\n<li>Must be willing to work 1st Asian, 2nd European, or 3rd Americas shifts</li>\n<li>Be extremely flexible and reliable during rapid and volatile market conditions</li>\n<li>Must demonstrate excellent math skills and quick calculations</li>\n<li>Be very detail-oriented</li>\n<li>Be a team player that is well organized and possesses the ability to handle multiple tasks simultaneously</li>\n<li>Have the ability to meet deadlines and handle a variety of projects concurrently in a fast-paced business environment</li>\n<li>Be a self-starter and able to work with minimal supervision</li>\n<li>Eager to work in high-pressure volatile markets</li>\n<li>Determine priorities and follow up in a timely fashion</li>\n<li><strong>At this time we are only seeking applicants that have bilingual fluency in English and Chinese for this position.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 21px;">&nbsp;</span></p>', 'https://www1.apply2jobs.com/FXCM/ProfExt/index.cfm?fuseaction=mExternal.showJob&RID=706&CurrentPage=4&sid=37#', '', 5, 226, 2),
(481, 1402794604, 'Bilingual English & Cantonese-Chinese Program Facilitator', 'Free Arts NYC Mission', 'Management', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美国', '纽约州', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div id="box-Jobdescription" class="box widget imagine  opened">\n<div class="body">\n<div id="listing-description" class="description formattedText">\n<p><strong>Free Arts NYC Mission:</strong>Free Arts NYC provides under-served children and families with a unique combination of educational arts and mentoring programs that help them to foster the self-confidence and resiliency needed to realize their fullest potential.</p>\n<p><strong>Parents and Children Together with Art (PACT) Program:</strong>PACT is an eight week, theme-based art experience for families. Working as a design team, families use art as a vehicle to enhance their communication and problem-solving skills. PACT activities are designed to increase parental involvement and graduate in complexity to encourage positive forms of family communication and sustained teamwork. With a 1:2 volunteer to family ratio, program facilitators and trained volunteers implement a creative arts curriculum that requires them to develop ideas and work collaboratively. Each session begins with exposure to a professional artist that serves as an inspiration image, followed by an art experience, and concludes with a sharing circle.</p>\n<p><strong>Job Summary:</strong>&nbsp;PACT Program Facilitators take primary responsibility for providing leadership, structure and on-going support for their weekly PACT groups. This includes ensuring each group embodies Free Arts NYC''s philosophy "There are no mistakes in art!"; supporting and guiding positive engagement between volunteers and families and between parents and children; and maintaining groups as safe spaces for participants and volunteers at all times.</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fully bilingual in Cantonese-Chinese and English</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Candidates will have a Masters in Art Education, Studio/Fine Arts, Social Work, Community Development or a related field</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>1-2 years experience working with special needs populations, particularly those on the autism spectrum</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>1-2 years experience working with families and/or group facilitation with parents/guardians</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>2-3 years experience working with under-served populations &ndash; in school, community center and/or social service agency settingsthat includes:</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Team teaching or collaborative teaching</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Working with a wide variety of art materials and techniques;</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Developing programming for under-served/at risk youth and families</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Demonstrable commitment to engaging with values related to diversity</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>A genuine passion for engaging families via the arts.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Excellent written and verbal communication skills.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office applications and on-line data collection systems</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Attend a PACT program Training (3 hrs, paid), New Facilitator Orientation (2 hours, paid) and semesterly PACT Facilitator Staff Meetings (3 hours paid, at beginning of cycle), Curriculum Reviews (3 hrs, paid), and PACT Facilitator Roundtables (2 hrs, paid, at the end of cycle).</li>\n<li>Review the curriculum and plan how to best adapt lesson plans for your group prior to the program session.</li>\n<li>Track participant and volunteer attendance using forms provided by Free Arts NYC, and return completed forms to PACT staff at designated dates.</li>\n<li>Maintain a safe, supportive group environment in accordance with Free Arts NYC''s policies and trainings.</li>\n<li>Lead, explain, and demonstrate group activities, and/or create opportunities for volunteers to be active participants/learners and lead group activities.</li>\n<li>Remain alert to the needs of your volunteers; assist them when required, encouraging them to fully participate in all group activities and engage with the kids &amp; families.</li>\n<li>Remainalert to the needs of kids and families and assist them as required</li>\n<li>Take primary responsibility for classroom management and handling any challenging behaviors that arise.</li>\n<li>When appropriate, provide feedback to partner agency staff about kids and families'' progress and well-being.</li>\n<li>Lead pre-session Group Prep and post-session Group Debriefs with volunteers.</li>\n<li><em>Evaluation Activities:</em></li>\n<li>Promptly complete weekly online surveys reporting on each session;</li>\n<li>Promptly complete "Post" Individual Family Progress Surveys at the end of the cycle ;</li>\n<li>Promptly complete 1 Family Case Study at the end of the cycle at the end of the cycle.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>MORE ABOUT YOU:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>You have a genuine enthusiasm for Free Arts NYC''s mission.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>You are a team-player and have a positive attitude.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>You are organized, with strong multi-tasking skills.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Ideal Characteristics</strong>: Ideal candidates have experience working collaboratively with people from diverse backgrounds,are game for creative experimentation, welcome constructive feedback and regularly seek to identify and address areas for improvement.</p>\n<p><strong>Salary:</strong>&nbsp;$100/program session, $33.33/hour for meetings and trainings</p>\n<p><strong>Time Commitment:</strong>&nbsp;This position is contracted to lead a PACT 8 week-cycle and/or individual PACT Art Night sessions. Sessions includes a 30 minute set-up period, 1.5-2 hour workshop, 30 minute debrief with volunteers on-site at one of Free Arts NYC''s partner agencies.</p>\n<p><strong>Location:</strong>&nbsp;Positions are available in Manhattan (afternoon-early evening).</p>\n<p><em>Free Arts NYC is an Equal Opportunity Employer, committed to seeking a diverse staff with respect to gender, age, race, ethnicity, national origin, class, educational background, religion, sexual orientation, and physical ability. All applicants are welcome.</em></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', '', 'Jennifer@freeartsnyc.org', 5, 122, 2),
(482, 1402795861, 'Pediatric Physician', 'StaffPointe', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美国', '纽约州', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>JOB DESCRIPTION:&nbsp;</strong><br />Private practice group is seeking a Pediatrician for their growing practice in Manhattan, New York. Opportunity for a Pediatrician to serve the Chinese-speaking patient population in a 100% outpatient setting. You MUST be fluent in Chinese.&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>HOURS and RESPONSIBILITIES&nbsp;</strong><br />Monday thru Friday, 9:30 to 5:30. Reasonable Patient volumes, you will not be pressured by numbers. Light telephone call is triaged using an answering service, and shared between physicians. NO inpatient responsibilities with this position.&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>REQUIREMENTS:&nbsp;</strong><br />Must be Board Eligible, Board Certified in Pediatrics. Prefer physicians with active New York license. Fluency in Chinese is required.&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>SALARY / BENEFITS:&nbsp;</strong><br />This offers a competitive salary with excellent benefit package that includes 4 weeks of vacation, 1 week for CME, health insurance, and paid malpractice plus more.&nbsp;</p>', '', 'ls@staffpointe.com', 5, 87, 2),
