(485, 1402797155, 'Bilingual (in Chinese) Experienced Full Charge Bookkeeper', 'MayBao Ltd', 'Finance', '', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美国', '纽约州', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Real Estate Management Company seeks individual with at least 3 years diversified hands on bookkeeping experience.</p>\n<p>Duties and responsibilities include but are not limited to:</p>\n<p>&middot; Maintain accounts receivable and payable, including, produce monthly billing, tracking outstanding invoices, making regular deposits, and processing payments for bills, invoices, and payroll.<br />&middot; Maintain the company''s financial books and records, including, preparation of journal entries, accruals, depreciation and adjusting journal entries, preparing supporting schedules in excel.<br />&middot; End of month bank reconciliation and financial statement (P&amp;L, Balance Sheet and Cash Flow) preparation, ad-hoc projects as needed.<br />&middot; General office clerical duties, including, filing, answering telephones, scheduling appointments, updating employee calendars, etc.</p>\n<p>Job Requirements:</p>\n<p>&middot; At least 3 years bookkeeping experience, 2+ years prior experience in real estate entity preferred<br />&middot; Knowledge in Property Management Software Yardi Genesis, proficiency in QuickBooks and Microsoft Office especially Microsoft Excel<br />&middot; Highly organized individual with attention to detail and ability to multi-task and handle situation efficiently and accurately in a fast-paced environment<br />&middot; Capable to work independently and within a team <br />&middot; Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree required, preferably in Accounting or Finance<br />&middot; Eligibility to work in the US without sponsorship<br />&middot; Fluent English and Chinese writing and speaking</p>\n<p>Compensation:</p>\n<p>&middot; Good base salary with full benefits (Medical and paid vacation)</p>\n<p>Position Type</p>\n<p>&middot; Full-Time</p>', '', 