(490, 1402936603, 'Production Planner', 'Emser Tile', 'International Commerce', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', 'Carson', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table class="emser" border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="2">\n<p><strong>Requirements and Responsibilities Production Planner</strong></p>\n<br />\n<p>The Production Planner is responsible for scheduling and planning factory production to allow steady flow of product to Emser Distribution Centers. The Production Planner analyzes data and reports to identify changes in production needs. He or She will quantify and qualify factory issues with goal to resolve problems in a timely manner. The Production Planner performs a variety of complicated tasks and analysis. This role requires a bachelor degree and/or 2+ years of experience in production planning. &nbsp;He or She must be self-motivated with great negotiation skills. This includes excellent communication skills required to guide and instruct overseas suppliers. The Production Planner must have collaborative skill set and be able to work with multiple sources to include supply chain colleagues, company leadership and overseas suppliers. &nbsp;This role reports to the Sr. Production and Development Manager.</p>\n<br />\n<p><strong>Key Results:</strong></p>\n<br />\n<p>The Production Planner is responsible to ensure factory production is in accordance with Emser needs.&nbsp; He or She will make sure factories are allocating sufficient production space on required dates to assure products are available to ship on time.&nbsp; The Production Planner will be responsible for resolving any factory production issues.&nbsp; They must liaison with purchasing and forecasting team along with the factories in regards to production requirements and product needs. He or She will manage, update, and alert Supply Chain team on factory updates/issues. They must possess the ability to work in a fast pace changing environment and still meet daily performance timelines.</p>\n<br /><br /></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="2" bgcolor="ffffff">\n<p class="aheader">Experience and Skills:</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="2">\n<p><strong>Duties and Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Analyze, budget, expedite new introduction initial buys</li>\n<li>Schedule and manage all segments that will affect factory space/production</li>\n<li>Strategize, lead and coordinate solution on production issues not related to quality</li>\n<li>Production analysis (production forecast, factory capacity, allocation report, inventory needs)</li>\n<li>Manage and back up Expeditors</li>\n<li>Issue temporary PO</li>\n<li>Maintain &amp; resolve credit memo, deposit and payment issues</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Qualifications:</span></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor''s Degree with 2+ years&rsquo; experience in production planning</li>\n<li>Ability to negotiate, instructs, manage, and collaborate with overseas suppliers</li>\n<li>Must have strong communication skills both written and orally.</li>\n<li>Computer literate (Microsoft Excel required)</li>\n<li>Speak and read Mandarin/Cantonese a plus.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'http://emser.submit4jobs.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=83037.viewjobdetail&CID=83037&JID=166709', '', 5, 101, 2),
