(507, 1403537406, 'Customer Service Rep', 'East West Bank', 'Finance', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美国', '纽约州', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>As an East West Bank employee, you will be part of a growing and stable organization that provides career path development opportunities while serving a growing and profitable market.<br /><br />As a valuable East West Bank team member, your duties (not limited to) will include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Acknowledge and engage customers who approach the customer service desk&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Enter sales transactions into the computer system with accuracy.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Process credit applications, while maintaining confidentiality of customer records.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Effectively explain financing plans and other terms of sale to the customer&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Conduct costumer follow-up phone calls.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Take care of all customers through direct action or indirectly by assisting others.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Travel up to 50%</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Qualifications/Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Previous customer service experience in a call center or related field.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Strong verbal, written, and oral communication skills&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Solid computer skills (i.e. MS Office, Word, Excel, etc.)&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Extremely detail oriented&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Ability to multi-task, self- motivated, with an effective drive to resolve issues quickly.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>High School diploma or equivalent.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Must have reliable transportation&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>Bilingual in English and Chinese (Mandarin) required</strong></li>\n</ul>', 'https://sjobs.brassring.com/TGWEbHost/jobdetails.aspx?jobId=1828026', '', 5, 134, 2),
(508, 1403538180, 'Preop & Recovery RN/ RNPREREC', 'Surgery Partners', 'Service', 'Whittier, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Whittier', 33.979179, -118.032845, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '惠提尔', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Assists in provision of nursing care to patients in an Ambulatory Surgical Center setting. Assumes total responsibility for patient care in accordance with physician''s orders and centers policies.&nbsp; Graduate of Accredited School of Nursing; current state RN License.&nbsp; CPR required.&nbsp; ACLS required.&nbsp; Minimum one year in pre-operative, intra-operative and post-operative surgical patient care. <strong>Must be bilingual in Chinese.</strong></p>', 'http://www.miracleworkers.com/jobs/-/J3G2H26FFQ3BG3RXG4J', '', 5, 70, 2),
(509, 1403538397, 'Marketing & Office Intern', 'Law Office of Bobby C Chung', 'Law', 'San Gabriel, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Gabriel', 34.096111, -118.105835, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '圣盖博', 'None', 'Internship', '<p>Small immigration law firm (bccvisalaw.com) in San Gabriel, CA seeks a part-time Marketing &amp; Office Intern available to work at least 30 hours per week. The Intern will assist in various areas of office administration and customer service, including answering phone, scheduling appointments, managing calendar, communicating with clients, etc. The Intern will also assist staff with marketing projects, such as writing content for our website and social media.<br /><br />Ideal candidates include current college students or recent college graduates seeking to develop career in marketing or business administration. Successful completion of the 4 months internship will lead to job offer as a full-time or part-time Marketing &amp; Administrative Assistant. We offer a collegial work environment and support our employees to have work-life balance.<br /><br />One year marketing or office administration experience preferred, but not required. We will train the Intern in all aspects of the job. Candidates must be detail oriented with excellent writing, organizational, computer, and people skills. Must have knowledge of social media platforms such as Facebook, Twitter, Youtube, etc. We look for self starter individual who works well under pressure and can prioritize and balance competing demands. Sense of humor and friendly attitude a plus.<br /><br />Bilingual in Mandarin Chinese is preferred, but not required.<br /><br />Internship pays from $9 to $10 per hour determined by education, work experience, skills, and interview.<br /><br />Qualified applicants should submit a resume, cover letter, and a writing sample.<br /><br />NO phone calls please.&nbsp;</p>', 'http://www.barefootstudent.com/los_angeles/jobs/internship/marketing_office_inter