(513, 1403626106, 'Assistant Commodities Trader', 'Selby Jennings', 'Finance', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美国', '纽约州', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>&nbsp;A successful commodities trading firm in the NYC Metro area is looking to add an assistant commodities trader to a well established team. The firm has been quite profitable over the past few years and is expanding the group. They are both a merchant of physical commodities and a financer of upper-and mid-stream commodity-producing assets.&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>Position overview<br /></strong>This role will be working directly with commodities derivatives traders, assisting with structured physical commodity trades. The team is made up of 15 people and you would be reporting directly to the head of Quant Trading. Qualified candidates must have experience with structuring trades and market knowledge of commodities. This is an excellent opportunity to work with some of the best traders in the commodities industry and continue to expand upon your knowledge base and grow your career.&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;<br /><strong>Requirements<br /></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>2-3 years of industry experience</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Knowledge around commodities derivatives trading and structuring</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Masters/PhD in a quantitative field from top quartile school</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Financial statement modelling experience</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Strong communication skills (Bilingual Chinese is a plus)</strong></li>\n</ul>\n</ul>', 'http://www.selbyjennings.com/vacancies/2014/06/23/assistant-commodities-trader-56841485/', '', 5, 135, 2),
(514, 1403626336, 'Head of Legal & Compliance', '中国农业银行', 'Finance', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美国', '纽约州', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><span lang="EN-GB"><span style="font-family: Arial;">Working in the high volume of payment environment. Manage and oversee the day to day Compliance issues/matters of the Branch, ensuring employees and operations are in adherence to the relevant internal and external policies, regulations and guidelines.</span></span></p>\n<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span lang="EN-GB"><span style="font-family: Arial;">Key Responsibilities:</span></span></span></strong></p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="font-family: Arial;">Develop Compliance programs for the New York Branch, reviewing and updating policies and procedures on an ongoing basis to ensure they are compliant with U.S. regulations and requirements.</span></p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="font-family: Arial;">Coordinate with the Head Office in China to ensure that New York Branch policies and procedures are compliant with Chinese regulations and requirements.</span></p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="font-family: Arial;">Regularly review all business, products, operations and administrative departments within the Branch to ensure compliance with internal policies and procedures, applicable supervisory guidelines and adequacy of operational and systems controls.&nbsp;&nbsp;Also ensures Branch complies with applicable Federal Reserve and New York State banking regulations.</span></p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="font-family: Arial;">Oversees compliance of the New York Branch with the Bank Secrecy Act, USA Patriot Act, OFAC regulations, and all other applicable BSA/AML/OFAC statutes, regulations and best practices.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="font-family: Arial;">Maintain Branch internal control standards, including timely implementation of internal and external audit points together with any issues raised by external regulators.</span></p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="font-family: Arial;">Perform or coordinate the annual Compliance reviews of the Branch&rsquo;s policies, procedures and other operational processes to ensure they are in accordance with ABC and regulatory standards and policies; optimize relations with regulators by addressing any issues.</span></p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="font-family: Arial;">Conduct or manage Compliance training seminars to ensure all employees are aware of and understand the relevant banking regulations.</span></p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="font-family: Arial;">Serve as liaison to New York State Banking Department and U.S. regulatory agencies during Branch examinations by Federal Reserve Bank of New York and New York State Banking Department.</span></p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="font-family: Arial;">Motivate, train and develop Compliance team in order to maximize effectiveness and promote positive team working.</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-GB"><span style="font-family: Arial;">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span lang="EN-GB"><span style="font-family: Arial;">Knowledge &amp; Experience Requirements:</span></span></span></strong></p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="font-family: Arial;">Bachelor&rsquo;s degree or equivalent; Advanced degree or J.D. preferred.</span></p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="font-family: Arial;">Typically requires 10+ years relevant Compliance experience&nbsp;in U.S..</span></p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="font-family: Arial;">Experience with an international bank with thorough understanding of Compliance processes and practices utilized in the U.S. branches of international banks.&nbsp;&nbsp;Specifically requires knowledge of AML, BSA, KYC, OFAC, Patriot Act&nbsp;and all appropriate banking regulations and reporting requirements.</span></p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="font-family: Arial;">Experience with IT issues as they relate to vendor selection for AML/OFAC and suspicious activity monitoring software.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://jobview.monster.com/Head-of-Legal-Compliance-Job-New-York-City-NY-US-135804451.aspx', '', 5, 137, 2),
