(525, 1403713512, 'Purchasing Coordinator', 'Mega Green Recycles', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', 'Carson', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Mega Green Recycles is in the business of import/export of recyclable goods. We are looking for a highly organized and multi-talented individual who can provide strong purchasing support.</p>\n<p><strong>CHINESE SPEAKING PREFERRED.</strong><br /><br />DUTIES:<br /><br />- Perform buying duties (purchasing of recyclable goods primarily electronic waste)<br />- Respond to customer and supplier inquiries about order status, changes, or cancellations.&nbsp;<br />- Track the status of requisitions, contracts, and orders.<br />- Contact suppliers in order to schedule or expedite deliveries and to resolve shortages, missed or late deliveries, and other problems.&nbsp;<br />- Prepare purchase orders and send copies to suppliers and to departments originating requests.&nbsp;<br />- Review requisition orders in order to verify accuracy, terminology, and specifications.&nbsp;<br />- Determine if inventory quantities are sufficient for needs, ordering more materials when necessary.&nbsp;<br />- Prepare, maintain, and review purchasing files, reports and price lists.&nbsp;<br />- Compare suppliers'' bills with bids and purchase orders in order to verify accuracy.&nbsp;<br />- Locate suppliers, using sources such as catalogs and the internet, and interview them to gather information about products to be ordered.&nbsp;<br />- Calculate costs of orders, and charge or forward invoices to appropriate accounts.&nbsp;<br />- Compare prices, specifications, and delivery dates in order to determine the best bid among potential suppliers.&nbsp;<br />- Check shipments when they arrive to ensure that orders have been filled correctly and that goods meet specifications.&nbsp;<br />- Approve bills for payment.&nbsp;<br />- Maintain knowledge of all organizational and governmental rules affecting purchases, and provide information about these rules to organization staff members and to vendors.&nbsp;<br />- Monitor in-house inventory movement and complete inventory transfer forms for bookkeeping purposes.&nbsp;<br />- Prepare invitation-of-bid forms, and mail forms to supplier firms or distribute forms for public posting.&nbsp;<br />- Monitor contractor performance, recommending contract modifications when necessary.<br />- Provide assistance to the Team with projects and tasks.<br /><br />REQUIREMENTS:<br /><br />- Proactive and self-controlled work ethic; Self-starter.<br />- Good organizational and excellent time management skills.<br />- Exceptional skills of customer service.<br />- Superior written and verbal communication skills.<br />- Able to develop and maintain good relationships with our suppliers.<br />- Highly proficient level computer skills including Ms Word, PowerPoint and Excel.<br />- Strong record tracking of work with various levels at every account.<br />- Able to understand our business needs.<br />- Willingness in traveling and working in a team of professionals.</p>', 'http://jobview.monster.com/Purchasing-Coordinator-Job-El-Monte-CA-US-135843412.aspx', '', 5, 156, 2),
(526, 1403733321, '贷款经理 Fund Manager', 'M&E Financial Group', 'Finance', 'Irvine, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Irvine', 33.683949, -117.794693, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '欧文', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>ME Finance Group 金融公司招聘中国区贷款经理职位，限橘郡地区(Orange County)</strong><br /><strong>任职资格：</strong><br /><strong>有贷款，销售或者在金融公司工作的经历</strong><br /><strong>强大的时间管理能力和自我管理能力</strong><br /><strong>有强烈的创业精神与追求卓越的激情</strong><br /><strong>能够和公司一起成长</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Qualifications:&nbsp;</strong><br /><strong>&bull; Sales and sales closing experience</strong><br /><strong>&bull; Capable of handling rejection and overcoming objections&nbsp;</strong><br /><strong>&bull; Strong Time Management and self-management skills</strong><br /><strong>&bull; Ability to grow with an expanding organization&nbsp;</strong><br /><strong>&bull; Highly motivated to achieve and exceed goals</strong><br /><strong>&bull; A strong entrepreneurial spirit with a passion for excellence</strong><br /><strong>&bull; Proficient in the use of a computer&nbsp;</strong><br /><strong>&bull; Professional appearance and work ethic</strong><br /><strong>公司网址：<a href="http://www.thebizcash.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">www.thebizcash.com</a></strong><br /><strong>有意者请发送简历至<a href="mailto:ali@thebizcash.com">ali@thebizcash.com</a>&nbsp;或者电话联系949-468-0945</strong></p>\n<p><strong>全职兼职都可</strong></p>', '', 'ali@thebizcash.com', 832, 23, 2),
(527, 1403797027, '中英文 Business Development Associate - Entry Level', 'Axon US Corporation', 'Management', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美国', '纽约州', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>We are seeking highly motivated and creative individuals to join our company. Applicants who can demonstrate work place professionalism and uphold strong work ethics are strongly encouraged to apply.</p>\n<p>This is a great opportunity for recent graduates that have an interest in eCommerce.</p>\n<p><strong>Immediate hire and position open till filled.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p>Conduct research and screen for new business opportunities<br />Maintain existing professional business relationships with third-party vendors<br />Assist in various ad-hoc projects<br />Provide regular feedback on progress reports<br />Resolve customer issues regarding their orders, questions about products<br />Represent the company with pride</p>\n<p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>\n<p>Associate or Bachelor degree<br />Proficient in Microsoft Office<br />Exceptional attention-to-detail with the ability to meet aggressive deadlines<br />Strong quantitative, analytical, and creative problem solving skills<br />Excellent verbal and written communication and interpersonal skills<br />Able to multitask and be organized<br />Professionalism<br />Available for Full Time work Monday through Friday</p>\n<p><strong>Pluses, but not required:</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Bilingual in English and Chinese Mandarin</strong><br />High GPA<br />Experience in management<br />Experience in online retail</p>\n<p>Axon US Corp is an online retail company based in New York, but operating globally. Business includes international sourcing, web marketing, and database analyzing covering the fields of international purchasing and selling, products development, market exploitation and brand promotion.</p>\n<p>We offer you an open and equal atmosphere, challenging work and unlimited space to make progress. We welcome individuals with passion, dreams, experience and ability to join us, growing with us and creating our better future.</p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Axon-US-Corporation/jobs/Business-Development-Associate-bd31680af2c8acbf', '', 5, 308, 2),
(528, 1403797435, '中文社工经理', 'Asian Community Care Management', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美国', '纽约州', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>General Summary</strong><br />The Social Worker assists in the facilitation and coordination of community resources, in-home support services and other community-based services. He /She develops and maintain a therapeutic relationship with the client, which may include linking the client with systems that provide him or her with needed services, resources, and opportunities.</p>\n<p><strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Services within the company include care management, counseling, life coaching and bereavement groups</li>\n<li>Responsible for the assessment and intervention of the psychosocial needs of patients, families, and/or significant others in the home setting.</li>\n<li>Will work in close conjunction with patient, patient''s family and company practitioners</li>\n<li>Provides education and counseling/therapy to patients</li>\n<li>Promote community resources and assist with coordination of care</li>\n<li>Screen new patients that meet high-risk criteria</li>\n<li>Completes comprehensive psychosocial assessments on assigned patients</li>\n<li>Collaborates with an interdisciplinary team to develop a patient focused, safe, feasible plan</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Valid New York State licensed Social Worker</li>\n<li>Must be fluent in Chinese (Mandarin and/or Cantonese) and English</li>\n<li>Must have strong analytic capacity with ability to make professional decisions in a highly communicative manner</li>\n<li>Excellent administrative, organizational and communication (oral and written) skills, especially with long-term care patients</li>\n<li>Proficient in MS Office Suite</li>\n<li>Minimum of one year social work experience in a health care setting preferred</li>\n<li></li>\n</ul>', 'http://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=8ea72d3bd27d8a31', '', 5, 131, 2),
(529, 1403797890, 'Part-time Front Office Manager', 'AJ Construction', 'Management', 'Walnut, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Walnut', 34.020290, -117.865341, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '沃尔纳特', 'None', 'Part Time', '<ul>\n<li>Hiring one part time office manager/assistant for a Construction company.</li>\n<li>Must be good at Windows softwares, independent, hardworking.</li>\n<li>Age around 20 to 35 years old, live within 30 minutes from Walnut, CA.</li>\n<li>*<strong>Must be fluent in English and Chinese</strong>*, and able to use social media</li>\n<li>The assistant is asked to *visit construction sites*, purchase construction materials and supplies, communicate with workers, type paperworks, post on social media, and so on.</li>\n<li>Prefers experienced people and people with related major.</li>\n<li>Work for around 20 hr/week.</li>\n</ul>', '', 'andyjiang922@gmail.com', 5, 147, 2),
(530, 1403798549, '中文老师', 'Broadway Elementary School', 'Language', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', 'Carson', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Broadway Mandarin Immersion, located in Venice, CA and part of Los Angeles Unified School District (LAUSD), is seeking highly motivated applicants for the full-time position of elementary Mandarin teacher. Broadway&rsquo;s Mandarin Immersion program serves grades K-5 and operates on the 50/50 model. Successful applicants will be enthusiastic collaborators who can develop innovative instructional units with their teaching partners. Candidates should have a strong understanding of second language acquisition across the four language skills, and be able to integrate Chinese culture in creative classroom lessons. Teachers work in partnership with administration, staff, and parents to foster a nurturing and supportive learning environment.</p>\n<p>For more information on the program, visit: http://www.broadwayelementary.org/mi</p>\n<p>Qualified candidates should email resume and cover letter to Principal Susan Wang.</p>\n<p>Candidates must have native-level proficiency in spoken and written Mandarin, and be able to teach traditional characters. Must have California Elementary Multiple Subject Credential and a Bilingual, Cross-Cultural, Language and Academic Development (BCLAD) authorization in Mandarin. Applicants with certification from other states must be prepared to apply for a California teaching credential, and to pass all associated exams. (Please do not apply if you are unable or unwilling to obtain the needed California teaching credentials.)</p>\n<p>Prior experience in dual language elementary education and project-based learning are highly valued. Training in Gifted and Talented Education (GATE) is strongly desired.</p>', '', 'swang1@lausd.net', 5, 188, 2),
(531, 1403799108, '中英文 Health Care Coordinator', 'Chinese American Service League', 'Management', 'Chicago, IL, United States', 'United States', 'Illinois', 'Chicago', 41.878113, -87.629799, '美国', '伊利诺伊州', '芝加哥', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="post_description">\n<p>The Health Care Coordinator will work closely with the FCS Program Manager and other team members to streamline health initiatives within the agency to ensure effective service delivery and high quality health services. He/She will develop strategic collaboration with community partners, identify gaps in services and&nbsp; educate the community about the ECHO (Enhancing Community Health Outreach) Program. He/She will also work on evaluation of the effectiveness of CASL''s health programs, develop evaluative tools to implement within the agency by centralizing program outcomes through surveys, client feedback and quality assurance.</p>\n<h2>Mandatory Job Qualifications</h2>\n<p>Requires a Master''s Degree in Public Health, Social Work, or related field and a minimum of 1 year&rsquo;s work experience in health, social service, and/or education fields.&nbsp;Knowledge and experience in developing Client Database System, strong computer skills in data analysis of outcome performance, excellent written and verbal communication skills are required, as are the ability to speak, write, and read Chinese. (Cantonese preferred.) .</p>\n</div>\n<div class="post_apply">\n<h2>How to Apply</h2>\n<p>This job is open for online applications.</p>\n<p>To apply, please email the followings to Jobs@CASLservice.org:</p>\n<p>Cover letter<br />Resume<br />CASL Application (which can be downloaded at<a href="http://caslservice.org/images/stories/pdfs/employment_application.pdf">http://caslservice.org/images/stories/pdfs/employment_application.pdf</a>)</p>\n</div>', 'http://www.npo.net/job/health-care-coordinator-bilingual-chinese-english/64031', 'Jobs@CASLservice.org', 5, 136, 2),
(532, 1403905216, '中英双语奢侈品销售专员 全职/兼职', 'Bloomingdale''s', 'Marketing', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美国', '纽约州', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<h1 dir="ltr"><strong>【招聘】中英双语奢侈品销售专员 全职/兼职：Bloomingdale''s 59th Street, NYC</strong></h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir="ltr">地点：纽约市，纽约</p>\n<p dir="ltr">职位类别：百货</p>\n<p dir="ltr">申请编号：BLM18495</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><strong>概况：</strong></h3>\n<p dir="ltr">Bloomingdale&rsquo;s正在寻求一位普通话和英文流利的双语销售专员。你的时尚声音与权威是获得高档客户群信赖的关键；能够轻松地与人对话、建立关系、保持联系是成功的条件；在快节奏的佣金环境中工作，让销售驱动你的收入是激励你的动力。我们最优秀的员工目标明确，能在快节奏的工作环境中平衡多个重心，更重要的是真正享受工作的乐趣。</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><strong>基本职能：</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr">用普通话和英语流利地交流</p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr">卓越的销售能力，擅于倾听并响应客户需求，提供相应服务</p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr">对当下时尚潮流有敏锐的感知</p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr">通过人际交流建立并培养与客户的联系</p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr">通过建立反复客户增长个人销售额，利用Bconnected管理客户档案</p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr">满足或超越销售指标和忠诚度目标</p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr">对产品知识有专业程度的了解，熟知其功能及优点，并与客户分享</p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr">通过展现对店内产品及服务的了解建立销售和忠诚度</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 dir="ltr">&nbsp;</h3>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><strong>技能概要：</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr">普通话和英语双语交流能力</p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr">有动力、目标明确、有企业家前景</p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr">竭力满足并超越销售目标和客户期望</p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr">能够建立联系、与他人沟通、解决问题，并影响他人</p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr">熟悉奢侈品品牌及服务，对行业充满热情</p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr">渴望在快节奏的环境中工作，能够同时处理多个重点和学习新的程序</p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr">拥有出色的沟通技巧，能与客户、同事和经理交流</p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr">能够成为一个高效团队中的一员，或在少量直接监管下独立工作</p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr">能够适应灵活的零售业工作时间表，包括周末、晚上、延长服务时间，和主要活动日</p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr">接触过奢侈品牌及有零售销售经验者优先</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p dir="ltr">Bloomingdale&rsquo;s是一个机会均等的雇主，致力于构造一个多元化和包容的工作环境。</p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><strong>有意者请将简历发送至：Avery@chinaluxuryadvisors.com</strong></h3>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 'avery@chinaluxuryadvisors.com', 844, 365, 2),
