(537, 1404143012, '中英双语 Provider Account Manager', 'MJHS', 'Management', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美国', '纽约州', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>The challenges of affordable healthcare continue to create new opportunities. Elderplan and HomeFirst, our Medicare and Medicaid managed care health plans, are outstanding examples of how we are expanding services in response to our patients'' and members'' needs. These high-quality healthcare plans are designed to help keep people independent and living life on their own terms.<br /><br />We truly value our staff and further acknowledge their contributions by offering:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Employee and family health coverage</li>\n<li>Competitive salaries</li>\n<li>Employer contributed pension plan</li>\n<li>Generous time off</li>\n<li>Tuition reimbursement</li>\n<li>403(b) retirement plan</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br /><br />Responsibilities:&nbsp;<br />The Provider Account Manager develops and maintains strong relationships with strategically important IPAs. The Provider Account Manager coordinates with appropriate cross functional resources to ensure successful execution of the provider contract and the achievement of provider membership growth and financial results.<br /><br />Qualifications:&nbsp;<br />Four year college degree from an accredited institution. Minimum one to three years of experience in managed care or health care organization. Superior communication skills; <strong>bilingual English/Chinese required</strong>. Strong critical thinking skills and work ethic; strong problem-solving capacity.&nbsp;</p>', 'https://careers-mjhs.icims.com/jobs/2873/provider-account-manager/job', '', 5, 199, 2),
(538, 1404143213, 'Financial Analyst', 'MKVF Management', 'Finance', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美国', '纽约州', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div id="jobwrapper">\n<div id="jobcopy">\n<div id="jobBodyContent"><span id="TrackingJobBody">Financial Analyst. NYC. Financial analysis of Chinese listed companies: Review financial statements &amp; legal documents; Develop flexible financial models to perform valuation analysis; Gather data &amp; info from multiple Chinese sources including Nat''l Bureau of Statistics &amp; Chinese companies in the same industry. Req''d: Master''s degree economics, finance or related. Knowledge of Int''l Finance, Financial Markets &amp; Financial Risk; Securities Law; Financial Derivatives; Security Investment Analysis; Chinese Civil &amp; Economic Law. M-F, 9-5. Send resume to Job#3, MKVF Management Co. LLC, 1212 6th Avenue, 16th. Fl, NY, NY 10036.</span>&nbsp;<img src="http://media.newjobs.com/jobview_standard/images/pixel.gif" alt="" width="1" height="1" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'http://jobview.monster.com/FINANCIAL-ANALYST-Job-US-136071153.aspx', '', 5, 289, 2),
(539, 1404143432, '兼职中文老师', 'Chicago State University', 'Language', 'Chicago, IL, United States', 'United States', 'Illinois', 'Chicago', 41.878113, -87.629799, '美利坚合众国', '伊利诺伊州', '芝加哥', 'None', 'Part Time', '<p>All faculty positions are governed by the tenets of a collective bargaining agreement. Faculty are hired, evaluated, and retained on the basis of conditions covered in the union contract. Primary duties include teaching and related activities assigned during a term of 4.5 months. It is expected that each faculty member engages in teaching and teaching-related activities. Non-tenure track faculty report to a department chairperson or director.<br />Teaching: faculty members are expected to teach; develop syllabi and teaching materials (ability to organize, analyze, and present knowledge or materials) related to courses taught. Some disciplines require discipline specific certifications and/or licensure in the field for practice or functioning within the State of Illinois; degree specific course work and/or graduate degrees in the discipline.</p>\n<p>Appropriate educational background with a Master degree from an accredited institution and completed 60 semester hours or the equivalent of graduate study toward an advanced degree;</p>\n<p>Experience in teaching Chinese language to adults.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'https://chicagostate.peopleadmin.com/pools/2989', '', 5, 424, 2),
(540, 1404143814, 'Project Manager', 'Yoyo Chinese', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', 'Carson', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div id="q1" class="question">\n<div class="qContent">\n<div class="qBody">\n<section id="description">\n<p><em>To weed out spammers and make sure you read our job post carefully, please use &ldquo;I love pizza&rdquo; as the subject line. Thank you!</em></p>\n<p>We are an online Chinese language education company that uses videos to teach Chinese to students from all over the world.</p>\n<p>In our opinion, there are two sides to being a stellar project manager - managing projects and managing people. We&rsquo;re looking for someone who&rsquo;s absolutely great at both.</p>\n<p>IF YOU&rsquo;RE INTERESTED IN WORKING FOR US, YOU ARE:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Extremely organized and detail-oriented:&nbsp;You&rsquo;re so organized that you always have some kind of to-do list at hand. You&rsquo;re so detail-oriented that when you approve something, people are confident it&rsquo;s ready to go out, error-free. Errors and inconsistencies immediately jump out at you, and you care about details like file-naming practices.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Crazy about building systems:&nbsp;You love building systems so the whole company can run on autopilot. You believe the success of a company should be independent of any specific individual. You believe that any mistake that happens in a business is not just human error, but a problem with the system.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Obsessed with planning:&nbsp;You always have fun taking a big idea and translating it into a plan with a timeline of clear deliverables. You are skilled at both macro and micro thinking. You make sure the big picture is always moving forward by way of all the tiny details that need to get done.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>A solution-driven problem solver:&nbsp;Your goal is to get things done. You hate playing the &ldquo;blame game&rdquo; but instead like to just correct the issue and move on. You love unraveling any problem, figuring out what&rsquo;s really going on, and finding the missing pieces.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>A self-starter:&nbsp;You have an entrepreneurial spirit and hate to be micromanaged. You are always proactive about what else you can do to add value to the company.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Clear and straightforward communicator:&nbsp;You have to be an absolutely clear communicator. You can always express your thoughts clearly and make sure listeners are on the same page. You constantly ask thoughtful questions and provide constructive feedback at the same time.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Someone we can lean on:&nbsp;You are a natural mentor and sounding board, and knowing that you helped someone else succeed gives you enormous satisfaction. You love coaching and pushing people to do their best. You see people&rsquo;s strength and talents and have the ability to draw it out of themeven more.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Just like any startup company, we look for people who can wear different hats. Here are some job responsibilities you&rsquo;ll have:</p>\n<p>JOB RESPONSIBILITIES:</p>\n<p>Manage Projects:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Build / refine our internal business system to make it more scalable, in terms of designing and documenting the business process and workflow to streamline the training of new staff.</li>\n<li>Supervise and coordinate our new academic courses like a producer (hiring writers, overseeing course planning, scheduling shoot, editing video, uploading schedule)</li>\n<li>Oversee and plan our app development process (hiring developers, uploading the app onto different mobile platforms, etc.).</li>\n<li>Organize and guide daily/weekly planning meetings.</li>\n</ul>\nManage People:\n<ul>\n<li>You&rsquo;ll be serving as HR director to take charge of hiring and employee related issues.</li>\n<li>You&rsquo;ll be delegating work to different staff and tracking each one&rsquo;s progress.</li>\n<li>You&rsquo;ll help the company president to review each staff&rsquo;s progress and make sure everyone&rsquo;s on track.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>REQUIREMENTS</p>\n<ul>\n<li>3-5 years of project management experience</li>\n<li>Ability to speak Chinese is a big plus</li>\n<li>Video/audio producing or editing experience is a plus</li>\n<li>Project experience with developing a mobile app is a plus</li>\n<li>Basic knowledge of accounting is a plus</li>\n<li>Knowledge of common CMS and CRM</li>\n<li>Experience working with overseas team members is a plus.</li>\n<li>Graphic design and web design background is a plus.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>ABOUT OUR COMPANY</p>\n<p>We officially launched the website of the company (<a href="http://www.yoyochinese.com/" target="_blank">www.yoyochinese.com</a>) in 2012. In two short years, the company has grown to a comprehensive Chinese learning site with tens of thousands of members. While we continue to grow the company organically by developing more popular products and expanding our marketing efforts, we are also keen on building a strong foundation so the company is highly scalable to accommodate explosive growth.</p>\n<p>NEXT STEP:</p>\n<p>This job will start out part-time, but depending on how fast you can excel and demonstrate your abilities, this can change to a full-time position.</p>\n<p>If you&rsquo;re interested, please complete the questionnaire in the following link AND send your resume to&nbsp;<a href="mailto:info@yoyochinese.com" target="_blank">info(at)yoyochinese(dot)com</a>.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/yoyoprojectmanager" target="_blank">https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/yoyoprojectmanager</a></p>\n<p>Thank you, and we look forward to hearing from you soon!</p>\n</section>\n<section id="perks"></section>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/yoyoprojectmanager', 'info@yoyochinese.com', 5, 174, 2),
(541, 1404144370, 'Staff Accountant', 'Wu and Wang Associates Inc', 'Finance', 'Rowland Heights, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Rowland Heights', 33.976124, -117.905342, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '罗兰岗', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>CPA firm in Rowland Heights seeking experienced full-time staff accountant. Duties include preparing individual and business income tax returns, sales tax returns, payroll tax returns and bookkeeping. Must be fluent in Chinese and English. Will train if needed.</p>\n<p>Please email resume and salary history.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=95a536f44be1f94c', '', 5, 152, 2),
(542, 1404144432, '中文 Marketing Coordinator', '国泰银行 Cathay General Bancorp', 'Marketing', 'El Monte, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'El Monte', 34.068623, -118.027565, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '艾尔蒙地', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Create strategic, thoughtful media plans for bank campaigns/promotions and make recommendations based on target market/audience analysis, pricing, etc.</li>\n<li>Serve as the primary media contact and foster ongoing media relationships.</li>\n<li>Execute media buys (TV, print, online, radio, and directories) and manage deadlines.</li>\n<li>Provide ad material information for ad creation/adaptation.</li>\n<li>Coordinate Chinese press releases and marketing copy for various marketing materials/collaterals.</li>\n<li>Review and edit Chinese copy submitted internally and from ad agencies/vendors.</li>\n<li>Invoicing &ndash; review all media contracts and final invoices; verify expenses for project leaders&rsquo; approval.</li>\n<li>Maintain marketing statements for bank control accounts; prepare monthly statements for approval; prepare petty cash (by checks) for corporate events, recordkeeping, etc.</li>\n<li>Support other units in the bank for Chinese translation, e.g., web page content updates, HR documents, VRS scripts (Call Center), Compliance notices, customer letters, branch signage, etc.</li>\n<li>Source and review new media channels for potential advertising opportunities.</li>\n<li>Coordinate and assist with branch merchandising and merchandising communications.</li>\n<li>Provide support to team leaders as needed for various projects and ad hoc tasks.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br />QUALIFICATIONS</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Some marketing and/or banking experience a plus.</li>\n<li><strong>Bilingual &ndash; strong written and verbal skills in Cantonese or Mandarin</strong>.</li>\n<li>Proficient Chinese copywriting ability.</li>\n<li>Can multi-task and work within tight deadlines.</li>\n<li>Possess a strong interest in media planning and public relations.</li>\n<li>A wide degree of creativity and latitude is expected.</li>\n<li>Working knowledge of a wide range of software including MS Office (Word, Excel, Outlook, and Publisher), Adobe, and Illustrator.</li>\n<li>College graduate with major in marketing, public relations, or communications preferred.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>It is the individual responsibility of every employee to maintain a current awareness and understanding of appropriate banking laws, regulations, internal policies and procedures, and to comply fully with those laws, regulations, policies and procedures.</p>\n<p><br />From time to time, employees may be assigned tasks or duties as deemed appropriate by their supervisors.</p>\n<p><br />The above statements are intended to describe the general nature and level of work being performed.&nbsp; They are not intended to be construed, as an exhaustive list of all responsibility, duties and skills required of personnel so classified.</p>\n<p><br />EOE. Minorities/Women/Protected Veterans/Individuals with Disabilities</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://jobview.monster.com/Marketing-Coordinator-Job-El-Monte-CA-US-136054885.aspx', '', 5, 327, 2),
(544, 1404230943, 'SAT Program Coordinator', 'The Salvation Army', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美国', '纽约州', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong><br />Responsible for SAT Program Math and English Curriculum&nbsp;<br /><br />Teach and assigned class materials and exams&nbsp;<br /><br />Supervising and monitoring the program activities&nbsp;<br /><br />Report students&rsquo; SAT result&nbsp;<br /><br />Ensure supervision of students at all times&nbsp;<br /><br />Be present and invite students to Fellowship time.&nbsp;<br /><br />Prepare a &ldquo;good job&rdquo; sheet for each student&nbsp;<br /><br />Other assignments and tasks may be added at the discretion of The Salvation Army.&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>Requirements:</strong><br /><strong>Qualifications:</strong><br />Bachelor Degree or over&nbsp;<br /><br />Have experience and work for the SAT Program for 2 year or more;&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>Bilingual, able to speak and write in Chinese and English</strong>; additional dialects a plus;&nbsp;<br /><br />Matured individual with ability to exhibit patience, compassion and sensitivity to the emotional needs of student;&nbsp;<br /><br />Ability to remain calm and work under pressure or tense environment.&nbsp;</p>', '', 'Maureen.Ki@use.salvationarmy.org', 5, 161, 2),
(545, 1404231287, 'Primary Care Physician', 'Reunion Medical Services', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美国', '纽约州', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="articleBody">\n<p>BC/BE IM/FP physician needed&nbsp;for an expanding primary care services in Flushing, NYC area. Office-based practices only. NO inpatient work. New IM/FP graduate welcome to apply! Chinese speaking a plus. Great pay and benefits. Partnership offered. Please send CV.</p>\n</div>', '', 'unimed11355@hotmail.com', 5, 128, 2),
(546, 1404231500, 'Import Logistic Coordinator', 'Maxfieldseafood', 'International Commerce', 'City of Industry, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'City of Industry', 34.019733, -117.958672, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '因达斯特里', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Seafood company in City of Industry is seeking a full time Import Logistics Coordinator.&nbsp;</p>\n<div>\n<div>*Assist the Import Manager with incoming container shipments.</div>\n<div>*Experience in freight forwarding and international trading is a plus.&nbsp;</div>\n<div><strong>*Must be bilingual in Chinese and English.&nbsp;</strong></div>\n</div>\n<div>*Quick learner, Multi-task, Organized and must have experience in Microsoft Office (Excel, Word, Outlook, etc...)</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Benefits available after 60 days (Health, Dental &amp; Vision)</div>', '', 'hr@maxfieldseafood.com', 5, 296, 2),
(547, 1404231892, 'Project Engineer', 'Alpine', 'Engineering', 'Torrance, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Torrance', 33.835850, -118.340630, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '托伦斯', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Alpine Electronics of America, Inc. is the industry-leading manufacturer of high performance mobile electronics, founded in 1978. Alpine is the only manufacturer specializing in mobile multimedia, an integrated system approach incorporating digital entertainment, security and navigation products for your mobile entertainment. As a consolidated subsidiary of Alps Electric Co., Ltd., one of the world''s premier manufacturers of electronic components for computer, communications and car electronic equipment, Alpine is the specialized supplier of quality mobile electronics systems.&nbsp;<br /><br />We are currently seeking an experienced Project Engineer to join our Product Engineering Group (PEG) located at our headquarter office in Torrance, California . This position is primarily responsible for, but is not limited to the following areas:&nbsp;<br /><br /></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Coordinates multiple projects, creation of project development plans as well as reporting development status of new or existing products with focus on Local Development activities with the global Alpine team.</li>\n<li>Supports wide range of technologies related to automotive electronics, consumer electronics or mobile application products.</li>\n<li>Demonstrates strong communication skills with many areas of the organization including the customers, suppliers, internal staffs, management, and the global Alpine team members.</li>\n<li>Ability to categorize and describe subtle, audible nuances in various audio products (including speakers, amplifiers and other playback sources). This ability should be augmented by a thorough knowledge of various electrical test equipment and software.</li>\n<li>In situations where a test is not readily available to make objective, quantitative measurements, the candidate must have enough technical knowledge of the device under test to develop a test to give the needed results.</li>\n<li>Requires technical writing skills and an excellent command of the English language will support duties involving the creation of manuals for locally developed products or the proof-reading of manuals created overseas.</li>\n<li>Working from home or during off business hours is not uncommon could arise under extreme circumstances or during business travel.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements&nbsp;<br /><br /></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Minimum BS degree in Electrical Engineering or equivalent.</li>\n<li>Typically, two years related automotive electronics experience or equivalent combination of education, training and experience.</li>\n<li>System level A14experience with automotive electronics, consumer electronics, smart phones or other mobile electronics products is preferred.</li>\n<li>Sound knowledge of technical communication, interpersonal, and project analysis skills along with ability to set and meet deadlines.</li>\n<li>Ability to read, analyze and interpret technical documents, professional journals and technical procedures.</li>\n<li>Ability to effectively present information and respond to questions from groups of managers, clients, customers and the general public. In some cases, presenting learned technologies in the from of a training session or PowerPoint presentation may be required.</li>\n<li>Sound knowledge of Bluetooth, WiFi or other wireless technologies.</li>\n<li>Ability to implement and adhere to processes and procedures.</li>\n<li>Basic troubleshooting skills.</li>\n<li>Project Management skills and ability to manage multiple projects.</li>\n<li><strong>Ability to speak/write Japanese and/or Chinese (Mandarin), is a plus but not required.</strong></li>\n<li>Domestic and International quarterly travel may be required.</li>\n</ul>', 'https://alpine.ats.hrsmart.com/cgi-bin/a/highlightjob.cgi?jobid=431', '', 5, 172, 2),
(548, 1404232285, 'Senior Architect', 'archinect.com', 'Design', 'Long Beach, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Long Beach', 33.770050, -118.193741, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '长滩', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>International architectural firm seeks experienced architect fluent in Mandarin and English to be based in Los Angeles office. &nbsp;<strong>Background in detailed schematic production and Chinese standards a plus</strong>. &nbsp;Helpful if familiar with hospitality and entertainment design. &nbsp;Full-time position with benefits after two-month trial period. &nbsp;Please respond with resume, portfolio and salary requirements.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://archinect.com/jobs/entry/103092957/senior-architect', '', 5, 120, 2),
(549, 1404262364, '客户经理', 'adSage', 'Marketing', 'Bellevue, WA, United States', 'United States', 'Washington', 'Bellevue', 47.610378, -122.200676, '美利坚合众国', '华盛顿', '贝尔维尤', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>Account Manager</strong></p>\n<p>Hiring office location: Bellevue, WA</p>\n<p>Account Manager is responsible for:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Day to day operations of client''s digital marketing campaigns, providing reports and analysis of account performance and offering actionable insights to client.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Design and execute testing programs to optimize campaign, content, and performance.</li>\n<li>Collaborate with other departments internally to provide best customer experience and results to clients.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>BS/BA in quantitative business, marketing, research, or equivalent experience preferred.</li>\n<li>Fluency in Chinese and English required</li>\n<li>1+ years of working experience preferred.</li>\n<li>Understanding of&nbsp;Search Engine Marketing fundamentals.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Ability to integrate and analyze data from multiple sources to create actionable insights.</li>\n<li>Excellent communication and presentation skills.</li>\n<li>Prior experience in customer service and/or marketing&nbsp;industry is a plus.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Applicants must be legal to work in the US.</p>\n<p>About adSage</p>\n<p>adSage is&nbsp;a leading online advertising technologies and services provider in China, employing&nbsp;over&nbsp;600&nbsp;professionals in six offices across U.S. and China. adSage is driven to help companies successfully enter the China market by providing professional consultations and digital marketing campaign services.&nbsp;adSage is also the authorized international partner of Baidu, 360 and Sogou in North America. For more information please visit www.adsage.cn.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 'katherinez@adsage.com', 879, 144, 2),
(550, 1404263878, '市场销售', '美国通訊網络及能源公司', 'Marketing', 'San Francisco, CA, United States ', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '旧金山', 'None', 'Part Time', '<p>灣區-美国通訊網络及能源公司招聘人才，sale/Marketing，業績獎金，業績月薪，年度假，有機會發展國際市場（2016开始发展 台湾），招聘人數有限，請email 聯絡。</p>\n<p>hui_franco99@hotmail.com</p>', '', 'hui_franco99@hotmail.com', 816, 218, 2);
