(551, 1404343440, '职点迷津 北美寻人启事（招聘启事）', 'trans-new.com', 'Technology', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美国', '纽约州', '纽约', 'None', 'Part Time', '<header class="entry-header">\n<h1 class="entry-title">职点迷津 北美寻人启事（招聘启事）</h1>\n</header>\n<div class="entry-content">\n<p>1.体力过人，精力旺盛。具体是指能够在团队里自由协作，长期能待机，瞬间可激活。放心，我们还是会比最苦逼的互联网公司轻松的。林黛玉请绕行。</p>\n<p>2.承压能力强悍，应变力强。具体是指能即时响应&ldquo;一夜七次郎&rdquo;：一晚上自我否定七轮这都不叫事儿，要有死磕精神。玻璃心请绕行。</p>\n<p>3.有清晰的目标感和彪悍的执行力。具体是指自己吹过的牛逼都能自己变成现实，以及，罗胖吹过的牛逼你也能变成行动。空想家请绕行。</p>\n<p>4.有良好的合作界面。能快速与人建立合作关系，沟通中善于提供解决方案，是个&ldquo;理性乐观派&rdquo;。阴谋论者请绕行。</p>\n<p>5.聪明到能够低调隐藏自己的智商优越感。具体是指在过去一年中你至少每月读过一本&ldquo;硬硬的好书&rdquo;。请以书单为证。知音杂志不算，中医养生术不算。</p>\n<p>我们提供：<br /> 1.先进的互联网思维</p>\n<p>2.北美生活工作的第一手经验</p>\n<p>3.不打卡、不固定工作时间，自我管理为主，彼此较劲为辅；</p>\n<p>4.与中国最牛逼的企业和各界大神合作的机会；</p>\n<p>5.每天都是全新的，绝不在重复中浪费生命；</p>\n<p>6.你自己可以决定在未来公司期权池中的所得份额；</p>\n<p>7.打破社群与公司、上级与下级、部门与部门之间的隔离墙，随时鼓励利用公司资源个人创业，只要你靠谱，公司做你的第一个天使。</p>\n<p>我们寻找：</p>\n<p>岗位一：文案大神</p>\n<p>深度掌握&ldquo;微信体&rdquo;的秘笈，而且具有神速度，耍酷卖萌样样精通，能够把一个活动创意变成朋友圈疯转的微信文案。</p>\n<p>具体要求：</p>\n<p>1.两年以上正式工作经历，有社交媒体内容运营经验者优先；</p>\n<p>2.有在公开渠道发表文字作品者优先；</p>\n<p>3.认同职点迷津价值观，对职点迷津微信内容熟悉；</p>\n<p>4.对文字表达敏感，对错别字零容忍。</p>\n<p>岗位二：会员体验师</p>\n<p>每天与会员打成一片，成为职点迷津百事通，各种信息都能汇总在你的大脑里，即时响应会员们的各种吐槽和询问。</p>\n<p>具体要求：</p>\n<p>1.Excel达人；</p>\n<p>2.普通话标准；</p>\n<p>3.有死磕精神，强迫症和完美主义者优先；</p>\n<p>4.经验丰富的客服达人们优先。</p>\n<p>岗位三：会员运营师</p>\n<p>需要你搭建起团队与会员、会员与会员的连接渠道，让会员小伙伴们线上线下愉快地玩耍起来，同时也要拓展会员社群。</p>\n<p>具体要求：</p>\n<p>1.社交媒体重度患者；</p>\n<p>2.有强烈的好奇心，喜欢捯饬各种新奇特；</p>\n<p>3.有社群运营经验那是极好的，要是再懂点电商那就更好了。</p>\n<p>岗位四：视频TMT内容主编</p>\n<p>罗胖是一个用生命热爱未来、热爱新商业的家伙。创新商业是道大菜，需要有个Big Guy掌勺。因此，我们专门为TMT领域延请重磅主编一枚。</p>\n<p>具体要求：</p>\n<p>1.是深度的创新商业观察者，有洞察力，有判断力。曾担任传统媒体或互联网媒体TMT方向主编或主笔；</p>\n<p>2.会讲故事，能写有逻辑、有层次、有趣味的&ldquo;大稿子&rdquo;；</p>\n<p>3.有牛叉的资料搜集能力，能啃下硬选题；</p>\n<p>4.性格健康阳光，协作能力好，耐罗胖蹂躏。十易其稿并陪罗胖困守演播室8个小时，仍然能快乐吐槽；</p>\n<p>5.有自己的自媒体品牌更受欢迎，职点迷津愿意助你更快共同成长。</p>\n<p>岗位五：视觉设计师</p>\n<p>负责职点迷津各种活动的视觉设计，从页面、海报到移动端全平台覆盖。参与到公司接下来的产品建设，根据目标用户进行创新性设计。</p>\n<p>具体要求：</p>\n<p>1.有两年以上工作经验，美术/平面设计/艺术设计/多媒体设计等相关专业；</p>\n<p>2.有成熟的作品集；</p>\n<p>3.我们需要扎实的美术功底，但我们更需要放飞的想象力，跟我们一起做一些不一样的尝试。</p>\n<p>岗位六：产品经理</p>\n<p>负责职点迷津接下来各种互联网产品尝试，负责团队未来在电商/会员社群等方面的产品创意/构思/筹备/推进/实施。并且负责与外部各种不同背景的企业进行产品技术上的合作与探讨。</p>\n<p>具体要求：</p>\n<p>1.两年以上工作经验，曾独当一面负责过一个产品从最初构思到上线的全流程；</p>\n<p>2.沟通能力好，思路灵活，有想法，愿意去体验一切新奇的事物；</p>\n<p>3.逻辑思维分析能力强，能把控所有需求和节点。</p>\n<p>岗位七：市场经理</p>\n<p>需要针对品牌定位、产品方向，争取各方资源，开发新的市场合作伙伴及合作形式，与行业组织、媒体联系，建立稳定的合作关系；跟进并达成合作，完成方案、合同、相关流程，落实执行并对执行结果负责。</p>\n<p>具体要求：</p>\n<p>1.两年以上市场营销或客户服务经验，能独立撰写合同、方案；</p>\n<p>2.具有敏感的商业和市场意识以及优秀的营销策划能力和业务推进能力；</p>\n<p>3.具备良好的沟通、协调、反应和组织能力；</p>\n<p>4.工作严谨、细致、耐心，具有出色的团队合作精神；</p>\n<p>5.具备英文读写能力。</p>\n<p>如果你觉得自己是符合以上标准的死磕侠，欢迎发邮件给hr@trans-new.com：</p>\n<p>1.请在邮件标题注明&ldquo;【职位】＋个人姓名＋电话&rdquo;；</p>\n<p>2.个人简历请用word格式清晰介绍自己；</p>\n<p>3.请用1000字以内篇幅简要分析&ldquo;职点迷津目前的不足与风险&rdquo;；</p>\n<p>4.能够证明你符合上述标准的各种背景资料(超大附件未必能加分，有料的话一条就过)。</p>\n<p>5.我们会在接下来的很多项目中开放&ldquo;社群职位&rdquo;，如果你暂时不能加入我们团队，届时也可以兼职参与我们的项目，一样可以一起愉快地玩耍。</p>\n<p>如果你有料有趣，那么，有种就来吧。</p>\n</div>', 'http://columbusxp.info/apply', 'hr@trans-new.com', 884, 279, 2),
(552, 1404755431, 'Project Engineer', 'Crosscity construction corp.', 'Engineering', '美国纽约', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', '纽约', '纽约', 'H1B', 'Full Time', '<p>武汉五月花大酒店投资商现在纽约皇后区开发房产项目，现在手头有四个建筑项目，目前招募项目工程师： <br />主要职责：<br />1.协调项目经理工作，负责和设计师，结构师，机械师等方面的人沟通，保证大家清楚项目进程和自己的职责。<br />2.负责建材采购，电话联系供货商，部分建材需要去现场买。<br />3.在建筑工地督促项目的进程，根据建筑图纸安排工作进度，确保按图纸高质量正确施工。<br />4.现场测量，更新建筑图纸。</p>\n<p>基本要求：<br />1.会读 AutoCAD drawing<br />2.能开车，有车，因为有时要去政府部门送文件，取文件，出门采购等。<br />3.工程背景优先。<br />4. quick learner.<br />5. 最好会中文。</p>\n<p>不是建筑背景没关系，来了学就是。<br />有兴趣者请发送简历至： jasongaoxiaofeng@gmail.com</p>', '', 'jasongaoxiaofeng@gmail.com', 458, 167, 2),
(554, 1404834929, 'Press Officer', '香港经济贸易办事处', 'Media', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', '纽约', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<h2>About the Job</h2>\n<div id="jobBodyContent">\n<h2 align="center"><strong><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">Government of the&nbsp;</span></strong><strong><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">Hong Kong</span></strong><strong><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;Special Administrative Region</span></strong></h2>\n<h2 align="center"><strong><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">Hong Kong Economic and Trade Office,&nbsp;</span></strong><strong><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">New York</span></strong></h2>\n<p align="center"><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<h3><strong><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">PRESS&nbsp;</span></strong><strong><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">OFFICER</span></strong></h3>\n<p align="center"><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">(From US$</span><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">5</span><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">6</span><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">,000 to US$</span><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">65</span><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">,000 per annum, depending on experience)</span></p>\n<p align="center"><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p align="justify">The successful candidate will be responsible for assisting the head of the communications and public relations unit with handling public relations, and executing publicity programs and media events in the eastern US; conducting research requests, updating website contents; responding to enquiries from the media and the public; monitoring newspaper reports on Hong Kong/China; compiling news summaries and developing and liaising with relevant contacts.&nbsp;</p>\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p align="justify"><strong><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">Term</span></strong><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">:&nbsp; Two and one-half year contract term.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p align="justify"><strong><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">Gratuity</span></strong><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">:&nbsp; 10% of total base salary, to be paid upon satisfactory completion of the employment contract.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';"><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif;"><strong>Requirements:&nbsp;</strong></span><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif;">(a) Bachelor&rsquo;s degree or equivalent, preferably in public relations, media studies, marketing or related fields; (b) minimum 4 years of relevant public relations and communications experience in public relations consultancies and/or media organizations; (c) excellent presentation and written skills in English and Chinese (preferably in both Cantonese and Putonghua); (d) comprehensive understanding of and keen interest in Hong Kong; (e) strong computer proficiency including proven video editing and production skills; and (f)&nbsp;</span><span style="color: black; font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif;">valid permit for working in the US.</span></span></p>\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';"><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif;">Applications should be made by e-mail or first class mail and must include a complete, detailed resume.&nbsp;&nbsp;If a candidate is selected for interview, original copies of academic qualification certificates and transcripts, record of previous employment and written reference letters must be provided.&nbsp;&nbsp;Applications must arrive&nbsp;<strong>before the closing date.</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;Only short-listed candidates will be notified of the result of their applications.&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p align="center"><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">Hong Kong</span><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;Economic &amp; Trade Office</span></p>\n<p align="center"><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">115 East 54</span><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">th</span><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;Street</span><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">,&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">New York</span><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">,&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">NY</span><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">10022</span><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p align="center"><strong><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">E-mail address:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">jobs@hketony.gov.hk</span></p>\n<p align="center"><strong><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">Closing Date:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';"><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif;"><em>July 21, 2014</em></span></span></span></p>\n<p align="center"><strong><em><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">For more information on our</span></em></strong><strong><em><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;office</span></em></strong><strong><em><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">, please&nbsp;</span></em></strong><strong><em><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">access the following website:</span></em></strong></p>\n<p align="center"><strong><em><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';"><a href="http://www.hketony.gov.hk/ny">www.hketony.gov.hk/ny</a></span></em></strong></p>\n<p><em><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;</span></em></p>\n<p align="center"><em>Personal data provided by job applicants will be used strictly in</em></p>\n<p align="center"><em>accordance with the HKSAR Government&rsquo;s personal data policies,</em></p>\n<p align="center"><em>details of which can be obtained from the Hong Kong Economic &amp; Trade Office.</em></p>\n</div>', '', 'jobs@hketony.gov.hk', 5, 299, 2),
(555, 1404835413, '中英文 Service, Sales Associate', 'Hudson Group', 'Marketing', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', '纽约', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Job Summary</span></strong>: Provide excellent customer service and maximize sales by assisting in the daily operation of the store.</p>\n<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Job Responsibilities</span></strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Acknowledge and greet customers as they enter the store or approach the cashwrap.</li>\n<li>Follow all company policies, cash handling policies and special store loss prevention procedures.</li>\n<li>Communicate effectively with customers, fellow employees and store management.</li>\n<li>Effectively operate a cash register.</li>\n<li>Understand how to sell Lottery tickets, Mass Transportation tickets and Telephone Calling Cards.</li>\n<li>Know basic store layout to assist customers in their selection of product and be able to answer customer questions about the entire store.</li>\n<li>Be knowledgeable and familiar with the surrounding businesses/offerings within the facility.</li>\n<li>Assist other store employees in maintaining security in stores.</li>\n<li>Stock merchandise.</li>\n<li>Inform management of any out of stock situations.</li>\n<li>Help maintain a neat, clean, organized store, which includes sweeping, dusting, straightening of merchandise on store fixtures and displays.</li>\n<li>Perform related work as assigned.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Knowledge, Skill and Ability</span></strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Ability to interact with diverse personalities.</li>\n<li>Proficiency in the operation of a cash register.</li>\n<li>High degree of interpersonal skills.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Education and Experience</span></strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Must Speak English and Chinese</strong></li>\n<li>High School Graduate or equivalent.</li>\n<li>Prior stockroom or warehouse experience preferred.</li>\n</ul>', 'http://hudsongroup.com/careers_details.php?jobid=3295', '', 5, 190, 2),
(556, 1404835716, '中文 Service Coordinator', 'The Shield Institute', 'Finance', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', '纽约', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>SERVICE COORDINATOR</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in health or human services from an accredited college or university with one year&rsquo;s experience either in ID/DD field or in service coordination with any population or Associates degree or equivalent credits in heath or human services with three year''s experience in the ID/DD field or in service coordination with any population. <strong>Bilingual (English/Mandarin Chinese or South Asian Dialect) preferred</strong>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p align="center"><span style="font-family: Arial;"><strong>Letter of interest, a resume and proof of eligibility should be sent to:<br /></strong></span></p>\n<p align="center"><span style="font-family: Arial;"><strong>Director of Human Resources</strong></span></p>\n<p align="center"><span style="font-family: Arial;"><strong>The Shield Institute</strong></span></p>\n<p align="center"><span style="font-family: Arial;"><strong>144-61 Roosevelt Avenue, Flushing, NY 11354</strong></span></p>\n<p align="center"><span style="font-family: Arial;"><strong>Email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:hr@shield.org">hr@shield.org</a></strong></span></p>\n<p align="center"><span style="font-family: Arial;"><strong>Fax: 718-961-7669</strong></span></p>\n<p align="center"><span style="font-family: Arial;"><strong>Visit our website at:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.shield.org/">www.shield.org</a></strong></span></p>\n<p align="center"><span style="font-family: Arial;"><strong>EOE/AAP</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial;"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 'hr@shield.org', 5, 249, 2),
(557, 1404836155, '中文 Project manager', 'NewEgg', 'Management', 'City of Industry, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'City of Industry', 34.019733, -117.958672, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '因达斯特里', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Purpose Of The Job:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<p>Assist Executive Assistant to Chairman by supporting the operational initiatives and corporate project management.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Conduct organizational studies and evaluations, design systems and procedures, conduct work simplification and measurement studies, and prepare operations and procedures manuals to assist management in operating more efficiently and effectively. Includes program analysts and management consultants.</p>\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Responsibilities/Duties:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<ul>\n<li>Identify opportunity for new business development or room for operational efficiency improvement</li>\n<li>Initiate proposal for the identified opportunity and project plan to improve operational efficiency</li>\n<li>Manage project development from initiation to closure.</li>\n<li>Work with project sponsor and stakeholders to complete project charter outlining scope, goals, deliverables, required resources, budget, and timing.</li>\n<li>Complete work breakdown structure to estimate effort required for each task.</li>\n<li>Provide project schedules to identify when each task will be performed.</li>\n<li>Clearly communicate expectations to team members and stakeholders.</li>\n<li>Act as a mediator between stakeholders and team members.</li>\n<li>Resolve any issues and solve problems throughout project life cycle.</li>\n<li>Effectively manage project scope by ensuring any changes to scope are documented and approved with project change request form.</li>\n<li>Track and report on project milestones and provides status reports to sponsors.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Performs other related duties and tasks as assigned by management</li>\n</ul>\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Minimum Requirements &amp; Special Attributes:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor Degree in Business Admin. / Engineering related field.&nbsp; &nbsp;MBA or PMP certification is a plus.</li>\n<li>5 years of E-commerce experience</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Good written and oral communication skills in English and Mandarin Chinese</li>\n</ul>\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Essential Mental and Physical Functions:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">&bull; Sitting for extended periods is common.<br />&bull; Regular use of the telephone and company e-mail for company communication is essential.<br />&bull; Good manual dexterity for the use of common office equipment such as computer terminals, calculator, copiers and FAX machines.<br />&bull; Some short travels between various company sites.<br />&bull; No heavy lifting is expected.<br />\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Equipment Used:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">Standard office and computer equipment including MS Office software.\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Work Environment:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">Standard office environment with limited exposure to elements or health hazards.\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Supervisory Responsibilities:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">Decisions have major implications on the management and operations of an area within a department. Job may contribute to important strategy, operational, and business decisions that affect the department.\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Language Skills:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text"><strong>Must be able to read, write, speak, and comprehend Mandarin Chinese</strong>\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Travel Requirements:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">Less than 5% of the job will require local travel by car between job sites.<br />\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</div>', 'https://careers-newegg.icims.com/jobs/1971/project-manager/job', '', 5, 280, 2),
(558, 1404836872, 'Purchasing Associate', 'APEC, Advanced Purification Engineering Corp', 'Marketing', 'City of Industry, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'City of Industry', 34.019733, -117.958672, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '因达斯特里', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>We are online''s leading brand of water purification products. Our company is conveniently located in City of industry. We are seeking a motivated purchasing/ administrative associate to join our team.</p>\n<p>The primary responsibilities are:</p>\n<p>Provide general purchasing of inventory, materials, &amp; office supplies and equipment.</p>\n<p>Provide comprehensive product and pricing research online.</p>\n<p>Analyze costs in order to stay within the established budget.</p>\n<p>Creating high quality sales, inventory, and costs reports for management.</p>\n<p>Research, negotiate with vendors, able to present our company well and completely.</p>\n<p>Order/ freight coordinating, tracking and resolve issues.</p>\n<p>Perform all necessary admin tasks to support department.</p>\n<p>The ideal candidate must:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>4 year US college degree required.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>2-3 years of related working experience preferred.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fluent in English, bilingual in Chinese preferred (or familiar w/ Chinese culture).</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Must be detail-oriented, reliable, multi-tasking, good learner, strong math &amp; PC skills.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Has passion for always learning new things and helping people.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Excellent written and verbal communication skills</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Excellent MS Word, Excel, QuickBooks, and Outlook(compatible) skills.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Must have strong attention to detail, patient, organized, and professional.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Must have legal status to be able to work in the U.S.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You will be working in a friendly environment with great benefits and room for growth in a company with 17 year business history. This is a great opportunity for any career minded individuals who is seeking for an exciting career and becoming a crucial member of a top ecommerce company. We look forward to hearing from you.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=518ce4ebc2deec62', '', 5, 219, 2),
(559, 1404837106, 'Retail Sales Associate', 'Tumi', 'Marketing', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '旧金山', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Overview:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<p>We are&nbsp;the high-profile, leading-edge luxury lifestyle brand with an ever-expanding international presence. We have developed a dedicated following among the world&rsquo;s most discerning consumers: celebrities, politicians, business innovators and affluent travelers. These influential style leaders choose&nbsp;our products because they offer the ultimate in sophisticated design, unsurpassed quality and smart functionality.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>We are currently seeking a Mandarin Chinese speaking&nbsp;<strong>Retail Sales Associate.</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Responsibilities:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Maximizing&nbsp;sales by enhancing&nbsp;our brand image.</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ensuring a consistent and superior customer experience.</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Development of&nbsp;new customer relationships and interaction&nbsp;with existing customers to increase sales.</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Attainment of&nbsp;monthly sales, conversion and other KPI goals.</p>\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Qualifications:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<p>In addition to intelligence and&nbsp;high energy,&nbsp;the ideal candidates will have related luxury or specialty retail experience, a good selling presence and superior customer service skills. Fluency in both Mandarin Chinese and English is required.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'https://retailcareers-tumi.icims.com/jobs/1831/sales-associate-%28mandarin-chinese-speaking%29/job', '', 5, 198, 2),
(560, 1404869283, 'Data Analyst 数据分析', 'CLE', 'Finance', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', '纽约', '纽约', 'H1B', 'Full Time', '<p>You must be passionate about digging into data and understanding the stories the data are telling. You will be equally passionate about helping others solve problems, gain insights, and make decisions using data.</p>\n<p>Requirements&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Interprets results using a variety of techniques, ranging from simple data aggregation via statistical analysis to complex data mining independently.</li>\n<li>Basic knowledge of Excel (formulas, formatting, navigation, filtering); Intermediate</li>\n<li>Detail-oriented, ability to focus on a repetitive task for long periods of time.</li>\n<li>Quantitative background/experience preferred; high degree of numeracy (computation, estimation, interpretation)</li>\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in related field such as math, science, business, engineering, or social science or equivalent work experience</li>\n<li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills</li>\n<li>Problem-solving ability</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Email your Resume and Cover letter to&nbsp;CLEcareer@hotmail.com</p>\n<p>择优办理H1B</p>', '', 'CLEcareer@hotmail.com', 902, 9, 2),
(561, 1404870834, 'Financial Analyst', 'Asia Bank', 'Finance', 'NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', '纽约', '纽约', 'H1B', 'Full Time', '<p>Skills &amp; Requirements</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Developing, maintaining and analyzing complex scenario-based financial models to forecast consolidated company</li>\n<li>Preparation of quarterly and annual reports on Form 10-Q and 10-K&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Monitor regulatory rules and FAQs for changes to reporting requirements and communicate those changes to affected schedule owners and data aggregators.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Qualifications&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-Strong analytical skills/ Fundamental knowledge of corporate finance</p>\n<p>-A bachelor''s degree in business, finance, economics or engineering. MBA preferred.</p>\n<p>-Knowledge of corporate finance principles including ability to perform balance sheet analysis, net income statement analysis, cash flow analysis</p>\n<p>-Requires ability to handle multiple tasks.</p>\n<p>Will sponsor H1B or other working visa for the right candidates.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Please Email your resume and cover letter with at least one reference letter to&nbsp;abkhrjack@hotmail.com</p>', '', 'abkhrjack@hotmail.com', 903, 3, 2),
(562, 1405439250, '市场营销专员（兼职）', '北美SPA折扣网 Doubleowl', 'Marketing', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '旧金山', 'None', 'Part Time', '<div class="longwb_box S_line3">\n<div class="WBA_content">\n<p>职位名称：市场营销专员（兼职）</p>\n<p>工作地点：加州旧金山湾区东北部</p>\n<p>细分城市：Richmond，Berkeley，Concord，Walnut Creek，Antioch</p>\n<p>职位描述：</p>\n<p>1、在以上细分城市中寻找潜在商家，代表公司与商家签署合作合同</p>\n<p>2、通过线上线下的方式，向更多的人宣传DoubleOwl网站，以及其他附</p>\n<p>属社交网络，提高知名度。</p>\n<p>3、定期对所在区域进行相关数据收集与分析，可以将数据报告给总部，</p>\n<p>并提出改进方案。</p>\n<p>应聘条件：</p>\n<p>1、对市场营销工作抱有热情，中英文流利，善于与人交流。</p>\n<p>2、对SPA，Massage行业有经验，或者有兴趣，乐于学习。</p>\n<p>3、具备良好的心理素质，能够妥善处理好商家与公司之间的问题。</p>\n<p>4、具备良好的数据分析能力、沟通技巧。</p>\n<p>简介与福利：</p>\n<p>1、充满激情和年轻活力的创业团队。</p>\n<p>2、专业服务湾区数年，行业领先，发展迅速。</p>\n<p>3、优厚的薪资待遇：成功签单100家SPA/ Massage店，可获得$15000</p>\n<p>酬金。（另，签单5家、10家、20家等不同级别，有其他相对应酬金。</p>\n<p>有意者可邮件预约详谈。）</p>\n<p>4、可以接受公司提供的专业培训，积累人脉，获得销售经验，特别优</p>\n<p>秀的有机会获得公司颁发的证书及推荐信。</p>\n<p>欢迎你加入北美最有影响力的专业SPA折扣信息网 DoubleOwl.com(新浪微博&nbsp;<a href="http://www.weibo.com/n/%E5%8C%97%E7%BE%8ESPA%E6%8A%98%E6%89%A3%E7%BD%91_Doubleowl">@北美SPA折扣网_Doubleowl</a>&nbsp;)。在这里，你的兴趣可以得到满足，你的特长可以得到发挥，你的想法可以获得采纳。</p>\n<p>请发送你的中英文简历至：vasilyx@doubleowl.com (邮件标题请注明：你的姓名+应聘），我们会在第一时间给予回复。&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</div>', '', 'vasilyx@doubleowl.com', 5, 204, 2),
(563, 1405439660, 'Bilingual Medical Marketing Representative', 'RS Medical Imaging', 'Marketing', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', '纽约', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>A growing radiology facility seeking to immediately hire a bright individual that can speak both English and Chinese to help represent the company and act as a liaison between itself and referring physicians.</p>\n<p>The job will entail marketing the company to various physicians'' offices and practices in the Brooklyn and Queens, New York area. The radiology field is developing and expanding in new ways and this individual will help develop new business relations as well as maintaining existing ones. He/she must speak English and Chinese. The individual should have great communication skills, patience, and be highly motivated. An understanding of the medical/radiology field is not required but would be beneficial.</p>\n<p>The position is for full time employment only and will include a salary as well as potential bonuses. Typical working days and hours are Monday through Friday from 9:00 am until 5:30 pm.<br />Must haves:</p>\n<p>-Ability to speak Chinese and English<br />Please fax a resume and cover letter to 718-975-2990 or call 718-686-0895/ 347-627-4215.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=aaf1ece25f0c7c9c', '', 5, 139, 2),
(564, 1405440012, 'Account Executive', 'Marc Jacobs International', 'Marketing', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', '纽约', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<article>\n<h2>JOB DESCRIPTION</h2>\n<div id="job_description">\n<p>Manages the MBMJ wholesale international business in Southeast Asia, Japan, and Taiwan.&nbsp; Develops implements &amp; manages plans to drive sales within these regions. Responsible for meeting/exceeding sales goals.<br /><br /></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Partners closely with Director of Sales and Senior Management to develop, implement &amp; analyze international business strategies to maximize overall sales growth &amp; profitability in assigned regions.</li>\n<li>Foster and maintain Strong relationships with our company owned and franchise partners in Asia.</li>\n<li>Maintains updated knowledge of sales &amp; market trends &amp; practices within the industry.</li>\n<li>Sell-in seasonal merchandise to franchise partners that meets regional needs while maintaining brand aesthetic</li>\n<li>Monitors &amp; reports on sales, budgets &amp; costs to Director and Senior Management on a regular basis.</li>\n<li>Sources new ideas and identifies strategies to improve and grow the MBMJ business in assigned regions.</li>\n<li>Troubleshoots &amp; provides solutions to sales team on customer service issues.</li>\n<li>Develops/coordinates special discounts, sales &amp; promotions with Hong Kong office and partners</li>\n<li>Travel to Asia to Stay abreast of industry trends and conditions.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</article>\n<article>\n<h2>QUALIFICATIONS</h2>\n<div id="qualifications">\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelors Degree&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Minimum 3-5 years relevant experience in international retail specialty or luxury/fashion environment</li>\n<li>Excellent communication and organizational skills</li>\n<li>Strong computer skills</li>\n<li>Well-developed interpersonal skills.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Ability to multitask</li>\n<li>Manage from a distance</li>\n<li>Act as brand ambassador</li>\n<li>Experience in luxury retail</li>\n<li>Bilingual in Mandarin Chinese a plus</li>\n<li>Seeking a self-starter with strong organizational skills, detailed oriented</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article>', 'https://www.smartrecruiters.com/MarcJacobs/77993089-account-executive-mbmj-international', '', 5, 240, 2),
(565, 1405440802, 'Chinese Speaking Contact Center Quality Analyst', 'BPA International', 'Marketing', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', '纽约', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>Company Overview :</strong><br />BPA Quality is the world leader in providing Remote Call Quality Assurance solutions to the Call Center Industry.&nbsp;<br />Our activities are focused on maximizing the potential of the vital contact between an organization and its customer through Contact Centers.&nbsp;<br />The core of our business is providing Remote Call Monitoring Services where we evaluate interactions between Agents and Customers &ndash; in a minimum of 25 languages. From this Analysis we are able to provide detailed feedback that can be used to improve Agent performance as well as helping organizations develop overall strategies to improve Customer Service and Maximize Sales.&nbsp;<br />In addition to the analysis of customer/agent contacts, BPA provides proactive support and advice to help our clients use the resulting data. Whether it&rsquo;s helping construct metrics to measure performance or providing training to help Supervisors coach more effectively, our objective is to develop a close working partnership with our Clients in their pursuit of excellence in customer service and customer engagement.&nbsp;<br />www.bpaquality.com&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>What You&rsquo;ll Do:</strong><br />Analyze contacts (Phone/Chat/Email/Social Media) for trends that will enable our clients to grow and develop their internal teams and external teams&nbsp;<br /><br />Communicate professional and grammatically correct coaching comments&nbsp;<br /><br />Apply technology, scripts, and product knowledge&nbsp;<br /><br />Ensure that all customer contacts are properly logged into a secure online database&nbsp;<br /><br />Liaise with various BPA departments, i.e. Research, etc.&nbsp;<br /><br />Attend team meetings, pep sessions, focus groups, and training sessions as scheduled&nbsp;<br /><br />Work on activities and/or projects as requested by the Team Leader&nbsp;<br /><br />Identify and relay to Team Leader areas for improvement within the evaluating and coaching delivery process&nbsp;<br /><br />Relay customer/client service problems to Team Leader when necessary&nbsp;<br /><br />Support the operation through business processes and practices designed to support employee retention, productivity, profitability, and consumer satisfaction&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>Call Researcher Job Requirements:</strong><br />Fluent Mandarin Speaker&nbsp;<br /><br />Must have lived and worked in China for a minimum of 5 years&nbsp;<br /><br />Some College Work/Graduate preferred&nbsp;<br /><br />One year of customer service experience, call center preferred&nbsp;<br /><br />Technically proficient in Microsoft Word, Excel and Outlook&nbsp;<br /><br />Aptitude for technology (e.g., Multiple Operating Systems, Mobile, Entertainment Interfaces)&nbsp;<br /><br />Must be able to type 25 WPM&nbsp;<br /><br />Experience in customer service and sales greatly preferred&nbsp;<br /><br />Strong written and oral communication skills with all levels of the organization&nbsp;<br /><br />Must be able to pass a full background check&nbsp;<br /><br />Strong customer service, interpersonal and relationship-building skills&nbsp;<br /><br />Strong multi-tasking skills&nbsp;<br /><br />Strong organizational, time management, planning and problem solving skills&nbsp;<br /><br />Strong team building skills, to work well within a close team environment- self sufficient&nbsp;<br /><br />Demonstrate a strong desire to succeed&nbsp;<br /><br />Resourceful and works well with minimal supervision&nbsp;<br /><br />Ability to demonstrate a high degree of professionalism&nbsp;<br /><br />Working knowledge of computers&nbsp;<br /><br />Experience with Customer Contact systems an asset&nbsp;<br /><br />Quality Monitoring experience is an asset&nbsp;</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=8768d5e0b9ff234e', '', 5, 202, 2),
(566, 1405441092, '中文 Accounting Assistant', 'Regional Centers Holding Group ', 'Finance', 'Long Beach, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Long Beach', 33.770050, -118.193741, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '长滩', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Summary: A fast growing international business is seeking a full-time Accounting Assistant to collect and report its financial data to help CPA in tax return and financial report preparation, book keep its capital, asset/liability, loan, and investment accounts, compiling monthly reports, opening and maintaining investment accounts etc.</p>\n<p>Responsibilities<br />Document company and client financial transactions<br />Prepare revenue/sales monthly entries<br />Open, maintain and resolve issues on clients&rsquo; accounts<br />Reconcile both domestic and overseas corporate bank accounts</p>\n<p>Qualifications: Undergraduate degree in accounting or equivalent. Familiarity with Quickbooks and Microsoft Excel, experience using any other accounting software a plus. Must be a quick learner and team player, strong knowledge in Accounting and Corporate Finance is needed. Good reporting and presentation skills, attention to detail, deadline-oriented, able to read and research on internet and report results, keep confidentiality, knows how to manage time, decent data entry and math skills. A foreign language in Chinese is required.</p>\n<p>Salary/Pay: Competitive W-2 salary, medial insurance, vacation days etc. based on individual qualifications.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=b153365173cc000b', '', 5, 289, 2),
(567, 1405441442, 'Branch Manager - Westminster Branch (Pacific Rim Division) ', 'Bank of the West', 'Finance', 'Westminster, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Westminster', 33.751343, -117.993996, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '威斯敏斯特', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>What sets Bank of the West apart from other banks is our team members&ndash;they embody the optimistic spirit of the West. There is a spirit here that drives us to do more. Our team of more than 10,000 employees is vital to the success of our Bank. They reflect our modern western values&mdash;straightforward, entrepreneurial and optimistic. We seek to create a corporate culture that fosters and rewards excellence, encourages creative thinking and respects diversity &ndash; an environment where team members are engaged, supportive of one another and enthusiastic about serving our customers. Bank of the West offers the stability of a company that has a 135 year history and is part of BNP Paribas, a European leader in global banking and financial services and one of the 6 strongest banks in the world. We offer opportunities across our diverse business lines &ndash; Retail Banking, Commercial Banking, National Finance, and Wealth Management.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Position Summary</strong></p>\n<p><a name="Text6"></a>Responsible for the sales/service activities, marketing plan, operating budget, profitability and operational integrity of the branch.&nbsp;&nbsp;Provides overall leadership for the branch.&nbsp;&nbsp;Understands, communicates and works to achieve the mission of the Bank.&nbsp;&nbsp;This description applies to five levels (Job Codes 2075, 1647, 1645, 1644 and 1641.)&nbsp;&nbsp;Level assignment is based on a variety of factors including, but not limited to: scope and complexity of responsibility, market area, size of office, experience and expertise of manager.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Position Accountabilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a name="Text44"></a>Ensures that the branch sales/service supports the overall corporate objective to provide superior service. Participates in selling Bank products and providing excellent customer service.</li>\n<li><a name="Text8"></a>Plans, implements, and manages the operating and capital budgets to maximize branch profitability.</li>\n<li><a name="Text9"></a>Ensures that the branch meets all regulatory compliance standards.&nbsp;&nbsp;Follows all operating policies and procedures.&nbsp;&nbsp;Ensures branch personnel comply with all laws and regulations. Documents and communicates individual compliance performance in annual staff evaluations.</li>\n<li><a name="Text10"></a>Directs branch business development through outside calls, in-branch selling,&nbsp;&nbsp;telemarketing, branch campaigns, and targeted direct mailing.&nbsp;&nbsp;Develops and manages an annual branch marketing plan with specific goals.</li>\n<li><a name="Text11"></a>Ensures expansion of customer relationships through branch cross-selling activities.</li>\n<li><a name="Text12"></a>Manages the branch portfolio for optimum performance.</li>\n<li>Promotes staff development through training, cross-training, and career planning.&nbsp;&nbsp;Trains staff in the area of customer service, sales, operations,&nbsp;&nbsp;and Bank products.&nbsp;&nbsp;Ensures that ongoing sales and product service training is provided.</li>\n<li>Oversees and administers all branch human resource issues.</li>\n<li>Participates in events that demonstrate support for the community and increase business opportunities for the Bank.&nbsp;&nbsp;Ensures compliance with CRA outreach programs.</li>\n<li>Performs other duties as assigned.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Qualifications</h2>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Required Education or Equivalent Experience</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree Required</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Required Experience</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Years of functional/professional experience:&nbsp;<a name="Text41"></a>Five to eight years banking experience; Five years lending experience including commercial, consumer and real estate (depending upon branch)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Field of Experience</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Complete knowledge of sales, branch banking and consumer lending</li>\n<li>Working knowledge of the Bank&rsquo;s products (i.e., deposits, cash management, loans and other fee income generating products).</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'https://botw.taleo.net/careersection/jobdetail.ftl?job=007013', '', 5, 158, 2);
