(568, 1405525454, 'Generalist Junior Research Analyst', '某全球顶级咨询公司', 'Consulting', 'Shanghai, China', 'China', 'Shanghai', 'Shanghai', 31.230415, 121.473701, '中国', '上海市', '上海', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p align="left">Talents are needed to fill out our Generalist Junior Research Analyst vacancies.&nbsp; This position provides an excellent&nbsp;platform for&nbsp;junior researchers to build up broad and solid fundamental&nbsp;knowledge and skills in a wide range of topics, including macroeconomics, public sector, real estate, etc.<br />&nbsp;<br /><strong>PRIMARY RESPONSIBILITIES</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Based in Shanghai, provide research support to consulting teams worldwide looking at the Chinese market</li>\n<li>Articulate, scope, and prioritize research needs, and identify and gather relevant company, industry, and economic information using a broad spectrum of appropriate sources&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Provide synthesis, insight, and practical implications within tight deadlines, via end products in the form of single exhibits, written summaries, basic fact packs, and spreadsheets Conduct interviews with regulators and companies and share insights&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Serve as a thought partner, leveraging internal and external networks, to engage in team problem solving, share evolving business trends and best practices, and contribute to knowledge creation initiatives&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Continue to build knowledge in wide range of fields, as well as to identify, review, and maintain information sources and databases</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p align="left"><strong>EXPECTED CREDENTIALS</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Excellent communication skills in English and Mandarin (both oral and written)&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Bachelor and/or master''s degree from top universities&nbsp;</li>\n<li>0-2 years work experience&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Solid understanding of economic, financial and general business concepts and terminology&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Experience in conducting business or academic research&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Comprehensive computer skills including database searching, power point, word processing, spreadsheet analysis and online research&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Good people skills, team orientation, and professional&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>', 'http://blog.renren.com/blog/301211369/931350043', 'ishafaa02@experis.com.cn', 5, 292, 2),
