(573, 1406045868, 'Mandarin Preschool Head Teacher', 'Mandarin Seeds', 'Language', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', '纽约', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Seeking a head teacher for a 100% Mandarin immersion preschool program that incorporates arts, music, science, stories, and Mandarin language learning in the curriculum. <strong>The candidate must be a native speaker in Mandarin Chinese</strong>, with education background in Early Childhood education, music education, art education, or bilingual education. Graduate degrees in education-related fields are preferred. The candidate must also have prior teaching experience, as well as skills for creating dynamic lesson plans, implementing classroom management, and communicating students assessment with director and parents. Our ideal teacher is highly motivated, energetic, patient, punctual at all times, and most importantly, love working with children.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=a14170562fc4762b', '', 5, 143, 2),
(574, 1406046075, 'Graphic/Web Designer- Bilingual in Mandarin', 'Product Company', 'Technology', 'Walnut, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Walnut', 34.020290, -117.865341, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '沃尔纳特', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>We are a product company located in Walnut, California. We are currently seeking a web design and developer with PC and Mac experience.<br />The candidate will design company''s website and is capable of working with different social media Apps.<br />Must have a good design eye with presentation and print media experience.<br />Minimum 1 year experience within a company required.<br />Must speak English and Mandarin Chinese.</p>\n<p>If you think you fit the above description, please send us your resume. Be prepared to bring your portfolio and web design to your interview.</p>\n<p>Thank you.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=3c8d2a2da33b820e', '', 5, 154, 2),
(575, 1406046216, 'Restaurant Manager', 'Rice Field Corporation', 'Resturant', 'Rosemead, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Rosemead', 34.080566, -118.072845, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '罗斯米德', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>A Southeast Asian Restaurant is looking for a Restaurant Manager:</p>\n<p>Job Responsibilities</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Ensure all staff members arrive to work on time and well groomed according to the restaurant&rsquo;s Personal Hygiene Policy.</li>\n<li>Maintain safe, secure, and healthy environment by establishing, following, and enforcing sanitation standards and procedures.</li>\n<li>Build sales and guest counts / maximize sales and profits by teaching, coaching and holding meetings with staff members and chefs in regards to the quality of food and services.</li>\n<li>Understand restaurant menu completely and train staff member to introduce or make recommendation when taking orders.</li>\n<li>Control cash and other receipts by adhering to cash handling and reconciliation procedures.</li>\n<li>Ensure that all products are received in correct unit count and condition in accordance with the restaurant&rsquo;s receiving procedures.</li>\n<li>Control costs by minimizing waste and managing inventory.</li>\n<li>Ensure only high standards of food preparation make it out to guests.</li>\n<li>Manage staff performance with clear feedback, recognition, reviews, coaching, and take disciplinary action if necessary.</li>\n<li>Handle all staff and guest requests or concerns quickly with care and fairness.</li>\n<li>Perform other duties and responsibilities as assigned.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Job Requirements and Qualifications</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Must have at least three (3) years full service restaurant management experience.</li>\n<li>Proven track record of success as a restaurant manager.</li>\n<li>Fluent in English and Chinese.</li>\n<li>Demonstrate ability to train and develop employees.</li>\n<li>Proficient in MS Word, Excel, Outlook and familiarity with restaurant POS systems.</li>\n<li>Passion for exceeding guests&rsquo; expectations. Energetic and possess a can-do attitude.</li>\n<li>Detail oriented with the highest standards of accuracy and ethics.</li>\n<li></li>\n</ul>', 'http://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=cd85b555e8654e6a', '', 5, 128, 2),
(576, 1406060789, 'Inside sales and operations manager', 'New Cyberian', 'Technology', 'San Jose, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Jose', 37.339386, -121.894958, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '圣何塞', 'H1B', 'Full Time', '<p>A hi-tech multimedia company in San Jose is looking for a responsible individual to fill a full-time position as an inside sales and operation manager. &nbsp;To qualify for the position you need to have the following qualifications.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Have good common sense</li>\n<li>Fluent in English, both conversational and written</li>\n<li>Detail orientated</li>\n<li>Be responsible</li>\n</ol>\n<p>If you are interested in the position please submit your r&eacute;sum&eacute;. Foreign students with OPT status are welcome to apply.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 'isaac@newcyberian.com', 955, 245, 2),
(577, 1406236548, 'Parent-Child Educator (Teacher)', 'Chinese American Service League', 'Service', 'Chicago, IL, United States', 'United States', 'Illinois', 'Chicago', 41.878113, -87.629799, '美利坚合众国', '伊利诺伊州', '芝加哥', 'None', 'Part Time', '<h1>About CASL</h1>\n<p>A nurturing hub within the heart of Chinatown in Chicago, Chinese American Service League (CASL) is the largest most comprehensive social service agency in the Midwest dedicated to serving the needs of Chinese Americans. Over the years, we continue to connect families and individuals of all ages with the vital support they need to flourish physically, economically, mentally, and socially, enabling them to thrive and contribute to the greater Chicago community. We provide child educational services, elder services, employment training services, employment training services, family counseling, and housing/financial education to clients of all ages and backgrounds. For more information, please check out:&nbsp;<a href="http://caslservice.org/">http://caslservice.org/</a></p>\n<h1>Job Description</h1>\n<p>Using a team approach, the Parent-Child Educator plans, implements, and evaluates classroom programming for families with children, birth to five years old, e.g. participates in team lesson planning and leading age-appropriate group activities. Helps publicize and organize other activities, e.g. field trips. Surveys families for their input; keeps records of participation and feedback from various activities.</p>\n<h2>Mandatory Job Qualifications</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>An Associate''s degree in early childhood education or related field</li>\n<li>Strong written and verbal communication skills&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<div class="post_description">\n<h2>Desired Qualifications</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Chinese/English bilingual preferred</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class="post_apply">\n<h2>How to Apply</h2>\n<p>Please email the followings to Jobs@CASLservice.org:</p>\n<p>Cover letter<br />Resume<br />CASL Application (<a href="http://To%20apply,%20please%20email%20the%20followings%20to%20Jobs@caslservice.org%20%20cover%20letter%20resume%20casl%20application%20%28which%20can%20be%20downloaded%20at%20http">http://caslservice.org/images/stories/pdfs/employment_application.pdf</a>)</p>\n</div>', 'http://caslservice.org/about-us/job-openings', '', 962, 133, 2),
