(602, 1407272542, '中英文翻译员', 'LanguageLine Solutions', 'Language', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '洛杉矶', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="content-sections">\n<section id="job-description-section" class="minimized">\n<h2>JOB DESCRIPTION</h2>\n<div id="pnlJobDescription" class="section-body">\n<p><strong>LanguageLine Solutions</strong>, the world&rsquo;s leading over-the-phone interpretation provider, is seeking to increase its&nbsp;<strong>Chinese (Mandarin, Cantonese)</strong>&nbsp;interpreter personnel.&nbsp;<br /><br /><br />Work from home the days and hours that suit you best! Our interpreters work from the comfort of their home and it is one of the biggest benefits of being a LanguageLine Solutions interpreter. The U.S. Census Bureau says an average employee spends 1,000 hours a year commuting to and from work. By working at home, our interpreters save time, money, gasoline and have a better quality of life.&nbsp;<br /><br /><br />If you have excellent language skills we, will help you become an Over-the-Phone Interpreter. Make a difference in people&rsquo;s lives!&nbsp;<br /><br />Work from the comfort of your home!&nbsp;<br /><br /><br /><strong>We offer:</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Paid orientation &amp; on-going training</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;No experience necessary-- We help you get started!&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>If you are a&nbsp;<strong>Chinese(Mandarin or Cantonese)&nbsp;</strong>speaker and have excellent proficiency in English with a strong listening and comprehension skills as well as good customer service skills you can become an interpreter for LanguageLine Solutions.&nbsp;<br /><br />For over 25 years, LanguageLine Solutions has provided telephone interpretation and document translation services to all cultural communities in over 175 languages, 24 hours a day, every day of the year. For that entire time, it has provided a voice for speakers of Asian, American, European, African and the Pacific island languages, as well as for those who wish to provide services to them.&nbsp;<br /><br />The company is now increasing numbers of employment opportunities in the global economy to all telephone interpreters, particularly&nbsp;<strong>Chinese(Mandarin or Cantonese)&nbsp;</strong>and<strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>English&nbsp;</strong>speakers.&nbsp;<br /><br />If you would like to work from home and are proficient in English and a second language, please apply.</p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p align="center">EOE/AA</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div id="jobDescriptionTextFade">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section id="job-requirements">\n<h2>JOB REQUIREMENTS</h2>\n<div class="section-body">\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Excellent English proficiency along with&nbsp;<strong>Chinese(Mandarin or Cantonese)&nbsp;</strong>proficiency</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Strong listening and comprehension skills</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Outstanding customer service skills</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Eligible to work in the US</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Must be 18 years or older</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;This is a work at home position</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section id="job-snapshot-section">\n<h2>JOB SNAPSHOT</h2>\n<div class="section-body">\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Employment Type</strong>Full-Time/Part-Time</div>\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Job Type</strong>Customer Service, Telecommunications, Other</div>\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Education</strong>Not Specified</div>\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Experience</strong>Not Specified</div>\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Manages Others</strong>Not Specified</div>\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Industry</strong>Other Great Industries, Telecommunications</div>\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Required Travel</strong>Not Specified<br /><br /></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>', 'http://www.careerbuilder.com/jobseeker/jobs/jobdetails.aspx?Job_DID=JHT0NV6MH911TSMDGC5&siteid=cb001&showNewJDP=yes&ipath=EXINDsep_google_feed#', '', 980, 196, 2),
(603, 1407272793, '中文会计助理', 'Regional Centers Holding Group Inc.', 'Finance', 'Long Beach, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Long Beach', 33.770050, -118.193741, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '长滩', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>A fast growing international business is seeking a full-time Accounting Assistant to collect and report its financial data to help CPA in tax return and financial report preparation, book keep its capital, asset/liability, loan, and investment accounts, compiling monthly reports, opening and maintaining investment accounts etc.</p>\n<p>Responsibilities<br />Document company and client financial transactions<br />Prepare revenue/sales monthly entries<br />Open, maintain and resolve issues on clients&rsquo; accounts<br />Reconcile both domestic and overseas corporate bank accounts</p>\n<p>Qualifications:<br />Undergraduate degree in accounting or equivalent.<br />A foreign language in CHINESE is required.<br />Willing to relocate to Long Beach, CA<br />Familiarity with Quickbooks and Microsoft Excel, experience using any other accounting software a plus.<br />Must be a quick learner and team player, strong knowledge in Accounting and Corporate Finance is needed.<br />Good reporting and presentation skills, attention to detail, deadline-oriented, able to read and research on internet and report results, keep confidentiality, knows how to manage time, decent data entry and math skills.</p>\n<p>Salary/Pay: Competitive W-2 salary, medial insurance, vacation days etc. based on individual qualifications.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Regional-Centers-Holding-Group-Inc./jobs/Chinese-Speaking-Accounting-Assistant-b153365173cc000b', '', 980, 241, 2),
(604, 1407273271, '中英文网络营销员', 'Confidence USA, Inc', 'Technology', 'Port Washington, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'Port Washington', 40.825657, -73.698189, '美利坚合众国', '纽约', '华盛顿港', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Confidence U.S.A. Inc., an international manufacturer and retailer of premium dietary supplements and natural health products is searching for a bilingual (English/Mandarin) Internet Marketing Specialist to join our company. The Internet Marketing Specialist coordinates all aspects of e-commerce product marketing material. Works with other internet partners and outside agencies to ensure marketing directions are clear, accurate, and on schedule.</p>\n<p>Responsibilities:<br />- Maintain product marketing and informational content on all applicable websites.<br />- Meet regularly with management and IT for status updates and to discuss new initiatives. Prioritize projects to meet deadlines.<br />- Implement enhancements and updates to the website as well as provide recommendations on how to best meet marketing goals while maintaining usability.<br />-Investigating and implementing new marketing trends and strategies.<br />- Liaise with management and IT to develop new site functionality and to assist in their online initiatives. Troubleshoot site issues and determine appropriate resolution as needed.<br />- Work with outside vendors for creative and production services as necessary.</p>\n<p>Requirements:<br />-Bilingual in Mandarin and English (both written and oral)<br />-Graphic design a plus<br />-SEO experience a plus<br />-Copyright experience a plus<br />-Knowledge of dietary supplement and/or natural health food industry a plus</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/viewjob?cmp=Confidence-USA,-Inc.&t=Bilingual+Internet+Marketing+Specialist&jk=b338a5ff8deadae2&sjdu=QwrRXKrqZ3CNX5W-O9jEvSj0hztkggTN-w372Dbd460JrIjyCvg1xRxymVcO9XI09rhwz1m_ykxr1ANi_F0YqFw0xrM7GNqrdgbxJAYsGkmBbBTVppmnyceHLuu1WaJG', '', 980, 107, 2),
(605, 1407273518, '中国特许经营销售经理', 'Caffébene Inc', 'Marketing', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', '纽约', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Caffebene USA is looking for a Franchise Sales Manager to head the franchise sales efforts in the Chinese American Market.</p>\n<p>Caffe Bene is the leading coffee franchise chain from South Korea. Established in 2008, we have grown to over 1,300 stores all over the world. Entering the US market in 2012, we have opened in 10 American stores, with 20 more to be opened within this year. With our exquisite interior design, healthy diverse menu, and organized business operations system, we distinguish ourselves from our competitors and create a trendy environment of comfort and relaxation.</p>\n<p>Currently, we are looking for a Sales Manager to manage the Chinese team at our NYC headquarters.</p>\n<p>Main duties and responsibilities will include but not limited to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Pitching our company and franchise opportunity to potential Chinese clients</li>\n<li>Building and maintaining trustful relationships with clients</li>\n<li>Following up with clients in a timely manner</li>\n<li>Travelling and working at different franchise shows and seminars</li>\n<li>Coming up with creative ideas for Chinese advertising</li>\n<li>Effectively manage the Chinese sales team</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Education and Experience required:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelors Degree</li>\n<li>3 years minimum of previous sales experience</li>\n<li>Experience in managing others</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Skills and abilities required:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fluency in Mandarin Chinese (speaking, reading, writing)</li>\n<li>The candidate must be able to work independently</li>\n<li>Be able to multitask</li>\n<li>Ability to communicate verbally, and understand and follow written and verbal instructions</li>\n<li>Team player who can work well with different personalities</li>\n<li>Ability to work and adapt in an Asian cultural work environment</li>\n</ul>\n<p>All interested candidates please respond. We are looking to hire as soon as possible.</p>\n<p>Compensation: Based on Experience</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Caffébene-(NYC)/jobs/Chinese-Franchise-Sales-Manager-7974b3938c91eee9', '', 980, 150, 2),
(606, 1407273705, '中文儿童教师', 'China Institute in America', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', '纽约', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>China Institute in America , a non-profit, non-partisan, educational, and bi-cultural organization based in NYC, is seeking experienced children&rsquo;s Mandarin teachers. Grouped by ages three and up, children learn a dynamic mix of Chinese language and culture through a whole language approach in active classroom environments. Successful candidates should be native speakers of Chinese who have teaching experience using simplified characters and who have a very good command of spoken English. They should be vivacious in the classroom and eager to nurture children&rsquo;s learning and growth. They must feel comfortable creating their own curricula and finding materials to suit classroom needs, levels, and abilities. Teaching assignments may entail classroom teaching or private tutoring and may be onsite, offsite in other schools, or in students&rsquo; homes. Classes are taught using simplified characters. Competitive hourly wage.&nbsp;<br /><br />Please send cover letter and CV, including resident status, to:&nbsp;<br /><br />Ms. Shenzhan Liao&nbsp;<br />Director of Education&nbsp;<br /><br />China Institute&nbsp;<br />125 East 65th Street&nbsp;<br />New York, NY 10065</p>', '', 'sliao@chinainstitute.org', 980, 188, 2),
(607, 1407273897, '普通话成人课程教师', 'China Institute in America', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', '纽约', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>China Institute in America , a non-profit, non-partisan, educational, and bi-cultural organization based in NYC, is seeking experienced Mandarin teachers within the tri-state region for its Adult Language Program. Positions currently available include teachers for our group classes, and tutors for our private and corporate tutoring programs.&nbsp;<br /><br />Successful candidates should be native speakers of Chinese who speak standard Mandarin with clear diction and who have a good command of spoken English. They should be comfortable with dealing with students from diverse backgrounds within the business world and private sector; be presentable in appearance and disposition; punctual; enthusiastic in their instruction and, for private tutoring, must be able to choose materials suited for each students&rsquo; needs, level, and abilities. Minimum educational requirement: B.A. degree.&nbsp;<br /><br />Group classes are held onsite at China Institute. All classes use pinyin and simplified characters. Most tutoring assignments are offsite and held at our students&rsquo; office or home with some assignments taking place onsite at China Institute. Competitive hourly wage available. Applicants must have permission to work.&nbsp;<br /><br />Please send cover letter and CV, including resident status, to:&nbsp;<br /><br />Wanling Zhang&nbsp;<br />Program Manager, Adult Language &amp; Studio Programs&nbsp;<br /><br />China Institute&nbsp;<br />125 East 65th Street&nbsp;<br />New York, NY 10065</p>', '', 'wzhang@chinainstitute.org', 980, 272, 2),
(608, 1407278336, '中英双语Customer Service Representative全/兼职', 'GotoBus.com / TakeTours.com', 'Service', 'Monterey Park, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Monterey Park', 34.062511, -118.122849, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '蒙特雷帕克', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>GotoBus.com / TakeTours.com is a leading online marketplace for interstate bus tickets, tours, sightseeing trips, vacation packages and hotels. We partners with over 300 bus and tour operators worldwide and we are one of the fastest growing travel businesses on the internet.<br /><br />We have an immediate opening for Customer Service Representative full-time/part-time positions (9am to 6pm PST). The ideal candidate will have excellent customer service, effective communication skills, and the ability to multitask in a fast paced environment.<br /><br />Job Description:<br /><br />- This position is responsible to assist customers with all phases of their travel arrangements. The individual will be required to respond to customer''s inquiries over the phone, email and live-chat in a courteous manner.&nbsp;<br />- Prepare monthly statements and mail out checks.<br />- Confirm bookings with the tour operators and notify travelers any updates with their itinerary in a timely fashion.<br />- Maintain a close relationship with the service providers and solve any issues related to the booking process.<br /><br />Job Requirements:<br /><br />- Associate Degree or higher education.<br />- Must be able to speak, read and write fluently in both English and Chinese.<br />- Must be able to work on one day on the weekend.<br />- Experience in the travel industry is a plus.</p>', 'http://www.taketours.com/ps/p1/43788.html', 'jobs@gotobus.com', 980, 228, 2),
(609, 1407297122, 'iOS app设计师', '91qin.me', 'Design', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '旧金山', 'None', 'Part Time', '<p>初创团队开发一款社交类的app需要一位志同道合的懂设计ios app的设计师。</p>\n<p>app的构架不会很复杂。会有3到5个views。需要设计一些flow，icon和user interaction。</p>\n<p>有表情设计经验的优先。</p>\n<p>除了会用photoshop和illustrate这些画图工具，最好也会一些交互类的工具，比如proto io或者framerjs之类的。</p>', '', 'wushizhang@gmail.com', 5, 231, 2),
(610, 1407380622, '行政助理', '130 Administrative Services', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '洛杉矶', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Job Responsibilities:<br />This position will provide detailed administrative project support and requires both knowledge of architecture/engineering/construction project processing and strong general hands on administrative skills.</p>\n<p>PRIMARY FUNCTIONS:</p>\n<p>Provide word processing for specifications and contracts (AIA forms) to create Project Manuals and Office Master Specification and Provide administrative support to one or more Managers or Project Teams, including maintaing individual and project related schedules.</p>\n<p>TYPICAL DUTIES <br />&bull;Type project specifications and AIA contract forms using all aspects of the word processing system including spell check, editing techniques and program enhancements to maximize efficient use of the system. <br />&bull;Make typing revisions to specifications for revised editions (i.e. Addenda/Bulletins, Construction Issues etc.) including format revisions to pages as required. <br />&bull;Assemble Addenda, Bulletins and Construction Issues by obtaining the Project Master folder and pulling the corresponding front or back sheet master to maintain "two-sided" specification page formatting. <br />&bull;Type Office Master Specifications (used in reproduction of the ivory master "mark-ups"), using all aspects of the word processing system. <br />&bull;Whenever possible, proofread work directly from computer screen. When necessary, work with another processor to ensure accuracy. <br />&bull;Return typed, proofread specifications to author. <br />&bull;Advise Manager of Specifications of problems with workload, scheduling or equipment and software. <br />&bull;File Project Specification Masters after project is run for issue. Subsequent Addenda, Bulletins and Construction Issues shall be filed with Project Masters (in proper location to ensure Project Master folder is always complete and current. Previous issue Project Masters will be replaced by current versions and stored in the back of the Project Master). <br />&bull;Work with managers assigned to desk to become a valued team member. Develop good rapport and interaction with other staff and with the Company''s clients. <br />&bull;Prepare a variety of documents; letters, reports, spreadsheets, memos, confidential material lists, etc. <br />&bull;Compile/prepare various reports for manager''s use or distribution. Write reports, memos or letters for manager''s signature or distribution. <br />&bull;Create and maintain filing system; maintain required records for manager and team. Maintain updated job log for desk. <br />&bull;Answer phones, screen calls, take and forward messages, answer routine questions and follow through on requests. Organize priority items for manager''s attention. Screen and route mail/phone messages during manager''s absence. <br />&bull;Maintain electronic calendar for manager and review with them daily. Keep switchboard informed of their availability. <br />&bull;May be required to relieve the switchboard. <br />&bull;Perform routine administrative duties involved in the operation of office programs, projects and activities, many of which are confidential and require the use of judgment, tact and knowledge of our Operations and Personnel standards. <br />&bull;Provide assistance with work overload from other desks when necessary. <br />&bull;May be responsible for, or cross-trained for corporate travel including airline, hotel and car reservations, preparation of itineraries; schedule meetings and take minutes; preparation of confidential government reports; handling of confidential personnel information; client proposals/contracts containing employee rates; maintain telephone or voice mail systems, maintaining office project files; maintenance of office lists (i.e. phone extensions, home addresses, etc.); or conference room scheduling and distribution of daily schedules.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Job Qualifications:<br />&bull;High school diploma. <br />&bull;Minimum three years word processing and secretarial experience or two-year degree in Secretarial Science.<br />&bull;Bilingual written and verbal skills in Mandarin Chinese is required<br />&bull;Excellent proofreading, grammar and typing skills. <br />&bull;Working knowledge of business procedures, letter/report formats, business machines, transcription equipment and general office routines necessary.<br />&bull;Ability to type 65-75 wpm accurately. <br />&bull;Computer literacy with experience in word processing software.</p>\n<p><br />PHYSICAL REQUIREMENTS <br />&bull;Ability to sit for long periods of time. <br />&bull;Ability to use office equipment for communication and documentation purposes. <br />&bull;Visual acuity to perform responsibilities. <br />&bull;Ability to access and file documents from file drawers.</p>', 'http://cr.harleyellisdevereaux.com/careers/Careers.aspx?adata=ECzEettUENJ%2bMsA8mkSBDUtcBUMA1TDrvY1ehFrCFohD36Tgiwhwv2KgcJ6pyAqYkhLOZJWDs7vIGyvPqIUQtoO6s%2bIRG7DMz6hGFrV0a1aTvaSR1fWw44aB0w2tDbQvmrb%2fmu%2fAk2AQXeNJWnZvQmvikDmtSzWew9pb1%2fKGWqVYJxDJqPncQ%2fVnpzJicLZlnzlOQ1ZOMxG265UdJGv8V559FG96jvOMul9FQRfgRohU', '', 980, 155, 2),
(611, 1407380768, '市场营销助理', 'Sysco', 'Marketing', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '洛杉矶', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Overview:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<p>At Sysco we understand that building a great company is just like creating a great product - you must have all the right ingredients. For us, those ingredients are the cultures, backgrounds, ideas, and experiences behind our diverse workforce that embodies Sysco.&nbsp; Sysco is the global leader in selling, marketing and distributing food products to restaurants, healthcare and educational facilities, lodging establishments and other customers who prepare meals away from the home.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This Sysco Los Angeles position will be servicing the Los Angeles, CA area.</p>\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Responsibilities:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<p>This position is responsible for promoting the company&rsquo;s products and services and for building relationships with new and existing accounts.&nbsp; The main focus is to help Sysco customers succeed while achieving sales and profit goals established by the company.&nbsp;&nbsp;This is a 100% sales commissioned opportunity with a salaried based training.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Responsibilities:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This position often requires working non-traditional hours (evening, weekends and holidays) in order to successfully meet customers&rsquo; needs.&nbsp; You must reside within the territory you are applying for.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>An individual must be able to satisfactorily perform each essential duty listed below.&nbsp; The requirements listed are representative of the knowledge, skill, and/or ability required. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Essential Skills and Knowledge:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Develop new business, penetrate existing accounts, and minimize lost business to achieve profitable sales growth and special objectives within assigned territory.</li>\n<li>Seek and qualify prospects in accordance with Company account stratification goals.</li>\n<li>Research customer business needs and develop a mix of products and service to meet needs. &nbsp;</li>\n<li>Evaluate market trends and recommend products to customers, based on business needs and goals.</li>\n<li>Be informed of market conditions, product innovations, and competitors'' products, prices, and sales; share information with customers as part of value-added services provided.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Essential Duties</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Sales Activities:&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Develops, on a daily basis, a product mix penetration of each account by selling all major product categories through the presentation of new products, services, ideas, uses and applications in an effort to meet all established sales and profit objectives; demonstrates a working knowledge of all product categories sold.</li>\n<li>Develops and maintains a list of prospective accounts and sales forecasts to ensure complete market coverage and long-term sales efficiency.</li>\n<li>Completes and up-dates "Training Guide and Checklist" evaluation system and submits information for review by District Sales Manager and Regional Sales Manager as required.</li>\n<li>Develops prospective accounts through market analysis, personal and telephone contacts, and other sales techniques to ensure complete market coverage and long-term sales efficiency.</li>\n<li>Maintains, on a daily basis, a product price book, merchandising material, route list, and lead list to enhance sales activities through planning based on accurate and precise information; completes and up-dates, on a daily basis, all applicable sales forms and call reports to ensure a complete and timely flow of sales information.</li>\n<li>Sells, on a daily basis, excess and/or obsolete inventory items, as identified, through special customer contacts and sales techniques in an effort to reduce product waste and unsatisfactorily high inventory levels.</li>\n<li>Works closely with Sysco specialists, manufacturing representatives, and brokers in supporting company promotions or obtaining information on products or services.</li>\n<li>Performs merchandising research of, on a daily basis, product discounts, product service information, special offers and/or company promotions; utilizes information in sales activities in an effort to increase profitability and enhance customer satisfaction.</li>\n<li>Attends and participates in informational seminars, learning based meetings, and other sessions in an effort to advance individual knowledge of sales techniques, product specifications, and department functions.</li>\n<li>Attends all department sales meetings, as scheduled and participates in other activities as requested; reports on industry/market competition as requested; assists with reviewing inventory levels.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Customer Service&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Provides service to existing accounts, on a daily basis, through proper salespersonship, service, or response to complaints in an effort to retain/enhance customer satisfaction.</li>\n<li>Notifies supervisor immediately if an existing account is determined to be in jeopardy of being discontinuedto ensure that every possible effort is made to retain that account.</li>\n<li>Up-dates customer, on a continuous basis, about any new products/services and pricing information to retain/enhance customer satisfaction.</li>\n<li>Checks messages, on a continuous basis, for customer complaints, problems, or interests and takes the necessary actions in an effort to retain/enhance customer satisfaction.</li>\n<li>Responds to any customer questions or inquiries by providing relevant information or obtaining the information from the appropriate source and immediately relaying it to the customer in an effort to retain/enhance customer satisfaction.</li>\n<li>May make product deliveries to customers as needed.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Credit Activities&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Maintains an appropriate average of accounts receivable days outstanding as determined by supervisor to maintain cash flow and profitability objectives.</li>\n<li>Completes and routes to Credit Department a properly completed credit application for new accounts, as needed, to ensure a complete and timely flow of sales information.</li>\n<li>Provides customers with relevant information concerning company credit terms to avoid interruptions in cash flow and to ensure customer satisfaction.</li>\n<li>Ensures that customers are adhering to company credit terms and notifies supervisor and applicable departments if a problem exists to avoid interruptions in cash flow and to ensure profitability.</li>\n<li>Performs related duties as assigned</li>\n</ul>\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Qualifications:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<ul>\n<li>High School diploma or GED required and a minimum of one year experience working in an outside/commissioned sales position in a related industry is required.&nbsp; Experience as either a chef, foodservice/catering operations manager, or procurement manger is preferable.</li>\n<li>A demonstrated ability to plan and organize work activities; manage work time efficiently; follow procedures and policies; perform moderate mathematical calculations; identify and solve problems; write clearly and concisely.</li>\n<li>Knowledge of sales techniques, marketing principles, communications related to sales, credit and customer service activities.</li>\n<li>Must have computer skills in order to utilize sales tools and techniques and be proficient with office applications such as Microsoft Outlook, Word, Excel, PowerPoint, etc.</li>\n<li>Must possess excellent interpersonal and communication abilities.</li>\n<li>Must possess and maintain a valid State of California Driver&rsquo;s License. A conviction for DUI within the last three years will render the candidate ineligible to apply.</li>\n<li>Must obtain and provide adequate liability insurance as determined by Sysco ($300,000 per accident, $100,000 per person, $100,000 property and uninsured motorist $30,000/$60,000).</li>\n<li>Must have reliable transportation for use in sales activities.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Preferred Requirements:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Business, Sales, Marketing, Hospitality; or Culinary Arts.</li>\n<li>Restaurant management / chef experience.</li>\n<li>Preferred proved track record of successful selling and a stable work history.</li>\n<li><strong>Fluent in English/Chinese (Mandarin and/or Cantonese) or English/Spanish.</strong>&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Competencies:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Building Trust</p>\n<p>Building Customer Loyalty</p>\n<p>Follow-up</p>\n<p>Sales Ability / Persuasiveness</p>\n<p>Managing Work</p>\n<p>Adaptability</p>\n<p>Communication</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Physical Demands:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This work requires the following physical activities: climbing, bending, stooping, kneeling, twisting, reaching, sitting, standing, walking, lifting up to 20 lbs. of material, finger dexterity for activities such as data entry and calculator use, grasping, repetitive motions, speaking, hearing, visual acuity, and mobility between departments.&nbsp;&nbsp; Use of both hands is required.&nbsp; The work is performed primarily indoors.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The physical demands described here are representative of those that must be met by an employee to successfully perform the essential functions of this job. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Applicants must be currently authorized to work in the U.S. on a full-time basis without future employment sponsorship.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Sysco&nbsp;Los Angeles&nbsp;is proud to be an EEO/AA employer - M/F/D/V.</p>\n<p>This opportunity is available through Sysco&nbsp;Los Angeles.&nbsp; This is not a Corporate position.</p>\n<p><strong>All hiring decisions will be made at the sole discretion of Sysco&nbsp;Los Angeles.</strong></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'https://jobs-sysco.icims.com/jobs/13876/*marketing-associate--sysco-los-angeles-%28los-angeles%2c-ca-territory%29*/job?hub=7&mode=job&iis=Indeed&iisn=Indeed.com', '', 980, 160, 2),
