(626, 1408088415, '中文编辑', 'Adecco', 'Language', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', '纽约', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Adecco is currently assisting a local client in their search for an experienced Mandarin Editor in New Rochelle. This position is a long term temporary job opportunity. The Mandarin Editor will be responsible for ensuring the translation of a series of books/education information is correct and works for the Chinese market. If you are interested in putting your knowledge to work, APPLY NOW!<br class="jobDetailsNewLine" /><br class="jobDetailsNewLine" />Responsibilities for the Mandarin Editor include but are not limited to:<br class="jobDetailsNewLine" />-Translating a series of books/educational information from English to Traditional and Modern Mandarin.<br class="jobDetailsNewLine" />-Ensuring context and accuracy of translations for Chinese Market.<br class="jobDetailsNewLine" />-Maintaining schedule.<br class="jobDetailsNewLine" /><br class="jobDetailsNewLine" />This position is a long term temp job with an excellent educational organization!<br class="jobDetailsNewLine" /><br class="jobDetailsNewLine" />Adecco provides one of the most comprehensive benefits package in the industry to contract workers.&nbsp;<br class="jobDetailsNewLine" /><br class="jobDetailsNewLine" />Equal Opportunity Employer Minorities/Women/Veterans/Disabled</p>', 'http://www.adeccousa.com/jobs/creative/us_en_1_173860_10688324/mandarin-editor?bid=1000&utm_source=Indeed&utm_medium=organic&utm_campaign=Indeed', '', 980, 232, 2),
(627, 1408088591, '双语商务顾问', 'First Data', 'Marketing', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '旧金山', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table width="92%">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Requisition No.</td>\n<td width="80%">38573BR</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Job Title</td>\n<td width="80%">Bilingual Business Consultant - San Francisco, CA</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>About First Data</td>\n<td width="80%">First Data is a leading provider of payment solutions for financial institutions and merchants around the world. With over 42 Billion merchant transactions annually and nearly 750 Million credit/debit cards on file, First Data powers the payments value chain in over 80 countries across the globe. We are proud of our extensive customer relationships supporting over 7,000 financial institutions and the largest merchant distribution network in the industry with over 1,200 partners servicing merchants large and small.<br /><br />Our 25,000 employees are industry experts helping businesses simplify payment processing and improve the customer experience with our broad portfolio of solutions, including: Credit and Debit card issuing and acquiring, STAR&reg; PIN-Debit Network, Point of Sale Terminals and deployment services via our subsidiary, TASQ Technology, Gift Card and Loyalty Solutions, TeleCheck&reg; Electronic Check Acceptance Services, MoneyNetwork&reg; Payroll Distribution, eCommerce and online banking solutions, world-class security services like our new TransArmorsm STAR&reg; CertiflashSM Solutions, and more.&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>First Data. Beyond the Transaction.</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Job Description</td>\n<td width="80%">\n<p>First Data Business Consultant<br /><br /><br />Must live in San Francisco&nbsp;<br /><br />Only candidates fluent in Chinese-Mandarin or Cantonese will be considered<br /><br />Job Description</p>\n<br /><br />\n<p>The world''s largest Merchant Services Company is seeking energetic Sales people for this field based, outside Business Consultant position. This position will give you the ability to sell the full suite of First Data products to small and midsize businesses including: Clover Tablet, Perka Loyalty, Data Analytics, credit, debit, check, gift card, and cash advances. This is accomplished through a consultative sales approach to new and existing clients.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The position will also be responsible for retaining clients by building relationships and growing portfolios through relationship management and cross sales.<br /><br />Your sales efforts will be complemented by referrals obtained from a strong working relationship developed with our over 1,400 nationwide bank partnerships and other referral sources, both large and small.<br /><br />This position offers a&nbsp;tiered compensation&nbsp;structure which includes:&nbsp;<br /><br /></p>\n<br /><br /><br /><br />\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>A&nbsp;base salary with benefits</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<br /><br />\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Commissions&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<br /><br />\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Multi-year residuals</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<br /><br />\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>New hire ramp up bonus</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<br /><br />\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Annual achievement bonuses</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<br /><br />\n<ul>\n<li>Recognition awards and expense reimbursement.</li>\n</ul>\n<br /><br />\n<p>In addition, we offer our Sales team continual formalized training and operational support to ensure that you are kept educated on our products to maximize your success.<br />&nbsp;<br />As a member of our Regional Sales force, you will always represent the First Data values of embodying the highest ethical standards and treating others with dignity and respect.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Candidate Requirements</td>\n<td width="80%"><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />\n<p>Ideal Candidate Requirements:<br /><br />Technologically savvy; comfortable with tablet and cloud based solutions</p>\nEntrepreneurial spirit<br />Creative and personable<br /><br /><br /><br /><br />\n<p>Qualifications:</p>\n<br /><br />\n<ul>\n<li>&nbsp;Experience and proven success in selling advanced solutions to small and midsize businesses in a short sales cycle is a strong plus; not required</li>\n</ul>\n<br /><br /><br /><br />\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Ability to develop a plan to effectively produce top line revenue growth by meeting or exceeding key metrics for revenue, account retention, and profitability</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<br /><br />\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Drive growth by continuously creating and selling customer value propositions to new clients and well as the assigned client base that focuses on our competitive advantage while leveraging our broad suite of solutions</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<br /><br />\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Diverse experience networking and prospecting using social media, service organizations, cold calling, and other sales&nbsp;skills to help achieve revenue goals<br /><br /></li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<br /><br />\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Strong listening skills to ensure success as main point of contact for your portfolio of clients;&nbsp;relationship management or account management experience a plus</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<br /><br />\n<ul>\n<li>Effective communication skills are required; both written and verbal</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Preferred Qualifications</td>\n<td width="80%">\n<p>Preferred Qualifications:</p>\n<br /><br /><br /><br />\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree or an equivalent combination of formal education and work experience in a similar role.&nbsp;SH14&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Country</td>\n<td width="80%">United States</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>State</td>\n<td width="80%">Nebraska</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>City</td>\n<td width="80%">San Francisco</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Primary Location Address</td>\n<td width="80%">WFH-WORK FROM HOME (99WST)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Job Function</td>\n<td width="80%">Sales</td>\n</tr>\n<tr