(632, 1408327572, '新业务开发实习生', 'Time Inc', 'Technology', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', '纽约', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>Intern, New Business Development &nbsp;&ndash; Time Inc.</strong><br />&nbsp;<br />Time Inc is one of the largest branded media companies in the world. The company engages more than 138 million U.S. consumers in print, online and via mobile devices each month. With influential brands such as TIME, PEOPLE, SPORTS ILLUSTRATED, INSTYLE, and REAL SIMPLE, Time Inc. has owned some of the biggest news stories of the decade and is home to celebrated franchises such as the FORTUNE 500, TIME 100, PEOPLE''s Most Beautiful and the SPORTS ILLUSTRATED Swimsuit Issue.<br />&nbsp;<br /><strong>Position Description:&nbsp;</strong><br />This is an intern role with the individual contributing to multiple projects at one time.&nbsp; We&rsquo;re looking for somebody who&rsquo;s good with research, data collection, analysis, creation of presentations and other written materials, and presentation and discussion of such materials with senior management. The intern will have exposure to all of Time Inc. (including magazines, all things digital and non-magazine operations) and across all of Time Inc. brands.<br />&nbsp;<br /><strong>Responsibilities can include projects in the following areas:&nbsp;</strong><br />- Strategic reviews (print and digital) for individual business units and Time Inc. as a whole<br />- New business development<br />- Evaluation of industry trends and competitive landscape<br />- Advertising sales go-to-market<br />- Strategic and operational implications of potential acquisitions or investments<br />- Customer segmentation<br />- Growth strategy<br />- Advertising solutions innovation<br />- Cross-divisional project management on ad hoc strategic initiatives<br />- Presentation creation for senior executives<br />- Financial and operating data gathering and analysis<br />&nbsp;<br /><strong>The person:&nbsp;</strong><br />- Strong ownership and ability to work independently and be resourceful<br />- Excellent analytical skills, both quantitative and qualitative<br />- Ability to tackle unstructured problems and solve them<br />- Ability to interpret financial data<br />- Strong communication skills<br />- Strong interpersonal skills including ability to work in teams and to interact with internal and external senior level management<br />- Ability to work on multiple projects simultaneously and set priorities under tight timeframes in an unstructured environment<br />- Displays professional maturity and initiative<br />&nbsp;<br /><strong>Education and Background:&nbsp;</strong><br />&bull; Prior internship experience a plus<br />&bull; Knowledge and understanding media industry (including digital businesses)<br />&bull; MS Excel, Word and Powerpoint<br />&nbsp;<br />To apply, please include a cover letter with your submittal. Tell us about yourself and why you&rsquo;d be a good fit for this position and for Time Inc.<br />&nbsp;<br />Time Inc. is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. We are committed to attracting, retaining and maximizing the performance of a diverse and inclusive workforce.</p>', 'https://careers.timeinc.com/TGWEbHost/jobdetails.aspx?jobId=682978&PartnerId=25960&SiteId=36', '', 980, 183, 2),
(629, 1408202966, '诚聘华人贷款专员 丰厚佣金10%', 'M&E Financial Group', 'Finance', '美国伊利诺伊州芝加哥', 'United States', 'Illinois', 'Chicago', 41.878113, -87.629799, '美利坚合众国', '伊利诺伊州', '芝加哥', 'H1B', 'Part Time', '<p>M&amp;E Financial Group 多年专精商业贷款现招聘华人贷款专员</p>\n<p>工作地点不限工作时间灵活全职兼职均可</p>\n<p>任职要求：</p>\n<p>可在美国合法报税</p>\n<p>优秀的沟通和顾客服务技巧</p>\n<p>有贷款，销售或者在金融公司工作的经历者优先</p>\n<p>中文流利者优先</p>\n<p>也欢迎房屋经纪，保险经纪在我公司兼职</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>公司地址：2082 Business Center Drive, Suite 195, Irvine, CA 92612</p>\n<p>请发简历至mli@thebizcash.com 或致电626-376-0501了解更多信息</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>M&amp;E Financial Group is Hiring Full Time &amp; Part Time Chinese Market Commercial Loan Agent</p>\n<p>Could work at home, flexible working time, 10% commission.</p>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<p>Could file tax within United States</p>\n<p>Good communication and sales skills</p>\n<p>Finance industry experience preferred</p>\n<p>Sales experience preferred</p>\n<p>Mandarin and Cantonese speaking agents preferred</p>\n<p>Insurance agents and real estate agents are welcomed to work as part time employees</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Company Address: 2082 Business Center Drive, Suite 195, Irvine, CA 92612</p>\n<p>Please send your resume to <a href="mailto:mli@thebizcash.com">mli@thebizcash.com</a> or call 626-376-0501</p>', '', 'mli@thebizcash.com', 1044, 189, 2),
(630, 1408218654, '行政助理', 'America Chung Nam', 'Management', 'City of Industry, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'City of Industry', 34.019733, -117.958672, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '因达斯特里', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>We are looking for experienced and professional administrative individuals to join our growing company.&nbsp;&nbsp;The main duties are to provide administrative support to a member of our senior management team.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Job duties include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Produce reports, summaries, communications and other information for senior management using available technologies.</li>\n<li>Handle requests for information, most of which are highly confidential, preparing all correspondences.</li>\n<li>Support the senior management team member by reading, researching, and routing correspondences; drafting letters and documents; collecting and analyzing information; initiating telecommunications.</li>\n<li>Maintain appointment schedule by planning and scheduling meetings, conferences, teleconferences, and travel.</li>\n<li>Accurately represent the senior management team member by attending meetings in their absence.</li>\n<li>Greeting clients and guests in person or on the telephone.</li>\n<li>Prepare reports by collecting and analyzing information.</li>\n<li>Provide historical reference by developing and utilizing filing and retrieval systems; recording meeting discussions.</li>\n<li>Maintain office supplies inventory by checking stock to determine inventory level; anticipating needed supplies; evaluating new office products; placing and expediting orders for supplies; verifying receipt of supplies.</li>\n<li>Maintain professional and technical knowledge by attending educational workshops; reviewing professional publications; establishing personal networks; participating in professional societies.</li>\n<li>Perform other administrative duties as assigned or requested.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;Job requirements are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>REQUIRED: Strong Proficiency in English and Chinese</strong></li>\n<li><strong>REQUIRED: Excellence in Written and Verbal Communication in English and Chinese.</strong></li>\n<li>College degree preferred.</li>\n<li>Highly desired characteristics: honesty, dependability, and hard working.</li>\n<li>Detail-oriented and proactive thinker.</li>\n<li>Relentless follow-up skills with a friendly and positive attitude.</li>\n<li>Ability to Multi-Task.</li>\n<li>Excellent computer skills with MS Office and Outlook</li>\n<li>Local Candidates Preferred</li>\n</ul>', 'http://hire.jobvite.com/CompanyJobs/Careers.aspx?k=Job&c=qnz9VfwK&j=oAfoZfwW&s=Indeed', '', 980, 148, 2),
(631, 1408249156, 'Senior Accountant - External Reporting', '蒂芬妮', 'Management', 'Parsippany-Troy Hills, NJ, United States', 'United States', 'New Jersey', 'Parsippany-Troy Hills', 40.859634, -74.423347, '美利坚合众国', '新泽西州', '帕西帕尼－特洛伊希尔斯', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="description-module container">\n<div class="content">\n<div class="description-section">\n<h3 class="sub-header">Job description</h3>\n<div class="rich-text">\n<p>Tiffany &amp; Co. is currently seeking a Senior Accountant &ndash; External Reporting. The Senior Accountant &ndash; External Reporting will be responsible for assisting with the coordination and preparation of the Company''s external financial reporting requirements and other required government (census) reporting. Additionally, this position will assist with the preparation and review of other financial statements such as for the Company&rsquo;s pension and 401(K) plans. This individual will partner with Investor Relations and business units across the Company to gather and analyze information to be included in the Company&rsquo;s publicly reported financial information.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Senior Accountant &ndash; External Reporting will assist with the preparation of SEC-compliant quarterly 10-Q filings, Press Releases and the Company''s Annual Report (Form 10-K and Proxy). Responsibilities include researching, drafting and supporting footnote and MD&amp;A disclosures. S/he will also coordinate and complete special projects as requested by management, as well as assist in the preparation of various internal reports as requested by management. The Senior Accountant will assist with the preparation of other financial statements such as for the Company&rsquo;s pension plan and the 401k plan. This position will prepare and submit all required U.S. Government and Canadian census filings.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="skills-section">\n<h3 class="sub-header">Desired Skills and Experience</h3>\n<div class="rich-text">\n<p>To be qualified for this position you must have:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A 4 year Accounting degree</li>\n<li>4+ years professional experience</li>\n<li>Strong knowledge of U.S. GAAP, including experience in researching accounting literature</li>\n<li>Strong communication (oral and written), listening and analytical skills</li>\n<li>Ability to manage own work and multi-task amid shifting priorities</li>\n<li>Ability to work under tight deadlines and must be willing to work extended hours</li>\n<li>Ability to interface with all levels of management as well as with external auditors\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Preferred Qualifications:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>CPA strongly preferred</li>\n<li>Experience working with HFM and JD Edwards</li>\n<li>Experience working with WebFilings and knowledge of XBRL reporting requirements</li>\n<li>Previous experience, such as public accounting or comparable accounting/finance experience, with 10Q, 10K and other SEC filings</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id="company-module" class="company-module container">\n<h2 class="container-header">About this company</h2>\n<div class="content">\n<div class="rich-text">\n<p>Tiffany &amp; Co. operates jewelry and specialty retail stores and manufactures products through its subsidiary corporations. Its principal subsidiary is Tiffany and Company. The Company operates TIFFANY &amp; CO. retail stores and boutiques in the Americas, Asia-Pacific and Europe and engages in direct selling through Internet, catalog and business gift operations. Other operations include consolidated results from ventures operated under trademarks or trade names other than TIFFANY &amp; CO.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'https://www.linkedin.com/jobs2/view/18670815?trk=vsrp_jobs_res_name&trkInfo=VSRPsearchId%3A3301255351408139899981%2CVSRPtargetId%3A18670815%2CVSRPcmpt%3Aprimary', '', 980, 125, 2),
(633, 1408468372, '中日餐企台', 'yeung II sushi', 'Resturant', 'Hoboken, NJ, United States', 'United States', 'New Jersey', 'Hoboken', 40.743992, -74.032364, '美国', '新泽西州', '霍博肯', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>熟手汽车送外买 需要住在布鲁克林 有意请打电话 917 535 6255</p>', '', '', 1057, 31, 2),
(649, 1408843280, '外语教师', 'LinguaLearn', 'Language', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '洛杉矶', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>LinguaLearn is currently seeking native speakers of the following foreign languages to teach their language to language learners through Skype: Dutch, French, German, Greek, Hindi, Indonesian, Italian, Japanese, Korean, Mandarin Chinese, Mixteco, Nahuatl, Portuguese, Quechua (of Cuzco), Spanish, Swedish, Tagalog (Filipino), Vietnamese, and Yucatec Maya. To apply, you do not necessarily need to already be an experienced professional teacher, but please respond to the following questions in your application:</p>\n<p>1. What is your name (first and last)?</p>\n<p>2. What is your native language/language you want to teach?</p>\n<p>3. Please provide a general outline (in any form you desire) of how you plan to teach the language to your students. (For example, "I plan to start with greetings and introductions in the first lesson, then...") Please be as detailed as you can.</p>\n<p>4. Do you have any experience teaching the language? (Note that lack of experience does not automatically disqualify you from being hired.) If so, please describe.</p>\n<p>5. Do you have any kind of certificate of sufficient knowledge of your native language? (Again, if you do not, this does not automatically disqualify you from being hired.) If so, please upload a copy of the certificate and include it in the email as an attachment.</p>\n<p>6. In what country do you currently reside?</p>\n<p>7. Please note that we are more interested in you being passionate about teaching your language, and having a good plan/method to teach your language, therefore being able to teach it well, than we are in holding of credentials (although credentials may also be taken into consideration). Thus, please describe why you think you would make a good language teacher, and if you feel you have the sufficient passion for the language to teach it.</p>\n<p>8. It is of utmost importance that the teacher not be in any way, shape, or form, rude, disrespectful, judgmental, condescending, or impatient towards his/her student(/s). Violation of this policy will not be tolerated, and students will be given the opportunity to report violation of this if they need to. If you prepared to refrain from displaying these qualities regardless of the student''s personal qualities, including, but not limited to, age, gender, religion, nationality, sexual orientation, and demeanor, then please respond "Yes." Otherwise, you need not apply.</p>\n<p>9. Another policy that will not be tolerated on part of the teacher is not showing up for the student''s lesson(s). Do you promise to respect this policy? (Yes/No)</p>\n<p>Please note that lessons will be reviewed by the students on our website, so the higher ratings you get for your lessons, the more likely students will be to book their lessons with you.</p>\n<p>Pay rate will be $20 per each hour of teaching.</p>\n<p>After we receive your emailed application, you will be contacted within 24 hours informing and congratulating you if you have been hired. Thank you very much for applying, and good luck in the application process! : )</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/LinguaLearn/jobs/Foreign-Language-Instructor-13c9e3d4e55e3e28', '', 980, 187, 2),
(639, 1408477910, '中文应用软件测试员', '手机app公司Quixey', 'Technology', 'Mountain View, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Mountain View', 37.386051, -122.083855, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '山景城', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>工作机会，湾区Mountain View， CA】手机app公司Quixey现招聘中文应用软件测试员，需中英文阅读流利，拥有美国合法工作身份，contracter, $15/hr</p>', '', 'charlie@quixey.com', 980, 198, 2);
