(644, 1408590175, '项目行政助理', 'Harley Ellis Devereaux', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '洛杉矶', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table id="CRCareers1_tblJobDescrDetail" border="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="JDHeaderStyle" colspan="2">Job Responsibilities:</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="MainBodyText" colspan="2">This position will provide detailed administrative project support and requires both knowledge of architecture/engineering/construction project processing and strong general hands on administrative skills.<br /><br />PRIMARY FUNCTIONS:<br /><br />Provide word processing for specifications and contracts (AIA forms) to create Project Manuals and Office Master Specification and Provide administrative support to one or more Managers or Project Teams, including maintaing individual and project related schedules.<br /><br />TYPICAL DUTIES&nbsp;<br />&bull;Type project specifications and AIA contract forms using all aspects of the word processing system including spell check, editing techniques and program enhancements to maximize efficient use of the system.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Make typing revisions to specifications for revised editions (i.e. Addenda/Bulletins, Construction Issues etc.) including format revisions to pages as required.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Assemble Addenda, Bulletins and Construction Issues by obtaining the Project Master folder and pulling the corresponding front or back sheet master to maintain "two-sided" specification page formatting.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Type Office Master Specifications (used in reproduction of the ivory master "mark-ups"), using all aspects of the word processing system.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Whenever possible, proofread work directly from computer screen. When necessary, work with another processor to ensure accuracy.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Return typed, proofread specifications to author.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Advise Manager of Specifications of problems with workload, scheduling or equipment and software.&nbsp;<br />&bull;File Project Specification Masters after project is run for issue. Subsequent Addenda, Bulletins and Construction Issues shall be filed with Project Masters (in proper location to ensure Project Master folder is always complete and current. Previous issue Project Masters will be replaced by current versions and stored in the back of the Project Master).&nbsp;<br />&bull;Work with managers assigned to desk to become a valued team member. Develop good rapport and interaction with other staff and with the Company''s clients.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Prepare a variety of documents; letters, reports, spreadsheets, memos, confidential material lists, etc.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Compile/prepare various reports for manager''s use or distribution. Write reports, memos or letters for manager''s signature or distribution.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Create and maintain filing system; maintain required records for manager and team. Maintain updated job log for desk.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Answer phones, screen calls, take and forward messages, answer routine questions and follow through on requests. Organize priority items for manager''s attention. Screen and route mail/phone messages during manager''s absence.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Maintain electronic calendar for manager and review with them daily. Keep switchboard informed of their availability.&nbsp;<br />&bull;May be required to relieve the switchboard.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Perform routine administrative duties involved in the operation of office programs, projects and activities, many of which are confidential and require the use of judgment, tact and knowledge of our Operations and Personnel standards.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Provide assistance with work overload from other desks when necessary.&nbsp;<br />&bull;May be responsible for, or cross-trained for corporate travel including airline, hotel and car reservations, preparation of itineraries; schedule meetings and take minutes; preparation of confidential government reports; handling of confidential personnel information; client proposals/contracts containing employee rates; maintain telephone or voice mail systems, maintaining office project files; maintenance of office lists (i.e. phone extensions, home addresses, etc.); or conference room scheduling and distribution of daily schedules.&nbsp;<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="JDHeaderStyle" colspan="2">Job Qualifications:</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="MainBodyText" colspan="2">&bull;High school diploma.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Minimum three years word processing and secretarial experience or two-year degree in Secretarial Science.<br />&bull;Bilingual written and verbal skills in Mandarin Chinese is required<br />&bull;Excellent proofreading, grammar and typing skills.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Working knowledge of business procedures, letter/report formats, business machines, transcription equipment and general office routines necessary.<br />&bull;Ability to type 65-75 wpm accurately.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Computer literacy with experience in word processing software.&nbsp;<br /><br /><br />PHYSICAL REQUIREMENTS&nbsp;<br />&bull;Ability to sit for long periods of time.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Ability to use office equipment for communication and documentation purposes.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Visual acuity to perform responsibilities.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Ability to access and file documents from file drawers.&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'http://cr.harleyellisdevereaux.com/careers/Careers.aspx?adata=EBT4ezAzJhY8XLyYOaB3ATRAA2oqS1i7JYOGtdvKjn%2bK05nTwIJc80qAt60R5tvHhX9VfohKCf8p1CwU%2fowhvUhnsxkT9Jk7OoXj8Hwsbt%2fRviSPJphOsFfz0vCF1lzZFphz1RsYYtoNZ0Gj9w3w3ZSsrF33zIPPrne7cRJCbn%2bFZKkVcILwsEsTR28JsNY3LkuDZbNshdjVC6TAGjfG2j0hvVPJIqOU7ElmkDFeTdHF', '', 980, 153, 2),
(646, 1408650504, '银行电话客服', 'Wells Fargo ', 'Finance', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '洛杉矶', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="content-sections">\n<section id="job-description-section" class="minimized">\n<h2>JOB DESCRIPTION</h2>\n<div id="pnlJobDescription" class="section-body">\n<p>IMPORTANT NOTE:&nbsp; Please ensure your contact information (e-mail address and phone number) is current in your Wells Fargo Jobs Profile. Initial contact will be made via e-mail. Please check your e-mail regularly for updates.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Please note: If there is an exceptionally high volume of applicants for this job posting, this job posting may close before the indicated expiration date.</p>\n<p>Currently hiring for a training class starting on August 4<sup>th</sup>.&nbsp; Training hours are 8:30am &ndash;5:00pm Monday-Friday for 6 weeks (Must be available to attend entire paid training class).&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Current schedules being offered after training will be:</p>\n<p>Mandarin &ndash; 8:00am-4:30pm or 9:00am-5:30pm with Saturday and Sunday off</p>\n<p>Cantonese &ndash; 6:00am-2:30pm with Saturday and Sunday off</p>\n<p>Salary Range - $13.62/hr. - $14.81/hr. DOE plus eligible to participate in the WFCC Service Incentive Plan</p>\n<p>Our next big investment is in you!&nbsp; Wells Fargo offers:</p>\n<br />\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li><br />A broad array of medical, dental, and vision plans</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Paid Time Off</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>401 (k) and Stock Purchase Plans</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Discounts and Savings on Wells Fargo financial products, home mortgages and services</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Tuition Reimbursement</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Wellness Benefits</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Commuter Benefits</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<br /><br />\n<p>Please review the requirements for a Phone Banker before applying<strong>.</strong>&nbsp; A Phone Banker spends nearly 100% of his/her time on the phone answering questions for Wells Fargo customers. The working environment is fun and relaxed with a casual dress code but is also demanding and structured, and involves overcoming customers&rsquo; banking concerns which can include some escalated issues.</p>\n<p>Phone Bankers are expected to sell products and services and achieve aggressive sales goals which are measured daily.&nbsp; Our best Phone Bankers thrive on customer interaction and never miss an opportunity to enhance the customer&rsquo;s relationship with Wells Fargo by marketing new products and services. They always handle each customer with a friendly, courteous touch while following strict procedures for handling various types of inquiries.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>We provide our Phone Bankers with continuous coaching and development which not only enhances their ability to provide exemplary service and product solutions to our customers, but also enhances the Phone Bankers&rsquo; career growth. Our successful bankers demonstrate self-motivation, a positive attitude, have the ability to work well on a team and have a solid work history.&nbsp; They also demonstrate strong listening, written and verbal communication skills.&nbsp; They are receptive to coaching and feedback, have the desire to meet/exceed goals and solve problems while working in a fast paced environment.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Our Phone Bankers play a critical role in our customers&rsquo; lives; therefore, predictable and reliable attendance is an essential function of the position.&nbsp;</p>\n<div id="jobDescriptionTextFade">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section id="job-requirements">\n<h2>JOB REQUIREMENTS</h2>\n<div class="section-body"><strong>* Basic Qualifications:&nbsp;</strong><br />6 months customer service and sales experience.<br /><br /><strong>* Minimum Qualifications:&nbsp;</strong><br />\n<p>Basic computer skills including the ability to navigate multiple windows and applications and utilize search tools to find information.</p>\n<p>6+ months sales experience (list specific sales experience in resume/work history)</p>\n<p>Experience with supporting both Chinese (Mandarin/Cantonese) and English speaking customers.<br /><br /><br />The successful passing of the language proficiency assessment (speaking and reading) is required to qualify for the bilingual Chinese (Mandarin/Cantonese)/English queue (administered during the interviewing process).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section id="job-snapshot-section">\n<h2>JOB SNAPSHOT</h2>\n<div class="section-body">\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Employment Type</strong>Full-Time</div>\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Job Type</strong>Sales, Banking</div>\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Education</strong>Not Specified</div>\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Experience</strong>Not Specified</div>\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Manages Others</strong>Not Specified</div>\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Industry</strong>Banking - Financial Services</div>\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Required Travel</strong>Not Specified</div>\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Job ID</strong>5009238<br /><br /></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>', 'http://www.careerbuilder.com/jobseeker/jobs/jobdetails.aspx?Job_DID=J3F3CT65C1GK8L7T6R7&siteid=sep_cb001_13_2072_00&showNewJDP=yes&ipath=EXGOO', '', 980, 163, 2),
(647, 1408650890, '幼儿园中文教师', 'Preschool', 'Language', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', '纽约', '纽约', 'H1B', 'Full Time', '<p>曼哈顿下城大型Preschool招聘信息：2. 招聘幼儿园中文教师 招聘对象：大专或本科文凭，需会讲简单日常英文，有合法工作身份者。 招聘条件：热爱教育工作，身心健康，有责任心和耐心。&nbsp;</p>', '', 'cimpastato@preschoolofamerica.us', 980, 295, 2),
(648, 1408740476, '业务经理', 'East West Bank', 'Management', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', '纽约', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table border="0" width="92%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" align="center">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="TGAlignLeft" width="80%"><span class="TEXT"><span class="TEXT">East West Bank is a one of the largest independent banks headquartered in California serving consumers and businesses throughout the U.S. and Greater China. East West Bank is publicly traded with 27.4 billion in assets. With over 130 locations worldwide including California, Texas, New York, Georgia, Massachusetts, Nevada, Washington, and Greater China &ndash;East West Bank is committed to helping their customers&rsquo; enterprises succeed. At East West Bank, we build bridges that provide an important financial link that turns opportunities into growth and prosperity.<br /><br />As an East West Bank employee, you will be part of a growing and stable organization that provides career path development opportunities while serving a growing and profitable market.<br /><br />As a valuable East West Bank team member, your duties (not limited to) will include:&nbsp;<br /></span></span><br />\n<ul>\n<li>Expand customer portfolio and develop new business opportunities&nbsp;</li>\n<li>New Accounts&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Consumer and Commercial lending&nbsp;</li>\n<li>International Banking&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Work closely with other business units to create sales opportunities for the Bank</li>\n</ul>\n<span class="TEXT"><span class="TEXT">Qualifications/Requirements:&nbsp;<br /></span></span><br />\n<ul>\n<li>Bilingual in English and Chinese (Mandarin) is a plus&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Understanding of East West Bank&rsquo;s processes to exercise the Bridge Banking concept&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Strong ownership&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Self-motivator with sense of urgency to serve and develop business&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Ability to meet and exceed goals successfully by managing daily and weekly sales routines/activities</li>\n</ul>\n<p>East West Bank is an Equal Opportunity Employer<br /><br />&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign="top"><span class="Fieldlabel"><label for="Job Family">Job Family</label></span></td>\n<td class="TGAlignLeft" width="80%"><span id="Job Family" class="TEXT">Commercial Banking</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign="top"><span class="Fieldlabel"><label for="Auto req ID">Auto req ID</label></span></td>\n<td class="TGAlignLeft" width="80%"><span id="Auto req ID" class="TEXT">3821BR</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign="top"><span class="Fieldlabel"><label for="Position Type">Position Type</label></span></td>\n<td class="TGAlignLeft" width="80%"><span id="Position Type" class="TEXT">Full-Time</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign="top"><span class="Fieldlabel"><label for="Country">Country</label></span></td>\n<td class="TGAlignLeft" width="80%"><span id="Country" class="TEXT">United States</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign="top"><span class="Fieldlabel"><label for="State / Province">State / Province</label></span></td>\n<td class="TGAlignLeft" width="80%"><span id="State / Province" class="TEXT">New York</span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'https://sjobs.brassring.com/TGWEbHost/jobdetails.aspx?jobId=1906378&PartnerId=25446&SiteId=5504', '', 980, 154, 2),
(653, 1409028996, '贷款专员', 'M&E Financial Group', 'Finance', 'Irvine, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Irvine', 33.683949, -117.794693, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '欧文', 'H1B', 'Part Time', '<p>M&amp;E Financial Group 多年专精商业贷款现招聘华人贷款专员</p>\n<p>工作地点不限工作时间灵活全职兼职均可</p>\n<p>佣金是贷款总金额的10%，佣金将在公司汇款后5个工作日内发放，如果客户倒债，与专员没有关系。</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>任职要求：</p>\n<p>可在美国合法报税</p>\n<p>中文流利者优先</p>\n<p>也欢迎房屋经纪，保险经纪在我公司兼职</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>公司地址：2082 Business Center Drive, Suite 195, Irvine, CA 92612</p>\n<p>请发简历至mli@thebizcash.com 或致电626-376-0501了解更多信息</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>M&amp;E Financial Group is Hiring Full Time &amp; Part Time Commercial Loan Agent.</p>\n<p>Could work at home, flexible working time, 10% commission. Commission would be distributed to agents&rsquo; bank account within 5 days after the funding of the loan. If clients default, agents have no responsibility.</p>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<p>Could file tax within United States</p>\n<p>Good communication and sales skills</p>\n<p>Finance industry experience preferred</p>\n<p>Sales experience preferred</p>\n<p>Insurance agents and real estate agents are welcomed to work as part time employees</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Company Address: 2082 Business Center Drive, Suite 195, Irvine, CA 92612</p>\n<p>Please send your resume to <a href="mailto:mli@thebizcash.com">mli@thebizcash.com</a> or call 626-376-0501</p>', 'http://www.thebizcash.com/', 'mli@thebizcash.com', 1044, 201, 2),
(654, 1409078814, '中文教师', 'Chinese Language Academy of Los Angeles', 'Language', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '洛杉矶', 'None', 'Part Time', '<p>Chinese Language Instructor position (part-time) available at Chinese Language Academy of Los Angeles. We offer competitive salary and a supportive environment for your to grow. The Chinese Language teacher will be developing curriculum and instructing students of various levels and backgrounds. Since we offer classes at the client&rsquo;s site (LA County and Orange County) as well, the actual teaching place may vary.</p>\n<p>Job Qualifications:<br />1. Native fluency in Chinese Mandarin;<br />2. Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree or above in Chinese Linguistics, Chinese Literature, Foreign Language Education, Asian Studies or a closely related field. A Master''s degree is strongly preferred;<br />3. High proficiency level in English; a deep understanding of American culture;<br />4. At least two years&rsquo; experience in teaching Chinese as a foreign language in a classroom setting;<br />5. Knowledge of current teaching methodologies and practices in teaching Chinese language in the U.S..<br />6. Currently live in Greater Los Angeles area.</p>\n<p>Only candidates who have met all qualifications above will be considered. If interested, please send your resume and cover letter.</p>\n<p>Your resume will be thoroughly reviewed. Degree verification, reference checks and background check will be conducted on provisionally hired instructor(s) prior to the first class.</p>\n<p>Thank you for your interest!</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Chinese-Language-Academy/jobs/Chinese-Mandarin-Instructor-b080a7ea3ba751ce', '', 980, 191, 2),
(651, 1409007004, '销售助理', 'Cartier', 'Finance', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', '纽约', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Cartier, l''artisan des passions.<br />Purpose<br />We are seeking a Team Player who represents the highest standards of the Maison to assist with providing<br />sales assistance to all boutique staff and clients as needed.<br />Responsibilities<br />- Greet the clients in a professional and positive Cartier manner.<br />- Determine through detailed and specific discovery process the objectives of the client&rsquo;s visit.<br />- Escort the client to a viewing desk and deliver refreshments personally or with the aid of the available<br />boutique assistants.<br />- Assist in managing the phone volume and delegate the calls to the proper people through systematic<br />allocation.<br />- Assist in the merchandising and overall daily maintenance of the HJ cases and under stock.<br />- Maintain proper visual standards for all HJ cases, including jewelry polishing/steam cleaning.<br />- Qualify sales leads and assure each is directed to the appropriate sales team member in a systematic<br />manner.<br />- Maintain and update VIP client-care and event list database by partnering with HJ Sales Associates and<br />Management.<br />- Daily review of open service orders for HJ sales.<br />- Call clients as needed for service order pick up.<br />- Special projects as needed.<br />- Rotation into other departments as needed for similar responsibilities.<br />Profile<br />- Excellent interpersonal and communication skills are required<br />- Must be available to work retail hours including weekends<br />- Previous experience in luxury retail or hospitality is a plus<br />www.cartier.comales Assistant<br />- Strong understanding of Customer Service needs and Customer (internal and external) priorities<br />- Strong attention to detail with the ability to handle multiple tasks simultaneously and with precision.<br />- Bi Lingual or tri lingual Chinese or Portuguese would be a plus<br />- Professional appearance, demeanor and communication needed<br />- Self-Starter with Team-Player approach<br />- Detail oriented<br />- Data Entry as needed<br />- 4-year College degree preferred<br />Type of Position<br />Permanent<br />Work Location<br />USA - New York<br />Contact<br />Should you wish to apply, simply click the "Apply" button above. We look forward to hearing from you.<br />Our employees are part of a global family working in a fair, open and trusted environment. It is important for us to<br />ensure that new employees joining the Group have a strong commitment to our shared values.<br />We therefore reserve the right to ask all candidates in the final stages of recruitment to undergo a pre-employment<br />screening. Our approach to pre-employment screening is based on the principles of transparency, mutual respect and is<br />conducted in line with all applicable regulations.</p>', 'https://jobs.richemont.com/sap/bc/webdynpro/sap/hrrcf_a_posting_apply?PARAM=cG9zdF9pbnN0X2d1aWQ9NTNERjExQzk5NzU3MDkzMEUxMDA4MDAwMEEyNDA3REMmY2FuZF90eXBlPUVYVCZwYz0y&sap-ep-themeroot=SAP_CORBU&sap-client=010&sap-language=EN#', '', 980, 168, 2),
(652, 1409008712, '护照签证专家', 'VisaHQ', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '洛杉矶', 'None', 'Full Time', '<section class="section section--text">\n<h2 class="section__header">DESCRIPTION</h2>\n<p>We are looking for a full-time Passport and Visa Specialist to join our growing team in Los Angeles, CA. There is a good potential for growth with and within the company.<br /><br />Work directly with the Department of State, Embassies and Consulates. Receive, prepare, and submit applications for travel visas to various countries. Provide wide range of support to our clients that include answering telephone calls, emailing, responding to inquires, and using a variety of online applications. The person in this position must be highly organized, detailed oriented, and punctual.</p>\n</section>\n<section class="section section--text">\n<h2 class="section__header">REQUIREMENTS</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>At least an Associate''s Degree</li>\n<li>Experience in the field of travel preparation is highly desired</li>\n<li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills</li>\n<li>Knowledge of foreign languages is preferred (Russian, Spanish, Chinese, French)</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class="section section--text">\n<h2 class="section__header">BENEFITS</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Competitive salary</li>\n<li>Medical and dental insurance</li>\n<li>Vacation, sick days</li>\n<li>Paid holidays</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong><em>About VisaHQ</em></strong></p>\n<p>VisaHQ is undisputed leader of the passport and visa services industry in North America. We are privately owned, nimble, and technology savvy. We pioneered the shift to online visa application processing, and we have a sustainable competitive edge that is widening every day.&nbsp;We have 8 offices across the United States and Canada, as well as a number of international offices.&nbsp;We have been ranked as an Inc 5,000 fastest growing company three times in a row, including a top-20 ranking in the travel industry and a number 1 position in the D.C. metro area.</p>\n<p><em><strong>We are on the move... Join us!</strong></em></p>\n</section>', 'http://visahq.workable.com/jobs/16935', '', 980, 185, 2),
(655, 1409097746, '走四方旅游网诚聘销售客服丶网站美工、产品编辑、计调OP', '走四方旅游网(www.usitrip.com)', 'Service', 'Rowland Heights/Monterey Park, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Rowland Heights', 33.976124, -117.905342, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '罗兰岗', 'H1B', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>走四方旅游网诚聘销售客服丶网站美工、产品编辑、计调OP</strong></p>\n<p>走四方旅游网(usitrip.com)隶属Unitedstars International Ltd.(美国联星国际旅游集团)，公司总部位于美国加州洛杉矶，有Monterey Park和Rowland Heights两处营业部。上<a href="http://www.usitrip.com/">http://www.usitrip.com</a>了解公司基本概况。</p>\n<p><strong>现在诚聘</strong><strong>销售客服丶网站美工、产品编辑、计调</strong><strong>OP多名</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>1、销售客服</strong></p>\n<p><strong>工作职能：</strong><br /> 1.通过公司的网络平台对客户进行旅游线路的销售。<br /> 2.有良好的沟通技能与客户进行一对一的销售及客服。<br /> 3.能按时的完成公司每个月的销售指标。<br /> 4.经过公司的培训，能快速了解公司业务，熟悉公司产品。<br /> 5.有效处理客户投诉丶订单跟踪，各种客户突发事件处理，并且能与主管及时沟通。<br /> <strong>技能要求：</strong><br /> 1.中文沟通流利，口齿清晰，语言表达能力强，有一定英语基础。<br /> 2.打字速度快，会办公软件。<br /> 3.对电子商务平台有一定了解，知道网络营销的基本概念。<br /> 4.有耐心，面对不同客户都能展现出专业水准。<br /> 5.沟通能力丶应变能力强，能及时处理客户的问题。<br /> 6.有管理能力，能协调团队处理各种问题。</p>\n<p><br /> <strong>2、网站美工</strong></p>\n<p><strong>工作职能：</strong><br /> 1.负责网站的促销专题制作。<br /> 2.网站板块更新，Banner设计制作。<br /> 3.负责公司微博丶微信内容的图片设计丶长微博排版制作。<br /> 4.协助主管负责促销专题的策划制作。<br /> 5.对淘宝丶天猫丶旅游网站等促销专题制作有相当了解，会分析竞争对手的专题。<br /> <strong>技能要求：</strong><br /> 1.2年以上的网站美工工作经验。<br /> 2.熟练运用Photoshop，Illustrator，Flash，Dreamweaver，CSS等&nbsp;。<br /> 3.对颜色运用敏感，有良好的设计能力。<br /> 4.对专题设计有自己的想法，会比较分析竞争对手的内容。<br /> 5.沟通能力强，能和产品部协调安排好推广内容的制作。<br /> 6.有一定的策划能力，能独立完成网页专题的制作。</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>3、</strong><strong>产品编辑</strong></p>\n<p><strong>工作职能：</strong>&nbsp;<br /> 1.&nbsp;负责产品内容的更新，与供应商市场部互动配合网页做后台上传更新；&nbsp;<br /> 2.&nbsp;负责撰写编辑旅游线路产品；<br /> 3.&nbsp;负责跟进市场部，商品部新合作项目，并对渠道开拓及渠道维护负责；&nbsp;<br /> 4.&nbsp;对客服遇到的急需问题进行收集和答案整理，信息采集和编辑；&nbsp;<br /> 5.&nbsp;优化网站内容及线路介绍，包括二级名称，线路内容；&nbsp;<br /> 6.&nbsp;根据公司计划完成线路内容的整理，内容完善，价格核对以及销售培训资料的制作。<br /> <strong>技能要求：</strong>&nbsp;<br /> 1.&nbsp;有一定的中英文写作能力和策划能力，有良好中英文表达功底，有编辑策划经验者优先考虑；&nbsp;<br /> 2.&nbsp;善于收集信息和整合编辑，拥有敏锐的观察力和解析力，思维严谨，有网站编辑经验者优先；<br /> 3.&nbsp;打字速度快，熟练使用office办公软件，熟悉数据库操作；&nbsp;<br /> 4.&nbsp;文字编辑能力强，有一定的中文撰写能力；<br /> 5.&nbsp;做事认真，有耐心，积极主动，能吃苦耐劳，能承受一定压力，具团队合作意识；<br /> 6.&nbsp;对旅游线路具有一定程度的了解。</p>\n<p><br /> 4、<strong>计调</strong><strong>OP</strong></p>\n<p><strong>工作职能</strong>：</p>\n<p>1. 负责公司包团定制业务操作；</p>\n<p>2. 熟悉旅游行业，能熟练操作酒店预订丶车辆预订等业务;</p>\n<p>3. 负责对外的产品拓展，开发新的合作商；&nbsp;</p>\n<p>4. 负责包团定制部门的内部协调，制定合适的包团旅游产品；</p>\n<p>&nbsp;<strong>技能要求：</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>1. 熟练OP的业务操作；</p>\n<p>2. 能独立完成包团行程设计;<br /> 3. 英语口语能力较强，能独立完成供应商拓展，开发资源；&nbsp;<br /> 4. 对北美旅游资源有一定了解；&nbsp;<br /> 5. 思路清晰丶责任心强，能完成包团所需的酒店丶机票丶车辆的预订；<br /> 6. 务实丶踏实能按时完成公司分配的任务。</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>如果您还在找工作，那就不要怀疑自己的能力，请投简历至</strong><a href="mailto:hr@usitrip.com"><strong>hr@usitrip.com</strong></a><strong>，或直接致电走四方人事专线：</strong><strong>626-636-0184</strong><strong>工作地点在罗兰岗或蒙市，办公环境舒适，理想的工作平台，良好的发展空间！走四方期待您的加入！</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 'hr@usitrip.com', 1027, 17, 2),
(656, 1409114799, 'google收购分析师，在线合作伙伴', 'google', 'Technology', 'Beijing, China', 'China', 'Beijing', 'Beijing', 39.904030, 116.407524, '中国', '北京市', '北京', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="detail-item">\n<div class="detail-content offset">\n<p>The Online Partnerships Group (OPG) uses our portfolio of product solutions, including AdSense and DoubleClick tools, to help online publishers grow their businesses. You''ll provide innovative, industry-leading online advertising solutions for publishers and developers and proactively identify new opportunities. Some of the largest publishers on the web rely on our products and we''re always trying to exceed their expectations and strengthen our long-term partner relationships. Our team helps grow Google''s business with the largest online publishers and provides account management for users of AdSense, DoubleClick and more.</p>\n<p>As an Acquisition Strategist, you will proactively identify the growth opportunities for online or mobile partnerships and acquire prospective publishers to AdSense or AdMob networks. You have advanced data and analytical capabilities to identify large opportunities from the market. Your knowledge of online media combined with your communication skills and analytical abilities shapes how new business grows. You leverage your entrepreneurial drive to target, educate and persuade new customers to embrace Google''s latest advertising products and technologies. Using your influencing and relationship-building skills, you provide Google-caliber client service, research and market analysis. You anticipate how decisions are made, understand the industry and verticals as well as details of individual campaigns and persistently explore and uncover the business needs of clients.</p>\n</div>\n<div class="heading">Responsibilities</div>\n<div class="detail-content offset">\n<ul>\n<li>Acquire new customers to the network and build a&nbsp;strong&nbsp;pipeline for sustainable business growth.</li>\n<li>Collaborate with global teams to meet local markets'' expectations.</li>\n<li>Scalable initiatives for the larger pool of publishers to drive business growth and customer satisfaction.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class="tagstory">\n<div class="double">\n<div class="heading">Minimum qualifications</div>\n<div class="detail-content offset">\n<ul>\n<li>BA/BS degree or equivalent practical experience</li>\n<li>Ability to speak and write Mandarin and English fluently and idiomatically.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="double">\n<div class="heading">Preferred qualifications</div>\n<div class="detail-content offset">\n<ul>\n<li>MBA or advanced degree.</li>\n<li>Technology/online industry experience. Knowledgeable about consumer mobile products, internet, online products, customers, online advertising technologies and strategies, and market dynamics.</li>\n<li>Working experience in internet, advertising, e-commerce, publishing and online services. Ad sales experience.</li>\n<li>Self-directed, motivated and&nbsp;driven&nbsp;performer with exceptional multi-tasking abilities toward goals.</li>\n<li>Strategic thinking and&nbsp;strong&nbsp;data analysis skills.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="detail-item">\n<div class="heading">Area</div>\n<div class="detail-content offset">\n<p>There''s always more information out there, and our Partnerships team works to get it. We develop relationships with a range of organizations, from content providers to publishers, and find ways for them to reach their audiences and manage their digital businesses. We find great content for our products, and we also work with partner sites to syndicate our own Google products. From&nbsp;negotiating&nbsp;agreements to solving technical problems for partners, we''re in pursuit of gathering the world''s information.</p>\n</div>\n<div class="detail-content offset">\n<div class="tagstory">\n<div class="double">\n<div class="heading">Partnerships</div>\n<img class="conditional-format" src="https://www.google.com/about/careers/files/team_partnerships_image_348x348.jpg" alt="" />\n<div class="conditional-format">\n<p>Expand our business into new territories.</p>\n<span style="color: #444444;"><a href="http://www.google.com/about/careers/teams/partnerships/">Learn more about our Partnerships teams</a></span></div>\n</div>\n<div class="double">\n<div class="heading">Beijing</div>\n<img class="conditional-format" src="https://www.google.com/about/careers/files/location_beijing_image_348x348.jpg" alt="" />\n<div class="conditional-format">\n<p>As Google''s biggest office in China, we&rsquo;re located in a part of Beijing known as a tech epicenter. Our Googlers come from across the country and around the world, and we&rsquo;re home to engineers developing core Google products for global markets and sales teams working with advertisers big and small.</p>\n<span style="color: #444444;"><a href="http://www.google.com/about/careers/locations/beijing/">Learn more about our Beijing office</a></span></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="detail-item">\n<div class="heading">Job details</div>\n<div class="detail-content">\n<div>\n<div class="greytext info">Team or role:</div>\n<div class="info-text">Partnerships</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div class="greytext info">Job type:</div>\n<div class="info-text">Full-time</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div class="greytext info">Last updated:</div>\n<div class="info-text">Jul 23, 2014</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div class="greytext info">Job location(s):</div>\n<div class="info-text">Beijing, Beijing, China</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'https://www.google.com/about/careers/search?from=singlemessage&isappinstalled=0#!t=jo&jid=36605001&', '', 980, 132, 2),
(657, 1409185049, '高级中文成本会计师', 'Markwins International Corporation', 'Finance', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '洛杉矶', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Markwins is an global cosmetic manufacturer with expertly designed cosmetics and beauty care collection. We have leading beauty brands of Monster High, Front Cover, Wet n Wild, and Fergie both global and nationwide trend focused. We are seeking professional Senior Cost Accountant to join the US headquarters in City of Industry.</p>\n<p>Responsible for cost accounting, analysis and associated management including formulation of procedures and deal with external auditors<br />- Prepare, analyze and report weekly, monthly &amp; quarterly gross margin analysis by brand by customer type<br />- Analyze cost accounting data and assist with cycle count/physical inventories<br />- Prepare detailed account analysis and reconcile sales, cost and inventory, liability accounts by customer type by division<br />- Review and analyze inventory and margin reports, conduct research and perform analytical studies in regards to cost analysis and profitability<br />- Assist in month end closing, prepare journal entries as necessary, analyze inventory evaluation, inventory roll forward<br />- Communicate daily with China accounting team to work on the accounting books and coordinate with China manufacturing department<br />- Support and assist internal department reporting requirements such as audit &amp; tax schedules; deal with internal and external auditors<br />- Monitor inventory, costing, gross margin schedules and ensure timely submission to management<br />- Monitor and check the rationality of original expenses evidences<br />- Evaluate and audit the performance of factory productivity</p>\n<p>We require a Bachelors Degree in Accounting with 3+ years of related experience, proficient in Microsoft Excel &amp; Office and is able to adapt to different computer programs for efficient data gathering and analysis, strong organizational and communication skills. Able to research, compile, analyze, interpret data with recommendation. Able to work on details, analyze and reconcile complex accounts and reserves. Knowledge of GAAP &amp; cost accounting standards is required. Knowledge of Power Link systems is preferred. Cosmetic industry background is a plus. Able to work independently under minimal supervision. Bilingual/Chinese is required.</p>\n<p>Qualified candidates should submit their full resume with salary history and expectation to Human Resources via either facsimile (909) 595-8820 or email. Only local candidate without the need for work visa sponsorship will be considered. Ref- CA</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Markwins-International-Corporation/jobs/Senior-Cost-Accountant-44feda1d2b4ca203', '', 980, 121, 2),
(658, 1409249462, '中日餐企台', 'yeung II sushi', 'Resturant', 'Hoboken, NJ, United States', 'United States', 'New Jersey', 'Hoboken', 40.743992, -74.032364, '美利坚合众国', '新泽西州', '霍博肯', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>有意请联系 917 365 6506</p>', '', '', 1057, 10, 2),
(659, 1409259376, '国际业务行政助理', 'GlobalMed', 'Finance', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', '纽约', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p class="simple_format">Company Info</p>\n<p class="simple_format">GlobalMed, a privately held telemedicine company headquartered in Scottsdale, Arizona, is the leader of telemedicine companies in telehealth hardware and software R&amp;D, design, engineering, manufacture and support. Our team of telemedicine software developers and engineers work closely with scientific and medical professionals&mdash;from concept to application&mdash;to understand and translate unmet needs into next-generation integrated telemedicine tools that are unsurpassed in quality, affordability and flexibility. Our award-winning patented new medical technologies and unique intellectual properties culminate in solutions that exceed even the most challenging requirements for clarity, accuracy, accessibility, convenience and cost-effectiveness, and that create an ecosystem of connected health. Our innovative solutions are supported by unsurpassed service and unequaled customer responsiveness, making us the leader of all telemedicine companies.</p>\n<p class="simple_format">Job Description</p>\n<p class="simple_format">Develop and maintain business relationships with companies outside of the United States by identifying new business opportunities, developing strategies for increasing GlobalMed&rsquo;s global footprint. Travel outside the US will be required for tradeshows and client meetings. Position is tasked with conference calls, videoconferencing, and remote demonstrations to support customers, partners and prospects outside the United States. Will also require time spent documenting business development efforts and supporting the US Sales Team as needed.</p>\n<p class="simple_format">Main Responsibilities (3-8 bullet points):</p>\n<p class="simple_format">Identifying new business opportunities.&nbsp;<br />Developing strategies for increasing GlobalMed&rsquo;s global footprint.&nbsp;<br />Traveling outside the US for tradeshows and client meetings.&nbsp;<br />Deliver Client/Prospect remote presentations / videoconference to different time zones&nbsp;<br />Manage Sales Pipeline&nbsp;<br />Meet Sales Quotas&nbsp;<br />Educational Requirements:</p>\n<p class="simple_format">- Four year college degree, advance degree (M.B.A. or equivalent) preferred</p>\n<p class="simple_format">- Must speak and write Mandarin Chinese (Fluency required).</p>\n<p class="simple_format">- Must also be computer savvy</p>\n<p class="simple_format">- Excellent written and oral communication skills</p>\n<p class="simple_format">Minimum Requirements:</p>\n<p class="simple_format">- Able to travel internationally</p>\n<p class="simple_format">- Demonstrated experience managing sales pipeline</p>\n<p class="simple_format">- Demonstrated experience meeting sales and delivered revenue quotas</p>\n<p class="simple_format">- Experience in international business development (Business experience in Mandarin Chinese Speaking Country Preferred)</p>', 'http://www.doostang.com/signups/signup_syndicate_nonfinance/636437?utm_source=IndeedRiskInternal&utm_medium=sponsored&rx_medium=cpc&rx_campaign=indeed20&rx_source=indeed&rx_content=Doostang_ALL_Internal&utm_campaign=RiskInternal&utm_keyword=&kme=close%20loop%20syndication%20job%20lander%20hit&km_campaign=RiskInternal&km_job_board=Indeed&job_id=1388663251', '', 980, 231, 2),
(660, 1409259789, '国际研究生项目协调员', '南加大', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '洛杉矶', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div id="form_tab_1" class="form_tab">\n<div class="containers">\n<div id="form_container_5486" class="form_container">\n<h3>POSTING DETAILS</h3>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr><th>Requisition ID</th>\n<td>1001750</td>\n</tr>\n<tr><th>Position ID</th>\n<td>P01427519</td>\n</tr>\n<tr><th>Academic Title</th>\n<td>International Graduate Programs Coordinator</td>\n</tr>\n<tr><th>Department</th>\n<td>Viterbi/Graduate and Professional Programs</td>\n</tr>\n<tr><th>Location</th>\n<td>University Park Campus</td>\n</tr>\n<tr><th>Employment Type</th>\n<td>Full-Time</td>\n</tr>\n<tr><th>Percent of time for Part-time Position</th>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr><th>Employment Terms</th>\n<td>New, Fixed Term</td>\n</tr>\n<tr><th>Hiring Range</th>\n<td>$23.00 - $27.00</td>\n</tr>\n<tr><th>Job Announcement</th>\n<td>\n<p>The Graduate and Professional Programs Office (<span class="caps">GAPP</span>) at the&nbsp;<span class="caps">USC</span>&nbsp;Viterbi School of Engineering is seeking an International Graduate Programs Coordinator. The position reports to the Assistant Dean, Graduate Recruitment and is a full time, one year, fixed-term position. As the primary liaison for the Viterbi School&rsquo;s international engineering graduate students, with a specific focus on international Chinese graduate students, this position will assess this targeted student group and coordinate the planning and delivery of student programs and services that will enhance the quality of student life for the Chinese population of Viterbi graduate students, in particular students in the Master&rsquo;s program.</p>\n<p>Job Responsibilities:</p>\n<p>&bull; Strategize and implement a program to early promote and publicize the Viterbi school&rsquo;s graduate programs to the international Chinese student community.</p>\n<p>&bull; Active in all student conversion activities, including the crafting of targeted interactions and messages. Act as a resource for information exchange on program services.</p>\n<p>&bull; Provide early on-boarding to newly admitted/certified students by building relationship prior to new students&rsquo; arrival at the Viterbi school. Upon arrival, assist students to successfully acculturate into the United States and&nbsp;<span class="caps">USC</span>&nbsp;community.</p>\n<p>&bull; Coordinate orientation programming that translates important messages in mandarin, including, but no limited to, academic integrity and safety.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr><th>FLSA</th>\n<td>Non-Exempt</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<div id="form_container_5487" class="form_container">\n<h3>MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS</h3>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr><th>Minimum Education</th>\n<td>\n<p>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr><th>Minimum Experience</th>\n<td>\n<p>1 year Combined education/experience as substitute for minimum experience</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr><th>Minimum Field of Expertise</th>\n<td>\n<p>Student personnel administration</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<div id="form_container_5488" class="form_container">\n<h3>PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS</h3>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr><th>Preferred Education</th>\n<td>\n<p>Master&rsquo;s degree in student personnel administration, education, counseling or related field.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr><th>Preferred Experience</th>\n<td>\n<p>Fluent in mandarin. Excellent communication skills. First-hand knowledge of Chinese culture.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr><th>Supervises</th>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr><th>Supervises - Nature of Work</th>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr><th>Preferred Field of Expertise</th>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<div id="form_container_5489" class="form_container">\n<h3>ADDITIONAL INFORMATION</h3>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr><th>Special Instructions to Applicants</th>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr><th>Quicklink for Posting</th>\n<td><a href="http://jobs.usc.edu/postings/30493" target="_blank">http://jobs.usc.edu:80/postings/30493</a></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<h2 class="tab">Supplemental Questions</h2>\n<div class="form_container">\n<p><span class="reqd">Required fields are indicated with an asterisk (*).</span></p>\n</div>\n<h2 class="tab">Applicant Documents</h2>\n<div class="form_container"><strong>Required Documents</strong><ol>\n<li>Resume/CV</li>\n</ol><strong>Optional Documents</strong></div>', 'https://jobs.usc.edu/postings/30494', '', 980, 265, 2),
(661, 1409337422, 'Project Engineer(H1b sponsorship)', 'shell', 'Engineering', 'Deer Park, Texas, United States', 'United States', 'Texas', 'Deer Park', 29.705229, -95.123817, '美利坚合众国', '得克萨斯', '迪尔帕克', 'H1B', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>&nbsp;CONTACT INFORMATION:</strong></p>\n<p>Employer: Shell(H1b sponsorship)</p>\n<p>Name: Ms. Eve</p>\n<p>Title: Coordinate Recruiter</p>\n<p>Email: <a href="mailto:jie@trans-new.com">jie@trans-new.com</a></p>\n<p>Application method: send your resume to the email above</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Job Description</p>\n<p>The Project Engineer manages a wide variety of projects (up to $20 mln, depending on the position level) for the Deer Park Site.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Project Engineer has the primary responsibility for execution of Downstream Project Processes as they apply to front end development, detailed design and procurement. This includes execution of procedures such as MOC and PSSR. He/she also develops proposals in collaboration with operations, process engineering and discipline representatives. In addition, the project engineer will assist with mechanical start-up plans and procedures, provide technical support during start-ups, support training and assure documentation and knowledge transfer.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>In this role, he/she is accountable for safe, effective and efficient execution of all phases of the projects, including incorporation of the appropriate level of location input. The project engineer will work in a support role with the construction department for field construction.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Project Engineer may also be involved in departmental training activities; and/or serve on a variety of departmental and Plant Teams.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<p>&bull;The assignment will be in the Project Engineering Group in the Projects and Turnaround Department.</p>\n<p>&bull;Must have legal authorization to work in the US on a full-time basis for anyone other than current employer.</p>\n<p>&bull;Bachelor''s degree in Engineering.</p>\n<p>&bull;Minimum three (3) years project experience.</p>', '', 'jie@tans-new.com', 1100, 15, 2);
