f" alt="" /></td>\n<td colspan="2" align="right" valign="top">\n<div id="win0divHRS_SCH_WRK_HRS_REG_TEMPlbl"><span class="PSEDITBOXLABEL">Regular/Temporary</span></div>\n</td>\n<td colspan="6" align="left" valign="top">\n<div id="win0divHRS_SCH_WRK_HRS_REG_TEMP"><span id="HRS_SCH_WRK_HRS_REG_TEMP" class="PSEDITBOX_DISPONLY">Regular</span></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td height="14"><img src="https://employment.wellsfargo.com/cs/PSEA/cache/PT_PIXEL_1.gif" alt="" /></td>\n<td colspan="9" align="left" valign="top"><hr class="PSHORIZONTALRULE" align="left" width="100%" /></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td height="116"><img src="https://employment.wellsfargo.com/cs/PSEA/cache/PT_PIXEL_1.gif" alt="" /></td>\n<td colspan="9" align="left" valign="top">\n<div id="win0divHRS_SCH_PSTDSC$0">\n<table id="ACE_HRS_SCH_PSTDSC$0" class="PABACKGROUNDINVISIBLE" border="0" width="885" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width="6" height="8"><img src="https://employment.wellsfargo.com/cs/PSEA/cache/PT_PIXEL_1.gif" alt="" width="6" height="1" /></td>\n<td width="879"><img src="https://employment.wellsfargo.com/cs/PSEA/cache/PT_PIXEL_1.gif" alt="" width="879" height="1" /></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td height="20"><img src="https://employment.wellsfargo.com/cs/PSEA/cache/PT_PIXEL_1.gif" alt="" /></td>\n<td align="left" valign="top">\n<div id="win0divHRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCR$0"><span id="HRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCR$0" class="PABOLDTEXT">Job Description</span></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td height="18"><img src="https://employment.wellsfargo.com/cs/PSEA/cache/PT_PIXEL_1.gif" alt="" /></td>\n<td align="left" valign="top">\n<div id="win0divHRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCRLONG$0">\n<div id="HRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCRLONG$0" class="PSLONGEDITBOX"><br />\n<div id="RTEDiv777" class="PT_RTE_DISPLAYONLY">\n<div><strong>Start your future now</strong></div>\n<div>Whether you&rsquo;re just beginning your career or taking it to the next level, Wells Fargo has the right job for you.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>A Phone Banker spends nearly 100% of his/her time on the phone answering questions for Wells Fargo customers. The working environment is fun and relaxed with a casual dress code but is also demanding and structured, and involves overcoming customers&rsquo; banking concerns which can include some escalated issues.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Phone Bankers are expected to sell products and services and achieve aggressive sales goals which are measured daily.&nbsp; Our best Phone Bankers thrive on customer interaction and never miss an opportunity to enhance the customer&rsquo;s relationship with Wells Fargo by marketing new products and services. They always handle each customer with a friendly, courteous touch while following strict procedures for handling various types of inquiries.&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>We provide our Phone Bankers with continuous coaching and development which not only enhances their ability to provide exemplary service and product solutions to our customers, but also enhances the Phone Bankers&rsquo; career growth. Our successful bankers demonstrate self-motivation, a positive attitude, have the ability to work well on a team and have a solid work history.&nbsp; They also demonstrate strong listening, written and verbal communication skills.&nbsp; They are receptive to coaching and feedback, have the desire to meet/exceed goals and solve problems while working in a fast paced environment.&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Our Phone Bankers play a critical role in our customers&rsquo; lives; therefore, predictable and reliable attendance is an essential function of the position.&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Currently hiring for training class starting on November 3<sup>rd</sup>.&nbsp;&nbsp; Training hours are 8:30am &ndash;5:00pm Monday-Friday for 6 weeks (Must be available to attend entire paid training class).&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Current schedules being offered after training will be between the hours of 6:00am to 7:00pm with Saturday and Sunday off.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Salary Range - $13.62/hr. - $14.81/hr. DOE plus eligible to participate in the WFCC Service Incentive Plan</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Our next big investment is in you!&nbsp; Wells Fargo offers:</div>\n<ul>\n<li>A broad array of medical, dental, and vision plans</li>\n<li>Paid Time Off</li>\n<li>401 (k) and Stock Purchase Plans</li>\n<li>Discounts and Savings on Wells Fargo financial products, home mortgages and services</li>\n<li>Tuition Reimbursement</li>\n<li>Wellness Benefits</li>\n<li>Commuter Benefits</li>\n</ul>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Please note: Based on the volume of applications received, this job posting may be removed prior to the indicated close date.&nbsp;&nbsp; If you do not apply prior to the closing of this posting, we encourage you to apply for other opportunities with Wells Fargo.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>IMPORTANT:&nbsp; Please ensure your contact information (e-mail address and phone number) is current in your Wells Fargo Jobs Profile. Initial contact will be made via e-mail.&nbsp; Please check your e-mail regularly for updates.&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td height="20"><img src="https://employment.wellsfargo.com/cs/PSEA/cache/PT_PIXEL_1.gif" alt="" /></td>\n<td align="left" valign="top">\n<div id="win0divHRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCR$1"><span id="HRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCR$1" class="PABOLDTEXT">Basic Qualifications</span></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td height="18"><img src="https://employment.wellsfargo.com/cs/PSEA/cache/PT_PIXEL_1.gif" alt="" /></td>\n<td align="left" valign="top">\n<div id="win0divHRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCRLONG$1">\n<div id="HRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCRLONG$1" class="PSLONGEDITBOX"><br />\n<div id="RTEDiv985" class="PT_RTE_DISPLAYONLY">6 months customer service and sales experience.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td height="20"><img src="https://employment.wellsfargo.com/cs/PSEA/cache/PT_PIXEL_1.gif" alt="" /></td>\n<td align="left" valign="top">\n<div id="win0divHRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCR$2"><span id="HRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCR$2" class="PABOLDTEXT">Minimum Qualifications</span></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td height="12"><img src="https://employment.wellsfargo.com/cs/PSEA/cache/PT_PIXEL_1.gif" alt="" /></td>\n<td align="left" valign="top">\n<div id="win0divHRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCRLONG$2">\n<div id="HRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCRLONG$2" class="PSLONGEDITBOX"><br />\n<div id="RTEDiv132" class="PT_RTE_DISPLAYONLY">\n<p>Basic computer skills including the ability to navigate multiple windows and applications and utilize search tools to find information.</p>\n<p>Experience with supporting both Chinese (Mandarin/Cantonese) and English speaking customers.<br /><br />The successful passing of the language proficiency assessment (speaking and reading) is required to qualify for the bilingual Chinese (Mandarin/Cantonese)/English queue (administered during the interviewing process).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'https://employment.wellsfargo.com/psc/PSEA/APPLICANT_NW/HRMS/c/HRS_HRAM.HRS_APP_SCHJOB.GBL?Page=HRS_APP_JBPST&FOCUS=Applicant&SiteId=1&JobOpeningId=5034816&PostingSeq=1&', '', 980, 348, 2),
(686, 1410655950, 'Java Developer', '硅谷Pre-IPO软件公司', 'Technology', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '旧金山', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>硅谷Pre-IPO软件公司，招募优秀的Java Developer,懂Cassandra/分布式系统，Lucene/搜索技术者最佳</p>', '', 'info@trans-new.com', 980, 112, 2),
(687, 1410656991, 'iOS developer', 'Google ', 'Technology', 'Mountain View, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Mountain View', 37.386051, -122.083855, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '山景城', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="detail-item">\n<div class="detail-content offset">\n<p>Software Engineers have a penchant for solving complex and interesting problems. Pushing the boundaries of current mobile platforms, you will perform technological feats under constrained environments and will be presented with exciting challenges in native or mobile application development. Our Software Engineers in Mobile Applications work on many projects that carry varying responsibilities. You will build Google products (Advertising, Android, Google+, Chrome, Earth, Gmail, Maps, Search, Wallet or other exciting projects) for either Android or iOS.</p>\n<p>If you are an Android Developer, you will develop applications primarily in Java and using the Android SDK. You might design and develop open-source Android applications that are part of the Android Open Source Project or closed-source Google applications that are the interface to Google services on Android.</p>\n<p>If you are an iOS Developer, you will develop applications and SDKs primarily in Objective-C and using the iOS SDK.</p>\n</div>\n<div class="heading">Responsibilities</div>\n<div class="detail-content offset">\n<ul>\n<li>Design and implement new user-facing features in Google&rsquo;s products.</li>\n<li>Build the libraries and frameworks that support large, complex web applications like Gmail, Google Search, and Google Maps.</li>\n<li>Optimize web applications to maximize speed and scale. Support diverse clients from high powered desktop computers to small footprint mobile devices.</li>\n<li>Write client-side code for web-based applications, create fast, easy-to-use, high volume production applications, and develop prototypes quickly.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class="tagstory">\n<div class="double">\n<div class="heading">Minimum qualifications</div>\n<div class="detail-content offset">\n<ul>\n<li>BA/BS in Computer Science or related technical field&nbsp;<br />or equivalent practical&nbsp;experience. &nbsp;</li>\n<li>1 year relevant work experience.</li>\n<li>Programming experience in Java, Objective-C, or C++.</li>\n<li>Experience in mobile application development.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="double">\n<div class="heading">Preferred qualifications</div>\n<div class="detail-content offset">\n<ul>\n<li>Deep technical knowledge of mobile application development (either Android or iOS).</li>\n<li>Considerable programming experience in either Java, Objective-C or C++.</li>\n<li>Knowledge of UI frameworks (either Android, iOS, XML), MVP application design and complex, reactive touch based UI.</li>\n<li>Strong foundation in computer science, with strong competencies in data structures, algorithms and software design optimized for embedded systems.</li>\n<li>Specialist domains: Embedded/device systems, mobile optimized websites, mobile web browsers, client application development for Windows/Mac (Chrome, WebKit, etc.), third party libraries for either Android or iOS.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="detail-item">\n<div class="heading">Area</div>\n<div class="detail-content offset">\n<p>Google is and always will be an engineering company. We hire people with a broad set of technical skills who are ready to tackle some of technology''s greatest challenges and make an impact on millions, if not billions, of users. At Google, engineers not only revolutionize search, they routinely work on massive scalability and storage solutions, large-scale applications and entirely new platforms for developers around the world. From AdWords to Chrome, Android to YouTube, Social to Local, Google engineers are changing the world one technological achievement after another.</p>\n</div>\n<div class="detail-content offset">\n<div class="tagstory">\n<div class="double">\n<div class="heading">Mountain View (Global HQ)</div>\n<img class="conditional-format" src="https://www.google.com/about/careers/files/location_mountain-view_image_348x348.jpg" alt="" />\n<div class="conditional-format">\n<p>Want to stop talking about changing the world and actually do it? At Google Mountain View, our global headquarters, we make products for hundreds of millions of users around the world that change the ways they create, share, communicate, collaborate and do business.</p>\n<span style="color: #444444;"><a href="http://www.google.com/about/careers/locations/mountain-view/">Learn more about our Mountain View global headquarters</a></span></div>\n</div>\n<div class="double">\n<div class="heading">Software Engineering</div>\n<img class="conditional-format" src="https://www.google.com/about/careers/files/team_swe_image_348x348.jpg" alt="" />\n<div class="conditional-format">\n<p>Develop the next-generation technologies that change how millions interact.</p>\n<span style="color: #444444;"><a href="http://www.google.com/about/careers/teams/engineering/swe/">Learn more about our Software Engineering roles</a></span></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="detail-item">\n<div class="heading">Job details</div>\n<div class="detail-content">\n<div>\n<div class="greytext info">Team or role:</div>\n<div class="info-text">Software Engineering</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div class="greytext info">Job type:</div>\n<div class="info-text">Full-time</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div class="greytext info">Last updated:</div>\n<div class="info-text">Sep 11, 2014</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div class="greytext info">Job location(s):</div>\n<div class="info-text">Mountain View, CA, USA</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'https://www.google.com/about/careers/search#!t=jo&jid=34157&', '', 980, 153, 2),
(688, 1410747570, '销售协调员', 'Devicom International Inc', 'Marketing', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '洛杉矶', 'None', 'Full Time', '<h2>About the Job</h2>\n<div id="jobBodyContent">\n<p><span style="font-family: Times;">Devicom</span><span style="font-family: Times;">&nbsp;Int&rsquo;l Inc is an international e-Commerce solution provider. We are looking for a Marketing Coordinator to help us manage and grow our marketing department. With a consumer-branded focused approach, the Marketing Coordinator will assist the Marketing Team in initiatives that support assigned retail product lines in a corporate marketing environment. This Coordinator aids in the execution of outlined retail e-Commerce strategies while looking for continuous product and marketing improvements, enhancements and opportunities that drive business growth. The marketing coordinator will also work with team in China to collectively develop manage and execute both branded and private label programs according to specified timelines while being able to coordinate and communicate customer related issues to our product team in China.</span></p>\n<p><br /><span style="font-family: Times;">Essential Duties:</span><br /><span style="font-family: Times;">&bull; Participate in creating and executing marketing and product initiatives to achieve planned growth, customer satisfaction and product goals</span><br /><span style="font-family: Times;">&bull; Work with VP of Marketing and Product Managers on executing marketing or product tasks and initiatives that serve the customers'' and company business objectives</span><br /><span style="font-family: Times;">&bull; Clearly manage communications between Retail Marketing, Customer Service, Product Management and the IT to achieve goals associated with assigned projects</span><br /><span style="font-family: Times;">&bull; Responsible for the management and tracking of tasks, timelines, internal/external tasks, communication and approvals, for assigned projects, from product concept to receipt of finished goods</span><br /><span style="font-family: Times;">&bull; Serve as liaison to the Product Sales Team on specific customer programs, working on deliverables related to meeting customer expectations&bull;</span><br /><br /><span style="font-family: Times;">Requirements:</span><br /><span style="font-family: Times;">&bull; Must have excellent verbal and written skills in Chinese and English</span><br /><span style="font-family: Times;">&bull; Must have excellent project management skills</span><br /><span style="font-family: Times;">&bull; Intermediate to advanced skills with Microsoft Word products (Word, Excel, PowerPoint)</span><br /><span style="font-family: Times;">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Times;">Experience:</span><br /><span style="font-family: Times;">&bull; BS (minimum) in marketing, business or related ecommerce or&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family: Times;">Internet</span><span style="font-family: Times;">&nbsp;field</span><br /><span style="font-family: Times;">&bull; Proven ability to effectively communicate with internal and external partners, at all levels, both in Chinese and English.</span><br /><span style="font-family: Times;">&bull; Ability to effectively work simultaneously on many projects with ever-changing priorities</span><br /><span style="font-family: Times;">Ability to be self-motivated and a self-starter and adapt to a fast-paced environment</span></p>\n</div>', 'http://jobview.monster.com/Marketing-Coordinator-Job-Cerritos-CA-US-139395231.aspx?WT.mc_n=Indeed_US&from=indeed', '', 980, 150, 2),
(689, 1410809204, 'Accounting & HR specialist', '中集集团北美公司', 'Finance', 'Moreno Valley, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Moreno Valley', 33.942467, -117.229675, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '莫雷诺谷', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>工作/加州Riverside/Moreno Valley 中集集团北美公司正招聘Accounting &amp; HR specialist。要求：Bachelor degree in Accounting，有美国当地人事工作经验。中英文流利</p>', '', 'siying.song@cimc.com', 980, 302, 2),
