(691, 1410906052, '顶级设计公司招聘商务拓展专员', '环球梦想设计公司', 'Design', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', '纽约', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>环球梦想顶级华人设计公司公司位于纽约华尔街,专为国内外大型公司提供品牌策划,网站设计&amp;app设计与开发,广告设计等业务。</p>\n<p>1、熟悉项目销售或服务业务模式;<br />2、根据公司要求,积极开发有效客户资源;<br />3、善于电话、面谈等沟通并能够记录有效的沟通信息;<br />4、负责销售区域内销售活动的策划和执行,完成销售任务;<br />5、管理维护客户关系以及客户间的长期战略合作计划;<br />6、配合部门主管完成临时安排的工作。<br />可兼职或全职,时间灵活自由<br />薪资:按项目分成,通过考核期有底薪与提成<br />提供:养老保险 医疗保险 生育保险 工伤保险 住房公积金 年终奖 员工旅游 员工培训<br />其它福利待遇:<br />其它福利待遇:<br />1、工资构成:无责底薪+车补+饭补+通讯费+节日奖金+年终奖金+年终分红。<br />2、公平公正的晋升空间,相关晋升从内部优秀员工中提拔产生。<br />3、公司提供各部门相关专业、技能的培训,让新人轻松上岗,能力获得最大提升。<br />4、公司营销部门提供销售业务和谈判、沟通技巧等各方面技能的专业培训,零经验一个月也能成精英。<br />5、公司提供丰富多采的奖励制度,如长期服务奖、月度最佳服务奖、销售精英奖、年度最佳个人/部门大奖。</p>\n<p>www.gdreamdesign.com</p>\n<p>222 Broadway New York,</p>\n<p>New York, USA</p>\n<p>Tel: 917-833-4088</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/viewjob?cmp=环球梦想设计公司&t=顶级设计公司招聘商务拓展专员&jk=5aa3b577052b836a&sjdu=QwrRXKrqZ3CNX5W-O9jEvRIRPotLQWL7t2hxr0GRf5CZEctvBkzur0TzMXmJa4FmpMMq1P2ZDWtcqqUs34cWZCAvI0prDMPbzNRnNKMIVaPyxMf6v8nMOnETGw1ea4pF7XaViJclywAvLNUV4NvCTnTKJ04UhGJL3CjqYI911PxYgel7Lut-VfskTDyEvYT697p7LshCeVcYjdU576I2hBRpUlUKaG57nSovpPQZg3w', '', 980, 228, 2),
(692, 1410921937, 'C/C++ Developer - Network Design and Security', 'Bloomberg正', 'Media', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', '纽约', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>要求：CS本科或硕士或工程相关的专业. 3+年使用C/C++， Python and/or Perl经验, 超强沟通， 解决问题能力. 熟悉Data Structures, Algorithms, and Object-Oriented design</p>\n<h3 class="sub-header">Job description</h3>\n<div class="rich-text"><strong>Job Requisition Number:</strong>42540<br /><br />The Role:<br /><br />Bloomberg''s Network Design Information Security (NDIS) Team is looking for a developer to provide the building blocks for an automation system encompassing both Open Source and third party vendor solutions that will encompass all aspects of monitoring, alarming, and network security configuration for several hundred proxy servers, firewalls, caches, and load balancers. The successful detail-oriented candidate will have the opportunity to work on the initial builds and implementation of this multi- platform and multi-tiered system, and be involved from requirements generation, to development planning, development, implementation, and feature and bug fix prioritization.<br /><br />Responsibilities:<br /><br />- Evaluate new technologies and growing NDIS'' internal automation projects<br />- Evaluate infrastructure requirements from dev and design/deploy production solutions<br />- Create productive models for integrating internal dev teams and vendors with our infrastructure<br />- Understand and collaboratively derive common dev workflows for a variety of security-related technologies<br /><br /><strong>Qualifications:<br /><br /></strong>- Bachelor''s or Master''s Degree in Computer Science, Engineering or related field (or equivalent expertise)<br />- Minimum of 3 years of C/C++ development experience, or related higher level languages. Along with strong Python and/or Perl development experience<br />- Solid understanding of Data Structures, Algorithms, and Object-Oriented design<br />- Strong problem solving skills<br />- Strong (especially written) English communication skills<br />- Experience with High-Performance Unix Programming will be an advantage<br />- Knowledge of open source queuing systems (RabbitMQ) will be an advantage<br /><br />Desired Qualifications:<br /><br />- Prior successful experience as a systems performance or site/systems reliability engineer<br />- Extensive experience working with fault tolerant approaches in a large scale distributed environment and high performance systems<br />- Demonstrated experience working in large, complex systems environments<br />- Deep understanding of internet and networking protocols<br />- A passion for performance excellence, robustness and engineering mindset<br />- MS in Computer Science or related technical field<br />- 6+ years relevant work experience, including experience in a high-volume or critical production service environment<br />- Expertise analyzing and troubleshooting large-scale distributed systems<br />- Knowledge of IP networking, network analysis and performance and application issues using standard tools such as tcpdump<br />- Ability to handle periodic on-call duty as well as out-of-band requests</div>', 'https://www.linkedin.com/jobs2/view/21767347?trk=vsrp_jobs_res_name&trkInfo=VSRPsearchId%3A3301255351410900225162%2CVSRPtargetId%3A21767347%2CVSRPcmpt%3Aprimary', '', 980, 144, 2),
(693, 1411087817, '质量保证工程师-电池技术', 'Arclyte Technologies', 'Technology', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '洛杉矶', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Quality Assurance Engineer<br />Arclyte Technologies &ndash; Alhambra, CA<br />Arclyte Technologies is looking to add a Quality Assurance Engineer to its growing team. This individual will be responsible in continuing the quality reputation Arclyte has built in the industry for the past 5 years. You will work with the executive VP of Supply Chain to reinforce and create testing standards and procedures as well as execute on the actual testing. Attention to detail and an eye for quality is critical, along with the ability to communicate effectively to internal team and external customers on results. In your role as a Quality Assurance Engineer, you will be the subject matter expert having great impact on Arclyte''s products and supply chain.</p>\n<p>Key Responsibilities<br />*Perform inspections and set quality assurance testing models for finished and semi-finished products<br />*Utilize standard engineering concepts, practices and procedures in electrical/mechanical engineering<br />*Communicate test results both verbally and written to manufacturers in Asia via email, phone, and/or QQ<br />*Assist Operations during Purchase Order receipt checking all products meet testing/quality standards<br />*Provide detailed evaluation reports to Supply Chain on all suppliers and manufacturers</p>\n<p>Requirements<br />*Fluent in reading, writing, and speaking Mandarin Chinese is a must<br />*Bachelor of Science in Electrical Engineering or Mechanical Engineering<br />*At minimum 2-3 years of engineering experience is preferred<br />*Very strong written and documentation skills<br />*Knowledge and/or experience in battery technology</p>\n<p>Compensation<br />*Annual Salary Range: $45,000 - $55,000<br />*Medical Insurance: 100% company covered policy<br />*401k: Eligible after 1 year of employment<br />*Paid Vacation, Holiday, and Sick Days</p>\n<p>Job Type: Full-time</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Arclyte-Technologies/jobs/QA-Engineer-f326a18c2af409a4', '', 980, 106, 2),
(694, 1411176583, 'Executive Assistant 行政助理', 'Global Law Group', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '洛杉矶', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Our Pasadena office has an immediate need to hire a Bilingual (Mandarin) Executive Assistant. This person report directly to the President and provides executive support in a one-on-one working relationship. The Executive Assistant serves as a primary point of contact for internal and external constituencies on all matters pertaining to the Office of the President. Responsibilities include but not limited to completes a broad variety of administrative tasks for the President including: managing and maintain all the schedules, plan and make travel arrangements, arrange and coordinate meetings and events, liaise with internal staff at all levels, interact with external corporate and personal contacts, assorted personal assistance tasks as requested by the President and coordinate project-based work as needed.</p>\n<p>Qualification:<br />- Bilingual in Chinese (Mandarin) is required.<br />- Proficient in Microsoft Office (Outlook, Word , Excel and Power Point).<br />- Strong organizational skills that reflect ability to perform and prioritize multiple tasks seamlessly with excellent attention to detail.<br />- Demonstrated proactive approaches to problem-solving with strong decision-making capability.<br />- Emotional maturity.<br />- Highly resourceful team-player, with the ability to also be extremely effective independently<br />- Bachelor''s degree required.<br />- 3 to 5 years of experience supporting C-Level executives.</p>\n<p>Compensations:<br />- We offer competitive salary and would vary depending on work experience.<br />- Medical insurance<br />- Dental insurance<br />- Vision Insurance<br />- 401K with company matching<br />- Vacation time off<br />- Sick time off<br />- Personal time off<br />- FSA<br />- Paid holidays</p>\n<p>Please email your resume with desired salary for immediate consideration.</p>\n<p>Job Type: Full-time</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Global-Law-Group/jobs/Bilingual-Executive-Assistant-bd19cfd8df752095', '', 980, 174, 2),
(695, 1411176994, '销售经理和销售代表', '大型地板公司', 'Marketing', 'Chicago, IL, United States', 'United States', 'Illinois', 'Chicago', 41.878113, -87.629799, '美利坚合众国', '伊利诺伊州', '芝加哥', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>大型地板公司，因扩展美国业务，在芝加哥开设新分部，公司在亚特兰大和休斯敦的分部已成立多年，之后还将在北美扩展10多个网点。现因业务需求诚招销售经理和销售代表若干。底薪+提成。 有意者请联系我们，点击申请。</p>', '', 'ddccfloor.chicago@gmail.com', 980, 184, 2),
