(699, 1411339638, '精神护理协调员(兼职)', 'Metropolitan Jewish Health System', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', '纽约', '纽约', 'None', 'Part Time', '<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Overview:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<p>Our groundbreaking hospice and palliative care programs offer a significant difference when dealing with a life-limiting condition. We offer a broad range of services in the community or facility-based to help patients and their families ease the burden of managing a life-limiting illness or end of life care. &nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>We truly value our staff and further acknowledge their contributions by offering:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Employee and family health coverage</li>\n<li>Competitive salaries</li>\n<li>Employer contributed pension plan</li>\n<li>Generous time off</li>\n<li>Tuition reimbursement</li>\n<li>403(b) retirement plan</li>\n</ul>\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Responsibilities:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<p>The Spiritual Care Coordinator is responsible for coordinating and providing direct pastoral support services to patients and families. &nbsp;The Coordinator also coordinates additional spiritual support with religious affiliations as requested by patients and families. In addition, the Spiritual Care Coordinator completes and prepares documentation from clinical contacts and patients, inputs clinical data into MISYS database and maintains updated intake reports.</p>\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Qualifications:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<p>We are seeking a candidate who is bilingual Chinese speaking (Cantonese and Mandarin) and possesses a Bachelor''s degree from an accredited college (Divinity Degree required) and a minimum of one year experience post graduate in a healthcare setting. &nbsp;Also, he or she needs to be proficient with the Microsoft Word and Microsoft Excel software applications. &nbsp;The candidate must have the ability to work within an interdisciplinary team environment and have excellent communication, listening and organizational skills. Strong teaching and public speaking abilities are a must for the role, as well as the ability to input clinical data proficiently. &nbsp;A valid NYS driver''s license is preferred. &nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_Navigation">&nbsp;</div>', 'https://careers-mjhs.icims.com/jobs/2886/spiritual-care-coordinator-part-time/job?mode=job&iis=Indeed.com&iisn=Indeed.com&mobile=false&width=950&height=500&bga=true&needsRedirect=false', '', 980, 122, 2),
(700, 1411441910, '双语伙伴（中英）照顾老人', 'At Comfort Keepers ', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', '纽约', '纽约', 'None', 'Part Time', '<div>\n<div><span class="tdHeader left">JOB DESCRIPTION</span></div>\n<div class="hrspacetop">&nbsp;</div>\n<hr />\n<div class="hrspacebottom">&nbsp;</div>\n<div id="jobdescri"><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_lblJobDescriptionFR"><strong>At Comfort Keepers</strong>&nbsp;nothing is more important than helping seniors live full, independent, and dignified lives within the comfort of their own homes.&nbsp;<strong>Comfort Keepers&nbsp;</strong>is dedicated to providing in-home elder care that enriches our clients'' lives and helps them maintain the highest possible level of independent living.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<br /><br />Comfort Keepers is seeking highly dependable and reliable Companion/Caregivers who love to work with the elderly population. We are currently looking for candidates who are willing to serve the Brooklyn area.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /><br />The Companion/Caregiver provides non-medical, in-home support and home management services to clients. He or she provides companionship to those individuals requiring socialization and minimum guidance for a safe, protected, clean, and orderly environment.<br /><br />The ideal candidate for this position has a high school diploma or GED and has at least two years of experience in this or a similar job, can work a flexible schedule that includes weekends and holidays, and is fluent in English and Chinese (speaking and writing).&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;We prefer, but is not required, that the candidate&nbsp;&nbsp;has reliable transportation, a valid driver''s license, a clean driving record, and current automobile insurance. In addition, he or she is genuinely concerned about helping people and has high moral standards of honesty and integrity. Empathy and the ability to listen, good time management skills, and professional dress, speech, and behavior are all required for this position.</span></div>\n<div class="clear height50">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div><span class="tdHeader left">RESPONSIBILITIES</span></div>\n<div class="hrspacetop">&nbsp;</div>\n<hr />\n<div class="hrspacebottom">&nbsp;</div>\n<ul>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_0" class="spaceleft20">Provides general attention to client&rsquo;s non-medical needs following an established Plan of Care</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_1" class="spaceleft20">Helps with activities of daily living by providing approved personal care activities, including bathing, dressing, toileting, grooming, oral hygiene, and/or ambulation as specified in the Plan of Care</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_2" class="spaceleft20">Provides companionship for the client, including talking and listening to, reading aloud, and providing social and emotional support</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_3" class="spaceleft20">Promotes the client&rsquo;s mental alertness through involvement in activities of interest</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_4" class="spaceleft20">Provides emotional support and promotes a sense of well-being</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_5" class="spaceleft20">Provides a clean, safe, and healthy environment for clients and family members by performing light housekeeping tasks including laundering of client&rsquo;s garments and linens and changing the bed</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_6" class="spaceleft20">May prepare and serve meals as directed and ensures that dishes are washed and kitchen is clean after each meal</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_7" class="spaceleft20">Helps client complete necessary phone calls, letter writing, etc., and accompanies client on walks, community trips, doctor&rsquo;s office, bank, beauty salons, etc.</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_8" class="spaceleft20">Reminds client to take self-administered medications</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_9" class="spaceleft20">Observes and reports any changes in the client&rsquo;s mental, physical, or emotional condition or home situation to the appropriate supervisor</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_10" class="spaceleft20">Establishes and maintains effective communication and a professional relationship with clients, family members, and co-workers</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_11" class="spaceleft20">Participates in in-service and continuing education programs, staff meetings, and client conferences as requested by his or her immediate supervisor</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_12" class="spaceleft20">Uses equipment and supplies safely and properly</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_13" class="spaceleft20">Maintains confidentiality regarding client information</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_14" class="spaceleft20">Performs other related duties as assigned</span></li>\n</ul>\n<div class="clear height50">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div><span class="tdHeader left">QUALIFICATIONS</span></div>\n<div class="hrspacetop">&nbsp;</div>\n<hr />\n<div class="hrspacebottom">&nbsp;</div>\n<ul>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_0" class="spaceleft20">Must be at least 21 years old</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_1" class="spaceleft20">High school diploma or GED preferred</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_2" class="spaceleft20">Two years relevant experience required</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_3" class="spaceleft20">Bilingual English/Chinese (speaking and writing)</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_4" class="spaceleft20">Successful completion of the Comfort Keepers training and orientation program</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_5" class="spaceleft20">Able to follow verbal and written instructions and document services provided</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_6" class="spaceleft20">Able to function independently in the home setting with minimal direct supervision</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_7" class="spaceleft20">Able to fulfill assignments with reliability and punctuality</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_8" class="spaceleft20">Able to maintain satisfactory relationships with clients, family, and team members</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_9" class="spaceleft20">Neat, clean, and professional appearance</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_10" class="spaceleft20">Able to stand, sit, walk, reach, kneel, crouch, and lift up to 25 pounds</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_11" class="spaceleft20">Unrestricted driver''s license and clean driving record</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_12" class="spaceleft20">Reliable transportation and valid automobile insurance</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_13" class="spaceleft20">Able to work days, evenings, weekends, and holidays</span></li>\n</ul>\n<div class="clear height50">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div><span class="tdHeader left">BENEFITS</span></div>\n<div class="hrspacetop">&nbsp;</div>\n<hr />\n<div class="hrspacebottom">&nbsp;</div>\n<ul>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptBenefit_lblBenefitName_0" class="spaceleft20">Holiday Pay</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptBenefit_lblBenefitName_1" class="spaceleft20">Vacation Pay</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptBenefit_lblBenefitName_2" class="spaceleft20">Retirement Plan</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptBenefit_lblBenefitName_3" class="spaceleft20">Disability Insurance</span></li>\n<li></li>\n</ul>\n</div>', 'https://comfortkeepers459.hyrell.com/UI/Views/Applicant/VirtualStepPositionDetails.aspx?TemplateId=114030&IsAutoRefresh=True&r=Indeed&tzi=Pacific%20Standard%20Time', '', 980, 165, 2),
(701, 1411442422, '业务员', '新媒体', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', '纽约', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>新媒体位于大颈镇纽约,近法拉盛。因快速业务成长需诚聘数名业务员。有销售经验优先，对销售工作有熱情，中英文流利；有良好的沟通能力，底薪加行业最高提成。工作环境好。公司地点交通方便， 可乘公车N21或N20直达公司门口。&nbsp;<br /><br />我们的要求：<br />1：讲中文，略懂英语。<br />2. 熟悉房地产业务者优先<br />3：有责任心<br />4：有销售意识<br />5: 愿意为自己积累财富而付出行动<br /><br />如果你对自己有信心，如果你想在这个多年打造的强大平台上面起飞， 为自己赢得可观的收入，那就马上联系面试！<br />请点击申请并附上简历，或电话至：516-829-2611<br /><br /></p>', '', 'contactus@jinti.net', 980, 167, 2),
(702, 1411442582, '在线商店管理员', 'Yoyo Chinese Inc ', 'Marketing', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '洛杉矶', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>We are an online Chinese language education company that uses video lessons to teach to students from all over the world. As a start-up, we have seen great success so far, but want a marketing manager who has the skills and vision to take the company further.</p>\n<p>This will be an exciting full-time position. You''ll not only design and execute creative marketing plans, you''ll also get to see, first-hand, how your hard work directly impacts the growth of a company with a strong product. As marketing manager, you''ll work closely with the company founder Yangyang Cheng and leading junior marketing staff to develop and execute concrete marketing strategies that will mold and shape the direction of this company.</p>\n<p>We''re looking for candidates who have an entrepreneurial spirit, who are comfortable working in a dynamic startup environment and enjoy the challenge of wearing different hats.</p>\n<p>We believe marketing is both a science and an art. If you''re someone who can achieve that beautiful balance of being analytical and creative, strategic and hands-on, thinking big and detail-oriented at the same time, we''ll be eager to meet you!</p>\n<p>JOB RESPONSIBILITIES:</p>\n<p>*Plan and execute weekly/monthly/quarterly marketing strategies with clearly defined goals.<br />*Coach, mentor, train and supervise daily activities of the marketing team.<br />*Review and improve the company''s existing sales funnel (autoresponder emails, website copies, existing social media channel)<br />*Develop social media and sharing strategies that drive new users and membership from social media platforms (company Blog, Youtube, Facebook, Linkedin, Twitter)<br />*Supervise the publication of content through various social media channels<br />*Design, execute and track ads campaigns.<br />*Identify partnerships and opportunities that will help grow our audience<br />*Prepare Google analytics and sales report and adjust strategies based on the report<br />*Plan and execute in-house PR plans (HARO, contact media) and/or work with external PR firms to manage the execution of PR plans.<br />*Plan and execute new revenue streams for the company<br />*Advise Yangyang, the company president, on various issues including budgeting, hiring, PR, company direction and strategy etc.</p>\n<p>REQUIREMENTS</p>\n<p>*Native English speaker<br />*Knowledge of the Chinese language is a big plus<br />*3-5 years previous online marketing experience<br />*Organized and detail-oriented<br />*Persuasive writing skills (understanding of marketing psychology)<br />*Results-driven, proven track record of meeting targets<br />*Non-conventional, creative and can think outside the box<br />*Respectful and outstanding leadership skills that motivate staff</p>\n<p>SKILLS</p>\n<p>*Familiar with analytics tools, A/B testing, SEO, online marketing automation platforms<br />*Familiar with email systems (mailchimp, constantcontact, etc)<br />*Familiar with CRM systems to track and analyze data.<br />*Hands-on knowledge of affiliate marketing<br />*Experience with basic design software (photoshop, inDesign, balsamiq mockup software), HTML/CSS and web design is a plus.<br />*Experience with editing videos and audio is a plus<br />*Experience with the language-education industry or any industry that focuses on delivering results to customers (e.g. fitness industry) is a plus</p>\n<p>We are growing fast and we are good to our people. If you''re interested, please apply for the position by filling out the following form AND sending an email with your name, cover letter and resume. Be creative and no cookie-cutter letters please! We''ll contact you shortly. Thank you and have a wonderful day!</p>\n<p>https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/YOYO_Marketing_Manager</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Yoyo-Chinese-Inc/jobs/Online-Marketing-Manager-c5749bd6a85a90b2', '', 980, 173, 2),
(704, 1411595120, '物业协调CFT', 'Panda Restaurant Group', 'Resturant', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '洛杉矶', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1617.row1" class="contentlinepanel" title=""><span id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1660.row1" class="text" title="">Panda Restaurant Group</span><span class="blockpanel"><span>&nbsp;</span></span>\n<p>At Panda, we all share a common mission: "Deliver exceptional Asian dining experiences by building an organization where people are inspired to better their lives." We invest in our people because great people run great operations that will exceed our guests'' expectations. Talk to any of our associates and you will experience a culture dedicated to its mission and our five fundamental values- Proactive, Respect/Win-Win, Growth, Great Operations, and Giving.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Panda Restaurant Group includes the original Panda Inn fine dining restaurants, Panda Express, our Gourmet Chinese food concept served in a fast casual environment, and Hibachi San, our Japanese grill concept. The family owned and operated company is still run by founders Andrew and Peggy Cherng.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Panda offers competitive benefits and rewarding opportunities, from entry-level positions to management. We have restaurant positions available nationwide and support center positions in Rosemead, CA. Come join the nation''s largest and fastest growing Asian restaurant company.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Description:</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Property Coordinator assists with repair and maintenance of plaza properties and performs lease administration work related to billing, accounts payable, and accounts receivable.&nbsp; This position coordinates with vendors and tenants on maintenance and repair and helps resolve property repair and maintenance issues.&nbsp;&nbsp; The Property Coordinator also reviews recurring charges in the property management system (Yardi) for all tenants to ensure charges are accurate and makes billing changes and corrections as needed.&nbsp; This position tracks, reviews, and codes property invoices (e.g., property tax, utility, repair and maintenance invoices) and ensures payment is processed on a timely basis.&nbsp; This position interacts with tenants to ensure repair and maintenance issues are resolved and amounts due to tenants related to the terms of the lease agreement are paid accurately and on a timely basis.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Create and maintain lease/tenant files into property management database software (Yardi Voyager)</li>\n<li>Prepare Rent Commencement Letters for new tenants</li>\n<li>Perform yearly CAM Reconciliation and handle any disputations</li>\n<li>Track, review and approve all monthly invoices (utility, vendor services invoices, etc.) and provide assistance in processing repair &amp; maintenance and other invoices to make sure payment is processed on time</li>\n<li>Assist in sending/mailing out Water Charge Back and other tenant receivables</li>\n<li>Assist in posting tenant receivables into Yardi tenant ledger</li>\n<li>Work closely with Accounting Team on all tenant related billing/payment issues</li>\n<li>Coordinate with vendors, contractors, tenants to resolve all repair &amp; maintenance issues</li>\n<li>Search for onsite property manager candidates for new properties</li>\n<li>Create and file vendor agreements</li>\n<li>Arrange turnover trip for respective regions</li>\n<li>New Property Set Up</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n<div class="staticcontentlinepanel">&nbsp;</div>\n<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1685.row1" class="contentlinepanel" title="">\n<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1701.row1" class="inlinepanel" title=""><span class="subtitle">Qualifications</span></div>\n<span class="blockpanel"><span>&nbsp;</span></span>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in a related field required</li>\n<li>Minimum one to two years of relevant experience required</li>\n<li>Successful completion of annual store training</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Panda Restaurant Group&rsquo;s culture is strongly guided by our Mission and Values, highlighted on the Panda websites. We recommend all interested candidates become familiar with our Mission and Values, as well as the principles of The Seven Habits of Highly Effective People, by Stephen Covey.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Panda Restaurant Group, Inc. is an Equal Opportunity Employer.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<span class="blockpanel"><span>&nbsp;</span></span><span class="blockpanel"><span>&nbsp;</span></span></div>\n<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1749.row1" class="contentlinepanel" title="">\n<h2 class="no-change-header-inline"><span id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1765.row1" class="subtitle" title="">Primary Location</span></h2>\n<span class="inline">&nbsp;</span><span id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1786.row1" class="subtitle" title="">|</span><span class="inline">&nbsp;</span><span id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1796.row1" class="text" title="">United States of America-CALIFORNIA-Rosemead</span></div>', 'https://pandarg.taleo.net/careersection/panda+corporate/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=14000843&src=JB-10061', '', 980, 117, 2),
