(721, 1412467571, '内审员', 'Sunrider International ', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '洛杉矶', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="snip">\n<p>Internal Auditor/Accounting/Finance</p>\n<p>Exciting opportunity for aggressive professional to travel worldwide, expose different cultures and advance to management position. The opening is located in our beautiful Headquarters in Torrance, CA.</p>\n<p>Company Information</p>\n<p>Sunrider International is an herbal and beauty product manufacturer and distributor with 30 years of history. We continue to grow, and have over 40 offices and 10 manufacturing facilities worldwide. We recently stepped into the hotel business and have purchased 3 hotels in Beijing and Taipei.</p>\n<p>As an auditor, you will travel to our affiliates all over the world (4 to 6 times per year), in addition to:<br />Conduct financial, operational and compliance audits of various operations and functions.<br />Be responsible for the execution of fieldwork; determine whether operating units are performing their accounting and control activities in accordance with policies, procedures and company objectives, and present recommendations to management for correcting deficiencies.</p>\n<p>We view our auditors as management trainees, and offer great opportunity for future growth.</p>\n<p>Qualifications<br />Bachelor degree in Finance/Accounting or related field<br />CPA, CIA, or CISA preferred<br />Audit experience preferred, but not required<br />Hotel audit or management experience preferred<br />Self-started with strong interpersonal, technical, and organizational skills<br />Good verbal and written communication skills.<br />4-6 times international travel per year.<br />Must be US citizen or green card holder.<br />Bilingual in Mandarin strongly preferred.<br />Hotel experience and/or Bi-lingua