(722, 1412467734, '办公室业务助理', 'Momoko International Inc.', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '洛杉矶', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Bilingual English and Chinese Office Operation Assistant<br />Momoko International Inc. &ndash; South El Monte, CA<br />Position Summary: This Office Operation Assistant will report directly to the office manager. This person will work on daily assignments to input and update all information on our eCommerce website as well as answer customer&rsquo;s inquiries. Excellent communication skills and a possitive attitude with customers is required.</p>\n<p>Primary Responsibilities:<br />1) Compose description, how to use, ingredients and pictures for new products. Both English and Chinese information shall be composed.<br />2) Update the quantity of products online once deliveries from our vendors arrive.<br />3) Answer customers&rsquo; inquries through phone, email and online chat.<br />4) Take care of walk-in customers.<br />5) Assist warehouse operation if needed.<br />6) Other duties, as assigned<br />7) fluent level of English and Chinese<br />8) knowledge of Japanese is a plus</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Momoko-International-Inc./jobs/Bilingual-English-Chinese-Office-Operation-Assistant-f441e10579796acc', '', 980, 163, 2),
(723, 1412467914, 'YouTube Video Inventory分析师', 'ICONMA', 'Technology', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '美利坚合众国', '加利福尼亚州', '旧金山', 'None', 'Full Time', '<h4 class="des-job">Description:</h4>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div id="navlistforjob">\n<p>Duration: 1 year</p>\n<p>Description: Video Inventory Analyst (Client Advertising Policy/Video Inventory Analytics) - MTV</p>\n<p>As a Client Video Inventory Classification Product Specialist you are responsible for ensuring the quality of Client&rsquo;s monetizable video inventory that is at the core of generating revenue from a broad range of new Client advertising products and content partner programs. Candidates are an independent, critical thinker with sound judgment who has a passion for Internet policy and a penchant for defining precise and scalable standards, especially in areas that are still evolving. Candidate will develop detailed knowledge of our constantly evolving technologies and product offerings, and ensure that feedback flows to the product team to fuel improvement and innovation. Candidate will assist with the implementation and enforcement of Client''s advertising and program policies through video classification. As a product expert in Client&rsquo;s Video Inventory Analytics, Candidate will work closely with Policy, Product Managers and Engineering Leads in Client Ads and also serve as the central point of contact for other departments and vendors. You will also be responsible for creating user-facing documentation and content to educate internal users and vendors about our product.</p>\n<p>Responsibilities:<br />Watch Client videos and become an expert in Client&rsquo;s Video Inventory classification systems.<br />Analyze data effectively to support the development of strategy and recommendations to video classification initiatives.<br />Actively drive tactical improvements for classification operations, including enhancements to tools and processes that increase quality and efficiency.<br />Work with cross functional stakeholders to ensure readiness for launch.<br />Directly interact with users and user feedback to understand their needs and champion these needs across internal stakeholders.</p>\n<p>Requirements:<br />BA/BS degree preferred with strong academic record.<br />2 years of experience preferred in support operations and/or technology product management.<br />Self-starter with ability to work independently and on multiple initiatives at the same time; excellent project manager.<br />Proficiency in the Chinese Language (Mandarin). Candidates who speak both Mandarin and Cantonese are desirable, but Mandarin is a requirement. No other dialects will be considered.</p>\n<p>Preferred experience:<br />Ability to design and deliver scalable support offerings for different channels.<br />Technical experience in machine-learning methodology a plus (e.g., solid understanding of product development flow, ability to translate technical concepts into non-technical terms).<br />Knowledge of Client&nbsp; content and publisher policies a plus.<br />Excellent communication skills (written and verbal).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h4 class="des-job">About Company:</h4>\n<p>ICONMA is a nationwide consulting firm with corporate headquarters in Troy, MI, providing Professional Staffing and Project Based Services and Solutions for Fortune 1000 clients in a broad range of industries. Core Industries served include: Biotech/Pharmaceutical, Cable, Clinical, Consumer Services, Energy, Engineering, Financial Services, Food &amp; Beverage, Government/Defense, Healthcare, Insurance, Logistics, Manufacturing, Media, Mortgage, Oil &amp; Gas, Pharmaceutical, Retail, Scientific, Services, Technology, Telecommunications, Transportation, and Utilities.</p>\n<p>ICONMA is a certified Woman-Owned &ldquo;Woman-Owned Business Enterprise&rdquo;, certified by Women&rsquo;s Business Enterprise National Council (WBENC) and National Women Business Owners Corporation (NWBOC).</p>\n<p>The company was founded on the principle that success is derived from delivering high quality service and resources in the most responsive, flexible, and innovative way. ICONMA invests in people and resources with a single goal: To provide our customers with the highest quality service in the most responsive manner.</p>\n<p>We measure success by the results of our customers. As a business partner, we know that world-class service and cost effective solutions are the primary keys to success. ICONMA uses technical expertise and business knowledge to help customers achieve these objectives.</p>', 'http://www.iconma.com/jobs_by_category_description.php?jid=1147&search=none', '', 980, 119, 2),
