(736, 1413161393, '医生助理', 'JIMMY WONG MD PLLC ', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', '纽约', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Position: Nurse Practitioner (NP) or Physician''s Assistant (PA) position.<br />Must have: 1) NP or PA degree.<br />2) Must speak Chinese (Cantonese and Mandarin) and English, with relative fluency.</p>\n<p>The purpose of this posting is for you to also learn a bit about me and gauge your interest in working with me in my practice, as well as in applying for the position. I am looking for a working colleague, not simply just someone that works for me.<br />I was born in New York City. My medical education was completed at the University of Buffalo School of Medicine, and my postgraduate residency was completed at Saint Vincent&rsquo;s Catholic Medical Center in Manhattan, where I completed my residency in Primary Care/Internal Medicine.<br />I am currently a sole practitioner in the lower Manhattan, Chinatown area of New York City. Our population varies from 13-100years old, and is an Internal Medicine practice. The main language that is spoken in the office is Cantonese (approximately 65%), Mandarin (34.9%), and English (0.1%). If you do not speak these dialects well, this working relationship will not succeed. Our office is not large by any means, but recently has undergone extensive renovations and does have 3.5 exam rooms at this time and a small lunch room/changing room for the staff. The practice has recently transitioned to a full EMR based medical record system (we are using the cloud based program MDLand) and we are mainly an appointment based office at this time. However, if you are familiar with the Chinese population, the idea of appointments is occasionally difficult to reinforce.<br />The latter is the main reason for my desire to hire an additional practitioner. If you are working in a practice currently that has appointments but also has a walk-in option for &ldquo;urgent&rdquo; care, you can imagine that working as a solo practitioner with a full schedule and then permitting a walk-in patient to be seen will cause a bit of a disruption in the schedule. In hiring someone to assist me, I hope to ease that burden and to continue to provide the kind of care that I enjoy providing. I do not wish to provide rapid-turnover type care that so often plagues practices in the busy urban setting. My primary allegiance and goal is to provide proper care for our patient population, and to expand to a newer, younger, and more educated population.</p>\n<p>Please send me your resume should you meet the qualifications above and are interested in the position. Thank you.</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/viewjob?cmp=JIMMY-WONG-MD-PLLC&t=Chinese+Speaking+Nurse+Practitioner+Position&jk=1b5518bd58c0684d&sjdu=QwrRXKrqZ3CNX5W-O9jEvUDm1SFVRa0Dymw2VlqHCcgtGLwyOhjJBQcaKlQHLzXTKRt2ar7YLDW5FkTwupNyyZuNVfywtOgsIons-2IS4e516maAY8DI5QYT3hteRLXYhV8Ma68OO0greBiXycXiGw', '', 980, 144, 2),
