(777, 1414678061, '咖啡店招聘全职|兼职服务员|周末工|半工计时薪', '木兰', 'Resturant', '美国纽约州纽约', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美国', '纽约', '纽约', 'None', 'Part Time', '<p>主要经营；咖啡\\奶茶、鲜榨果汁 各种饮料；<br />招聘职位：无需经验； 男女不限 年龄：18-45岁 <br />需 能流利沟通 有耐心 吃苦耐劳 为人真诚。<br />很适合学生假期兼职\\时间灵活自由。<br />周末兼职工作上班时间:08;30-19;30 计日新。<br />兼职半工\\上班时间12点-17点 晚17点- 22点\\计时新。<br />为防止,电话骚扰有意者联系我，联系请致信Eail咨询\\欢迎来信应聘。<br />Eail； quickscreen1@gmail.com白女士</p>', '', 'quickscreen1@gmail.com', 1345, 3, 2),
(778, 1414717432, '项目经理', 'Ivy Bridge Group', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '洛杉矶', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="snip">\n<p>Job Description: We are currently seeking an experienced and polished bilingual and bi-cultural (simplified Chinese and English) project manager, who will provide administrative support to executive and ensure the successful operation of an education project.</p>\n<p>Salary: DOE</p>\n<p>Project Manager who will be responsible for planning and reporting on all phases of the project life cycle, including: compliance with work orders and contracts, chain of custody and materials tracking, financial and time-based projections and forecasts, billing and volume metrics, and reporting on project-level information. The Project Manager is the primary communications channel to the client and works closely with operations and account management.</p>\n<p>Specific duties include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Oversee projects from initial set-up to delivery of the finished product, with a focus on client relations and communication.</li>\n<li>Work closely with executive to set up projects, job turnaround estimates, and job specifications.</li>\n<li>Continuously monitor multiple tasks and jobs within each department to ensure deadlines are met.</li>\n<li>Work closely with staff to ensure proper allocation of resources based on deadlines and priorities.</li>\n<li>serves as a liaison between Account Management, staff, and the client during the life of a project.</li>\n<li>Communicates frequently with executive to resolve issues and provide status updates according to the client''s needs. Manage executive&rsquo;s expectations throughout the life of a project.</li>\n<li>Ensure jobs are completed according to executive, industry standards, and that job specifications and deadlines are adhered to.</li>\n<li>Maintain accurate and current records of all aspects of a project relating to job tracking, specifications, and chain of custody related documents.</li>\n<li>Interact with clients to develop strong client relations.</li>\n<li>Provides final quality control check on client deliverables.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Background and Experience:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree required; Master&rsquo;s degree preferred but not necessary.</li>\n<li>Native &ndash;level grasp of English and Mandarin Chinese, in regards to speaking, reading, professional writing and translating.</li>\n<li>Working exposure to the education industry highly preferred but not necessary</li>\n<li>Knowledge and sensitivity to both western and Chinese culture nuance</li>\n<li>Prior administrative and project &ndash;management experience highly preferred.</li>\n<li>Exceptional organizational skills and attention to detail</li>\n<li>High proficiency in Microsoft word and excel, along with all applicable PC and Mac software.</li>\n<li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills.</li>\n<li>Candidates must have legal authorization to work in the US</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For immediate consideration, please send your resume and salary requirements to this posting.</p>\n<p>About Ivy Bridge Group, please visit www.ivybridgegroup.com.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Ivy-Bridge-Group/jobs/Project-Manager-Bilingual-2639105ef49b5b3b', '', 980, 107, 2),
(779, 1414718322, 'Customer Service -Mobile', '游戏发行商Netherfire', 'Entertainment', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '旧金山', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div align="left">Job Summary</div>\n<div align="left">The customer service agent will manage both the community as well as any incoming tickets sent by the player base. This is a position where you will be working in a team environment. You are responsible for working with the project manager and the producer in the development of the game, as well as post-launch events and updates. You&rsquo;ll also be working with the graphic designer and core artist on the creation of any art assets required for post-launch community events and updates. You&rsquo;ll also work with PR on post-launch PR materials, such as but not limited to social media, forum posts, blogs, written articles, and videos. Finally, you will be working with the project assistant on QA related tasks as well as be involved in any brainstorming sessions related to design, monetization, and live-ops.</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div align="left">Responsibilities</div>\n<p>&bull;Establish a presence in the community by keeping the players in the loop with the latest news and updates.<br />&bull;Inquire, gather, and organize player comments and suggestions and report them back to the publishing team.<br />&bull;Handle player tickets through Zendesk and solve them according to an established policy.<br />&bull;Monitor the wiki, forum, and all social media outlets with the PR.<br />&bull;Work with PR on post-launch PR materials, such as but not limited to social media, forum posts, blogs, written articles, and videos.<br />&bull;Work with the in-house artists and graphic designers in creating art assets for community purposes.<br />&bull;Team up with the marketing team to prepare and schedule marketing materials and be part of the UA and monetization process.<br />&bull;Be part of the live-ops / post-launch team in designing post-launch events to drive new game updates and breathe life into the games as they continue to grow and improve.<br />&bull;Attend scrums and be ready to give feedback. Your opinions matter!<br />&bull;Be part of discussions about metrics/product decision-making.<br />&bull;Take part in setting up product roadmaps and strategic planning.<br />&bull;Understand and participate in making a game go live on iOS and Android.<br /><br /></p>\n<div align="left">Qualifications</div>\n<p>&bull;Clear communication in proficient English, both written and verbal a must.<br />&bull;Demonstrate high level of organization.<br />&bull;Ability to multitask.<br />&bull;Be prepare to meet, scrum, and work during night time when the Chinese team is online.<br />&bull;Be willing to crunch before deadlines.<br />&bull;Be ready to QA art portion of the game as the development process progresses.<br /><br /></p>\n<div align="left">Plusses</div>\n<p>&bull;Bilingual in English and Chinese.<br />&bull;Previous experience working with video games.<br />&bull;Prior leadership.<br />&bull;Passion for games.<br />&bull;Familiar with internet culture.<br />&bull;Basic proficiency in Zendesk.<br />&bull;Basic proficiency in web analytics.<br />&bull;Basic proficiency with Adobe CS tools.</p>', '', 'hr@netherfire.com', 980, 115, 2),
(780, 1414718410, '外场服务人员', '桃园村 中餐馆', 'Service', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '旧金山', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>桃园村 中餐馆诚聘兼职外场服务人员需中英文流利，有无经验皆可。在Newark double tree hotel附近，详情请联系：408-964-0177</p>', '', '', 980, 93, 2),
(783, 1414987296, '中文翻译', 'American Apparel', 'Language', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '洛杉矶', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>American Apparel is a fashion manufacturer and retailer that is proud to be made in the USA! Employing over 12,000 people worldwide, we offer benefits such as comprehensive health care, an on-site clinic, and complimentary massages.<br /><br />We are looking for a Mandarin Translator to join our expanding Web Department. Composed of enthusiastic, diverse individuals, the Web Department currently boasts several online stores as well as third party integrations. Enjoy a fast-paced, collaborative experience among project managers, designers, store managers and more! We value your innovative ideas and look forward to seeing them on the web!<br /><br /><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Translate website content, marketing copy and product descriptions to Mandarin.</li>\n<li>Must have native speaking, reading and writing ability in Mandarin</li>\n<li>Data entry and administration of the Mandarin Online Store Content</li>\n<li>Solid understanding of fashion and retail copy requirements</li>\n<li>A very high proficiency in written simplified Chinese, will need to be able to translate technical terms and culturally-specific terms for a mainland Chinese audience.</li>\n<li>Ensure accuracy of website content and proactively initiate improvements</li>\n<li>Coordinate and collaborate with a multi-disciplined team of experts<br /><br /><br /><strong>Requirements</strong></li>\n<li>Must be native speaker in Mandarin .</li>\n<li>E-commerce / digital / marketing experience is a plus</li>\n<li>Minimum 2-4 years experience in a similar position</li>\n<li>Industry background in retail or fashion a plus&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Must be extremely thorough and detail oriented</li>\n<li>Creative and engaging writing style&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Being highly motivated and possessing a strong work ethic are essential&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Strong English communication skills</li>\n<li>Willing to work outside a 9-5 schedule, work nights and weekends if necessary<br /><br /><strong>Important</strong><br />This is a temporary position for three weeks.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://www.americanapparel.net/careers/apply/?opportunity_id=2477&utm_source=Indeed&utm_medium=organic&utm_campaign=Indeed', '', 980, 156, 2),
(784, 1414987388, '中文教师', 'Shuang Wen Academy Network', 'Language', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美国', '纽约', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Duties and Responsibility:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Develop and design Chinese language and culture curriculum, lesson plan, and instructional materials.</li>\n<li>Teach Chinese language and culture to students in a classroom.</li>\n<li>Employ a variety of instructional strategies that are based on the needs of students to motivate them in learning Chinese language and culture and to help them meet the learning goals at each grade level.</li>\n<li>Establish and maintain standards of student behavior needed to achieve a functional learning atmosphere in the classroom.</li>\n<li>Evaluate students&rsquo; academic and social growth, keep appropriate records, and prepare student report cards.</li>\n<li>Communicate with parents through conferences and other means to discuss students&rsquo; progress and cooperate with parents to resolve students&rsquo; behavioral and learning problems.</li>\n<li>Create an effective environment for learning through functional and attractive displays and bulletin boards.</li>\n<li>Maintain professional competence through in-service professional growth activities.</li>\n<li>Supervise students in out-of-classroom activities during the afterschool time.</li>\n<li>Participates cooperatively with the Educational Director administrator for performance evaluation.</li>\n<li>Serve as mentors and role models to the students.</li>\n<li>Direct and supervise the teaching assistant.</li>\n<li>Work with Chinese tutors to prepare and implement remedial sessions for the students who require extra assistance.</li>\n<li>Enforce program administration policies.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Qualifications:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Must pass full background check includes fingerprinting.</li>\n<li>Must be fluent in speaking and writing Chinese.</li>\n<li>Have college or equivalent education.<