(809, 1415753922, '中英双语业务发展主管', 'Sequoia Wealth Planning', 'Management', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美国', '纽约', '纽约', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="snip">\n<p><strong>Job Description:&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p>Due to the rapid growth of our cross border business between China and the United States, Sequoia Wealth Planning Inc is looking for a highly-motivated Business Development Manager, who is responsible for managing existing accounts and driving new business development efforts to achieve sales and profit goals for our line of business. The Business Development Manager will prospect new clients, meet with new and existing clients, identify needs of the current market and promote our existing products and services.</p>\n<p><strong>Duties and responsibilities:&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Identify and utilize a variety of sources to find business opportunities and generate leads.</li>\n<li>Provide market intelligence to management and contact business representatives of potential clients to identify their needs.</li>\n<li>Participate in and contribute to the finance team''s analysis of investment strategy and positioning for our clients, including manager oversight and selection.</li>\n<li>Building and maintaining long term relationships with clients and finance firm representatives.</li>\n<li>Cold-calling key decision makers to set appointments for your client''s sales team</li>\n<li>Generate opportunities for new long term client relationships, including new business presentations, managing RFPs and other inquiries.</li>\n<li>Perform additional assignments per Director''s and Managements'' direction.</li>\n<li>Regional travel, as necessary.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Skills, experience and qualifications:&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fully bilingual in Chinese and English. Cantonese-speaking is preferred.</li>\n<li>Bachelor''s degree in Business Management or other related finance degree is strongly preferred.</li>\n<li>Minimum of 4-5 years of finance field experience, with client service and business development experience.</li>\n<li>Solid written and verbal Chinese and English communication skills.</li>\n<li>Must be able to complete duties without supervision.</li>\n<li>Must be detailed-oriented and organized. Able to take initiative and able to prioritize workload.</li>\n<li>Demonstrated ability to interact and communicate effectively and professionally with all levels of company and client management is essential.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Compensation:&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p>Salary plus commission</p>\n<p>Please send your resume to us if you are interested in applying for this position. Thank you</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Sequoia-Wealth-Planning/jobs/Bilingual-Chinese-English-Business-Development-Executive-783f751d50ab6a31', '', 980, 133, 2),
(810, 1415829501, '市场推广顾问  Marketing Promoter   ', '美国厚仁教育', 'Marketing', '美国加利福尼亚州洛杉矶', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', '加利福尼亚州', '洛杉矶', 'None', 'Part Time', '<p><strong>职位</strong><strong>: </strong><strong>市场推广顾问</strong><strong>&nbsp; Marketing Promoter </strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>公司介绍：</strong></p>\n<p>美国厚仁教育有限公司成立于2010年5月，是由中美从事教育的专业人士共同创建、通过全球最具权威的美国国际招生协会AIRC(American International Recruitment Council)认证的跨国性专业教育机构，集留学申请、转学服务、紧急服务、学术辅导、浸入式课堂、落地服务、中美文化交流等业务于一体。厚仁教育总部设立于美国第二大教育资源集群地宾夕法尼亚州匹兹堡市，在中国经济文化教育中心北京设有分部，与西雅图、洛杉矶、波士顿、圣地亚哥、旧金山、华盛顿、圣塔芭芭拉等分区办事处构建最强教育网。厚仁教育旨在获取得天独厚的院校资源以及第一手教育信息；加强扩展院校合作；为提供优质的留学服务夯实基础。</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>这份工作将会带给你什么？</strong></p>\n<p>熟悉留学机构与美国大学的相关业务模式和合作流程；</p>\n<p>自身能力的迅速提升，锻炼反应能力、口才、勇气等可贵品质；</p>\n<p>推广自我，成为受欢迎的人；</p>\n<p>建立起和谐的人际关系网，积累无形的巨大财富；</p>\n<p>个人简历上丰富有力的一段经历；</p>\n<p>表现突出者，厚仁将提供推荐信，全力支持你的梦想！</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>岗位职责</strong><strong>:</strong></p>\n<p>1. 完成美国厚仁宣传活动和推广；</p>\n<p>2. 参与校园宣传，发放传单，张贴传单与宣传品；</p>\n<p>3. 在本校及周边学校各类宣传推广渠道建立联系并进行推广；</p>\n<p>4. 与学校的学生会、各类协会、组织建立联系，筹备校园宣讲会；</p>\n<p>5. 以电话的形式参加公<a name="_GoBack"></a>司组织的每周的例会；</p>\n<p>6. 主动向负责人汇报工作。</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>任职资格</strong><strong>:</strong></p>\n<p>1. 快速、有效找到生源：对有转学以及升学需求的学生有很强的敏感度；</p>\n<p>2. 表达能力强，具有较强的沟通能力及交际技巧，具有亲和力；</p>\n<p>3. 品行端正，工作积极主动，执行力和行动力强；</p>\n<p>4. 有相关工作经验在校学生且交际面宽、人脉广者优先。</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>欢迎选择这份极具挑战的工作，一个年轻充满活力的团队期待你的加入！</strong></p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p><strong>工作地点：不限，加州地区优先</strong></p>\n<p><strong>工作时间：灵活</strong></p>\n<p><strong>发简历至：</strong><a href="mailto:jobs@wholeren.com"><strong>jobs@wholeren.com</strong></a></p>\n<p><strong>联系电话：</strong><strong>213-785-2860</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>一手最新最全留学、转学资讯，请关注&ldquo;<strong>美国转学</strong>&rdquo;微信公众平台</p>', 'http://www.wholeren.com/', 'jobs@wholeren.com', 1368, 123, 2),
