(830, 1416597728, '研究助手', 'Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory', 'Management', 'Berkeley, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Berkeley', 37.871593, -122.272743, '美利坚合众国', 'California', 'Berkeley', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>POSITION DESCRIPTION: &nbsp;Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory has an opening for Research Associate- East Asia/China Environmental and Energy Economist position in Berkeley, CA. Conduct research and economic analysis related to environmental protection and development, implementation, and assessment of energy efficiency policies and programs in China. Assess the costs and benefits of various activities, policies or regulations that affect the environment. Provide technical assistance to Chinese partners through benchmarking with international best practices, training, and capacity building. Collect and analyze data to compare the environmental implication. Collect and analyze data for research on the use of energy-efficient technologies in China and information on energy-efficiency programs in China and around the world in written reports, to identify common and key elements of establishing and implementing these programs. &nbsp;Collect data from a variety of sources, making spreadsheets for data calculations, data comparison, and evaluating data to ensure they are properly sourced, categorized and updated. &nbsp;Under direction of scientific staff, understand and interpret data for application to research efforts and perform analysis of data as assigned. &nbsp;Publish results for in peer-reviewed publications. &nbsp;Utilizes graduate-level research and analysis skills.<br />REQUIREMENTS: &nbsp;Employer will accept Master&rsquo;s degree in Economics, Environmental Economics or East Asian Studies with concentration in energy/environmental and/or economic analysis/public policy. &nbsp;Education or experience must include:&nbsp;<br />1. Compile and analyze research data in Chinese Mandarin and English accurately; create databases and spreadsheets, charts, viewgraphs and other presentation materials;2. Interdisciplinary research and analysis skills including understanding of sociology, political science, economics, mathematics, and history;3. Evaluation and interpretation of Chinese government documents using Chinese Mandarin skills;4. Write, edit, translate and proofread technical and governmental documents in Chinese and English; and5. MS Excel, Access, Powerpoint, and MS Word.<br />Experience may be gained concurrently. &nbsp;Any suitable combination of education, training, or experience is acceptable.<br />Incumbents in this position are represented by a union for collective bargaining purposes.&nbsp;Equal Employment Opportunity: Berkeley Lab is an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, disability, age or protected veteran status.</p>', 'https://lbl.taleo.net/careersection/2/jobdetail.ftl?job=78061&src=JB-10181', '', 980, 135, 2),
(831, 1416597870, '博客作家（兼职）', 'Viki', 'Management', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '美利坚合众国', 'California', 'San Francisco', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Viki, a Rakuten Company (Japan Stock Exchange: 4755), is a global TV site with more than 32 million viewers a month watching the world&rsquo;s primetime TV and movies, subtitled in 200 languages by a community of fans. With billions of videos viewed and more than 600 million words translated, Viki brings global entertainment to fans everywhere.<br /><br />Working with the Community Management team, Bloggers will create entertaining and engaging content to engage fans and potential fans by writing creative posts for the Viki Blog, helping to turn the Viki blog into a destination for what&rsquo;s relevant in Asian and global TV entertainment news.<br /><br />This position is a part-time remote contractor position.<br /><br />Qualifications<br /><br />Excellent written skills!<br />A fun, witty writing style that&rsquo;s engaging in a short-form style<br />Love of global entertainment, especially K-drama, Taiwanese Drama, J-drama, Chinese Drama and other pop entertainment from Asia<br />***PLEASE NOTE: Please include 2 writing samples, preferably links to your blog, in your Cover Letter.<br /><br />This is a unique and excellent opportunity to join a very small team and make a difference as we 100x growth. We&rsquo;re small but diverse, with more than 25 nationalities and 40 languages represented among our 70+ employees. Come break down barriers that stand between great entertainment and fans everywhere.<br /><br /><br /><br />Any unsolicited resumes/candidate profiles submitted through our website or to personal email accounts of employees of Viki are considered property of Viki and are not subject to payment of agency fees.</p>', 'http://jobs.omidyar.com/jobdetail.php?jobid=302136', '', 980, 166, 2),
(832, 1416597972, 'Accountant / Administrator ', '国金控股GOLDEN ROYAL ENERGY INC', 'Finance', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '美利坚合众国', 'California', 'San Francisco', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="snip">\n<p>The Company</p>\n<p>Golden Kingdom Holdings (国金控股) is an industry group with business covering international trade, culture and entertainment,mining development and financial investment. As of now we have formed our finance and administration centers at Singapore, mining development and product sales centers in China and resource purchase centers in other overseas countries. We have set up offices in Singapore, Mainland China, Malaysia, India and<br />Macau.<br />Golden Royal Energy, Inc. is a wholly owned subsidiary of Golden Kingdom Holdings Group. The company mainly engaged in international trade of coal, iron ore, other minerals, and finished metal products, it is also expanding its business on the recovery and utilization of renewable resources, mining investment in the United States, Canada, Mexico and other neighboring countries. In addition, Golden Royal Energy is optimistic about America''s media culture and financial markets, so the company will make efforts on integrate of its media and culture business in Asia and the United States.</p>\n<p>Position:<br />Secretary</p>\n<p>Number of Opening: few</p>\n<p>Job Requirements:</p>\n<p>- Excellent language skills between English and Mandarin Chinese is a MUST !!!!</p>\n<p>- Bachelor degree or above with knowledge in accounting and economics (Recent graduates or candidates who have certain internship / working experience are highly preferred.)</p>\n<p>- Citizen or permanent resident in the United States is a MUST!!!! (We DON''T Offer sponsorship)</p>\n<p>- Candidates should live in San Francisco / Bay Area !!!!</p>\n<p>Job Type: Full-time</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'http://www.indeed.com/viewjob?cmp=GOLDEN-ROYAL-ENERGY-INC&t=Accountant&jk=04da1480a63ad7b2&sjdu=QwrRXKrqZ3CNX5W-O9jEvawE-dgWLvZTqeLQb4saX4iTzc7mRxhAO4m_Nw179l3-nuIhKJ35emVMJD1nRcCh3_a0jF3Qe0GcQGFH4BKding&pub=pub-indeed', '', 980, 162, 2),
(833, 1416598080, '中英文翻译员', 'Trustforte Language Services', 'Language', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', 'New York', 'New York', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Trustforte Language Services is looking for a fun, dedicated, hard-working individual to join our team as a Translator.</p>\n<p>The job consists of translating the following into English:<br />Birth certificates, marriage certificates, death certificates, diplomas, transcripts, pay statements and contracts, and other types of documents (into a native language is a plus)</p>\n<p>The individual must be able to work as a team, take initiative and be a quick learner.</p>\n<p>The candidate MUST:<br />- Read/write/understand at least two languages (not including English)<br />- Have translation experience<br />- be a Language or Linguistics or Translation Major or minor<br />- be interested in starting or continuing a career as a translator<br />- have proficiency in MS Word<br />- Must have Citizenship/Residency/Work Authorization Card</p>\n<p>The job requires to stay late and work some weekends during our busy periods.</p>\n<p>We are looking for candidates who are fluent in Chinese/English (Japanese or Korean is a plus)</p>\n<p>This is an entry-level position.</p>\n<p>This is an in-house, full-time position in our office in Manhattan, NY</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Trustforte-Language-Services/jobs/Chinese-Translator-5e8ea47ec8366c87', '', 980, 125, 2),
(834, 1416598174, '销售助理', 'HiFu Service Inc', 'Marketing', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', 'New York', 'New York', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="snip">\n<p>About HiFu, the company</p>\n<p>Our communication always starts with &ldquo;hi&rdquo;, no matter the culture or country. So does our business. Our mission is to fundamentally change the way that people communicate, especially when they are in another country with a completely different culture and language. Communication can exist and evolve in numerous ways &ndash; for example, Chinese travelers may decide to explore Tiffany in 5th Avenue, New York. They can learn about the merchandise in their native language, and then conduct the checkout process with the simple greeting of &ldquo;hi&rdquo; using our Mobile App to smoothly complete the transaction.<br />HiFu is the first technology company in the US that empowers cross-border mobile commerce for both consumers and merchants. We provide targeted mobile promotions and discounts for those traveling from overseas to shop in U.S. premium merchants. We are always a startup (with Offices in Silicon Valley, Manhattan and Beijing) and have signed over a dozen contracts with multiple leading business partners in US and China. HiFu was founded by a team of seasoned professionals with a wealth of experience in cross-border payment and commerce. We are excited and committed to make our partners and you successful.</p>\n<p>About us, the team</p>\n<p>We are an extremely passionate group of people with a shared conviction to bring Asian international travelers the best shopping experience by connecting them with the local US merchants &ndash; starting from luxury. We welcome like-minded talents of all diversities to join us and chill on this exciting journey.</p>\n<p>About the Job<br />You will be the area sales or business development representative responsible for the development of new strategic accounts and maintaining and building and growing relationships with key clients and merchants within the retail fashion industry in New York City. You will be responsible for maintaining and development of our merchant base in the area for our app services. Primary merchant base is in the Luxury Retail goods industry but also expands into private events, buying/selling, research, and logistics.</p>\n<p>You will be doing:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Research and develop new business opportunities with existing and potential new key merchant accounts while reporting to Business Development Director</li>\n<li>Build productive, professional relationships with decision makers and key personnel in assigned merchants</li>\n<li>Provide customer service and act as one of the primary points of contact for clients including resolving client issues and complaints</li>\n<li>Meet profitable sales volume goals and strategic objectives in assigned accounts.</li>\n<li>Assist with project management for the area including deployment and distribution of WiFi equipment</li>\n<li>Assess and validate client needs on an ongoing basis.</li>\n<li>Participate in Sales meetings planning and achieve company sales goals.</li>\n<li>Report on competitive product capabilities and developments. Research and communicate new product opportunities to be developed specific to the assigned accounts.</li>\n<li>Represent the company at various events and visit clients/merchants</li>\n<li>Maintain organizational communication with sales manager</li>\n<li>Professional attitude, appearance and conduct with a "go getter" attitude</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelors&rsquo; degree and or 2+ years related sales experience preferred</li>\n<li>Fluency in English and Mandarin and/or French preferred</li>\n<li>Previous retail industry, luxury background, sales experience is a plus.</li>\n<li>Ideal candidate is one who demonstrates they are a highly driven individual looking for a position with growth potential</li>\n<li></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/HiFu-Service-Inc/jobs/Sales-Associate-7e481350bab18146', '', 980, 124, 2);
