(869, 1417542083, 'Java Developer 工程师', 'Ames IT and Numeric Solutions', 'Technology', 'Ames, IA, United States', 'United States', 'Iowa', 'Ames', 42.034721, -93.620003, '美利坚合众国', 'Iowa', 'Ames', 'H1B', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>Application Developer</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>1+ yrs of experience with core Java/J2EE and/or c++ language;</li>\n<li>Very good understanding of Object Oriented Programming concepts;</li>\n<li>Familiar with MVC design framework;</li>\n<li>Hand on experiences with Spring and Struts framework;</li>\n<li>Good knowledge and hand on experiences with RDBMS like MS SQL Server or MySQL;</li>\n<li>Deep understanding and experiences with numeric methods and numeric simulations;</li>\n<li>Highly motivated individual who can work best in a team;</li>\n<li>Excellent in communication, must be goal oriented and very organized;</li>\n<li>MSc or PhD degree in Science/Engineering majors.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p>&uuml;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work on day-to-day project planning, estimation and resources planning with the project manager</p>\n<p>&uuml;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participate in application architecture design and implementation</p>\n<p>&uuml;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Supervise junior developers on code implementation and review</p>\n<p>&uuml;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Designs and develops user interfaces to internet/intranet applications by setting expectations and features priorities throughout development life cycle; determining design methodologies and tool sets; completing programming using languages and software products; designing and conducting tests.</p>\n<p>&uuml;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Recommends system solutions by comparing advantages and disadvantages of custom development and purchase alternatives.</p>\n<p>&uuml;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Integrates applications by designing database architecture and server scripting; studying and establishing connectivity with network systems, search engines, and information servers.</p>\n<p>&uuml;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Contributing to team meetings; troubleshooting development and production problems across multiple environments and operating platforms.&nbsp;</p>', 'http://ames-it-solutions.com/index.html', 'marcus.m@ames-it-solutions.com', 1441, 128, 2),
(870, 1417563341, '中文成人课程教师', 'China Institute in America', 'Language', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', 'New York', 'New York', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="snip"><span id="job_summary" class="summary">China Institute in America , a non-profit, non-partisan, educational, and bi-cultural organization based in NYC, is seeking experienced Mandarin teachers within the tri-state region for its Adult Language Program. Positions currently available include teachers for our group classes, and tutors for our private and corporate tutoring programs.&nbsp;<br /><br />Successful candidates should be native speakers of Chinese who speak standard Mandarin with clear diction and who have a good command of spoken English. They should be comfortable with dealing with students from diverse backgrounds within the business world and private sector; be presentable in appearance and disposition; punctual; enthusiastic in their instruction and, for private tutoring, must be able to choose materials suited for each students&rsquo; needs, level, and abilities. Minimum educational requirement: B.A. degree.&nbsp;<br /><br />Group classes are held onsite at China Institute. All classes use pinyin and simplified characters. Most tutoring assignments are offsite and held at our students&rsquo; office or home with some assignments taking place onsite at China Institute. Competitive hourly wage available. Applicants must have permission to work.&nbsp;<br /><br />Please send cover letter and CV, including resident status, to:&nbsp;<br /><br />Wanling Zhang&nbsp;<br />Program Manager, Adult Language &amp; Studio Programs&nbsp;<br /><br />China Institute&nbsp;<br />125 East 65th Street&nbsp;<br />New York, NY 10065&nbsp;</span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', '', 'wzhang@chinainstitute.org', 980, 234, 2),
(871, 1417638598, 'Community Research Aide(社区研究助手)', 'Weill Cornell Medical College', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美利坚合众国', 'New York', 'New York', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="snip">\n<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p>\n<p>Reporting to Program Coordinator, this is a part time temporary position (17.5 hours a week) for community outreach programs at the Weill Cornell Medical College Clinical and Translational Science Center (CTSC). These programs include, but are not limited to: Community Interactive Videoconferencing (CIVIC), an interactive two-way telehealth program promoting health wellness and education in New York City''s communities, and the Heart to Heart Campaign (H2H), a series of free health screenings conducted in underserved communities. This position will focus on building and expanding the CTSC&rsquo;s community network and organizing events. This is a temporary position until May 31, 2015 with possibility of extension depending upon grant funding.</p>\n<p><strong>Position Activities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Maintain and expand the CTSC community network by contacting and following up with community organizations</li>\n<li>Assist in the conduct of Community Based Clinical Research. This includes maintaining and entering data into research databases, conducting follow up survey phone calls for research studies and assisting with regulatory/IRB compliance.</li>\n<li>Perform basic analysis of research data and prepare summaries as needed</li>\n<li>Work with the CTSC community network to schedule and promote CTSC community events and programs</li>\n<li>Assist with promotion of CTSC community programs. This includes updating social media/website and creation of flyers and other promotional material.</li>\n<li>Assist in conducting community events. This includes site testing, transportation and delivery of equipment, event setup and on site coordination including handing out survey and administering questionnaires.</li>\n<li>Assist in the creation, preparation and review of materials for presentations and events</li>\n<li>Aid in logistics, planning and organization of community programs and the CTSC in general</li>\n<li>Assist with maintenance and testing of videoconferencing equipment</li>\n<li>Other assigned duties</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p>\n<p><em>Minimum Requirements</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li>High School Diploma Required</li>\n<li>Must be comfortable with public speaking and engaging community members</li>\n<li>Basic knowledge of data analysis and/or statistics</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Highly Desired Requirements</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree preferred</li>\n<li>Driver&rsquo;s license and willingness to drive around New York City preferred</li>\n<li>Proficiency in a second language, Spanish or Chinese preferred</li>\n<li>Candidate with background, experience and/or interest in public health is preferred</li>\n<li>Familiarity with AV equipment and/or Adobe software a plus</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Working Conditions/Physical Demands</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Must be willing to assist in moving telehealth equipment (50 lbs.)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Part time position, 17.5 hours per week. Must be willing to work flexible hours, evening and weekends as needed.</p>\n<p><em>Founded in 1898, and affiliated with what is now New York-Presbyterian Hospital since 1927, Weill Cornell Medical College is among the top-ranked clinical and medical research centers in the country. In addition to offering degrees in medicine, Cornell also has Ph.D. programs in biomedical research and education at the Weill Graduate School of Medical Sciences, and with neighboring Rockefeller University and the Sloan-Kettering Institute, has established a joint MD-PhD. program for students to intensify their pursuit of Cornell''s triple mission of education, research, and patient care.</em></p>\n<p><em>Weill Cornell Medical College''s educational mission emphasizes the importance of combining a strong foundation in the medical sciences with extensive clinical training in patient care. By promoting a true social commitment, stimulating creativity, and fostering independent thought and study, Weill Cornell Medical College continues to cultivate the best of tomorrow''s leaders in the field of medicine.</em></p>\n<p>Weill Cornell Medical College is an employer and educator recognized for valuing AA/EOE/M/F/Protected Veterans, and Individuals with Disabilities.</p>\n<p>Salary: $19.15 /hour</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Weill-Cornell-Medical-College/jobs/Community-Research-Aide-bfcca036719665ce', '', 980, 177, 2),
(872, 1417638897, 'Part-time US Branch Assistant (Bilingual English/Chinese)', 'NUUO US Inc', 'Marketing', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美利坚合众国', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>This part-time position is to be worked daily, Monday through Friday, 25-40 hours per week. Priority consideration will be given to the candidate who has a flexible schedule and can increase his/her hours as needed. Ideal candidate should have at least 1 year administrative experience or equivalent Microsoft Office proficiency, possess a friendly, helpful attitude for interacting with internal/external customers, have a high level of accuracy, attention to detail, multitasking ability, time management, and organizational skills. Transition to full-time position is possible depending on performance.</p>\n<p>DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES include but are not limited to the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Processes AR and AP for the accounting department.</li>\n<li>Answers incoming telephone calls in a courteous and efficient manner, determines purpose of calls, takes notes and forwards calls to appropriate personnel or department.</li>\n<li>Supports processing customer loaner and returns.</li>\n<li>Supports processing purchasing orders.</li>\n<li>Schedules interviews.</li>\n<li>Coordinates training requests with customers/sales/technical departments.</li>\n<li>Works with sales/marketing/technical departments to prepare for tradeshows/exhibitions.</li>\n<li>Clerical duties. Maintaining confidential files and records--paper and electronic documents.</li>\n<li>Supports data entry and verification.</li>\n<li>Coordinates and supports office daily activities. Needs frequent interaction with team members, communicating clearly in a positive and professional attitude.</li>\n<li>Needs to coordinate with Headquarter for knowledge sharing and process improvement.</li>\n<li>Other special projects as needed.</li>\n</ul>