(904, 1418442001, 'Los Angeles Chinese tutoring job', '私人', 'Language', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 'None', 'Part Time', '<p class="semibold align-right spc-zero-n">posted on: 12/10/14</p>\n<div class="box-white">\n<h3>Job description</h3>\n<p class="spc-zero-n">&ldquo;I''m seeking a tutor for my 8th grade daughter in Chinese and Geometry.&rdquo;&nbsp;<em class="TestOffSegment">- Young from Los Angeles, CA</em></p>\n</div>\n<ul class="spc-zero-n">\n<li>Apply to become a tutor to help this student and other students in your community</li>\n<li>Work with a variety of students in your best subjects</li>\n<li>Spend more time teaching and less time administering</li>\n<li>Set your own hours while you help students learn the subjects you love to teach</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Qualifications</h3>\n<ul class="spc-zero-n">\n<li>A love of learning</li>\n<li>Excellent communication skills</li>\n<li>Expertise in a variety of disciplines</li>\n<li>Passion for helping others learn and succeed</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Pay</h3>\n<ul class="spc-zero-n">\n<li>Set your own rate (most tutors charge between $30-60/hour)</li>\n</ul>', 'https://www.wyzant.com/viewjob?id=1996845&utm_source=Indeed&utm_medium=cpc&utm_campaign=IndeedS&g=IndeedSpaid', '', 980, 183, 2),
(945, 1420266824, '人力资源代表', 'Forest Lawn Memorial-Park Association', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>If you are a driven and determined Human Resources professional, passionate about creating a culture of respect and support, we would be delighted to meet you!&nbsp;<br /><br />Forest Lawn Memorial Parks &amp; Mortuaries, a well-established and reputable organization is seeking a Bilingual, Chinese speaking Employee Relations Representative to administer, coordinate, and participate in a wide variety of Human Resources functions including employee relations, training and communications. The ideal candidate must possess an outstanding ability to develop and nurture positive relationships with the management team and employees and to influence business results through HR processes. Must be self-motivated, driven, results oriented, and able to take ownership of established policies and procedures, while creating and implementing creative solutions to increase efficiency and boost employee morale. This position will report to the Human Resources Manager.&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>Essential Functions:&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;</strong>Provide general information to employees and management regarding Forest Lawn policies, practices, and procedures.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Be an important role in the communication flow within our organization by facilitating meetings with various departments, collecting information regarding their processes and recording their suggestions and concerns in a report format.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Guide employees and management members through a variety of employee relations issues such as performance concerns, discipline, terminations, employee development, employee conflict, grievances, and violations of policies/procedures.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Ensures prompt response and resolution of employment-related complaints