(907, 1418500134, '市场销售', 'The Asian Magazine', 'Media', 'Dallas, TX, United States', 'United States', 'Texas', 'Dallas', 32.780262, -96.800980, '美国', 'Texas', 'Dallas', 'H1B', 'Full Time', '<p>随着杂志的出版，The Asian Magazine亞尚杂志秉承着高水准的选材和高质量的原创成为了北美华人媒体圈中一股冉冉上升的新兴力量。作为多媒体平台，我们渴望交流与成长，渴望展示与创造，愿让我们 的声音被更多的华人所知晓。我们的团队是由一群热爱生活、充满梦想的年轻人组成，高效率的工作氛围让我们打造出了新媒体的时尚形象。未来很广，而梦想照进 现实的执行正等待着我们一起能量爆发。这将是一件多么让人兴奋不已又成就感十足的事情， 期待新的伙伴们一同来加入我们充满活力热情四溢的团队！<br /><br /><br /><strong>1. 市场销售(全职/实习皆可)</strong><br />1）性格开朗，形象良好，思维敏捷，具备较强的学习能力和优秀的沟通能力（中英文）<br />2）做事条理性强，具有良好的组织能力，拥有出色的应变能力和承压能力<br />3）有敏锐的市场洞察力，有强烈的事业心、责任心和积极的工作态度，吃苦耐劳<br />4）有车，有美国驾照<br />5）有相关销售工作经验者优先<br />薪酬：3个月实习期提供提成；实习期结束后提供底薪+提成模式</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>申请流程：</strong><br />请将你的简历、cover letter和其他相关材料发至career@theasianmagazine.com。<br /><br /><strong>其他：</strong><br />1) 可以提供OPT、CPT支持<br />2) 工作表现优异者，公司可以提供H1-B支持<br /><br /><strong>公司所在地：</strong>Plano,TX(Dallas地区)</p>\n<p><strong>新浪微博：</strong>TheAsianMagazine</p>\n<p><strong>微信公众平台：</strong>TheAsianMagazine</p>\n<p><strong>官方网站：</strong>www.theasianmagazine.com</p>', '', 'career@theasianmagazine.com', 805, 0, 2),
(908, 1418525398, '项目经理', 'Ivy Bridge Group', 'Finance', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="snip">\n<p>Job Description: We are currently seeking an experienced and polished bilingual and bi-cultural (simplified Chinese and English) project manager, who will provide administrative support to executive and ensure the successful operation of an education project.</p>\n<p>Salary: DOE</p>\n<p>Project Manager who will be responsible for planning and reporting on all phases of the project life cycle, including: compliance with work orders and contracts, chain of custody and materials tracking, financial and time-based projections and forecasts, billing and volume metrics, and reporting on project-level information. The Project Manager is the primary communications channel to the client and works closely with operations and account management.</p>\n<p>Specific duties include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Oversee projects from initial set-up to delivery of the finished product, with a focus on client relations and communication.</li>\n<li>Work closely with executive to set up projects, job turnaround estimates, and job specifications.</li>\n<li>Continuously monitor multiple tasks and jobs within each department to ensure deadlines are met.</li>\n<li>Work closely with staff to ensure proper allocation of resources based on deadlines and priorities.</li>\n<li>serves as a liaison between Account Management, staff, and the client during the life of a project.</li>\n<li>Communicates frequently with executive to resolve issues and provide status updates according to the client''s needs. Manage executive&rsquo;s expectations throughout the life of a project.</li>\n<li>Ensure jobs are completed according to executive, industry standards, and that job specifications and deadlines are adhered to.</li>\n<li>Maintain accurate and current records of all aspects of a project relating to job tracking, specifications, and chain of custody related documents.</li>\n<li>Interact with clients to develop strong client relations.</li>\n<li>Provides final quality control check on client deliverables.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Background and Experience:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree required; Master&rsquo;s degree preferred but not necessary.</li>\n<li>Native &ndash;level grasp of English and Mandarin Chinese, in regards to speaking, reading, professional writing and translating.</li>\n<li>Working exposure to the education industry highly preferred but not necessary</li>\n<li>Knowledge and sensitivity to both western and Chinese culture nuance</li>\n<li>Prior administrative and project &ndash;management experience highly preferred.</li>\n<li>Exceptional organizational skills and attention to detail</li>\n<li>High proficiency in Microsoft word and excel, along with all applicable PC and Mac software.</li>\n<li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills.</li>\n<li>Candidates must have legal authorization to work in the US</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For immediate consideration, please send your resume and salary requirements to this posting.</p>\n<p>About Ivy Bridge Group, please visit www.ivybridgegroup.com.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Ivy-Bridge-Group/jobs/Project-Manager-Bilingual-2639105ef49b5b3b', '', 980, 170, 2),
(909, 1418525777, '代理销售', '保险经纪公司', 'Marketing', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>保险经纪公司现招一名sales agent，commission base only，提供三个月的training。公司代理多家保险公司，业务有个人，商业，健康和人寿保险。要求基本英文对话能力，合法保税身份。职位适合在校大学生或需要part time job人士。有意向者请直接发简历到ella@sjlins.com, 或626-387-6688</p>', '', 'ella@sjlins.com', 980, 161, 2),
(910, 1418570403, '孔子学院招聘中文老师（全职+兼职）', '孔子学院招聘中文老师（全职+兼职）', 'Service', '美国纽约州纽约', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美国', 'New York', 'New York', 'H1B', 'Part Time', '<p>孔子学院( 英文：Confucius Institute )，是中国国家对外汉语教学领导小组办公室在世界各地设立的推广汉语和传播中国文化与国学的教育和文化交流机构。最重要的一项工作就是给世界 各地的汉语学习者提供规范、权威的现代汉语教材；提供最正规、最主要的汉语教学渠道。 作为周边地区唯一教授汉语拼音和简化字的学校，她的建立得到了华人社区广泛深远的响应和热情的支持参与，学院如雨后春笋般成长壮大，目前有在校学生100多名。作为一个非盈利的组织 ，学校以教授中文，弘扬中华文化，现已成为周边地区中国文化及中文学习中心。现招聘汉语中文教师和助教数名加入我们的教师队伍, 补习的对象都是5周岁左右的小朋友，要求需要绝对 的耐心。 应聘条件:要求华人同胞，必须一口会标准普通话，最好与教育相关专业，对儿童有爱心和耐心，对传播中文和中国文化充满热情，待人真诚热情、责任心强。 有意者请发送简历到我们的邮箱：quickscreen1@gmail.com联系人：张老师</p>', '', '', 1489, 3, 2);
