;"><a href="mailto:Chelle.zhang@tiandaoedu.com">Chelle.zhang@tiandaoedu.com</a></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><br /><span style="color: #4169e1;"><span style="font-family: 宋体;">注明姓名，所在地区和申请的职位，谢谢！</span></span><br />\n<div align="left">\n<div align="left">\n<div align="left"><span style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="color: #ff8c00;">或加微信522518506</span>，注明&lsquo;拍摄招聘&rsquo;</span>\n<div align="left"><span style="font-family: 宋体;"><span style="color: #4169e1;">待遇丰厚，速速报名吧~！<img src="http://www.moonbbs.com/static/image/smiley/dmsmiley02/47.gif" alt="" border="0" /></span></span></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', '', 'Chelle.zhang@tiandaoedu.com', 980, 173, 2),
(1015, 1423165405, 'panda快餐食堂经理', 'Panda Express', 'Resturant', 'Santa Monica, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Santa Monica', 34.019455, -118.491188, '美国', 'California', 'Santa Monica', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table class="tablelist" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID3451.row.row1" class="ftlrow" title="">\n<td class=" column165">&nbsp;</td>\n<td class="columnfull">\n<div class="editablesection">\n<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1581.row1" class="contentlinepanel" title="">\n<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1597.row1" class="inlinepanel" title=""><span class="subtitle">Description</span></div>\n<span class="blockpanel"><span>&nbsp;</span></span><span id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1624.row1" class="text" title="">Panda Express</span><span class="blockpanel"><span>&nbsp;</span></span>\n<p><strong>Are you Craving a Career?&nbsp; Ready for Growth?&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>COME SEE WHY PANDA MIGHT BE THE RIGHT PLACE!</strong></p>\n<p><br />At Panda, we all share a common mission: "Deliver exceptional Asian dining experiences by building an organization where people are inspired to better their lives." We invest in our people because great people run great operations that will exceed our guests'' expectations. Talk to any of our associates and you will experience a culture dedicated to its mission and our five fundamental values- Proactive, Respect/Win-Win, Growth, Great Operations, and Giving.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><br />Panda Restaurant Group includes the original Panda Inn fine dining restaurants, Panda Express, our Gourmet Chinese food concept served in a fast casual environment, and Hibachi San, our Japanese grill concept. The family owned and operated company is still run by founders Andrew and Peggy Cherng.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><br />Panda offers competitive benefits and rewarding opportunities, from entry-level positions to management. We have restaurant positions available nationwide and support center positions in Rosemead, CA. Come join the nation''s largest and fastest growing Asian restaurant company.</p>\n<p><br />Our continued growth in this location has created new career opportunities for Management, Crew Members, and Kitchen Team Members!!! Come join us.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Restaurant Management Team responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Lead all or some People aspects of a Panda Express restaurant including hiring, training, coaching, and development&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Ensure the safety of our Guests and Associates through training and execution of food safety and restaurant safety standards and guidelines&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Lead all or some Guest components of a Panda Express restaurant including excellent food quality, guest service, associate friendliness, and restaurant cleanliness through your team using proven systems and routines&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Lead all or some financial areas of a Panda Express restaurant including sales growth, cost management, and profit growth&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Applies thorough knowledge of all policies, procedures and practices utilized within unit managed&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Understands ways in which unit relates to and impacts PRG&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Demonstrates knowledge of PRG operations and objectives&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Seeks information regarding trends affecting food service industry</li>\n</ul>\n<div id="fck____FCKHiddenDiv">&nbsp;</div>\n<span class="text" title=""><span class="text" title=""><strong>We offer our Full-Time Management Team:</strong></span></span>\n<ul>\n<li>Progressive Compensation Package and Excellent Bonus Opportunity&nbsp;</li>\n<li>5 or more Weeks of Comprehensive Training to prepare you for success&nbsp;</li>\n<li>On-Going Career &amp; Leadership Development&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Medical, Dental, and Vision Insurance&nbsp;</li>\n<li>401 K with Company Match&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Paid Time Off and Paid Holidays&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Associate Discounts (Panda Express, Hibachi San, Panda Inn plus Theme Parks) and free meals when you work&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Lucrative Associate Referral Bonus&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Pre-Tax Dependent Care Flexible Spending Account&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n<div class="staticcontentlinepanel">&nbsp;</div>\n<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1649.row1" class="contentlinepanel" title="">\n<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1665.row1" class="inlinepanel" title=""><span class="subtitle">Qualifications</span></div>\n<span class="blockpanel"><span>&nbsp;</span></span>\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial;">Qualifications:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style="font-family: Arial;">College degree or equivalent experience preferred</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Arial;">High school or GED required</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial;"><strong>Additional expectations of our Management Team are:</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style="font-family: Arial;">Excellent leaders with great people skills&nbsp;</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Arial;">Proactive &ndash; Sees life as choices and chooses to make a positive impact.&nbsp;</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Arial;">People Oriented &ndash; enjoys working with our guests and associates, possess good communication and interpersonal skills.&nbsp;</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Arial;">Growth Oriented &ndash; knows that learning and growth are keys to personal and professional success and is willing and able to share learning with others.&nbsp;</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Arial;">Results Oriented &ndash; focuses on getting results without compromising guest, people, and financial areas.&nbsp;</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial;">ADA Statement: While performing duties, counter areas are often hot with steam from steam table and food vapors.&nbsp; Work space is restricted and employees are expected to remain standing for long periods of time.&nbsp; Employees must prepare hot and cold foods, use Chinese cook knife and other kitchen equipment and work quickly without losing accuracy.&nbsp; Employees may be required to lift up to 50 lbs., stand up to four hours and reach across counter tops measured at 36 inches to serve customers.&nbsp; Kitchens are hot and noise levels are usually high; storage space is limited and shelving is high.</span></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Panda Restaurant Group, Inc is an Equal Opportunity Employer</p>\n<span class="blockpanel"><span>&nbsp;</span></span><span class="blockpanel"><span>&nbsp;</span></span><span class="blockpanel"><span>&nbsp;</span></span></div>\n<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1719.row1" class="contentlinepanel" title="">\n<h2 class="no-change-header-inline"><span id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1735.row1" class="subtitle" title="">Primary Location</span></h2>\n<span class="inline">&nbsp;</span><span id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1756.row1" class="subtitle" title="">|</span><span class="inline">&nbsp;</span><span id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1766.row1" class="text" title="">United States of America-CALIFORNIA-Culver City</span><span class="blockpanel"><span>&nbsp;</span></span><span class="blockpanel"><span>&nbsp;</span></span>\n<h2 class="no-change-header-inline"><span id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1797.row1" class="subtitle" title="">Other Locations</span></h2>\n<span class="blockpanel"><span>&nbsp;</span></span><span id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1820.row1" class="text" title="">United States of America-CALIFORNIA-Santa Monica, United States of America-CALIFORNIA-Marina Del Rey, United States of America-CALIFORNIA-Hollywood, United States of America-CALIFORNIA-Culver City</span><span class="blockpanel"><span>&nbsp;</span></span></div>\n<div class="staticcontentlinepanel">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n<td class=" column165">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'https://pandarg.taleo.net/careersection/panda+restaurant/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=13000990&src=JB-10061', '', 980, 166, 2),
(1016, 1423165498, '中文老师', 'RAINBOW LEARNING SYSTEM', 'Language', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="snip">\n<p>Private school in LA seeks native Chinese women for language and culture teaching in Los Angeles.<br />Do you absolutely love to work with babies and children?<br />Lived in Native country for minimum 10 years. US resident Card Citizenship.<br />Rainbow is a school that uses a unique and modern Educational System that uses the early exposure to cultures to help babies and children develop their brain capacity as well as their emotionality. We start with children when they are 2months - 3 years old and they continue to study with us until they finish hight school.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/RAINBOW-LEARNING-SYSTEM/jobs/Chinese-Teacher-8e7102b30d935132', '', 980, 265, 2),
(1017, 1423274773, '旅游产品编辑', '走四方旅游网', 'Technology', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong><span lang="ZH-CN">产品编辑</span></strong><br /> <strong><span lang="ZH-CN">工作职能：</span></strong><br /> 1. <span lang="ZH-CN">负责产品内容的更新，与供应商市场部互动配合网页做后台上传更新；</span><span class="apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br /> 2. <span lang="ZH-CN">负责撰写编辑旅游线路产品；</span><br /> 3. <span lang="ZH-CN">负责跟进市场部，商品部新合作项目，并对渠道开拓及渠道维护负责；</span><span class="apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br /> 4. <span lang="ZH-CN">对客服遇到的急需问题进行收集和答案整理，信息采集和编辑；</span><span class="apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br /> 5. <span lang="ZH-CN">优化网站内容及线路介绍，包括二级名称，线路内容；</span><span class="apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br /> 6. <span lang="ZH-CN">根据公司计划完成线路内容的整理，内容完善，价格核对以及销售培训资料的制作。</span><br /> <strong><span lang="ZH-CN">技能要求：</span></strong><br /> 1. <span lang="ZH-CN">有一定的中英文写作能力和策划能力，有良好中英文表达功底，有编辑策划经验者优先考虑；</span><span class="apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br /> 2. <span lang="ZH-CN">善于收集信息和整合编辑，拥有敏锐的观察力和解析力，思维严谨，有网站编辑经验者优先；</span><br /> 3. <span lang="ZH-CN">打字速度快，熟练使用</span>office<span lang="ZH-CN">办公软件，熟悉数据库操作；</span><span class="apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br /> 4. <span lang="ZH-CN">文字编辑能力强，有一定的中文撰写能力；</span><br /> 5. <span lang="ZH-CN">做事认真，有耐心，积极主动，能吃苦耐劳，能承受一定压力，具团队合作意识。</span></p>\n<p><span lang="ZH-CN"><br /> <span lang="ZH-CN">如有兴趣者，请投简历至</span><strong>hr@usitrip.com</strong><span lang="ZH-CN">，标明应聘职位，或直接致电<strong>走四方人力资源部</strong></span><strong>626-389-0704</strong><span lang="ZH-CN">。</span><strong><span lang="ZH-CN">转正成为正式全职员工后都享受公司福利：全额医疗保险，</span></strong><strong>Paid Holiday</strong><strong><span lang="ZH-CN">，员工旅游折扣，工作满一年后可参加</span></strong><strong>401K</strong><strong><span lang="ZH-CN">计划，并享受带薪休假。</span></strong></span></p>', 'http://www.usitrip.com/', 'hr@usitrip.com', 1577, 209, 2),
(1018, 1423358298, '企台', '中餐buffet', 'Resturant', 'Kansas City, MO, United States', 'United States', 'Missouri', 'Kansas City', 39.099728, -94.578568, '美国', 'Missouri', 'Kansas City', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>中型中餐buffet诚请企台，男女皆可，小费佳，老板员工好相处，有意者9179070958</p>', '', '', 1684, 151, 2),
(1019, 1423550808, 'Investor Relations Manager 投资者关系经理', 'Golden Gate Global', 'Finance', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '美国', 'California', 'San Francisco', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><em>Full-time</em><br /><em>Salary, Incentive Compensation plus Benefits</em></p>\n<p><strong>About Golden Gate Global</strong><br />Golden Gate Global (GGG) channels foreign investment dollars into public and/or private projects in the US that create jobs for the US economy.</p>\n<p>GGG operates via a US federal program that helps to bring in foreign direct investment called the EB-5 Investment Immigration program. The intent of the EB-5 is to encourage the flow of capital into the U.S. economy and to promote employment of U.S. workers. It is estimated that in 2012 over $2 billion of foreign direct investment dollars were raised through the EB-5 program.</p>\n<p>GGG is a dynamic, growing company whose ownership and executive leadership have an unbeatable professional network throughout the State of California, US and overseas. Currently, GGG manages 4 EB-5 funds with over $200 million in EB-5 funds raised, and is expanding its portfolio to finance additional projects in California.</p>\n<p>In 2015, it is expected that GGG will raise approximately $300 million in new EB-5 funds.</p>\n<p>For more info please visit www.3GFund.com</p>\n<p><strong>Position</strong></p>\n<p>The Investor Relations Manager is a dynamic position that will be one of the company&rsquo;s primary interfaces with China-based referral sources, foreign investors and associated partners. He or she will support referral sources needs, and respond to foreign investor requests and inquiries. He or she must successfully grow and deepen existing relationships with our referral partners. In addition, he or she will also assist with case management of new referral source development, follow up on questions, attend EB-5 related networking events and be able to convert potential referral sources into GGG referral partners.</p>\n<p>The Investor Relations Manager will also act as the central accounts manager working with the client&rsquo;s professional service providers (immigration attorneys, foreign referral sources, escrow and banking providers) to facilitate successful EB-5 case processing. The Investor Relations Manager will provide a high level of customer service in monitoring and tracking all progress for each investor. He or she will also host visiting investors, and be responsible for managing and maintaining a database of investor data, providing regular reports on fundraising and investor status, and working with the entire GGG team.</p>\n<p>The Investor Relations Manager will respond to all referral sources and investor inquiries about the company&rsquo;s projects. This will require both strong interpersonal skills as well as a strong grounding in business, real estate, investment and legal terms. He or she will need to have worked with high net worth Chinese clientele. The Investor Relations Manager will also provide administrative support to the company. As part of a young company, all staff team members must be flexible, proactive and willing to support a variety of tasks, challenges and opportunities, as they arise. As most investors are from China, it is mandatory that the Investor Relations Manager speaks, reads, and writes in Chinese fluently.</p>\n<p>The Investor Relations Manager will report to the Senior Investor Relations Manager.</p>\n<p><strong>Duties/responsibilities:&nbsp;</strong><br /><em>Investor Accounts</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Monitor and track all developments for the client</li>\n</ul>\n<p>o Maintain accurate records of progress<br />o Submit regular reports on Investor progress and status to CEO and Principals</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Manage Investor caseloads</li>\n</ul>\n<p>o Act as primary lead on assigned client case load<br />o Proactively monitor client&rsquo;s immigration process<br />o Proactively communicate with client&rsquo;s professional service providers (e.g. legal, banking and fund administration partners)<br />o Quality control of investor processing<br />o Receive new leads and convert into active investor<br />o Provide regular reporting to the investors</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Coordinate and host investor tours and site visits</li>\n<li>Manage and support all forms of communication to investors including newsletters, investor reports and statements, notifications, etc.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Develop and Manage Referral Sources</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Develop referral sources</li>\n</ul>\n<p>o Conduct regular market research on EB-5 related events in the US<br />o Convert referral source leads into partners<br />o Support marketing efforts including investor event and EB-5 industry events</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Manage referral sources</li>\n</ul>\n<p>o Grow and deeper relationships with existing referral sources<br />o Provide regularly referral reports to CEO (e.g. referral agreement and referral performance)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Make formal and informal presentations to potential EB-5 investors and partners</li>\n<li>Act as referral concierge service to professional service network in-country and in US</li>\n<li>Travel to China and other countries is possible</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Administrative Support</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Provide administrative support to the company</li>\n<li>Office management support</li>\n<li>Support other company functions as directed and as needs arise</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Skills/Background</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Detail oriented and a demonstration of efficient organizational skills</li>\n<li>4-5 years experience in business, investment and/or real estate investment</li>\n<li>Exemplary written and verbal communication in Chinese</li>\n<li>High degree of customer service experience and orientation</li>\n<li>Understanding of China and Chinese business culture</li>\n<li>Fluency in English</li>\n<li>Proven ability to undertake and complete multiple projects and to work efficiently and diligently under pressure</li>\n<li>Demonstrated ability to work with high net worth individuals</li>\n<li>Ability to travel in China (including all necessary visa/passport requirements)</li>\n<li>Strong knowledge/experience of MS Office Suite, NetSuite</li>\n<li>Mandarin required; additional Cantonese dialect preferred</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>To Apply</strong></p>\n<p>Please submit the following application materials and information via email:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Cover Letter explaining your interest in the position and your professional / educational experience</li>\n<li>Resume</li>\n<li>Contact information for at least two references</li>\n<li>Writing Sample in English and Chinese</li>\n<li></li>\n</ul>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Golden-Gate-Global/jobs/Investor-Relation-Manager-43809a9ca7e753d8', '', 980, 180, 2),
(1020, 1423550916, '办公室管理员', 'un He Law Offices', 'Management', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美国', 'New York', 'New York', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="snip">\n<p>The New York office of one of the most prestigious Chinese law firms seeks Chinese/English bilingual Office Administrator to handle all aspects of office administration and bookkeeping.</p>\n<p>Qualifications:<br />1. College degree and a minimum of two years of professional experience in office administration required.<br />2. Requires strong interpersonal and communication skills and basic knowledge in bookkeeping.<br />3. Proficient in Microsoft Office - Word, Excel, Outlook, etc., with the ability to edit English and Chinese documents.<br />4. Must be detail-oriented, multi-tasking and organized.<br />5. English/Chinese bilingual proficiency in verbal and written are needed.<br />6. Knowledge of Quickbooks software a plus.</p>\n<p>Competitive salary and benefits and great office environment at Rockefeller Center.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Jun-He-Law-Offices/jobs/Chinese-English-Bilingual-Office-Administrator-8acd0a53e2995a8c', '', 980, 180, 2),
(1021, 1423551074, '粤语/普通话语言学家', 'MetLang', 'Finance', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '美国', 'New York', 'New York', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>Description</strong><br />Metropolitan/Metlang, a nationwide government contractor, is looking to hire linguists fluent in English and Cantonese/Mandarin for current and future staffing needs.&nbsp;<br /><br />Opportunities for individuals with or without a valid security clearance are also available if you are fluent in English and Cantonese/Mandarin.&nbsp;<br /><br />Metlang/Metropolitan is the largest employer in this industry, and we only hire employees and not subcontractors. We take pride in building a relationship with our employees while providing a stable work environment, competitive compensation and a weekly payroll.&nbsp;<br /><br />Whether you are new to our industry or a seasoned expert we encourage you contact us so that we can begin discussing employment opportunities with you. All applications will be handled with complete discretion.&nbsp;<br /><br />Metropolitan/Metlang is an EEO/AA employer. Qualified applicants are considered for employment without regard to age, race, color, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, disability, or veteran status. All qualified applicants will not be discriminated against on the basis of disability.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Qualifications</strong><br />The questions you are about to answer are specifically designed to determine your ability to qualify for a government security clearance, a key requirement for many of the positions we offer. Complete and truthful answers to these questions are crucial to your acceptance as a potential candidate. Please bear in mind that a seemingly adverse response to a question may not necessarily be a disqualifying factor, but an untruthful answer would be. Certain government agencies will administer a polygraph exam before allowing any linguist access to their facility. The answers you provide on this questionnaire will be used as a comparison for every security document you complete in conjunction with your security access - up to and including the polygraph exam.</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong><br />In order to work as a linguist under these contracts, you must be a native speaker of the foreign language with a college degree and/or some hands on experience with translation and/or interpretation.</p>\n<p><strong>Required Skills</strong><br />An excellent command of the English language, with the ability to provide clear and concise oral and written communication.&nbsp;<br /><br />Ability to work well under pressure to meet specific deadlines.&nbsp;<br /><br />Basic typing/word processing skills of at least 40 words per minute.&nbsp;<br /><br />Exceptions to these qualifications can be made for rare and exotic languages such as African, Latin American and Asian tribal languages. If you feel you that have the qualifications required to work as a linguist in the exciting field of law enforcement, please continue to the next screen, which will ask you some more specific questions.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Location</strong><br />Atlanta, New York, Los Angeles, Hawaii</p>\n<p><strong>Type</strong><br />Applicants selected will be subject to a Government security background investigation and must meet eligibility and suitability requirements.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://www.metlang.com/jobs_display.php?jobID=34&loc=NYC', '', 980, 208, 2),
(1022, 1423551188, '会计经理', 'DISH Network ', 'Finance', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Summary:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<p>DISH is an innovative industry leader distinguished by its pioneering spirit. Ever since our establishment in 1980, we&rsquo;ve been the ideal workplace for people with adventurous spirit and creativity, smart risk takers and aggressive winners - all those for whom the status quo just isn&rsquo;t enough. Our Fortune 200 Company continues to define the curve in television entertainment. We are always improving and extending our products and delivering greater value to people, including our workforce of 20,000 plus. Come explore the big picture with us!</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Intelligence. Creativity. Innovation. These are the things you&rsquo;ll find at DISH, the pioneer in television entertainment. We offer flexible career paths for dynamic, talented individuals who are ready to be rewarded and recognized. It&rsquo;s our way of giving back to exceptional people who have kept us at the forefront of our industry.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Specialized Sales and Distribution Channel has been a key contributor to DISH&rsquo; success and has helped propel DISH to the Fortune 200 company that it is today. This Sales Channel is responsible for partnering with authorized DISH retailers and developing go to market strategies that will increase our retailer&rsquo;s production and profitability. &nbsp;</p>\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Job Duties and Responsibilities:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<ul>\n<li>Develops and implements international strategic sales plans to accommodate corporate goals.</li>\n<li>Identifies and grows new and existing retailer base within international markets.</li>\n<li>Directs sales forecasting activities and sets performance goals accordingly.</li>\n<li>Reviews market analysis and creates SWOTs to help determine current opportunities and customer needs, price promotions, and discount rates.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Advises retailers, distributors, and sales staff concerning international sales and advertising techniques per specific markets.</li>\n<li>Helps support and represent various retailers and company at local grassroots events, tradeshows, etc. to promote International products and programming.</li>\n<li>Travel throughout specific territory to meet with prospects, current retailers, and Account Managers to discuss international updates and sales training.</li>\n<li>Responsible for international retailer development forums within assigned territory.</li>\n<li>Meets with international programmers, agencies, and advertising mediums to assist in increasing retailer sales opportunities and promotions.</li>\n<li>Prepares periodic sales report showing sales volume, potential sales, and areas of proposed retailer base expansion.</li>\n<li>Monitors and evaluates the activities and products of the competition, and works with corporate International team to track retailer participation with competitors.</li>\n<li>Other duties as required.&nbsp; This list is not meant to be a comprehensive inventory of all duties and responsibilities assigned to this position.</li>\n</ul>\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Skills - Experience and Requirements:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<ul>\n<li>Ability to effectively respond to and interact with all levels of organizational staff.</li>\n<li>Competencies include excellent presentation/facilitation, organizational, analytical, interpersonal and written/oral communication skills.</li>\n<li>Requires high level computer expertise, including use of internet, database, word processing, spreadsheet, and presentation applications.</li>\n<li>Flexible, innovative and the ability to manage staff, responsibilities and priorities in a fast paced, growth-oriented and time-critical environment.</li>\n<li>Ability to travel 50-75% of the time.</li>\n<li>Must maintain valid driver&rsquo;s license with a satisfactory driving record.</li>\n<li>Bachelor''s degree from four-year college or university; 3+ years related experience, 1-2 years outbound sales experience; or equivalent combination of education and experience.</li>\n<li>Mandarin or Cantonese language ability is required.</li>\n<li></li>\n</ul>\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_Navigation">&nbsp;</div>', 'https://dish-assessment1-dish.icims.com/jobs/30551/job?mobile=false&width=1209&height=500&bga=true&needsRedirect=false', '', 980, 133, 2),
(1023, 1423551292, '内销经理与技术支持', 'ELECTRONIC COMPANY', 'Finance', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '美国', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>andidate should be able to install, troubleshoot and program DVRs (analog, IP and hybrid) and alarm systems.</p>\n<p>Candidate must be be personable, have excellent customer service skills, and be able to perform custom wiring and installations on residential and commercial jobs in a timely manner. We are looking for someone enthusiastic and able to work in a team-setting as we operate in a family oriented environment. Candidates will have ample room to grow and opportunity to expand with the company.</p>\n<p>IDEAL CANDIDATE FOR TECH SUPPORT:</p>\n<p>Verifies security system functioning by testing equipment, connections, and signals; identifying and correcting problems.<br />Maintains records by documenting installation.<br />Maintains customer rapport by resolving concerns; answering questions.<br />Maintains safe and secure work environment by following safe practices; keeping security information confidential.<br />Updates job knowledge by participating in educational opportunities; reading technical publications.<br />Accomplishes organization goals by accepting ownership for accomplishing new and different requests; exploring opportunities to add value to job accomplishments.</p>\n<p>SKILLS/QUALIFICATIONS</p>\n<p>Safety Management, Facilities Management Systems, Equipment Maintenance, Functional and Technical Skills,Action Oriented, Electronic Systems Verbal Communication, Dealing with Complexity, Informing Others. MUST BE ABLE TO SPEAK CHINESE AND ENGLISH</p>\n<p>HOURS:<br />Mon-Fri 8:30am to 5:30pm<br />PAY RATE:<br />TECH SUPPORT:<br />$90,000/YEAR<br />SALES POSITION: $100,000/YEAR</p>\n<p>Required Skills and/or Knowledge Self-motivated, competitive spirit, and able to work independently<br />Proven prospecting skills<br />Good organizational and follow up skills<br />Perseverance and a positive attitude<br />Good listening and communication skills<br />Security product knowledge</p>\n<p>Required experience:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>CCTV surveillance : 2 years</li>\n<li></li>\n</ul>', 'http://www.indeed.com/viewjob?cmp=Netzeye&t=Inside+Sales+Manager+Tech+Support&jk=0a7ac468562ff5dd&sjdu=QwrRXKrqZ3CNX5W-O9jEvc892U_p2Lkh-iT3eLKjIIBSlbm6Swqz5iFREgUYO_78rTv17sqS_Jbyf_XITwFjj_eBbT5VepDP5jdH35B87-Y0Nm_SJd9fWSAsMFSKnXIb&pub=pub-indeed', '', 980, 161, 2),
