(1040, 1424714164, 'Program Coordinator', '美中商务与文化交流中心', 'Service', '美国哥伦比亚区华盛顿', 'United States', 'District of Columbia', 'Washington', 38.907192, -77.036873, '美国', 'District of Columbia', 'Washington', 'H1B', 'Full Time', '<p>The U.S.-China Business &amp; Culture Exchange, Inc (UCBCEC) is a fully incorporated international entity headquartered in the city of Fairfax, Virginia. We have representative office which is located in Beijing, China. UCBCEC seeks to stimulate mutually beneficial exchanges and communications between China and the United States in the fields of education, culture and commerce. UCBCEC achieves this goal through multiple channels that include coordinating training seminar and professional development workshops, organizing international conferences, and university cooperative partnership programs.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>UCBCEC is looking for full-time program coordinator working in our Fairfax office.</p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p><strong>PRO</strong><strong>GRAM </strong><strong>COORDINATOR</strong>&nbsp;(full-time)&nbsp;__Location: Fairfax VA</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>The excellent candidate would be provided with H1B sponsorship.</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:</p>\n<p>1)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Conduct research on specific&nbsp;subject matters&nbsp;proposed by clients;</p>\n<p>2)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Develop training outlines &amp; topics and draft training proposals, based on research and communications with clients through UCBCEC China offices;</p>\n<p>3)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Outreach to government agencies, professional association and other organization to arrange site visits upon the request of clients.</p>\n<p>4)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Plans and Works collaboratively on conferences, special events, projects, and tasks with other staff and partners to aid with efforts including, but not limited to, design agendas, call nights, training days, and internship programs.</p>\n<p>5)&nbsp;&nbsp;&