(1122, 1427607163, '兼职新闻记者和兼职工商记者', '侨报周末', 'Language', '美国麻萨诸塞州波士顿', 'United States', 'Massachusetts', 'Boston', 42.360081, -71.058884, '美国', 'Massachusetts', 'Boston', 'None', 'Part Time', '<p>《侨报周末》波士顿版招聘兼职新闻记者和兼职工商记者。需有合法工作身份，熟悉本地社区，勇于开拓，认真负责。弹性工作时间，有经验者优先。有意者请email resume tosguo@chinapress.net</p>', '', 'tosguo@chinapress.net', 980, 128, 1),
(1123, 1427815491, '项目协调员（支持H1B）', 'US-China Business & Culture Exchange ', 'Consulting', 'Washington, DC, United States', 'United States', 'District of Columbia', 'Washington', 38.907192, -77.036873, '美国', 'District of Columbia', 'Washington', 'H1B', 'Internship', '<p>The U.S.-China Business &amp; Culture Exchange, Inc (UCBCEC) is a fully incorporated international entity headquartered in the city of Fairfax, Virginia. We have representative office which is located in Beijing, China. UCBCEC seeks to stimulate mutually beneficial exchanges and communications between China and the United States in the fields of education, culture and commerce. UCBCEC achieves this goal through multiple channels that include coordinating training seminar and professional development workshops, organizing international conferences, and university cooperative partnership programs.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>UCBCEC is looking for full-time program coordinator working in our Fairfax office.</p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p><strong>PRO</strong><strong>GRAM </strong><strong>COORDINATOR</strong>&nbsp;(full-time)&nbsp;__Location: Fairfax VA</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>The excellent candidate would be provided with H1B sponsorship.</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:</p>\n<p>1)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Conduct research on specific&nbsp;subject matters&nbsp;proposed by clients;</p>\n<p>2)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Develop training outlines &amp; topics and draft training proposals, based on research and communications with clients through UCBCEC China offices;</p>\n<p>3)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Outreach to government agencies, professional association and other organization to arrange site visits upon the request of clients.</p>\n<p>4)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Plans and Works collaboratively on conferences, special events, projects, and tasks with other staff and partners to aid with efforts including, but not limited to, design agendas, call nights, training days, and internship programs.</p>\n<p>5)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Perform other tasks assigned by the supervisor.</p>\n<p>6)&nbsp; Perform as an interpreter between Mandarin and English to a large group setting.</p>\n<p>7）Communicate and coordinate with correspondence branch offices in China to coordinate the training programs, events, seminar, site visits, etc</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>QUALIFICATIONS:</p>\n<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Recent graduates of a bachelor-level program in public administration, law, international affairs, business, political science, humanities or social sciences or relevant areas. Experience in training is preferred. Master is preferred.</p>\n<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Demonstrated ability to be a passionate and well spokesperson for UCBCEC.</p>\n<p>- &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ability to manage multiple responsibilities and tasks effectively within an inter-connected small work environment.</p>\n<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to establish and maintain effective ongoing relationships with key counseling contacts in working partners as well as delegation.</p>\n<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ability to perform diverse and complex tasks with accuracy and attention to details;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ability to do interpretation for class lecture.</p>\n<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Excellent verbal, written, and public communication skills in both Mandarin and English.</p>\n<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Must have general knowledge on U.S. and China political system, government structure and the way both governments operate.</p>\n<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Candidate who has his/her own car would be a plus.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>If you are interested in the position, we would advise you to send&nbsp;<strong>the cover letter and your resume</strong>&nbsp;to us at ucbcec@yahoo.com. We tentatively do not accept inquiries by phone.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 'ucbcec@yahoo.com', 93, 212, 1),
